	("Neural Lash, Galvanic", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 14, 79,400, 20, 0, arc 4d4, 0, 0, "L", "Living, powered (capacity 20; usage 1), reach, stun, thought, unwieldy", "Similar to the living lash, a neural lash is a particularly flexible weapon that proves cumbersome to those without telepathic abilities. The neural lash has been bred to include bioelectric cells in addition to its neural fibers, delivering electricity damage and allowing the lash to deal nonlethal damage at its user’s direction. Barathu take credit for the development of the electroplax and amperometric neural lash, but later weapons manufacturers have improved upon those original models by developing the galvanic and voltaic neural lashes."),
	("Electroflail, Paragon", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 18, 360,000, 38, 0, arc 4d6, 0, 0, "1", "disarm, powered (capacity 20; usage 1)", "An electroflail is a 2-foot-long haft and a floating spiked or ridged ball; as there is no visible tether between the two components, an electroflail appears to be two separate weapons. An electromagnetic force causes the ball to stay within a predetermined range of the haft’s end0usually around 1 foot away0while also conducting a substantial electric charge to the ball that is discharged upon a strike. The magnetic field can also interfere with other weapons, allowing a proficient user to use an electroflail to knock opponents’ weapons out of their grasp. These weapons see frequent use among various Hellknight orders, which often custom order designs featuring grinning devils, complete with spiked wings. Electroflails are available in tactical, advanced, elite, and paragon models."),
	("Shock Truncheon, Tempest", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 19, 545,000, 39, 0, arc 6d4, 0, 0, "1", "powered (capacity 40; usage 2), stun", "These polycarbonate batons have a side-handle grip and a electrode-lined striking surface that delivers an electrical charge. "
	("Shadow Chains, Follower", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 1, 390, 2, 0, bind, 0, 0, "2", "analog, disarm, reach, trip", "Worshipers of Zon-Kuthon developed the first shadow chains using cutting-edge heat-transfer technology, but outsiders rapidly reverse-engineered the weapons, constructing functional facsimiles from their own tech. Shadow chains’ links rapidly absorb heat, while their heavily insulated handle protect their wielders from direct exposure to the freezing darkness. Many adherents of the Midnight Lord make use of the follower, acolyte, and penitent shadow chains, while only the most devout can afford the more powerful ecclesiastic and devotional shadow chains."),
	("Living Staff, Tactical", "Basic Melee 2-H", 5, 3,300, 3, 0, bind, 0, 0, "1", "block, living, powered (capacity 20; usage 1), reach", "Xenodruids developed the living staff, a gnarled and vineswathed pole, to use as a weapon and a sign of their allegiance. The staff itself can extend, and the vines can wrap around and entangle a target. Xenodruids on sentinel duty favor the tactical and advanced models. The elite and paragon models are more common among highly skilled warrior-mystics undertaking assault missions."),
	("Living Lash", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 6, 4,150, 4, 0, bind, 0, 0, "L", "living, powered (capacity 20; usage 1), reach, thought, unwieldy", "A living lash is grown from a network of filaments closely related to neural fibers, and it remains biologically active after its creation. This living connection to neurophysiology makes the weapon easy to manipulate using telepathy, but it’s difficult to wield without such abilities. These weapons are common only on worlds with telepathic species."),
	("Shadow Chains, Acolyte", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 7, 6,800, 7, 0, bind, 0, 0, "2", "analog, disarm, reach, trip", "Worshipers of Zon-Kuthon developed the first shadow chains using cutting-edge heat-transfer technology, but outsiders rapidly reverse-engineered the weapons, constructing functional facsimiles from their own tech. Shadow chains’ links rapidly absorb heat, while their heavily insulated handle protect their wielders from direct exposure to the freezing darkness. Many adherents of the Midnight Lord make use of the follower, acolyte, and penitent shadow chains, while only the most devout can afford the more powerful ecclesiastic and devotional shadow chains."),
	("Shadow Chains, Penitent", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 10, 18,800, 12, 0, bind, 0, 0, "2", "analog, disarm, reach, trip", "Worshipers of Zon-Kuthon developed the first shadow chains using cutting-edge heat-transfer technology, but outsiders rapidly reverse-engineered the weapons, constructing functional facsimiles from their own tech. Shadow chains’ links rapidly absorb heat, while their heavily insulated handle protect their wielders from direct exposure to the freezing darkness. Many adherents of the Midnight Lord make use of the follower, acolyte, and penitent shadow chains, while only the most devout can afford the more powerful ecclesiastic and devotional shadow chains."),
	("Living Staff, Advanced", "Basic Melee 2-H", 12, 39,500, 14, 0, bind, 0, 0, "1", "block, living, powered (capacity 20; usage 1), reach", "Xenodruids developed the living staff, a gnarled and vineswathed pole, to use as a weapon and a sign of their allegiance. The staff itself can extend, and the vines can wrap around and entangle a target. Xenodruids on sentinel duty favor the tactical and advanced models. The elite and paragon models are more common among highly skilled warrior-mystics undertaking assault missions."),
	("Shadow Chains, Ecclesiastic", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 14, 76,800, 22, 0, bind, 0, 0, "2", "analog, disarm, reach, trip", "Worshipers of Zon-Kuthon developed the first shadow chains using cutting-edge heat-transfer technology, but outsiders rapidly reverse-engineered the weapons, constructing functional facsimiles from their own tech. Shadow chains’ links rapidly absorb heat, while their heavily insulated handle protect their wielders from direct exposure to the freezing darkness. Many adherents of the Midnight Lord make use of the follower, acolyte, and penitent shadow chains, while only the most devout can afford the more powerful ecclesiastic and devotional shadow chains."),
	("Shadow Chains, Devotional", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 18, 261,000, 40, 0, bind, 0, 0, "2", "analog, disarm, reach, trip", "Worshipers of Zon-Kuthon developed the first shadow chains using cutting-edge heat-transfer technology, but outsiders rapidly reverse-engineered the weapons, constructing functional facsimiles from their own tech. Shadow chains’ links rapidly absorb heat, while their heavily insulated handle protect their wielders from direct exposure to the freezing darkness. Many adherents of the Midnight Lord make use of the follower, acolyte, and penitent shadow chains, while only the most devout can afford the more powerful ecclesiastic and devotional shadow chains."),
	("Living Staff, Elite", "Basic Melee 2-H", 16, 181,000, 42, 0, bind, 0, 0, "1", "block, living, powered (capacity 20; usage 1), reach", "Xenodruids developed the living staff, a gnarled and vineswathed pole, to use as a weapon and a sign of their allegiance. The staff itself can extend, and the vines can wrap around and entangle a target. Xenodruids on sentinel duty favor the tactical and advanced models. The elite and paragon models are more common among highly skilled warrior-mystics undertaking assault missions."),
	("Living Staff, Paragon", "Basic Melee 2-H", 20, 919,000, 49, 0, bind, 0, 0, "1", "block, living, powered (capacity 20; usage 1), reach", "Xenodruids developed the living staff, a gnarled and vineswathed pole, to use as a weapon and a sign of their allegiance. The staff itself can extend, and the vines can wrap around and entangle a target. Xenodruids on sentinel duty favor the tactical and advanced models. The elite and paragon models are more common among highly skilled warrior-mystics undertaking assault missions."),
	("Sword Cane, Tactical", "Basic Melee 1-H", 1, 250, 2, 0, bleed 1d3, 0, 0, "L", "analog, operative", "This thin blade comes with a scabbard that makes it resemble a stylish cane. Sword canes are popular on Absalom Station, where similar nonweapon items have some popularity as fashionable affectations. A sword cane can incorporate one of the following at the standard price for that item: 20 feet of retractable cable line, a personal comm unit, or a spotlight. A successful Perception check (DC = 15 + the weapon’s item level) is required to identify a sword cane as a weapon when it is sheathed."),
	("Sword Cane, Advanced", "Basic Melee 1-H", 4, 2,100, 2, 0, bleed 1d4, 0, 0, "L", "analog, operative", "This thin blade comes with a scabbard that makes it resemble a stylish cane. Sword canes are popular on Absalom Station, where similar nonweapon items have some popularity as fashionable affectations. A sword cane can incorporate one of the following at the standard price for that item: 20 feet of retractable cable line, a personal comm unit, or a spotlight. A successful Perception check (DC = 15 + the weapon’s item level) is required to identify a sword cane as a weapon when it is sheathed."),
	("Velstrac Flenser, Ascetic", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 2, 550, 2, 0, Bleed 1d4, 0, 0, "L", "powered (capacity 20, usage 1)", "Velstracs wield flensers0 blades designed to slice skin from muscle and muscle from bone0sometimes mounting these knives on rifles as bayonetS. Flensers are honed to supernatural sharpness and powered to vibrate with the rhythms of the wielder’s body. Velstracs have mastered the art of using these advanced melee weapons to inflict wounds while keeping targets alive. The table above shows an array of flensers, which can be purchased only in the darkest corners of the galaxy."),
	("Bone Cestus, Austere", "Basic Melee 1-H", 2, 600, 3, 0, bleed 1d4, 0, 0, "L", "analog", "Centuries ago, some kasathas crafted simple weapons out of crest-eaters’ bony protrusions; these formidable gauntlets were badges of honor for the mightiest kasathan warriors, and modern artisans have recreated that aesthetic in the form of bone cestuses, though now they are usually formed of state-of-the-art resin instead of crest-eater bone. Due to the flecks of minerals embedded within, bone cestuses are often warm to the touch, especially after they have been exposed to natural sunlight. These basic one-handed melee weapons are capable of punching through a foe’s defenses, sometimes puncturing vital organs in the process."),
	("Hook Sword", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 3, 1,420, 4, 0, bleed 1d4, 0, 0, "L", "analog, trip", "A larger cousin of the hook knife, the hook sword is a longsword with a pronounced hook at one edge of the blade’s tip. This barb not only deals gouging wounds, but it can also be used to trip an unwary foe. The drow invented the hook sword based on their design for the hook knife, but the weapon can be found all over the galaxy in the hands of brutal fighters."),
	("Sword Cane, Ultrathin", "Basic Melee 1-H", 7, 7,000, 5, 0, bleed 1d4, 0, 0, "L", "analog, operative", "This thin blade comes with a scabbard that makes it resemble a stylish cane. Sword canes are popular on Absalom Station, where similar nonweapon items have some popularity as fashionable affectations. A sword cane can incorporate one of the following at the standard price for that item: 20 feet of retractable cable line, a personal comm unit, or a spotlight. A successful Perception check (DC = 15 + the weapon’s item level) is required to identify a sword cane as a weapon when it is sheathed."),
	("Chitinblade, Tactical", "Basic Melee 2-H", 4, 1,890, 3, 0, bleed 1d6, 0, 0, "1", "analog", "The serrated, sweeping blade of a chitinblade is based on technology recovered from encounters with the Swarm. The source material can come from a natural part of a creature’s body, but the final weapon is detached and wielded with two hands. A tactical chitinblade is modeled on an animal counterpart with little modification, but high-tech materials and manufacturing improve on nature in the microserrated, nanoserrated, and ultraserrated models."),
	("Hook Knife", "Basic Melee 1-H", 7, 6,300, 4, 0, bleed 1d6, 0, 0, "L", "analog", "Slightly longer than a survival knife, a hook knife features a wicked barb along the blade’s back edge and deals vicious wounds to enemies when wielded effectively. The drow invented the hook knife, but the weapon is a favorite among cruel mercenaries and other unsavory types."),
	("Curve Blade, Carbon Steel", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 4, 2,230, 5, 0, bleed 1d6, 0, 0, "2", "analog", "This graceful, curving blade further increases the drama inherent in sword fighting. Carbon steel blades bite deeply, causing bleeding wounds. The blade of an ultrathin curve blade looks delicate, but it is as hard as carbon steel and keeps a fine edge. Buzzblade curve blades vibrate when powered, tearing organic flesh and causing additional bleed damage. Dimensional slice curve blades have only a narrow visible blade area, surrounded by a solid aura; these are the sharpest and most dangerous curve blades on the market."),
	("Thresherblade, Tactical", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 5, 3,200, 5, 0, Bleed 1d6, 0, 0, "1", "analog", "Modeled on the arm blades of the brutal thresher lord, the thresherblade has an organic basket hilt that can be closed around a forelimb for extra support, making it easier for a trained user to hold and wield the weapon in one hand despite the blade’s size."),
	("Bone Cestus, Measured", "Basic Melee 1-H", 7, 5,500, 7, 0, bleed 1d6, 0, 0, "L", "analog", "Centuries ago, some kasathas crafted simple weapons out of crest-eaters’ bony protrusions; these formidable gauntlets were badges of honor for the mightiest kasathan warriors, and modern artisans have recreated that aesthetic in the form of bone cestuses, though now they are usually formed of state-of-the-art resin instead of crest-eater bone. Due to the flecks of minerals embedded within, bone cestuses are often warm to the touch, especially after they have been exposed to natural sunlight. These basic one-handed melee weapons are capable of punching through a foe’s defenses, sometimes puncturing vital organs in the process."),
	("Sword Cane, Zero-Edge", "Basic Melee 1-H", 10, 18,000, 7, 0, bleed 1d6, 0, 0, "L", "analog, operative", "This thin blade comes with a scabbard that makes it resemble a stylish cane. Sword canes are popular on Absalom Station, where similar nonweapon items have some popularity as fashionable affectations. A sword cane can incorporate one of the following at the standard price for that item: 20 feet of retractable cable line, a personal comm unit, or a spotlight. A successful Perception check (DC = 15 + the weapon’s item level) is required to identify a sword cane as a weapon when it is sheathed."),
	("Painclaw, Demonic", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 11, 25,000, 9, 0, bleed 1d6, 0, 0, "1", "injection (see text), unwieldy", ""This powered gauntlet has bladed spikes for fingers, which have built-in injectors connected to three reservoirs for storing substances used with the injection weapon special property. A painclaw can carry up to 3 doses of a drug, an injury poison, or a medicinal compound. Rather than trigger the injection on the weapon’s first attack, you can choose whether to inject one of these substances upon dealing damage with the painclaw (and even select which material to inject, if the three reservoirs contain different compounds). A painclaw can inject only one substance per attack.
	("Garrote, Microfilament", "Basic Melee 2-H", 12, 34,800, 10, 0, bleed 1d6, 0, 0, "L", "analog, conceal, grapple, operative, throttle", "A pair of slim handles connected by flexible cable made of a strong alloy, the garrote is a weapon strongly associated with assassination. That’s no accident, as the weapon’s primary use is to silently strangle creatures. However, a garrote can also be used to ensnare appendages. The wire garrote is the simplest version, while the nanofiber, microfilament, and monowire models use increasingly fine cables to deal substantially more damage. For instance, the monowire version has a cable as thin as a single complex molecule, which closes into the handles when the weapon isn’t in use. This construction results in a nearly invisible cable with an extreme edge."),
	("Fangblade", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 7, 5,430, 6, 0, bleed 1d8, 0, 0, "1", "powered (capacity 20; usage 1)", "Cheaper and less elegant than a ripper dueling sword, a fangblade is closer to an industrial chainsaw, with a toothed, motor-driven chain wrapped around its blade."),
	("Velstrac Flenser, Singer", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 7, 6,600, 7, 0, Bleed 1d8, 0, 0, "L", "powered (capacity 20, usage 1)", "Velstracs wield flensers0 blades designed to slice skin from muscle and muscle from bone0sometimes mounting these knives on rifles as bayonetS. Flensers are honed to supernatural sharpness and powered to vibrate with the rhythms of the wielder’s body. Velstracs have mastered the art of using these advanced melee weapons to inflict wounds while keeping targets alive. The table above shows an array of flensers, which can be purchased only in the darkest corners of the galaxy."),
	("Pike, Advanced", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 9, 12,200, 9, 0, bleed 1d8, 0, 0, "2", "analog, reach", "A pike is composed of a sharpened-aluminum, stainless-steel, or carbon-steel spike atop a light metal or polycarbonate staff."),
	("Thresherblade, Microserrated", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 9, 13,800, 11, 0, bleed 1d8, 0, 0, "1", "analog", "Modeled on the arm blades of the brutal thresher lord, the thresherblade has an organic basket hilt that can be closed around a forelimb for extra support, making it easier for a trained user to hold and wield the weapon in one hand despite the blade’s size."),
	("Sword Cane, Molecular Rift", "Basic Melee 1-H", 13, 50,900, 13, 0, bleed 1d8, 0, 0, "L", "analog, operative", "This thin blade comes with a scabbard that makes it resemble a stylish cane. Sword canes are popular on Absalom Station, where similar nonweapon items have some popularity as fashionable affectations. A sword cane can incorporate one of the following at the standard price for that item: 20 feet of retractable cable line, a personal comm unit, or a spotlight. A successful Perception check (DC = 15 + the weapon’s item level) is required to identify a sword cane as a weapon when it is sheathed."),
	("Chitinblade, Microserrated", "Basic Melee 2-H", 9, 12,400, 10, 0, bleed 2d4, 0, 0, "1", "analog", "The serrated, sweeping blade of a chitinblade is based on technology recovered from encounters with the Swarm. The source material can come from a natural part of a creature’s body, but the final weapon is detached and wielded with two hands. A tactical chitinblade is modeled on an animal counterpart with little modification, but high-tech materials and manufacturing improve on nature in the microserrated, nanoserrated, and ultraserrated models."),
	("Bone Cestus, Imposing", "Basic Melee 1-H", 12, 32,000, 10, 0, bleed 2d6, 0, 0, "L", "analog", "Centuries ago, some kasathas crafted simple weapons out of crest-eaters’ bony protrusions; these formidable gauntlets were badges of honor for the mightiest kasathan warriors, and modern artisans have recreated that aesthetic in the form of bone cestuses, though now they are usually formed of state-of-the-art resin instead of crest-eater bone. Due to the flecks of minerals embedded within, bone cestuses are often warm to the touch, especially after they have been exposed to natural sunlight. These basic one-handed melee weapons are capable of punching through a foe’s defenses, sometimes puncturing vital organs in the process."),
	("Longsword, Microserrated", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 9, 12,100, 11, 0, bleed 2d6, 0, 0, "1", "analog", "The single edge of this sword looks homogeneous to the naked eye, but it is actually made of thousands of microscopic teeth. The teeth tear through organic matter, causing significant damage and bleeding."),
	("Curve Blade, Ultrathin", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 10, 18,100, 16, 0, bleed 2d6, 0, 0, "1", "analog", "This graceful, curving blade further increases the drama inherent in sword fighting. Carbon steel blades bite deeply, causing bleeding wounds. The blade of an ultrathin curve blade looks delicate, but it is as hard as carbon steel and keeps a fine edge. Buzzblade curve blades vibrate when powered, tearing organic flesh and causing additional bleed damage. Dimensional slice curve blades have only a narrow visible blade area, surrounded by a solid aura; these are the sharpest and most dangerous curve blades on the market."),
	("Garrote, Monowire", "Basic Melee 2-H", 17, 225,000, 22, 0, bleed 2d6, 0, 0, "L", "analog, conceal, grapple, operative, throttle", "A pair of slim handles connected by flexible cable made of a strong alloy, the garrote is a weapon strongly associated with assassination. That’s no accident, as the weapon’s primary use is to silently strangle creatures. However, a garrote can also be used to ensnare appendages. The wire garrote is the simplest version, while the nanofiber, microfilament, and monowire models use increasingly fine cables to deal substantially more damage. For instance, the monowire version has a cable as thin as a single complex molecule, which closes into the handles when the weapon isn’t in use. This construction results in a nearly invisible cable with an extreme edge."),
	("Sword Cane, Dimensional Slice", "Basic Melee 1-H", 16, 160,000, 22, 0, bleed 2d6, 0, 0, "L", "analog, operative", "This thin blade comes with a scabbard that makes it resemble a stylish cane. Sword canes are popular on Absalom Station, where similar nonweapon items have some popularity as fashionable affectations. A sword cane can incorporate one of the following at the standard price for that item: 20 feet of retractable cable line, a personal comm unit, or a spotlight. A successful Perception check (DC = 15 + the weapon’s item level) is required to identify a sword cane as a weapon when it is sheathed."),
	("Painclaw, Draconic", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 19, 560,000, 27, 0, bleed 2d6, 0, 0, "1", "injection (see text), unwieldy", ""This powered gauntlet has bladed spikes for fingers, which have built-in injectors connected to three reservoirs for storing substances used with the injection weapon special property. A painclaw can carry up to 3 doses of a drug, an injury poison, or a medicinal compound. Rather than trigger the injection on the weapon’s first attack, you can choose whether to inject one of these substances upon dealing damage with the painclaw (and even select which material to inject, if the three reservoirs contain different compounds). A painclaw can inject only one substance per attack.
	("Velstrac Flenser, Debater", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 12, 37,600, 13, 0, Bleed 2d8, 0, 0, "L", "powered (capacity 20, usage 1)", "Velstracs wield flensers0 blades designed to slice skin from muscle and muscle from bone0sometimes mounting these knives on rifles as bayonetS. Flensers are honed to supernatural sharpness and powered to vibrate with the rhythms of the wielder’s body. Velstracs have mastered the art of using these advanced melee weapons to inflict wounds while keeping targets alive. The table above shows an array of flensers, which can be purchased only in the darkest corners of the galaxy."),
	("Chitinblade, Nanoserrated", "Basic Melee 2-H", 13, 46,400, 18, 0, bleed 2d8, 0, 0, "1", "analog", "The serrated, sweeping blade of a chitinblade is based on technology recovered from encounters with the Swarm. The source material can come from a natural part of a creature’s body, but the final weapon is detached and wielded with two hands. A tactical chitinblade is modeled on an animal counterpart with little modification, but high-tech materials and manufacturing improve on nature in the microserrated, nanoserrated, and ultraserrated models."),
	("Grindblade", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 13, 45,700, 22, 0, bleed 2d8, 0, 0, "1", "analog", "The sharp edge of a grindblade has been crafted with advanced micropitting technology that turns it into a destructive rasp at close to the molecular level, capable of inflicting hideous damage. So sharp and savage is their edge that most grindblade designers don’t even bother giving them a point."),
	("Thresherblade, Nanoserrated", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 13, 50,300, 22, 0, Bleed 2d8, 0, 0, "1", "analog", "Modeled on the arm blades of the brutal thresher lord, the thresherblade has an organic basket hilt that can be closed around a forelimb for extra support, making it easier for a trained user to hold and wield the weapon in one hand despite the blade’s size."),
	("Pike, Elite", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 15, 95,700, 31, 0, bleed 3d8, 0, 0, "2", "analog, reach", "A pike is composed of a sharpened-aluminum, stainless-steel, or carbon-steel spike atop a light metal or polycarbonate staff."),
	("Chitinblade, Ultraserrated", "Basic Melee 2-H", 17, 219,000, 36, 0, bleed 3d8, 0, 0, "1", "analog", "The serrated, sweeping blade of a chitinblade is based on technology recovered from encounters with the Swarm. The source material can come from a natural part of a creature’s body, but the final weapon is detached and wielded with two hands. A tactical chitinblade is modeled on an animal counterpart with little modification, but high-tech materials and manufacturing improve on nature in the microserrated, nanoserrated, and ultraserrated models."),
	("Thresherblade, Ultraserrated", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 17, 268,650, 44, 0, Bleed 4d8, 0, 0, "1", "analog", "Modeled on the arm blades of the brutal thresher lord, the thresherblade has an organic basket hilt that can be closed around a forelimb for extra support, making it easier for a trained user to hold and wield the weapon in one hand despite the blade’s size."),
	("Velstrac Flenser, Recluse", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 17, 261,360, 45, 0, Bleed 4d8, 0, 0, "L", "powered (capacity 20, usage 1)", "Velstracs wield flensers0 blades designed to slice skin from muscle and muscle from bone0sometimes mounting these knives on rifles as bayonetS. Flensers are honed to supernatural sharpness and powered to vibrate with the rhythms of the wielder’s body. Velstracs have mastered the art of using these advanced melee weapons to inflict wounds while keeping targets alive. The table above shows an array of flensers, which can be purchased only in the darkest corners of the galaxy."),
	("Bone Cestus, Severe", "Basic Melee 1-H", 17, 230,000, 28, 0, bleed 5d6, 0, 0, "L", "analog", "Centuries ago, some kasathas crafted simple weapons out of crest-eaters’ bony protrusions; these formidable gauntlets were badges of honor for the mightiest kasathan warriors, and modern artisans have recreated that aesthetic in the form of bone cestuses, though now they are usually formed of state-of-the-art resin instead of crest-eater bone. Due to the flecks of minerals embedded within, bone cestuses are often warm to the touch, especially after they have been exposed to natural sunlight. These basic one-handed melee weapons are capable of punching through a foe’s defenses, sometimes puncturing vital organs in the process."),
	("Curve Blade, Buzzblade", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 16, 184,300, 44, 0, bleed 5d6, 0, 0, "2", "powered (capacity 40; usage 2)", "This graceful, curving blade further increases the drama inherent in sword fighting. Carbon steel blades bite deeply, causing bleeding wounds. The blade of an ultrathin curve blade looks delicate, but it is as hard as carbon steel and keeps a fine edge. Buzzblade curve blades vibrate when powered, tearing organic flesh and causing additional bleed damage. Dimensional slice curve blades have only a narrow visible blade area, surrounded by a solid aura; these are the sharpest and most dangerous curve blades on the market."),
	("Longsword, Ultraserrated", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 18, 368,100, 44, 0, bleed 6d6, 0, 0, "1", "analog", "The single edge of this sword looks homogeneous to the naked eye, but it is actually made of thousands of microscopic teeth. The teeth tear through organic matter, causing significant damage and bleeding."),
	("Curve Blade, Dimensional Slice", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 20, 815,000, 66, 0, bleed 6d6, 0, 0, "2", "powered (capacity 40; usage 2)", "This graceful, curving blade further increases the drama inherent in sword fighting. Carbon steel blades bite deeply, causing bleeding wounds. The blade of an ultrathin curve blade looks delicate, but it is as hard as carbon steel and keeps a fine edge. Buzzblade curve blades vibrate when powered, tearing organic flesh and causing additional bleed damage. Dimensional slice curve blades have only a narrow visible blade area, surrounded by a solid aura; these are the sharpest and most dangerous curve blades on the market."),
	("Flare Axe, White Star", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 11, 23,100, 16, 0, burn 1d10, 0, 0, "1", "powered (capacity 20; usage 1)", "A flare axe pushes a magnetically contained wave of plasma in a semicircular arc parallel to the haft that resembles a miniature solar flare. The color of plasma indicates the relative temperature (and therefore damage output) of each weapon: red star flare axes are the standard model, yellow star and white star flare axes are more dangerous, and blue star flare axes inflict the most destruction."),
	("Flare Axe, Red Star", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 1, 120, 2, 0, burn 1d4, 0, 0, "1", "powered (capacity 20; usage 1)", "A flare axe pushes a magnetically contained wave of plasma in a semicircular arc parallel to the haft that resembles a miniature solar flare. The color of plasma indicates the relative temperature (and therefore damage output) of each weapon: red star flare axes are the standard model, yellow star and white star flare axes are more dangerous, and blue star flare axes inflict the most destruction."),
	("Resistance Rod, Strain-Gauge", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 2, 510, 2, 0, burn 1d4, 0, 0, "L", "powered (capacity 20; usage 1)", "The metal rod has a carefully insulated grip and a resistance coil designed to generate substantial heat surrounding the bulk of the baton’s shaft. Though the weapon is named for its engineering, it is often used by members of the Android Abolitionist Front and other rebel groups because of its evocative name and ease of construction. Straingauge resistance rods retain some flexibility and are easier to use, while thermistor and piezoresistor resistance rods employ more advanced coils to generate a hotter output. Induction resistance rods operate at higher outputs and are significantly more dangerous."),
	("Flame Spinner, Fireball", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 1, 225, 3, 0, burn 1d4, 0, 0, "1", "analog, free hands (2), fueled (capacity 20; usage 1), unwieldy", "A flame spinner consists of two weighted balls attached to a length of cable; the pair is spun in an elegant, showy dance of spinning fire. Fireball and immolation flame spinners use petrol to generate a flaming nimbus around the ball’s metal casing, while supernova and fission flame spinners dispense with the casing and instead compress the petrol to generate a dense mass of blazing heat in place of each ball. Using a flame spinner effectively is difficult due to the complex handling required, and kasathas and other races with additional limbs find they have a substantial advantage in that regard."),
	("Heat-Amp Gauntlet, Mk 1", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 2, 500, 3, 0, Burn 1d4, 0, 0, "1", "powered (capacity 20, usage 1)", "Quorlus have developed gauntlets that store and amplify ambient heat, unleashing it in hand-to-hand combat. Notorious for their use of these weapons, quorlu infiltrators and sappers also use heat-amp gauntlets to start fires to hinder their enemies."),
	("Junk Censer", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 1, 125, 3, 0, burn 1d4, 0, 0, "L", "analog, fueled (capacity 20; usage 4), thrown (10.)", "A chain, cable, or other cord connects the long handle of this weapon to a perforated or grated container that is filled with exceptionally volatile compounds. Few are foolish enough to use such a weapon, so there’s been little advancement on its design, but many space goblins use junk censers with reckless and even gleeful abandon. While it is most often wielded in melee, the junk censer can also be thrown at an enemy. Like many cobbled-together weapons, a junk censer is unstable; on an attack roll of a natural 1, it deals its regular damage to the user and gains the broken condition."),
	("Inferno Knife", "Basic Melee 1-H", 4, 2,100, 2, 0, burn 1d6, 0, 0, "L", "analog, operative", ""Not all developments in military technology are successful. Originally designed to be a perfect survival tool, the inferno knife combines the cutting prowess of a survival knife with the virtues of a lighter and road flare. By squeezing one trigger, the user can inject a small stream of fuel from the hilt’s reservoir onto the blade’s tip, and a secondary trigger can ignite it, creating a small torch to signal others or light campfires. The product’s launch was disastrous, and users logged hundreds of complaints about the knives’ needless complexity. As a result, inferno knives have flooded the market and become showy weapons for criminals and performers, though timing the blade’s ignition in combat remains an unpredictable art.
	("Angel Wing, Movanic", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 4, 1,890, 3, 0, burn 1d6, 0, 0, "L", "powered (capacity 20; usage 2), unwieldy", "Though it appears as an extended sword hilt when still, the angel wing takes its name from the uncontained plasma that trails in an arc following the leading edge when the blade is swung. The weapon is favored by followers of Sarenrae, who take pride in mastering the sophisticated art of its use. Movanic angel wings have darker, almost shadowy blades; monadic angel wings have golden plasma trails; and the astral angel wing burns white hot. "
	("Blaze Scimitar, Acolyte", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 2, 740, 3, 0, burn 1d6, 20, 1, "1", "bright", "Known far and wide for their fighting prowess, Sarenites who delve into the darkest corners of the universe often take the holy weapon of their goddess with them. A blaze scimitar is made of a metallic alloy that can be heated to blistering temperatures again and again through use of a an induction magnet. These golden blades glow bright orange when activated and shed light in a wide area when they strike a blow. Due to their weight and the power required to follow through with attacks, they must be wielded with two hands."),
	("Searing Grip, Low-Heat", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 5, 3,010, 3, 0, burn 1d6, 0, 0, "L", "grapple, powered (capacity 20; usage 2)", "The searing grip was originally designed for artists who craft their visions in various metals. The grip has several layers of insulation to separate the wearer’s hand from the resistance coils lining the palm and fingers; as such, the glove is often mistaken for a simple well-insulated work glove. Lengthy application of this heat can soften many metals, which aids in sculpting efforts, but even a quick touch can inflict painful burns, allowing searing grips to double as low-profile weapons. The versions typically employed by sculptors are designated low-heat and high-heat, though this is a relative distinction, as both operate at temperatures capable of dealing substantial damage. The weaponized searing grip drops the pretense of being an artist’s tool, though those trained in its use find that its functionality doesn’t differ substantially from the other models."),
	("Flame Spinner, Immolation", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 5, 2,860, 4, 0, burn 1d6, 0, 0, "1", "analog, free hands (2), fueled (capacity 20; usage 2), unwieldy", "A flame spinner consists of two weighted balls attached to a length of cable; the pair is spun in an elegant, showy dance of spinning fire. Fireball and immolation flame spinners use petrol to generate a flaming nimbus around the ball’s metal casing, while supernova and fission flame spinners dispense with the casing and instead compress the petrol to generate a dense mass of blazing heat in place of each ball. Using a flame spinner effectively is difficult due to the complex handling required, and kasathas and other races with additional limbs find they have a substantial advantage in that regard."),
	("Heat-Amp Gauntlet, Mk 2", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 7, 7,500, 7, 0, Burn 1d6, 0, 0, "1", "powered (capacity 20, usage 1)", "Quorlus have developed gauntlets that store and amplify ambient heat, unleashing it in hand-to-hand combat. Notorious for their use of these weapons, quorlu infiltrators and sappers also use heat-amp gauntlets to start fires to hinder their enemies."),
	("Flare Axe, Yellow Star", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 5, 2,710, 4, 0, burn 1d8, 0, 0, "1", "powered (capacity 20; usage 1)", "A flare axe pushes a magnetically contained wave of plasma in a semicircular arc parallel to the haft that resembles a miniature solar flare. The color of plasma indicates the relative temperature (and therefore damage output) of each weapon: red star flare axes are the standard model, yellow star and white star flare axes are more dangerous, and blue star flare axes inflict the most destruction."),
	("Skyfire Sword, Tactical", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 7, 6,120, 5, 0, burn 1d8, 0, 0, "1", "powered (capacity 20; usage 2)", "Originally, these swords were known by their manufacturing ID, BSB–1750. Their popularity with the Skyfire Legion led to their colloquial name, Skyfire swords. Vents for burning gas jets line one edge of the hollow blade. When powered, magnetic fields contain and ignite the gases into a glowing corona of flames. "
	("Blaze Scimitar, Disciple", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 8, 9,200, 7, 0, burn 1d8, 20, 1, "1", "bright", "Known far and wide for their fighting prowess, Sarenites who delve into the darkest corners of the universe often take the holy weapon of their goddess with them. A blaze scimitar is made of a metallic alloy that can be heated to blistering temperatures again and again through use of a an induction magnet. These golden blades glow bright orange when activated and shed light in a wide area when they strike a blow. Due to their weight and the power required to follow through with attacks, they must be wielded with two hands."),
	("Resistance Rod, Thermistor", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 9, 12,600, 10, 0, burn 2d4, 0, 0, "L", "powered (capacity 20; usage 1)", "The metal rod has a carefully insulated grip and a resistance coil designed to generate substantial heat surrounding the bulk of the baton’s shaft. Though the weapon is named for its engineering, it is often used by members of the Android Abolitionist Front and other rebel groups because of its evocative name and ease of construction. Straingauge resistance rods retain some flexibility and are easier to use, while thermistor and piezoresistor resistance rods employ more advanced coils to generate a hotter output. Induction resistance rods operate at higher outputs and are significantly more dangerous."),
	("Angel Wing, Monadic", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 7, 5,500, 7, 0, burn 2d6, 0, 0, "L", "powered (capacity 20; usage 2), unwieldy", "Though it appears as an extended sword hilt when still, the angel wing takes its name from the uncontained plasma that trails in an arc following the leading edge when the blade is swung. The weapon is favored by followers of Sarenrae, who take pride in mastering the sophisticated art of its use. Movanic angel wings have darker, almost shadowy blades; monadic angel wings have golden plasma trails; and the astral angel wing burns white hot. "
