	("Ice Needle, Subterfuge", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 18, 384,000, 45, 0, Injection DC +2, 0, 0, "L", "conceal, injection, powered (capacity 80; usage 4)", "This handheld melee weapon appears to be nothing more than a handle with a slot in one end. Once a vial of an injectable substance is inserted into this slot, the ice needle forms a slender spike of ice around that liquid core, allowing you to inject the substance into a foe with a virtually untraceable weapon. Undercover and furtive ice needles are often used primarily for their injecting capabilities, while artifice, espionage, and subterfuge ice needles deal significant damage along with the injection."),
