	("Storm Hammer, Metamagnetic", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 20, 728,000, by grenade, 0, knockdown, 0, 0, "1", "powered (capacity 20; usage 2)", "This massive warhammer’s magnetic discharge deals additional damage that can sometimes knock a target to the ground. Dwarves in the Diasporan Star Citadels first developed storm hammers to bring larger foes to a more manageable height; many bear aesthetic designs hearkening to Angradd and other dwarven motifs. The materials used in a storm hammer’s construction determine the magnetic force and thereby the strength of the weapon; available versions include diamagnetic, paramagnetic, ferromagnetic, antiferromagnetic, and metamagnetic storm hammers."),
	("Bone Scepter, Chill", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 3, 1,490, 3, 0, leech, 0, 0, "L", "analog, antibiological", "These narrow clubs are often constructed of numerous intertwined bones0as one might expect from a weapon designed by Eoxians0infused with a silvery absolute-zero alloy that instantly draws the heat out of living creatures on contact. Chill bone scepters and void bone scepters have fine threads of the rare alloy, while rigor bone scepters and cadaver bone scepters shimmer with it."),
	("Bone Scepter, Void", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 8, 9,850, 7, 0, leech, 0, 0, "L", "analog, antibiological", "These narrow clubs are often constructed of numerous intertwined bones0as one might expect from a weapon designed by Eoxians0infused with a silvery absolute-zero alloy that instantly draws the heat out of living creatures on contact. Chill bone scepters and void bone scepters have fine threads of the rare alloy, while rigor bone scepters and cadaver bone scepters shimmer with it."),
	("Bone Scepter, Rigor", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 13, 51,800, 17, 0, leech, 0, 0, "L", "analog, antibiological", "These narrow clubs are often constructed of numerous intertwined bones0as one might expect from a weapon designed by Eoxians0infused with a silvery absolute-zero alloy that instantly draws the heat out of living creatures on contact. Chill bone scepters and void bone scepters have fine threads of the rare alloy, while rigor bone scepters and cadaver bone scepters shimmer with it."),
	("Bone Scepter, Cadaver", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 19, 598,000, 42, 0, leech, 0, 0, "L", "analog, antibiological", "These narrow clubs are often constructed of numerous intertwined bones0as one might expect from a weapon designed by Eoxians0infused with a silvery absolute-zero alloy that instantly draws the heat out of living creatures on contact. Chill bone scepters and void bone scepters have fine threads of the rare alloy, while rigor bone scepters and cadaver bone scepters shimmer with it."),
	("Resonant Gauntlet, Cellular", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 5, 3,230, 2, 0, nauseate, 0, 0, "L", "boost 1d4, powered (capacity 20; usage 1)", ""The translucent crystal network in a resonant gauntlet has its origins in the rings of the gas giant Liavara. The rings contain crystal fragments thought to record every sonic vibration that passes through them. Researchers have yet to fully decode the information they hold, but they have been able to develop a material that shares some of the crystal’s properties.
	("Resonant Gauntlet, Molecular", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 10, 19,900, 7, 0, nauseate, 0, 0, "L", "boost 3d4, powered (capacity 20; usage 1)", ""The translucent crystal network in a resonant gauntlet has its origins in the rings of the gas giant Liavara. The rings contain crystal fragments thought to record every sonic vibration that passes through them. Researchers have yet to fully decode the information they hold, but they have been able to develop a material that shares some of the crystal’s properties.
	("Resonant Gauntlet, Atomic", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 15, 124,000, 20, 0, nauseate, 0, 0, "L", "boost 4d4, powered (capacity 20; usage 1)", ""The translucent crystal network in a resonant gauntlet has its origins in the rings of the gas giant Liavara. The rings contain crystal fragments thought to record every sonic vibration that passes through them. Researchers have yet to fully decode the information they hold, but they have been able to develop a material that shares some of the crystal’s properties.
	("Resonant Gauntlet, Quantum", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 20, 901,000, 39, 0, nauseate, 0, 0, "L", "boost 3d12, powered (capacity 20; usage 1)", ""The translucent crystal network in a resonant gauntlet has its origins in the rings of the gas giant Liavara. The rings contain crystal fragments thought to record every sonic vibration that passes through them. Researchers have yet to fully decode the information they hold, but they have been able to develop a material that shares some of the crystal’s properties.
	("Neutriad Flail", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 5, 3,200, 4, 0, Push, 0, 0, "1", "disarm, force, powered (capacity 20, usage 1)", "A neutriad flail is a 5th level advanced melee weapon that deals 1d8 bludgeoning damage and has the push critical hit effect. It has the disarm, force, and powered (capacity 20, usage 1) special properties and 1 bulk, and it costs 3,200 credits."),
	("Electrovore Glove, Static", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 2, 750, 3, 0, recharge 2, 0, 0, "L", "powered (capacity 20; usage 1)", "With these battle gauntlets, enterprising weaponsmiths have harnessed the electrovore’s ability to conduct and siphon electrical energy. Using a combination of an electrovore’s spines, conductive wiring, and miniaturized storage cells, electrovore gloves deliver electricity damage and can even drain electrical impulses from living creatures and robots with a critical hit."),
	("Electrovore Glove, Aurora", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 7, 6,250, 7, 0, recharge 2, 0, 0, "L", "powered (capacity 20; usage 1)", "With these battle gauntlets, enterprising weaponsmiths have harnessed the electrovore’s ability to conduct and siphon electrical energy. Using a combination of an electrovore’s spines, conductive wiring, and miniaturized storage cells, electrovore gloves deliver electricity damage and can even drain electrical impulses from living creatures and robots with a critical hit."),
	("Electrovore Glove, Storm", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 13, 49,000, 21, 0, recharge 4, 0, 0, "L", "powered (capacity 40; usage 2)", "With these battle gauntlets, enterprising weaponsmiths have harnessed the electrovore’s ability to conduct and siphon electrical energy. Using a combination of an electrovore’s spines, conductive wiring, and miniaturized storage cells, electrovore gloves deliver electricity damage and can even drain electrical impulses from living creatures and robots with a critical hit."),
	("Electrovore Glove, Tempest", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 18, 375,000, 42, 0, recharge 4, 0, 0, "L", "powered (capacity 40; usage 2)", "With these battle gauntlets, enterprising weaponsmiths have harnessed the electrovore’s ability to conduct and siphon electrical energy. Using a combination of an electrovore’s spines, conductive wiring, and miniaturized storage cells, electrovore gloves deliver electricity damage and can even drain electrical impulses from living creatures and robots with a critical hit."),
	("Plasma Doshko, Red Star", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 6, 4,650, 5, 0, severe wound, 0, 0, "1", "powered (capacity 20; usage 2)", "The plasma versions of these traditional vesk weapons use the same popular naming convention as other plasma weapons. "
	("Plasma Sword, Tactical", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 9, 14,550, 9, 0, severe wound, 0, 0, "1", "powered (capacity 20; usage 2)", "A plasma generator is seated within this sword’s hilt. A plasma-resistant ceramic housing focuses the beam with the assistance of a localized force field, either in a single straight beam or along a magnetized blunted blade or wire-like lines. When the sword is unpowered, the plasma beam disappears."),
	("Plasma Doshko, Yellow Star", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 10, 17,000, 11, 0, severe wound, 0, 0, "1", "powered (capacity 20; usage 2)", "The plasma versions of these traditional vesk weapons use the same popular naming convention as other plasma weapons. "
	("Nova Lance, White Star", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 12, 39,500, 17, 0, severe wound, 0, 0, "2", "powered (capacity 40; usage 2), reach", "This long weapon bears a plasma sheath at its striking tip. Although similar weapons are produced on many worlds, nova lances’ use in Eoxian racing broadcasts has made them especially popular throughout the Pact Worlds. They are typically manufactured by corporations that specialize in plasma pistols and plasma rifles and thus their models follow the same naming conventions: red star, yellow star, white star, and blue star."),
	("Plasma Sword, Red Star", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 13, 54,300, 18, 0, severe wound, 0, 0, "1", "powered (capacity 40; usage 4)", "A plasma generator is seated within this sword’s hilt. A plasmaresistant ceramic housing focuses the beam with the assistance of a localized force field, either in a single straight beam or along a magnetized blunted blade or wire-like lines. When the sword is unpowered, the plasma beam disappears. "
	("Battle Ribbon, Zero-Edge", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 12, 35,200, 22, 0, severe wound, 0, 0, "1", "analog, operative, professional (dancer)", "The battleflowers of Ning have been using battle ribbons in ritualized combat for millennia, their use dating back to long before the Gap. The weapon is a 10-foot-long ribbon and about 3 inches wide with sharpened edges, and is employed in rippling and flowing motions around the user. Battle ribbons are difficult to use without training, so most who take up the battle ribbon seek apprenticeship with the famous battleflowers of Ning to learn the elaborate performance art0though acquiring such a mentor is difficult, as they take students only rarely. Battle ribbon varieties start with modern materials used in a traditional blade, then proceed to the innovations of the microedge and zero-edge battle ribbons."),
	("Kishaxe, Havoc", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 14, 70,000, 22, 0, severe wound, 0, 0, "2", "analog, archaic", "Though crudely crafted from bits of scrap and debris, kishaxes hit hard, with some models able to chop off limbs with a single brutal blow."),
	("Plasma Sword, Yellow Star", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 15, 127,000, 22, 0, severe wound, 0, 0, "1", "powered (capacity 40; usage 4)", "A plasma generator is seated within this sword’s hilt. A plasmaresistant ceramic housing focuses the beam with the assistance of a localized force field, either in a single straight beam or along a magnetized blunted blade or wire-like lines. When the sword is unpowered, the plasma beam disappears. "
	("Monowhip", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 15, 107,000, 25, 0, severe wound, 0, 0, "L", "analog, disarm, reach, trip", "Designed to deal maximum damage, a monowhip is woven of monofilament fibers reinforced with carbon particles. Weighted at one end and spooled from a tough carbon-fiber grip, it delivers surgical-quality lacerations with minimal strength. The cuts delivered are so clean that victims sometimes fail to notice a severed limb until they are overwhelmed by a rush of blood loss."),
	("Plasma Doshko, White Star", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 15, 126,800, 27, 0, severe wound, 0, 0, "1", "powered (capacity 20; usage 2)", "The plasma versions of these traditional vesk weapons use the same popular naming convention as other plasma weapons. "
	("Nova Lance, Blue Star", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 17, 279,000, 28, 0, severe wound, 0, 0, "2", "powered (capacity 40; usage 4), reach", "This long weapon bears a plasma sheath at its striking tip. Although similar weapons are produced on many worlds, nova lances’ use in Eoxian racing broadcasts has made them especially popular throughout the Pact Worlds. They are typically manufactured by corporations that specialize in plasma pistols and plasma rifles and thus their models follow the same naming conventions: red star, yellow star, white star, and blue star."),
	("Longsword, Zero-Edge", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 14, 79,500, 31, 0, severe wound, 0, 0, "L", "analog", "Crafted with quantum technology, the blade of this sword seems blurry due to its exceptionally fine edge."),
	("Solar Brand, Blue Star", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 17, 245,000, 31, 0, severe wound, 0, 0, "L", "powered (capacity 80; usage 4)", "A solar brand consists of a flat plate that fits against the back of the hand, secured with a grip or a band. Once activated, the solar brand generates a protruding, arrowhead-shaped field of plasma. A red star solar brand doesn’t leave devastating marks, but the stronger yellow star, white star, and blue star models can cause lasting damage."),
	("Plasma Sword, White Star", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 18, 415,600, 36, 0, severe wound, 0, 0, "1", "powered (capacity 40; usage 4)", "A plasma generator is seated within this sword’s hilt. A plasmaresistant ceramic housing focuses the beam with the assistance of a localized force field, either in a single straight beam or along a magnetized blunted blade or wire-like lines. When the sword is unpowered, the plasma beam disappears. "
	("Plasma Doshko, Blue Star", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 18, 364,100, 38, 0, severe wound, 0, 0, "1", "powered (capacity 20; usage 2)", "The plasma versions of these traditional vesk weapons use the same popular naming convention as other plasma weapons. "
	("Flame Doshko, Solar Flare", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 19, 595,000, 45, 0, severe wound, 0, 0, "1", "powered (capacity 20; usage 1)", "When activated, the blade of this doshko heats up by means of internal heating coils. The doshko deals fire damage and can also cause traumatic injuries. "
	("Plasma Sword, Blue Star", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 20, 920,250, 45, 0, severe wound, 0, 0, "1", "powered (capacity 40; usage 4)", "A plasma generator is seated within this sword’s hilt. A plasmaresistant ceramic housing focuses the beam with the assistance of a localized force field, either in a single straight beam or along a magnetized blunted blade or wire-like lines. When the sword is unpowered, the plasma beam disappears. "
	("Kishaxe, Onslaught", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 19, 540,000, 49, 0, severe wound, 0, 0, "2", "analog, archaic", "Though crudely crafted from bits of scrap and debris, kishaxes hit hard, with some models able to chop off limbs with a single brutal blow."),
	("Meteor Glaive, Paragon", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 18, 385,000, 55, 0, severe wound, 0, 0, "2", "fueled (capacity 40; usage 40), reach", "The glaive is an ancient weapon, originally developed for use by and against mounted warriors. The meteor glaive is the Skyfire Legion’s update on the original design, incorporating a petrol tank near the base of the slightly curved blade and relying on a long shaft to keep the wielder at a safe distance. Meteor glaives are classified into tactical, advanced, elite, and paragon models."),
	("Shock Pad, Static", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 2, 1,100, 2, 0, staggered, 0, 0, "L", "integrated (1 slot), powered (capacity 20; usage 1), stun", "A shock pad can be installed into an armor upgrade slot. When the user hits a target with the shock pad, the weapon emits an electric discharge that stuns or damages the target. These weapons are particularly valued in suits of powered armor that bring substantial strength to bear. Shock pads typically are available in static, aurora, storm, and tempest models."),
	("Stun Staff, Tactical", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 2, 750, 2, 0, staggered, 0, 0, "1", "block, powered (capacity 20; usage 1), stun", "Stewards often make use of the combined offensive and defensive flexibility of a stun staff, a polycarbonate staff with an electrodelined striking surface. These weapons are commonly used in riot control due to their ability to easily inflict nonlethal damage, but they’re also valuable in self-defense, and their streamlined appearance means they don’t attract overmuch attention at formal events where security is as necessary as discretion. As a cousin of the shock truncheon, the stun staff bears a similar naming convention, with the tactical stun staff as the most basic, followed by the static, aurora, storm, and tempest models. "
	("Zero Knife, Frostbite-Class", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 4, 2,810, 2, 0, staggered, 0, 0, "L", "conceal, operative, powered (capacity 40; usage 1)", "A zero knife appears much like a folded switchblade, though the hilt is somewhat bulkier due to the battery; when activated, the zero knife forms a blade formed entirely of an aura of intense cold rather than steel. The frostbite-class zero knife is an easily obtained weapon whose blade rapidly accumulates flakes of frozen material in most atmospheres. The more advanced hailstorm-class, blizzard-class, avalancheclass, and icequake-class zero knives incorporate technology that eliminates the build-up."),
	("Gale Baton, Tempest", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 6, 4,240, 3, 0, staggered, 0, 0, "L", "deflect, operative, powered (capacity 80; usage 4)", "A baton is a thin, solid metal shaft, usually with a textured rubber grip. A tactical baton can be used to inflict precise bludgeoning blows. An advanced baton, used by elite mercenary and security companies, often has an additional shaft, as well as a weighted end that can be powered to connect with substantially more force than a tactical baton. "
	("Spined Iceblade, Frostbite-Class", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 4, 2,150, 3, 0, staggered, 0, 0, "1", "powered (capacity 20; usage 1)", "The spined iceblade is a variant of the traditional kasathan spined blade. Its longer, curved handle includes internal channels where coolant builds up until it is released by the wielder’s movements. Frostbite-class, hailstorm-class, blizzard-class, and avalancheclass spined iceblades are all readily available in markets that regularly serve kasathas, but similar weapons appearing on distant worlds have intrigued kasathan archaeologists."),
	("Zero Knife, Hailstorm-Class", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 7, 5,540, 3, 0, staggered, 0, 0, "L", "conceal, operative, powered (capacity 40; usage 1)", "A zero knife appears much like a folded switchblade, though the hilt is somewhat bulkier due to the battery; when activated, the zero knife forms a blade formed entirely of an aura of intense cold rather than steel. The frostbite-class zero knife is an easily obtained weapon whose blade rapidly accumulates flakes of frozen material in most atmospheres. The more advanced hailstorm-class, blizzard-class, avalancheclass, and icequake-class zero knives incorporate technology that eliminates the build-up."),
	("Frost Maul, Aufeis", "Advanced Melee 2-H", 3, 1,240, 4, 0, staggered, 0, 0, "2", "powered (capacity 20; usage 2), sunder", "A two-handed hammer with a reservoir of coolant in its head, a frost maul simultaneously bludgeons and chills its target. As most substances become brittle and prone to shattering when subjected to extremely low temperatures, the frost maul excels at damaging objects it hits. Frost mauls come in aufeis, iceberg, floe, and glacier models."),
	("Mindspike, Tactical", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 6, 4,400, 4, 0, Staggered, 0, 0, "L", "analog", "The impact of this insectile-looking spike can cause pain or otherwise addle the target’s nervous system."),
	("Shock Pad, Aurora", "Advanced Melee 1-H", 6, 4,900, 5, 0, staggered, 0, 0, "L", "integrated (1 slot), powered (capacity 20; usage 1), stun", "A shock pad can be installed into an armor upgrade slot. When the user hits a target with the shock pad, the weapon emits an electric discharge that stuns or damages the target. These weapons are particularly valued in suits of powered armor that bring substantial strength to bear. Shock pads typically are available in static, aurora, storm, and tempest models."),
