	("Incendiary Grenade, Mk 5", "Grenades 1-H", 16, 44,000, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (10d6 F; 5d6 burn; 15.)", "Incendiary grenades detonate in a spray of superheated plasma."),
	("Incendiary Grenade, Mk 6", "Grenades 1-H", 18, 108,800, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (12d6 F; 6d6 burn; 15.)", "Incendiary grenades detonate in a spray of superheated plasma."),
	("Junkbot Grenade", "Grenades 1-H", 9, 2,250, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (10.; see text)", "When you use a junkbot grenade, you set it to either handy or healing, then throw it into a pile of inert technological equipment of at least 1 bulk. When the grenade lands, it spreads magical nanites over the blast radius. Over the course of the next round, the nanites convert the junk into a handy junkbot or healing junkbot, as those spells except as detailed here. Either spell has a caster level of 9th. You must command the junkbot verbally. The junkbot created from this effect lasts for 1 minute."),
	("Microbot Grenade, Mk 1", "Grenades 1-H", 6, 1,400, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (5.; 1d6)", "When a microbot grenade detonates, the blast radius fills with microbots like those created by the microbot assault spell. The microbots consider only creatures in the blast radius to be the thrower’s enemies, and they do not discriminate between the thrower’s allies and enemies. The microbots last for 3 rounds. More advanced grenades create more dangerous microbots. The first time a creature leaves the area of the microbot cloud during a round, that creature takes an amount of magical piercing damage according to the grenade’s type."),
	("Microbot Grenade, Mk 2", "Grenades 1-H", 9, 4,200, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (5.; 2d6)", "When a microbot grenade detonates, the blast radius fills with microbots like those created by the microbot assault spell. The microbots consider only creatures in the blast radius to be the thrower’s enemies, and they do not discriminate between the thrower’s allies and enemies. The microbots last for 3 rounds. More advanced grenades create more dangerous microbots. The first time a creature leaves the area of the microbot cloud during a round, that creature takes an amount of magical piercing damage according to the grenade’s type."),
	("Microbot Grenade, Mk 3", "Grenades 1-H", 12, 12,500, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (5.; 3d6)", "When a microbot grenade detonates, the blast radius fills with microbots like those created by the microbot assault spell. The microbots consider only creatures in the blast radius to be the thrower’s enemies, and they do not discriminate between the thrower’s allies and enemies. The microbots last for 3 rounds. More advanced grenades create more dangerous microbots. The first time a creature leaves the area of the microbot cloud during a round, that creature takes an amount of magical piercing damage according to the grenade’s type."),
	("Microbot Grenade, Mk 4", "Grenades 1-H", 15, 37,000, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (5.; 3d10)", "When a microbot grenade detonates, the blast radius fills with microbots like those created by the microbot assault spell. The microbots consider only creatures in the blast radius to be the thrower’s enemies, and they do not discriminate between the thrower’s allies and enemies. The microbots last for 3 rounds. More advanced grenades create more dangerous microbots. The first time a creature leaves the area of the microbot cloud during a round, that creature takes an amount of magical piercing damage according to the grenade’s type."),
	("Microbot Grenade, Mk 5", "Grenades 1-H", 18, 109,000, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (5.; 4d12)", "When a microbot grenade detonates, the blast radius fills with microbots like those created by the microbot assault spell. The microbots consider only creatures in the blast radius to be the thrower’s enemies, and they do not discriminate between the thrower’s allies and enemies. The microbots last for 3 rounds. More advanced grenades create more dangerous microbots. The first time a creature leaves the area of the microbot cloud during a round, that creature takes an amount of magical piercing damage according to the grenade’s type."),
	("Necro Grenade, Mk 1", "Grenades 1-H", 5, 870, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (1d8 C; 10), necrotic", "These grenades are crafted to resemble leering, pygmy-sized skulls. When a necro grenade detonates, it expels a shroud of chemical coolants from its exposed eyes and mouth. This freezing gas is laced with minor traces of negative energy, draining the living and healing undead caught in the area of effect."),
	("Necro Grenade, Mk 2", "Grenades 1-H", 9, 3,900, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (2d8 C; 15), necrotic", "These grenades are crafted to resemble leering, pygmy-sized skulls. When a necro grenade detonates, it expels a shroud of chemical coolants from its exposed eyes and mouth. This freezing gas is laced with minor traces of negative energy, draining the living and healing undead caught in the area of effect."),
	("Necro Grenade, Mk 3", "Grenades 1-H", 13, 14,640, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (4d8 C; 20), necrotic", "These grenades are crafted to resemble leering, pygmy-sized skulls. When a necro grenade detonates, it expels a shroud of chemical coolants from its exposed eyes and mouth. This freezing gas is laced with minor traces of negative energy, draining the living and healing undead caught in the area of effect."),
	("Necro Grenade, Mk 4", "Grenades 1-H", 17, 72,900, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (6d8 C; 20), necrotic", "These grenades are crafted to resemble leering, pygmy-sized skulls. When a necro grenade detonates, it expels a shroud of chemical coolants from its exposed eyes and mouth. This freezing gas is laced with minor traces of negative energy, draining the living and healing undead caught in the area of effect."),
	("Pheromone Grenade, Mk 1", "Grenades 1-H", 4, 325, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (10.; see text)", "Though scientists understand little about how a vracinea’s paralyzing scent affects the brain, weapon designers across the galaxy have been inspired by its effects and have replicated them with custom hybrid grenades. When it bursts, a pheromone grenade deals no damage, instead dispersing a powerful cocktail of supercharged pheromones and magically modified mind-altering chemicals in the listed blast radius. Each creature in the radius that inhales the pheromones (which bypass even active environmental protections from a suit of armor) must attempt a Will saving throw. A creature that fails its save is fascinated for a number of rounds equal to the grenade’s mark number as they gaze in wonder at sparkling trails that only they can see. A creature that succeeds at its save is immune to the effects of pheromone grenades for 24 hours. This is a mind-affecting effect."),
	("Pheromone Grenade, Mk 2", "Grenades 1-H", 8, 1,400, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (15.; see text)", "Though scientists understand little about how a vracinea’s paralyzing scent affects the brain, weapon designers across the galaxy have been inspired by its effects and have replicated them with custom hybrid grenades. When it bursts, a pheromone grenade deals no damage, instead dispersing a powerful cocktail of supercharged pheromones and magically modified mind-altering chemicals in the listed blast radius. Each creature in the radius that inhales the pheromones (which bypass even active environmental protections from a suit of armor) must attempt a Will saving throw. A creature that fails its save is fascinated for a number of rounds equal to the grenade’s mark number as they gaze in wonder at sparkling trails that only they can see. A creature that succeeds at its save is immune to the effects of pheromone grenades for 24 hours. This is a mind-affecting effect."),
	("Pheromone Grenade, Mk 3", "Grenades 1-H", 12, 5,300, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (20.; see text)", "Though scientists understand little about how a vracinea’s paralyzing scent affects the brain, weapon designers across the galaxy have been inspired by its effects and have replicated them with custom hybrid grenades. When it bursts, a pheromone grenade deals no damage, instead dispersing a powerful cocktail of supercharged pheromones and magically modified mind-altering chemicals in the listed blast radius. Each creature in the radius that inhales the pheromones (which bypass even active environmental protections from a suit of armor) must attempt a Will saving throw. A creature that fails its save is fascinated for a number of rounds equal to the grenade’s mark number as they gaze in wonder at sparkling trails that only they can see. A creature that succeeds at its save is immune to the effects of pheromone grenades for 24 hours. This is a mind-affecting effect."),
	("Pheromone Grenade, Mk 4", "Grenades 1-H", 16, 26,000, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (25.; see text)", "Though scientists understand little about how a vracinea’s paralyzing scent affects the brain, weapon designers across the galaxy have been inspired by its effects and have replicated them with custom hybrid grenades. When it bursts, a pheromone grenade deals no damage, instead dispersing a powerful cocktail of supercharged pheromones and magically modified mind-altering chemicals in the listed blast radius. Each creature in the radius that inhales the pheromones (which bypass even active environmental protections from a suit of armor) must attempt a Will saving throw. A creature that fails its save is fascinated for a number of rounds equal to the grenade’s mark number as they gaze in wonder at sparkling trails that only they can see. A creature that succeeds at its save is immune to the effects of pheromone grenades for 24 hours. This is a mind-affecting effect."),
	("Riot Grenade, Mk 1", "Grenades 1-H", 2, 185, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (staggered; 10.)", "Riot grenades are standard issue among police forces, as they deal nonlethal damage and slow the movements of creatures affected by the blast."),
	("Screamer Grenade, Mk 1", "Grenades 1-H", 4, 725, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (1d10 So; deafened 1d4 minutes; 15.)", "When detonated, a screamer grenade releases a piercing shriek of sonic energy. "
	("Screamer Grenade, Mk 2", "Grenades 1-H", 8, 2,720, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (2d10 So; deafened 1d4 minutes; 20.)", "When detonated, a screamer grenade releases a piercing shriek of sonic energy. "
	("Screamer Grenade, Mk 3", "Grenades 1-H", 12, 11,300, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (4d10 So; deafened 1d4 minutes; 25.)", "When detonated, a screamer grenade releases a piercing shriek of sonic energy. "
	("Screamer Grenade, Mk 4", "Grenades 1-H", 16, 43,500, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (7d10 So; deafened 1d4 minutes; 30.)", "When detonated, a screamer grenade releases a piercing shriek of sonic energy. "
	("Shock Grenade, Mk 1", "Grenades 1-H", 1, 130, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (1d8 E; 15.)", "A shock grenade releases a pulse of electrical energy on impact."),
	("Shock Grenade, Mk 2", "Grenades 1-H", 4, 650, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (1d12 E; 15.)", "A shock grenade releases a pulse of electrical energy on impact."),
	("Shock Grenade, Mk 3", "Grenades 1-H", 10, 5,380, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (3d12 E; 15.)", "A shock grenade releases a pulse of electrical energy on impact."),
	("Shock Grenade, Mk 4", "Grenades 1-H", 14, 23,600, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (6d12 E; 15.)", "A shock grenade releases a pulse of electrical energy on impact."),
	("Shock Grenade, Mk 5", "Grenades 1-H", 20, 110,000, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (9d12 E; 15.)", "A shock grenade releases a pulse of electrical energy on impact."),
	("Smoke Grenade", "Grenades 1-H", 1, 40, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (smoke cloud 1 minute; 20.)", "A smoke grenade deals no damage; instead, it releases a cloud of dense smoke. Each character who inhales smoke must succeed at a Fortitude saving throw each round (DC = 15 + 1 per previous check) or spend that round choking and coughing; he can do nothing else. A character who chokes for 2 consecutive rounds takes 1d6 nonlethal damage. (Active environmental protection from a suit of armor prevents this effect altogether.) Regardless of the armor a character wears, smoke obscures vision, granting concealment to anyone within it."),
	("Stickybomb Grenade, Mk 1", "Grenades 1-H", 1, 170, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (entangled 2d4 rounds; 10.)", "A stickybomb grenade detonates with a splash of adhesive resin."),
	("Stickybomb Grenade, Mk 2", "Grenades 1-H", 4, 675, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (entangled 2d4 rounds; 15.)", "A stickybomb grenade detonates with a splash of adhesive resin."),
	("Stickybomb Grenade, Mk 3", "Grenades 1-H", 10, 5,410, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (entangled 2d4 rounds; 20.)", "A stickybomb grenade detonates with a splash of adhesive resin."),
	("Summoning Grenade, Mk 1", "Grenades 1-H", 3, 250, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (10.; 1st-level summon creature; caster level 3rd)", "The explosion a summoning grenade generates is a reality-warping field that summons creatures as if you had cast a summon creature spell of a spell level and caster level according to the grenade’s type. The creatures to be summoned are set when the grenade is created, so you know what you’re getting when you buy, presupposing a scrupulous vendor. When the grenade detonates, the summoned creatures appear immediately in unoccupied spaces, but a creature needs to have only 1 square of its space inside the blast radius. If a creature doesn’t have enough room to appear, it doesn’t. Summoned creatures treat you as their summoner."),
	("Summoning Grenade, Mk 2", "Grenades 1-H", 6, 650, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (10.; 2nd-level summon creature; caster level 6th)", "The explosion a summoning grenade generates is a reality-warping field that summons creatures as if you had cast a summon creature spell of a spell level and caster level according to the grenade’s type. The creatures to be summoned are set when the grenade is created, so you know what you’re getting when you buy, presupposing a scrupulous vendor. When the grenade detonates, the summoned creatures appear immediately in unoccupied spaces, but a creature needs to have only 1 square of its space inside the blast radius. If a creature doesn’t have enough room to appear, it doesn’t. Summoned creatures treat you as their summoner."),
	("Summoning Grenade, Mk 3", "Grenades 1-H", 9, 2,000, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (15.; 3rd-level summon creature; caster level 9th)", "The explosion a summoning grenade generates is a reality-warping field that summons creatures as if you had cast a summon creature spell of a spell level and caster level according to the grenade’s type. The creatures to be summoned are set when the grenade is created, so you know what you’re getting when you buy, presupposing a scrupulous vendor. When the grenade detonates, the summoned creatures appear immediately in unoccupied spaces, but a creature needs to have only 1 square of its space inside the blast radius. If a creature doesn’t have enough room to appear, it doesn’t. Summoned creatures treat you as their summoner."),
	("Summoning Grenade, Mk 4", "Grenades 1-H", 12, 5,000, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (20.; 4th-level summon creature; caster level 12th)", "The explosion a summoning grenade generates is a reality-warping field that summons creatures as if you had cast a summon creature spell of a spell level and caster level according to the grenade’s type. The creatures to be summoned are set when the grenade is created, so you know what you’re getting when you buy, presupposing a scrupulous vendor. When the grenade detonates, the summoned creatures appear immediately in unoccupied spaces, but a creature needs to have only 1 square of its space inside the blast radius. If a creature doesn’t have enough room to appear, it doesn’t. Summoned creatures treat you as their summoner."),
	("Summoning Grenade, Mk 5", "Grenades 1-H", 15, 16,000, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (25.; 5th-level summon creature; caster level 15th)", "The explosion a summoning grenade generates is a reality-warping field that summons creatures as if you had cast a summon creature spell of a spell level and caster level according to the grenade’s type. The creatures to be summoned are set when the grenade is created, so you know what you’re getting when you buy, presupposing a scrupulous vendor. When the grenade detonates, the summoned creatures appear immediately in unoccupied spaces, but a creature needs to have only 1 square of its space inside the blast radius. If a creature doesn’t have enough room to appear, it doesn’t. Summoned creatures treat you as their summoner."),
	("Summoning Grenade, Mk 6", "Grenades 1-H", 18, 49,000, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (30.; 6th-level summon creature; caster level 18th)", "The explosion a summoning grenade generates is a reality-warping field that summons creatures as if you had cast a summon creature spell of a spell level and caster level according to the grenade’s type. The creatures to be summoned are set when the grenade is created, so you know what you’re getting when you buy, presupposing a scrupulous vendor. When the grenade detonates, the summoned creatures appear immediately in unoccupied spaces, but a creature needs to have only 1 square of its space inside the blast radius. If a creature doesn’t have enough room to appear, it doesn’t. Summoned creatures treat you as their summoner."),
	("Taserweb Grenade", "Grenades 1-H", 4, 720, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (10.; see text)", "A taserweb grenade is a 4th-level grenade ranged weapon with an explode radius of 10 feet. Creatures caught in its radius must succeed at a Reflex save (DC = 10 + half the weapon’s item level + your Dexterity bonus) or get caught in the filaments. The electric discharge of the filaments causes a creature that fails the save to become staggered for 1 round. The electric charge dissipates quickly, leaving the area covered in sticky strands of high-tensile fibers, making the affected area difficult terrain for 1d4 rounds as though the grenade also has the mire weapon special property. Each grenade has light bulk and costs 720 credits. "
	("Wonder Grenade", "Grenades 1-H", 10, 2,500, 0, 20, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (10.; see text)", ""When it detonates, a wonder grenade releases a locus of magical uncertainty, which explodes into a strange effect once it makes contact with reality. When the grenade detonates, roll d% on the following table to determine the effect. (The GM is free to make up a similar effect based on your surroundings and circumstances.) If any effect of the grenade allows a saving throw, the DC is equal to 15 + your key ability score modifier.
	("Plasma Claw, Electocellular", "Small Arms 1-H", 1, 280, 2, 20, 0, 20 charges, 2, "L", "living", "The Xenowardens bioengineered these large arthropod claws based on a creature from a lost world in the Vast0the claws create a burst of plasma as they snap shut. The organic plasma claw and biodynamic plasma claw models function most similarly to the original creature. Other manufacturers have created the slightly different electrocellular and synthecite models, which are less powerful versions of the two earlier models."),
	("Hydra Cannon, Python-Series", "Heavy 2-H", 2, 1,070, 3, 20, 0, 20 charges, 2, "2", "blast, shape 1, unwieldy", "Rather than firing a single burst of plasma, a hydra cannon generates countless discrete plasma filaments that spread outward in a pattern reminiscent of crawling serpents. The spread of these filaments can be somewhat controlled, allowing a proficient user to avoid hitting a limited number of creatures within the weapon’s area of effect. Python-series hydra cannons offer the least control, while viper-series, asp-series, and cobraseries hydra cannons offer increasingly fine-tuned control over their target areas."),
	("Lightning Pistol, Sheet", "Small Arms 1-H", 5, 3,000, 3, 20, 0, 40 charges, 4, "L", "line, stun, unwieldy", "When fired, this weapon erupts with a long, crackling bolt of electricity reminiscent of lightning. Sheet lightning pistols and ribbon lightning pistols are relatively common, but rocket and smooth-channel lightning pistols typically require a special license to carry legally."),
	("Mercy Pistol, Illuminator", "Small Arms 1-H", 1, 275, 3, 20, 0, 20, 2, "L", "Nonlethal", "Mercy pistols are the nonlethal firearms of choice for many guardians of Sarenite temples (including the Radiant Cathedral). The weapon fires a concentrated blast of light waves at a target, delivering an intense thrust of heat that eaves little to no mark or permanent damage."),
	("Rotating Pistol, Tactical", "Small Arms 1-H", 4, 1,900, 5, 20, 0, 4 rounds, 1, "L", "analog, conceal", "A rotating pistol is a modern execution of an ancient design found on Golarion and several other worlds. The multiple barrels on this pistol rotate while firing to dissipate heat, which allows a more powerful shot without melting the weapon. The rotating pistol’s shots deal significant damage to their target, but the weapon requires frequent reloading. Rotating pistols are available in tactical, advanced, and elite models."),
	("Mercy Pistol, Infrared", "Small Arms 1-H", 6, 4,300, 7, 20, 0, 20, 2, "L", "Nonlethal", "Mercy pistols are the nonlethal firearms of choice for many guardians of Sarenite temples (including the Radiant Cathedral). The weapon fires a concentrated blast of light waves at a target, delivering an intense thrust of heat that eaves little to no mark or permanent damage."),
	("Disintegration Pistol, Decimator", "Small Arms 1-H", 11, 28,000, 10, 20, 0, 20 charges, 2, "L", "n/a", "This hefty pistol has two small internal tanks that generate the energy needed to deliquesce the wielder’s targets. Disintegrator pistols come in liquidator, decimator, executioner, and eradicator models."),
	("Shuriken, Microserrated", "Special 1-H", 7, 1,120, 10, 20, Bleed, drawn, 0, "L", "quick reload, thrown", "Shuriken are bladed thrown weapons most common in the carbonedge form kasathas favor. However, these weapons are versatile and come in various forms for improved cutting power or specialized use. Additionally, the size of shuriken makes them easy to hide and carry. They are ideal for hit-and-run attacks and situations where it might not be prudent to retrieve a thrown weapon. This is like the carbonedge variety, but has microserrated edges to slice into targets better."),
	("Shuriken, Ultraserrated", "Special 1-H", 16, 29,100, 38, 20, Bleed, drawn, 0, "L", "quick reload, thrown", "Shuriken are bladed thrown weapons most common in the carbonedge form kasathas favor. However, these weapons are versatile and come in various forms for improved cutting power or specialized use. Additionally, the size of shuriken makes them easy to hide and carry. They are ideal for hit-and-run attacks and situations where it might not be prudent to retrieve a thrown weapon. Small but deadly, an ultraserrated shuriken has molecular-level serrations that enhance slashing."),
	("Hail Pistol, Subzero", "Small Arms 1-H", 1, 120, 2, 20, bleed 1d4, 20 charges, 1, "L", "n/a", "A hail pistol includes a chamber behind the barrel that circulates supercooled vapor and causes it to coalesce into razor-edged shards of ice that leave foes with rime-edged bleeding wounds. Subzero, gelid, ultracold, and absolute-zero hail pistols each produce progressively larger and more jagged shards."),
	("Perforator Pistol, Diffraction", "Small Arms 1-H", 2, 500, 2, 20, bleed 1d4, 20 charges, 2, "L", "penetrating", "Focused sound waves from a perforator pistol punch through objects and bodies. Drow employ perforators because the dark elves enjoy the weapon’s ability to inflict gruesome wounds, which are as effective against morale as against life and limb. Diffraction and refraction perforator pistols align and compound sound waves, while linear and phased perforator pistols are named for the internal matrices that focus wavelengths the pistols emitters generate."),
	("Hail Pistol, Gelid", "Small Arms 1-H", 8, 8,600, 7, 20, bleed 1d6, 20 charges, 1, "L", "n/a", "A hail pistol includes a chamber behind the barrel that circulates supercooled vapor and causes it to coalesce into razor-edged shards of ice that leave foes with rime-edged bleeding wounds. Subzero, gelid, ultracold, and absolute-zero hail pistols each produce progressively larger and more jagged shards."),
	("Perforator Pistol, Refraction", "Small Arms 1-H", 9, 13,000, 7, 20, bleed 1d6, 40 charges, 4, "L", "penetrating", "Focused sound waves from a perforator pistol punch through objects and bodies. Drow employ perforators because the dark elves enjoy the weapon’s ability to inflict gruesome wounds, which are as effective against morale as against life and limb. Diffraction and refraction perforator pistols align and compound sound waves, while linear and phased perforator pistols are named for the internal matrices that focus wavelengths the pistols emitters generate."),
	("Perforator Pistol, Linear", "Small Arms 1-H", 13, 46,000, 11, 20, bleed 2d6, 40 charges, 5, "L", "penetrating", "Focused sound waves from a perforator pistol punch through objects and bodies. Drow employ perforators because the dark elves enjoy the weapon’s ability to inflict gruesome wounds, which are as effective against morale as against life and limb. Diffraction and refraction perforator pistols align and compound sound waves, while linear and phased perforator pistols are named for the internal matrices that focus wavelengths the pistols emitters generate."),
	("Shuriken, Flash", "Special 1-H", 10, 3,120, 14, 20, Blind, drawn, 0, "L", "quick reload, thrown", "Shuriken are bladed thrown weapons most common in the carbonedge form kasathas favor. However, these weapons are versatile and come in various forms for improved cutting power or specialized use. Additionally, the size of shuriken makes them easy to hide and carry. They are ideal for hit-and-run attacks and situations where it might not be prudent to retrieve a thrown weapon. The friction of passing air and target impact activates a thrown flash shuriken so that the weapon delivers burn injuries and a potentially blinding flare."),
	("Flame Pistol", "Small Arms 1-H", 2, 470, 2, 20, burn 1d4, 20 petrol, 4, "L", "line, unwieldy", "A flame pistol shoots a line of ignited petrol from its barrel."),
	("Flame Pistol, Blaze", "Small Arms 1-H", 7, 5,500, 5, 20, burn 1d4, 20 petrol, 5, "L", "line, unwieldy", "A flame pistol shoots a line of ignited petrol from its barrel."),
	("Gulchgun", "Long Arms 2-H", 1, 90, 4, 20, burn 1d6, 4 shells, 1, "1", "analog", "Gulchguns are a feat of fearless ysoki tinkering; the rifles use scattergun shells as ammunition but detonate them entirely within the rifle’s internal chambers, instead firing a tongue of flame, accompanied by tremendous noise. The technology of the gulchgun eventually developed into the shorter and more stable shellgun, but ysoki purists and desperate buyers alike keep the market for these weapons alive."),
	("Shellgun, Blaze", "Small Arms 1-H", 9, 11,500, 7, 20, burn 1d6, 2 shells, 2, "L", "n/a", "A bulky weapon favored by scrappy fighters with limited resources, this oversized pistol uses scattergun shells as ammunition but creates a short-range tongue of flame. Thought to be inspired by the longer gulchgun, the shellgun is also a favorite of ysoki. Available models include the bombard shellgun, the blaze shellgun, and the fury shellgun."),
	("Plasma Pistol, Red Star", "Small Arms 1-H", 7, 7,200, 4, 20, burn 1d8, 20 charges, 4, "L", "line, unwieldy", "Plasma pistols fire a line of ionized plasma out to a relatively short range. The plasma can continue to burn after contact. "
	("Shellgun, Fury", "Small Arms 1-H", 12, 30,500, 10, 20, burn 2d6, 8 shells, 8, "L", "n/a", "A bulky weapon favored by scrappy fighters with limited resources, this oversized pistol uses scattergun shells as ammunition but creates a short-range tongue of flame. Thought to be inspired by the longer gulchgun, the shellgun is also a favorite of ysoki. Available models include the bombard shellgun, the blaze shellgun, and the fury shellgun."),
	("Shuriken, Singing", "Special 1-H", 13, 8,550, 21, 20, Confuse, drawn, 0, "L", "quick reload, thrown", "Shuriken are bladed thrown weapons most common in the carbonedge form kasathas favor. However, these weapons are versatile and come in various forms for improved cutting power or specialized use. Additionally, the size of shuriken makes them easy to hide and carry. They are ideal for hit-and-run attacks and situations where it might not be prudent to retrieve a thrown weapon. Designed by lashunta hunting specialists using the same acoustic principles as the singing disk, the singing shuriken generates a painful high-pitched whine when thrown and can befuddle a target with a piercing impact that disturbs the inner ear."),
	("Sting Pistol, Ant", "Small Arms 1-H", 4, 2,150, 4, 20, corrode 1d6, 20 charges, 5, "L", "living", "Sting pistols are living weapons based on samples of Swarm technology recovered during the last century. The chitinous weapon converts power to internally generate and shoot acidslicked needles that can cause lasting damage to the target. Ant models are sturdy and commonplace, though yellow jacket and wasp sting pistols are more powerful. Hornet models are the heaviest and most potent of these weapons."),
	("Dirge Cannon, Harmonic", "Heavy 2-H", 2, 900, 4, 20, deafen, 20 charges, 4, "3", "antibiological, blast, unwieldy", "Pirates are the most common users of dirge cannons. The potbellied, shoulder-resting weapons cause a brief but intense sound burst at frequencies and pressure sufficient to rupture living cells while leaving inorganic objects unharmed. The result is a weapon that can eliminate a starship’s crew without causing any damage to the vessel or its cargo. Those who prefer lighter damage favor harmonic and resonant cannons, leaving anharmonic and parametric models for situations that call for carnage."),
	("Decoupler, Bruiser", "Small Arms 1-H", 1, 430, 2, 20, demoralize, 20 charges, 2, "L", "n/a", "Some manufacturers have streamlined the disintegrator pistol’s design to create a more affordable option; the result of their efforts is referred to simply as a decoupler. A decoupler is smaller and lighter than a disintegrator pistol, trading some of its outright destructive power for the ability to deal superficial pain that can leave targets shaking in their boots. In the Apostaean city of Nightarch, the ruling House Zeizerer issues decouplers to its enforcers, many of whom refer to the weapons as “facilitators.” Manufacturers typically produce bruiser, pusher, and screamer decouplers."),
	("Shuriken, Grooved", "Special 1-H", 4, 370, 4, 20, Injection DC +2, drawn, 0, "L", "injection, quick reload, thrown", "Shuriken are bladed thrown weapons most common in the carbonedge form kasathas favor. However, these weapons are versatile and come in various forms for improved cutting power or specialized use. Additionally, the size of shuriken makes them easy to hide and carry. They are ideal for hit-and-run attacks and situations where it might not be prudent to retrieve a thrown weapon. Fine channels crisscross the surface of a grooved shuriken. When an injectable substance is applied to the shuriken, it gathers in these channels and surface tension holds it in place. The grooves allow injection delivery without a specialized mechanism. Each shuriken holds a single dose of a drug, poison, or medicinal."),
	("Handcannon, Bravado", "Small Arms 1-H", 2, 790, 4, 20, knockdown, 1 shell, 1, "1", "analog, free hands (1), unwieldy", "Handcannons are popular with those who want to impress or intimidate their foes through the sheer presence of their armament without having to invest in the training required to master longarms or heavy weaponry. Its oversized barrel and muzzle are somewhat precariously balanced on a one-handed grip, though most wielders use both hands to make the weapon more manageable in combat situations. The various model names of this weapon0bravado, swagger, bombast, braggadocio, and gasconade0were originally facetious references to the character of those who tend to favor them, though many users embrace the names unironically."),
	("Breaching Gun, Utility", "Long Arms 2-H", 4, 2,350, 5, 20, knockdown, 4 shells, 1, "1", "analog, breach, penetrating", "A breaching gun uses scattergun shells as ammunition against a single target at short range, dealing an impressive amount of damage and even tearing through doors and other objects. These weapons are most commonly seen in the hands of space pirates who need to blast through plastic interior doors, though expert users can use these weapons to break through airlock doors. Breaching guns also saw widespread use on Absalom Station in the aftermath of the Gap, as security forces desperately tried to maintain control over the station’s fractured and panicked population, which often required blasting through barricades and sealed interior airlocks. Utility, snub, impact, vortex, and grapeshot breaching guns are widely available on various worlds."),
	("Breaching Gun, Snub", "Long Arms 2-H", 7, 6,800, 11, 20, knockdown, 8 shells, 2, "1", "analog, breach, penetrating", "A breaching gun uses scattergun shells as ammunition against a single target at short range, dealing an impressive amount of damage and even tearing through doors and other objects. These weapons are most commonly seen in the hands of space pirates who need to blast through plastic interior doors, though expert users can use these weapons to break through airlock doors. Breaching guns also saw widespread use on Absalom Station in the aftermath of the Gap, as security forces desperately tried to maintain control over the station’s fractured and panicked population, which often required blasting through barricades and sealed interior airlocks. Utility, snub, impact, vortex, and grapeshot breaching guns are widely available on various worlds."),
	("Cavitation Pistol, Vapor", "Small Arms 1-H", 3, 1,430, 3, 20, pulse 1d4, 20 charges, 5, "L", "unwieldy", "A series of prongs takes the place of this pistol’s barrel; firing the weapon causes a small sphere of energy to form at their center and launch forward at speed. If the wielder times the shot perfectly, the plasma sphere pulses just as it hits the target, dealing damage to nearby creatures, but most find the feat difficult to replicate consistently. A vapor cavitation pistol creates a very focused sphere, while the inertial cavitation pistol creates one that implodes on impact. Hydrodynamic and thermodynamic cavitation pistols use more complex reactions that carry significantly more destructive power."),
	("Cavitation Pistol, Inertial", "Small Arms 1-H", 8, 9,700, 7, 20, pulse 1d6, 40 charges, 5, "L", "unwieldy", "A series of prongs takes the place of this pistol’s barrel; firing the weapon causes a small sphere of energy to form at their center and launch forward at speed. If the wielder times the shot perfectly, the plasma sphere pulses just as it hits the target, dealing damage to nearby creatures, but most find the feat difficult to replicate consistently. A vapor cavitation pistol creates a very focused sphere, while the inertial cavitation pistol creates one that implodes on impact. Hydrodynamic and thermodynamic cavitation pistols use more complex reactions that carry significantly more destructive power."),
	("Cavitation Pistol, Thermodynamic", "Small Arms 1-H", 18, 584,000, 19, 20, pulse 3d6, 80 charges, 10, "L", "unwieldy", "A series of prongs takes the place of this pistol’s barrel; firing the weapon causes a small sphere of energy to form at their center and launch forward at speed. If the wielder times the shot perfectly, the plasma sphere pulses just as it hits the target, dealing damage to nearby creatures, but most find the feat difficult to replicate consistently. A vapor cavitation pistol creates a very focused sphere, while the inertial cavitation pistol creates one that implodes on impact. Hydrodynamic and thermodynamic cavitation pistols use more complex reactions that carry significantly more destructive power."),
	("Dross Gun, Flux", "Long Arms 2-H", 10, 19,200, 13, 20, severe wound, 20 charges, 4, "1", "penetrating", "Early models of disintegrator weapons were designed solely to deal indiscriminate corrosion damage to targets. The dross gun is a slightly more refined version, though it lacks the overall power those initial prototypes had. Its shots are slightly more concentrated, dealing substantial damage to objects and dealing painful, lasting wounds to a target on a direct hit. A scrapper dross gun is the smallest model available, used as often to remove choice parts from a wrecked starship as it is to remove crew from the ship in the first place, and the scoring and flux models have increased wounding capabilities."),
	("Dirge Pistol, Harmonic", "Small Arms 1-H", 1, 440, 2, 20, sicken, 20 charges, 1, "L", "antibiological", "The oscillating sonic waves discharged from a dirge pistol work like those fired from a dirge cannon. Raiders and hijackers prize these weapons for their effect against living targets, which can leave many valuables unharmed. Harmonic and resonant dirge pistols generate stable oscillations, while the anharmonic, parametric, and radial dirge pistols have concentric generator cylinders to produce dissonant and more harmful output."),
	("Coolant Sprayer, Hiemal", "Heavy 2-H", 3, 1,600, 2, 20, staggered, 40 charges, 4, "3", "blast, entangle (1d4 rounds), unwieldy", "Coolant sprayers were designed following the principles of a flamethrower, but with an eye more toward hindrance than sheer damage. Experts can easily identify a coolant sprayer by the bulky insulation surrounding the sprayer’s coolant reservoir. The weapon expels a cone of activated coolant that stiffens and freezes living tissue. While not harmless, the effect is somewhat less deadly than most energy weapons. Hiemal, algid, glacial, and isothermal coolant sprayers all function in similar ways, though their destructive potential varies from one model to another."),
	("Anacite Ion Cannon, Static", "Heavy 2-H", 3, 1,550, 5, 20, staggered, 20 charges, 2, "2", "line, lockdown, unwieldy", "This heavy weapon was designed by Aballonian law-enforcement agencies for capturing criminal constructs without completely destroying them."),
	("Charge Emitter, Impulse", "Long Arms 2-H", 8, 10,900, 7, 20, staggered, 20 charges, 2, "1", "integrated (1 slot), stun", "This series of insulating reinforced-glass rings can be installed into armor upgrade slots and focuses an electrical charge into a targeted bolt. The sheer power necessary to project a bolt of electricity means that even an impulse charge emitter is a substantial weapon, and jolt charge emitters and surge charge emitters are significantly more powerful. Their relatively slim profile makes them popular for a number of users, from androids and others who benefit from a racial armor upgrade slot, to starship-repair crews in hostile space who want to keep their hands free for their work without leaving themselves totally undefended."),
	("Dross Gun, Scoring", "Long Arms 2-H", 5, 3,300, 4, 20, wound, 20 charges, 2, "1", "penetrating", "Early models of disintegrator weapons were designed solely to deal indiscriminate corrosion damage to targets. The dross gun is a slightly more refined version, though it lacks the overall power those initial prototypes had. Its shots are slightly more concentrated, dealing substantial damage to objects and dealing painful, lasting wounds to a target on a direct hit. A scrapper dross gun is the smallest model available, used as often to remove choice parts from a wrecked starship as it is to remove crew from the ship in the first place, and the scoring and flux models have increased wounding capabilities."),
	("Holy Water Grenade, Mk 2", "Grenades 1-H", 5, 940, 0, 21, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (4d6 B; 20), holy water", "Produced by priests of good-aligned deities, holy water grenades explode with a spray of consecrated water that harms undead creatures and evil outsiders while leaving other creatures and objects merely damp. This typically isn’t enough water to damage computers or other electronic or technological items."),
	("Solar Flare Grenade Mk 1", "Grenades 1-H", 3, 280, 0, 21, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "Explode (1d10 E & F, 20.) solar flare grenade also sends out an electromagnetic pulse following the plasma wave. Within the same area, all technological objects that use charges, technological objects that do not use charges but are powered by electricity, and constructs with the technological subtype must each attempt a Fortitude saving throw. If a technological object with charges fails the save, it loses a number of charges equal to the grenade’s mark. If a technological object that is powered by electrical means other than charge fails the save, its functions are suppressed for a number of rounds according to the grenade’s type (see below). If a construct with the technological subtype fails the save, it is staggered for a number of rounds according to the grenade’s type (see below); such a construct can attempt an additional Fortitude save at the end of each round to shrug off the effect."),, ""
	("Holy Water Grenade, Mk 3", "Grenades 1-H", 11, 7,680, 0, 22, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (4d12 B; 20), holy water", "Produced by priests of good-aligned deities, holy water grenades explode with a spray of consecrated water that harms undead creatures and evil outsiders while leaving other creatures and objects merely damp. This typically isn’t enough water to damage computers or other electronic or technological items."),
	("Solar Flare Grenade Mk 2", "Grenades 1-H", 6, 725, 0, 22, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (2d10 E & F, 20.)", "Solar flare grenade also sends out an electromagnetic pulse following the plasma wave. Within the same area, all technological objects that use charges, technological objects that do not use charges but are powered by electricity, and constructs with the technological subtype must each attempt a Fortitude saving throw. If a technological object with charges fails the save, it loses a number of charges equal to the grenade’s mark. If a technological object that is powered by electrical means other than charge fails the save, its functions are suppressed for a number of rounds according to the grenade’s type (see below). If a construct with the technological subtype fails the save, it is staggered for a number of rounds according to the grenade’s type (see below); such a construct can attempt an additional Fortitude save at the end of each round to shrug off the effect."),
	("Holy Water Grenade, Mk 4", "Grenades 1-H", 19, 175,000, 0, 23, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (8d12 B; 20), holy water", "Produced by priests of good-aligned deities, holy water grenades explode with a spray of consecrated water that harms undead creatures and evil outsiders while leaving other creatures and objects merely damp. This typically isn’t enough water to damage computers or other electronic or technological items."),
	("Solar Flare Grenade Mk 3", "Grenades 1-H", 9, 2,450, 0, 23, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "Explode (3d10 E & F, 20.) solar flare grenade also sends out an electromagnetic pulse following the plasma wave. Within the same area, all technological objects that use charges, technological objects that do not use charges but are powered by electricity, and constructs with the technological subtype must each attempt a Fortitude saving throw. If a technological object with charges fails the save, it loses a number of charges equal to the grenade’s mark. If a technological object that is powered by electrical means other than charge fails the save, its functions are suppressed for a number of rounds according to the grenade’s type (see below). If a construct with the technological subtype fails the save, it is staggered for a number of rounds according to the grenade’s type (see below); such a construct can attempt an additional Fortitude save at the end of each round to shrug off the effect."),, ""
	("Solar Flare Grenade Mk 4", "Grenades 1-H", 12, 6,500, 0, 24, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "Explode (4d10 E & F, 20.) solar flare grenade also sends out an electromagnetic pulse following the plasma wave. Within the same area, all technological objects that use charges, technological objects that do not use charges but are powered by electricity, and constructs with the technological subtype must each attempt a Fortitude saving throw. If a technological object with charges fails the save, it loses a number of charges equal to the grenade’s mark. If a technological object that is powered by electrical means other than charge fails the save, its functions are suppressed for a number of rounds according to the grenade’s type (see below). If a construct with the technological subtype fails the save, it is staggered for a number of rounds according to the grenade’s type (see below); such a construct can attempt an additional Fortitude save at the end of each round to shrug off the effect."),, ""
	("Riot Grenade, Mk 2", "Grenades 1-H", 5, 810, 0, 25, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (staggered; 10.)", "Riot grenades are standard issue among police forces, as they deal nonlethal damage and slow the movements of creatures affected by the blast."),
	("Solar Flare Grenade Mk 5", "Grenades 1-H", 15, 20,100, 0, 25, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "Explode (5d10 E & F, 20.) solar flare grenade also sends out an electromagnetic pulse following the plasma wave. Within the same area, all technological objects that use charges, technological objects that do not use charges but are powered by electricity, and constructs with the technological subtype must each attempt a Fortitude saving throw. If a technological object with charges fails the save, it loses a number of charges equal to the grenade’s mark. If a technological object that is powered by electrical means other than charge fails the save, its functions are suppressed for a number of rounds according to the grenade’s type (see below). If a construct with the technological subtype fails the save, it is staggered for a number of rounds according to the grenade’s type (see below); such a construct can attempt an additional Fortitude save at the end of each round to shrug off the effect."),, ""
	("Hydra Cannon, Viper-Series", "Heavy 2-H", 6, 4,800, 7, 25, 0, 20 charges, 2, "2", "blast, shape 2, unwieldy", "Rather than firing a single burst of plasma, a hydra cannon generates countless discrete plasma filaments that spread outward in a pattern reminiscent of crawling serpents. The spread of these filaments can be somewhat controlled, allowing a proficient user to avoid hitting a limited number of creatures within the weapon’s area of effect. Python-series hydra cannons offer the least control, while viper-series, asp-series, and cobraseries hydra cannons offer increasingly fine-tuned control over their target areas."),
	("Flame Rifle", "Long Arms 2-H", 2, 490, 3, 25, burn 1d6, 20 petrol, 5, "1", "line, unwieldy", "A flame rifle shoots a line of ignited petrol from its barrel."),
	("Plasma Pistol, Yellow Star", "Small Arms 1-H", 12, 40,300, 9, 25, burn 1d8, 40 charges, 8, "L", "line, unwieldy", "Plasma pistols fire a line of ionized plasma out to a relatively short range. The plasma can continue to burn after contact. "
	("Disintegration Pistol, Executioner", "Small Arms 1-H", 16, 200,000, 21, 25, corrode 1d6, 40 charges, 4, "L", "n/a", "This hefty pistol has two small internal tanks that generate the energy needed to deliquesce the wielder’s targets. Disintegrator pistols come in liquidator, decimator, executioner, and eradicator models."),
	("Riot Grenade, Mk 3", "Grenades 1-H", 7, 1,640, 0, 26, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (staggered; 15.)", "Riot grenades are standard issue among police forces, as they deal nonlethal damage and slow the movements of creatures affected by the blast."),
	("Riot Grenade, Mk 4", "Grenades 1-H", 11, 6,910, 0, 27, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (1d8 S; staggered; 15), nonlethal", "Riot grenades are standard issue among police forces, as they deal nonlethal damage and slow the movements of creatures affected by the blast."),
	("Riot Grenade, Mk 5", "Grenades 1-H", 15, 28,200, 0, 28, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (2d10 S; staggered; 20), nonlethal", "Riot grenades are standard issue among police forces, as they deal nonlethal damage and slow the movements of creatures affected by the blast."),
	("Riot Grenade, Mk 6", "Grenades 1-H", 17, 67,000, 0, 29, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (4d10 S; staggered; 20), nonlethal", "Riot grenades are standard issue among police forces, as they deal nonlethal damage and slow the movements of creatures affected by the blast."),
	("Riot Grenade, Mk 7", "Grenades 1-H", 20, 222,000, 0, 30, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (4d12 S; staggered; 25), nonlethal", "Riot grenades are standard issue among police forces, as they deal nonlethal damage and slow the movements of creatures affected by the blast."),
	("Pulsecaster Pistol", "Small Arms 1-H", 1, 250, 2, 30, 0, 20 charges, 1, "L", "nonlethal", "A smaller version of an arc pistol, the pulsecaster sends a lowenergy blast at its target. This blast stuns the target without dealing serious damage. "
	("Wave Modulator, I", "Small Arms 1-H", 2, 1,080, 2, 30, 0, 20 charges, 4, "L", "modal (sonic)", "The frequency of a wave modulator’s output can be adjusted to either burn a target or bombard it with damaging sonic bursts. Shirrens favor these boxy pistols because of the thrill of choosing the damage type of every shot fired. Wave modulators come in numbered models."),
	("Plasma Claw, Synthecite", "Small Arms 1-H", 5, 3,350, 3, 30, 0, 20 charges, 4, "L", "living", "The Xenowardens bioengineered these large arthropod claws based on a creature from a lost world in the Vast0the claws create a burst of plasma as they snap shut. The organic plasma claw and biodynamic plasma claw models function most similarly to the original creature. Other manufacturers have created the slightly different electrocellular and synthecite models, which are less powerful versions of the two earlier models."),
	("Semi-Auto Pistol, Tactical", "Small Arms 1-H", 1, 260, 3, 30, 0, 9 rounds, 1, "L", "analog", "The semiautomatic mechanism of this pistol discharges spent cartridges and reloads fresh ones in the barrel, provided a cartridge remains in the magazine. "
	("Wave Modulator, II", "Small Arms 1-H", 5, 3,400, 3, 30, 0, 20 charges, 4, "L", "modal (sonic)", "The frequency of a wave modulator’s output can be adjusted to either burn a target or bombard it with damaging sonic bursts. Shirrens favor these boxy pistols because of the thrill of choosing the damage type of every shot fired. Wave modulators come in numbered models."),
	("Lightning Pistol, Ribbon", "Small Arms 1-H", 8, 9,700, 4, 30, 0, 40 charges, 5, "L", "line, stun, unwieldy", "When fired, this weapon erupts with a long, crackling bolt of electricity reminiscent of lightning. Sheet lightning pistols and ribbon lightning pistols are relatively common, but rocket and smooth-channel lightning pistols typically require a special license to carry legally."),
	("Stormcaller, Sheet", "Heavy 2-H", 2, 1,100, 4, 30, 0, 20 charges, 5, "2", "flexible line, living, unwieldy", "Some barathu researchers who intensively study the titanic lightning storms found on their home world become obsessed with the phenomenon. The efforts of such scientists led to the creation of the stormcaller, a living weapon that generates a line of electricity originating not from the wielder but from a single point within the weapon’s relatively short range. Like most barathu creations, stormcallers are living creatures, and their massive shells are large enough to require two hands to wield, aided by the stormcaller wrapping its translucent tentacles around the user’s appendages. Sheet and ribbon stormcallers are powerful weapons in their own right, while rocket and smooth-channel stormcallers can summon electrical currents that live up to the weapons’ namesake."),
	("Arc Emitter, Advanced", "Long Arms 2-H", 9, 13,200, 5, 30, 0, 40 charges, 10, "1", "blast, stun, unwieldy", "Arc emitters discharge a cone of electrical energy that can damage and stun anyone within its area. Advanced arc emitters can be used at a longer range and are used by military forces to stun and subdue groups of enemies. "
	("Wave Modulator, III", "Small Arms 1-H", 8, 11,000, 5, 30, 0, 20 charges, 4, "L", "modal (sonic)", "The frequency of a wave modulator’s output can be adjusted to either burn a target or bombard it with damaging sonic bursts. Shirrens favor these boxy pistols because of the thrill of choosing the damage type of every shot fired. Wave modulators come in numbered models."),
	("Plasma Claw, Organic", "Small Arms 1-H", 10, 20,100, 7, 30, 0, 40 charges, 8, "L", "living", "The Xenowardens bioengineered these large arthropod claws based on a creature from a lost world in the Vast0the claws create a burst of plasma as they snap shut. The organic plasma claw and biodynamic plasma claw models function most similarly to the original creature. Other manufacturers have created the slightly different electrocellular and synthecite models, which are less powerful versions of the two earlier models."),
	("Lightning Pistol, Rocket", "Small Arms 1-H", 12, 37,000, 9, 30, 0, 40 charges, 8, "L", "line, stun, unwieldy", "When fired, this weapon erupts with a long, crackling bolt of electricity reminiscent of lightning. Sheet lightning pistols and ribbon lightning pistols are relatively common, but rocket and smooth-channel lightning pistols typically require a special license to carry legally."),
	("Wave Modulator, IV", "Small Arms 1-H", 11, 28,600, 9, 30, 0, 20 charges, 4, "L", "modal (sonic)", "The frequency of a wave modulator’s output can be adjusted to either burn a target or bombard it with damaging sonic bursts. Shirrens favor these boxy pistols because of the thrill of choosing the damage type of every shot fired. Wave modulators come in numbered models."),
	("Rotating Pistol, Advanced", "Small Arms 1-H", 11, 23,400, 10, 30, 0, 8 rounds, 1, "L", "analog, conceal", "A rotating pistol is a modern execution of an ancient design found on Golarion and several other worlds. The multiple barrels on this pistol rotate while firing to dissipate heat, which allows a more powerful shot without melting the weapon. The rotating pistol’s shots deal significant damage to their target, but the weapon requires frequent reloading. Rotating pistols are available in tactical, advanced, and elite models."),
	("Hydra Cannon, Asp-Series", "Heavy 2-H", 12, 41,000, 14, 30, 0, 20 charges, 2, "2", "blast, shape 3, unwieldy", "Rather than firing a single burst of plasma, a hydra cannon generates countless discrete plasma filaments that spread outward in a pattern reminiscent of crawling serpents. The spread of these filaments can be somewhat controlled, allowing a proficient user to avoid hitting a limited number of creatures within the weapon’s area of effect. Python-series hydra cannons offer the least control, while viper-series, asp-series, and cobraseries hydra cannons offer increasingly fine-tuned control over their target areas."),
	("Mercy Pistol, Ultraviolet", "Small Arms 1-H", 11, 25,000, 14, 30, 0, 20, 2, "L", "Nonlethal", "Mercy pistols are the nonlethal firearms of choice for many guardians of Sarenite temples (including the Radiant Cathedral). The weapon fires a concentrated blast of light waves at a target, delivering an intense thrust of heat that eaves little to no mark or permanent damage."),
	("Plasma Claw, Biodynamic", "Small Arms 1-H", 16, 189,000, 14, 30, 0, 40 charges, 8, "L", "living", "The Xenowardens bioengineered these large arthropod claws based on a creature from a lost world in the Vast0the claws create a burst of plasma as they snap shut. The organic plasma claw and biodynamic plasma claw models function most similarly to the original creature. Other manufacturers have created the slightly different electrocellular and synthecite models, which are less powerful versions of the two earlier models."),
	("Scattergun, Vortex", "Long Arms 2-H", 15, 91,900, 19, 30, 0, 12 shells, 1, "2", "analog, blast", "A scattergun fires fragmentary shells in a spray from its barrel, dealing damage to all targets in range. The shortened barrel of the snub scattergun makes it easier to conceal. Grapeshot, impact, and vortex scatterguns are designed to deliver enhanced damage. "
	("Scattergun, Grapeshot", "Long Arms 2-H", 18, 331,000, 26, 30, 0, 12 shells, 1, "2", "analog, blast", "A scattergun fires fragmentary shells in a spray from its barrel, dealing damage to all targets in range. The shortened barrel of the snub scattergun makes it easier to conceal. Grapeshot, impact, and vortex scatterguns are designed to deliver enhanced damage. "
	("Ionizer, Cupric", "Small Arms 1-H", 6, 4,650, 5, 30, arc 1d6, 20 charges, 1, "L", "integrated (2 slots), unwieldy", "The ionizer’s beam ionizes a path to its target, which serves as a route for the ensuing electric charge. There are several different elemental ions used in constructing ionizers, with the strength of the output based on the metal used. The most common are cupric, ferric, chromic, and stannic ionizers. Generally, the weapon’s hardware is stored in two upgrade slots of a piece of armor, while a connected wand-like barrel extends from an extremity. Aballon’s anacites designed the first ionizers, but they have long since spread throughout the Pact Worlds and beyond."),
	("Ionizer, Feric", "Small Arms 1-H", 10, 20,100, 10, 30, arc 2d4, 20 charges, 1, "L", "integrated (2 slots), unwieldy", "The ionizer’s beam ionizes a path to its target, which serves as a route for the ensuing electric charge. There are several different elemental ions used in constructing ionizers, with the strength of the output based on the metal used. The most common are cupric, ferric, chromic, and stannic ionizers. Generally, the weapon’s hardware is stored in two upgrade slots of a piece of armor, while a connected wand-like barrel extends from an extremity. Aballon’s anacites designed the first ionizers, but they have long since spread throughout the Pact Worlds and beyond."),
	("Ionizer, Chromic", "Small Arms 1-H", 14, 80,000, 12, 30, arc 3d4, 20 charges, 1, "L", "integrated (2 slots), unwieldy", "The ionizer’s beam ionizes a path to its target, which serves as a route for the ensuing electric charge. There are several different elemental ions used in constructing ionizers, with the strength of the output based on the metal used. The most common are cupric, ferric, chromic, and stannic ionizers. Generally, the weapon’s hardware is stored in two upgrade slots of a piece of armor, while a connected wand-like barrel extends from an extremity. Aballon’s anacites designed the first ionizers, but they have long since spread throughout the Pact Worlds and beyond."),
	("Ionizer, Stannic", "Small Arms 1-H", 19, 611,000, 22, 30, arc 5d8, 20 charges, 1, "L", "integrated (2 slots), unwieldy", "The ionizer’s beam ionizes a path to its target, which serves as a route for the ensuing electric charge. There are several different elemental ions used in constructing ionizers, with the strength of the output based on the metal used. The most common are cupric, ferric, chromic, and stannic ionizers. Generally, the weapon’s hardware is stored in two upgrade slots of a piece of armor, while a connected wand-like barrel extends from an extremity. Aballon’s anacites designed the first ionizers, but they have long since spread throughout the Pact Worlds and beyond."),
	("Kalo Shredder, Slipstream-Class", "Long Arms 2-H", 3, 1,610, 3, 30, bleed 1d4, 8 flechettes, 1, "1", "analog, automatic, underwater", "Favored by the much-romanticized kalo hunters of Kalo-Mahoi, kalo shredders fire razor-sharp flechettes with nearly silent magnetism. The gun’s distinctive organic design is grown from magnetic coral that grants you a +2 bonus to KAC against disarm combat maneuvers."),
	("Nova Rifle, Red Star", "Long Arms 2-H", 2, 940, 3, 30, blind, 20 charges, 2, "1", "line, unwieldy", "Much like traditional plasma rifles, nova rifles fire coherent gouts of plasma that can potentially travel some distance and burn multiple targets. However, nova rifles have a slimmer profile overall but a larger aperture, projecting plasma that’s both slightly cooler and more diffuse. The nova rifle’s intense visual display makes it a favorite of icons looking to make a statement or simply add pyrotechnics to their shows. Red star, yellow star, and white star nova rifles are all easily identified by the color of their plasma arcs."),
	("Forked Pistol, 6-Notch", "Small Arms 1-H", 2, 720, 2, 30, burn 1d4, 20 charges, 1, "L", "boost 1", "Plasma builds up and arcs between the two long, notched tines of this pistol, amplifying in power as the stream travels the length of the weapon. Forked pistols are named for the number of notches in their plasma-generating forks, as each notch contributes to a more powerful blast. Pistols are typically available in 6-notch, 8-notch, 9-notch, and 10-notch models."),
	("Forked Pistol, 8-Notch", "Small Arms 1-H", 6, 4,100, 2, 30, burn 1d4, 20 charges, 1, "L", "boost 1d4", "Plasma builds up and arcs between the two long, notched tines of this pistol, amplifying in power as the stream travels the length of the weapon. Forked pistols are named for the number of notches in their plasma-generating forks, as each notch contributes to a more powerful blast. Pistols are typically available in 6-notch, 8-notch, 9-notch, and 10-notch models."),
	("Ember Pistol, Truth-Sequence", "Small Arms 1-H", 2, 525, 3, 30, burn 1d4, 8, 1, "L", "n/a", "Lighter and more mobile versions of cinder rifles, these pistols are standard issue to the Dawn Patrol and many Sarenite authorities across the galaxy. The piercing rounds are shot from the bulky pistol at white-hot temperatures and can set their targets on fire. They are still thought of as a humane weapon by some, as the searing bullets often cauterize the wounds that they make."),
	("Ember Pistol, Salvation-Sequence", "Small Arms 1-H", 7, 5,700, 7, 30, burn 1d4, 10, 1, "L", "n/a", "Lighter and more mobile versions of cinder rifles, these pistols are standard issue to the Dawn Patrol and many Sarenite authorities across the galaxy. The piercing rounds are shot from the bulky pistol at white-hot temperatures and can set their targets on fire. They are still thought of as a humane weapon by some, as the searing bullets often cauterize the wounds that they make."),
	("Flare Gun, Survival", "Small Arms 1-H", 1, 90, 2, 30, burn 1d6, 1 flare, 1, "L", "analog, bright", "A survival flare gun is used to signal danger or call for help. Though not designed for combat, survival flare guns can deal fire damage at close range. "
	("Dragon Pistol, Wyrmling", "Small Arms 1-H", 5, 2,650, 3, 30, burn 1d6, 20 petrol, 1, "L", "n/a", "A dragon pistol features a wide muzzle that is often shaped like a dragon’s maw. The weapon discharges discrete orbs of flaming petrol that can cling to targets. A wyrmling dragon pistol casts small petrol globules, while drake and wyvern dragon pistols have increased outputs. The true dragon pistol is as devastating as it is rare."),
	("Burner, Ifrit-Class", "Heavy 2-H", 3, 1,300, 5, 30, burn 1d6, 40 petrol, 4, "2", "line, unwieldy", "Indistinguishable from a flamethrower to the lay observer, a burner uses petrol as fuel to produce a strong jet of flame. However, the subtly narrower nozzle and recoil-suppressing gyros allow a burner to fire streams of petrol with more control and focus than its traditional cousin. Ifrit-, salamander-, hellhound-, firedrake-, and phoenix-class burners are all widely available."),
	("Flamethrower, Pyre-Class", "Heavy 2-H", 6, 4,200, 5, 30, burn 1d8, 20 petrol, 4, "2", "analog, blast, unwieldy", "These portable flamethrowers consist of a heavy rifle-like design with an oversized petrol tank integrated into the weapon’s stock."),
	("Flame Pistol, Inferno", "Small Arms 1-H", 11, 23,000, 9, 30, burn 1d8, 20 petrol, 5, "L", "line, unwieldy", "A flame pistol shoots a line of ignited petrol from its barrel."),
	("Dragon Pistol, Drake", "Small Arms 1-H", 10, 17,000, 7, 30, burn 2d4, 20 petrol, 1, "L", "n/a", "A dragon pistol features a wide muzzle that is often shaped like a dragon’s maw. The weapon discharges discrete orbs of flaming petrol that can cling to targets. A wyrmling dragon pistol casts small petrol globules, while drake and wyvern dragon pistols have increased outputs. The true dragon pistol is as devastating as it is rare."),
	("Flamethrower, Salamander-Class", "Heavy 2-H", 8, 8,600, 7, 30, burn 2d6, 20 petrol, 5, "2", "analog, blast, unwieldy", "These portable flamethrowers consist of a heavy rifle-like design with an oversized petrol tank integrated into the weapon’s stock."),
	("Flame Pistol, Solar Flare", "Small Arms 1-H", 17, 220,000, 16, 30, burn 2d6, 20 petrol, 5, "L", "line, unwieldy", "A flame pistol shoots a line of ignited petrol from its barrel."),
	("Plasma Pistol, White Star", "Small Arms 1-H", 15, 107,500, 13, 30, burn 2d8, 100 charges, 20, "L", "line, unwieldy", "Plasma pistols fire a line of ionized plasma out to a relatively short range. The plasma can continue to burn after contact. "
	("Forked Pistol, 9-Notch", "Small Arms 1-H", 13, 48,100, 10, 30, burn 3d4, 40 charges, 2, "L", "boost 2d4", "Plasma builds up and arcs between the two long, notched tines of this pistol, amplifying in power as the stream travels the length of the weapon. Forked pistols are named for the number of notches in their plasma-generating forks, as each notch contributes to a more powerful blast. Pistols are typically available in 6-notch, 8-notch, 9-notch, and 10-notch models."),
	("Dragon Pistol, Wyvern", "Small Arms 1-H", 15, 95,000, 14, 30, burn 3d6, 20 petrol, 1, "L", "n/a", "A dragon pistol features a wide muzzle that is often shaped like a dragon’s maw. The weapon discharges discrete orbs of flaming petrol that can cling to targets. A wyrmling dragon pistol casts small petrol globules, while drake and wyvern dragon pistols have increased outputs. The true dragon pistol is as devastating as it is rare."),
	("Forked Pistol, 10-Notch", "Small Arms 1-H", 20, 801,000, 22, 30, burn 4d4, 40 charges, 4, "L", "boost 5d4", "Plasma builds up and arcs between the two long, notched tines of this pistol, amplifying in power as the stream travels the length of the weapon. Forked pistols are named for the number of notches in their plasma-generating forks, as each notch contributes to a more powerful blast. Pistols are typically available in 6-notch, 8-notch, 9-notch, and 10-notch models."),
	("Flamethrower, Hellhound-Class", "Heavy 2-H", 12, 35,100, 14, 30, burn 4d6, 40 petrol, 8, "2", "analog, blast, unwieldy", "These portable flamethrowers consist of a heavy rifle-like design with an oversized petrol tank integrated into the weapon’s stock."),
	("Flamethrower, Firedrake-Class", "Heavy 2-H", 15, 128,000, 21, 30, burn 6d6, 40 petrol, 10, "2", "analog, blast, unwieldy", "These portable flamethrowers consist of a heavy rifle-like design with an oversized petrol tank integrated into the weapon’s stock."),
	("Flamethrower, Phoenix-Class", "Heavy 2-H", 18, 367,500, 31, 30, burn 9d6, 40 petrol, 10, "2", "analog, blast, unwieldy", "These portable flamethrowers consist of a heavy rifle-like design with an oversized petrol tank integrated into the weapon’s stock."),
	("Acid Lancer, Corroder-Class", "Heavy 2-H", 4, 2,000, 5, 30, corrode 1d4, 20 caustrol, 4, "2", "analog, boost 1d4, line, unwieldy", "In addition to collecting the valuable composites the creature leaves behind, some entrepreneurs enter surnochs’ territory to hunt and kill them for their acid-producing glands and spines. These components can be made into heavy weapons known as acid lancers, which shoot jets of caustic fluid. A wielder of an acid lancer can squeeze the gland located near the trigger to give her next shot an extra boost of damaging acid. Acid lancers use a special synthetic acid called caustrol for ammunition, which has the same price and comes in the same size containers as petrol."),
	("Disintegrator Rifle, Liquidator", "Long Arms 2-H", 6, 4,740, 10, 30, corrode 1d6, 40 charges, 4, "2", "n/a", "Rather snub nosed compared to other longarms, a disintegrator rifle is heavier than it looks due to the row of round energygenerating compartments atop its frame. These compartments generate enough energy for the weapon to liquefy enemies’ bodies. Well-connected customers can purchase liquidator, decimator, executioner, and eradicator disintegrator rifles."),
	("Acid Lancer, Melter-Class", "Heavy 2-H", 9, 13,000, 7, 30, corrode 2d4, 20 caustrol, 5, "2", "analog, boost 1d6, line, unwieldy", "In addition to collecting the valuable composites the creature leaves behind, some entrepreneurs enter surnochs’ territory to hunt and kill them for their acid-producing glands and spines. These components can be made into heavy weapons known as acid lancers, which shoot jets of caustic fluid. A wielder of an acid lancer can squeeze the gland located near the trigger to give her next shot an extra boost of damaging acid. Acid lancers use a special synthetic acid called caustrol for ammunition, which has the same price and comes in the same size containers as petrol."),
	("Disintegrator Rifle, Decimator", "Long Arms 2-H", 11, 29,000, 16, 30, corrode 2d6, 40 charges, 4, "2", "n/a", "Rather snub nosed compared to other longarms, a disintegrator rifle is heavier than it looks due to the row of round energygenerating compartments atop its frame. These compartments generate enough energy for the weapon to liquefy enemies’ bodies. Well-connected customers can purchase liquidator, decimator, executioner, and eradicator disintegrator rifles."),
	("Disintegration Pistol, Eradicator", "Small Arms 1-H", 20, 745,000, 31, 30, corrode 2d6, 40 charges, 4, "L", "n/a", "This hefty pistol has two small internal tanks that generate the energy needed to deliquesce the wielder’s targets. Disintegrator pistols come in liquidator, decimator, executioner, and eradicator models."),
	("Disintegrator Rifle, Executioner", "Long Arms 2-H", 16, 210,000, 27, 30, corrode 3d6, 80 charges, 8, "2", "n/a", "Rather snub nosed compared to other longarms, a disintegrator rifle is heavier than it looks due to the row of round energygenerating compartments atop its frame. These compartments generate enough energy for the weapon to liquefy enemies’ bodies. Well-connected customers can purchase liquidator, decimator, executioner, and eradicator disintegrator rifles."),
	("Disintegrator Rifle, Eradicator", "Long Arms 2-H", 20, 745,000, 52, 30, corrode 4d6, 80 charges, 8, "2", "n/a", "Rather snub nosed compared to other longarms, a disintegrator rifle is heavier than it looks due to the row of round energygenerating compartments atop its frame. These compartments generate enough energy for the weapon to liquefy enemies’ bodies. Well-connected customers can purchase liquidator, decimator, executioner, and eradicator disintegrator rifles."),
	("Shrieking Larva", "Small Arms 1-H", 5, 2,800, 4, 30, deafen, 20 charges, 4, "L", "living, thought, unwieldy", "Lashunta biologists genetically engineered the shrieking larva from a creature found in Castrovel’s jungles. This living weapon is dormant until fed power through a manual trigger. A telepathic user can mentally trigger the larva to siphon energy as needed, causing the weapon to fire faster than by trigger. When powered, the stimulated larva shrieks. This simultaneously shrill and oscillating outburst forms a coherent beam emitted in the direction the larva is pointed."),
	("Screamer, Thunderstrike", "Heavy 2-H", 5, 3,350, 5, 30, deafen, 40 charges, 4, "2", "blast, unwieldy", "A screamer is a circular metal device with two handles on the back. The front of a screamer projects a cone of sonic energy that can damage and deafen anyone within the weapon’s area of effect."),
	("Dirge Cannon, Resonant", "Heavy 2-H", 7, 4,270, 7, 30, deafen, 40 charges, 4, "3", "antibiological, blast, unwieldy", "Pirates are the most common users of dirge cannons. The potbellied, shoulder-resting weapons cause a brief but intense sound burst at frequencies and pressure sufficient to rupture living cells while leaving inorganic objects unharmed. The result is a weapon that can eliminate a starship’s crew without causing any damage to the vessel or its cargo. Those who prefer lighter damage favor harmonic and resonant cannons, leaving anharmonic and parametric models for situations that call for carnage."),
	("Shout Rifle", "Long Arms 2-H", 1, 450, 2, 30, demoralize, 20 charges, 4, "1", "blast, nonlethal, unwieldy", "A shout rifle looks less like a rifle and much more like an elongated megaphone. It functions in much the same way, amplifying sound input, such as the wielder’s voice, to an extreme volume and projecting it outward in a wide area. Protest leaders use shout rifles, ensuring that their proclamations can be heard at a great distance. Law enforcement officials also appreciate these weapons for crowd control."),
	("Decoupler, Pusher", "Small Arms 1-H", 4, 2,300, 3, 30, demoralize, 40 charges, 2, "L", "n/a", "Some manufacturers have streamlined the disintegrator pistol’s design to create a more affordable option; the result of their efforts is referred to simply as a decoupler. A decoupler is smaller and lighter than a disintegrator pistol, trading some of its outright destructive power for the ability to deal superficial pain that can leave targets shaking in their boots. In the Apostaean city of Nightarch, the ruling House Zeizerer issues decouplers to its enforcers, many of whom refer to the weapons as “facilitators.” Manufacturers typically produce bruiser, pusher, and screamer decouplers."),
	("Psychic-Wave Cannon, I", "Heavy 2-H", 2, 1,100, 3, 30, demoralize, 20 charges, 4, "2", "blast, living, mind-affecting, unwieldy", "Unlike weapons that rely on physical projectiles or various energy forms to damage a target, a psychic-wave cannon targets a creature’s mind. The cannon contains an organic neural matrix that converts charges into a mental blast, damaging creatures with overwhelming psychic output. The numeral of a psychicwave cannon’s model indicates the strength of its output, but the weapon can’t harm objects and mindless creatures, as well as those immune to mind-affecting effects."),
	("Shout Projector, Exhorter", "Heavy 2-H", 1, 420, 3, 30, demoralize, 20 charges, 2, "2", "explode (10), integrated (2 slots), nonlethal,unwieldy", "Shout projectors amplify your speech to overwhelming or destructive volume, and then project it in a cone. Words and sheer sonic pressure in this cone can’t be ignored. All shout projectors can be installed as armor upgrades (taking one upgrade slot per hand needed to wield the weapon), allowing the projectors to be used hands-free. That way, a user can carry lethal weaponry, safety gear, or protest signage. Exhorter shout projectors can be useful for crowd control with a lighter touch. Damper and pacifier models are ostensibly for nonlethal but more coercive applications, while the riot and crackdown projectors are for heavy-handed use."),
	("Decoupler, Screamer", "Small Arms 1-H", 8, 10,800, 5, 30, demoralize, 40 charges, 2, "L", "n/a", "Some manufacturers have streamlined the disintegrator pistol’s design to create a more affordable option; the result of their efforts is referred to simply as a decoupler. A decoupler is smaller and lighter than a disintegrator pistol, trading some of its outright destructive power for the ability to deal superficial pain that can leave targets shaking in their boots. In the Apostaean city of Nightarch, the ruling House Zeizerer issues decouplers to its enforcers, many of whom refer to the weapons as “facilitators.” Manufacturers typically produce bruiser, pusher, and screamer decouplers."),
	("Caustoject, Liquidator", "Small Arms 1-H", 1, 225, 2, 30, Injection DC +2, 20, 2, "L", "Injection", "Much of the design of this pistol-like weapon is based off the biological systems of the disintegration lash class of small arms, though a caustoject’s more traditional appearance is in stark contrast to its techno-organic inspiration. Caustojects create an injectable field that transforms ordinary matter into an acidic compound, disintegrating their targets from the inside. Syringes can be loaded into these weapons, allowing other materials to be quickly injected instead of an acidic discharge (in which case only the injection effect occurs0no acid damage is dealt)."),
	("Nightarch Needler, Tactical", "Small Arms 1-H", 3, 1,650, 3, 30, Injection DC +2, 5 darts, 1, "L", "analog, injection", "Popular among the drow on Apostae, this needle gun can deliver deadly poisons. The weapon is so small you gain a +2 bonus to Sleight of Hand checks to hide it on your person."),
	("Caustoject, Decimator", "Small Arms 1-H", 6, 4,000, 4, 30, Injection DC +2, 20, 2, "L", "Injection", "Much of the design of this pistol-like weapon is based off the biological systems of the disintegration lash class of small arms, though a caustoject’s more traditional appearance is in stark contrast to its techno-organic inspiration. Caustojects create an injectable field that transforms ordinary matter into an acidic compound, disintegrating their targets from the inside. Syringes can be loaded into these weapons, allowing other materials to be quickly injected instead of an acidic discharge (in which case only the injection effect occurs0no acid damage is dealt)."),
	("Nightarch Needler, Advanced", "Small Arms 1-H", 8, 6,270, 7, 30, Injection DC +2, 5 darts, 1, "L", "analog, injection", "Popular among the drow on Apostae, this needle gun can deliver deadly poisons. The weapon is so small you gain a +2 bonus to Sleight of Hand checks to hide it on your person."),
	("Caustoject, Executioner", "Small Arms 1-H", 12, 32,900, 10, 30, Injection DC +2, 20, 2, "L", "Injection", "Much of the design of this pistol-like weapon is based off the biological systems of the disintegration lash class of small arms, though a caustoject’s more traditional appearance is in stark contrast to its techno-organic inspiration. Caustojects create an injectable field that transforms ordinary matter into an acidic compound, disintegrating their targets from the inside. Syringes can be loaded into these weapons, allowing other materials to be quickly injected instead of an acidic discharge (in which case only the injection effect occurs0no acid damage is dealt)."),
	("Nightarch Needler, Elite", "Small Arms 1-H", 13, 44,980, 14, 30, Injection DC +2, 5 darts, 1, "L", "analog, injection", "Popular among the drow on Apostae, this needle gun can deliver deadly poisons. The weapon is so small you gain a +2 bonus to Sleight of Hand checks to hide it on your person."),
	("Caustoject, Eradicator", "Small Arms 1-H", 18, 242,300, 27, 30, Injection DC +2, 20, 2, "L", "Injection", "Much of the design of this pistol-like weapon is based off the biological systems of the disintegration lash class of small arms, though a caustoject’s more traditional appearance is in stark contrast to its techno-organic inspiration. Caustojects create an injectable field that transforms ordinary matter into an acidic compound, disintegrating their targets from the inside. Syringes can be loaded into these weapons, allowing other materials to be quickly injected instead of an acidic discharge (in which case only the injection effect occurs0no acid damage is dealt)."),
	("Nightarch Needler, Paragon", "Small Arms 1-H", 18, 369,000, 28, 30, Injection DC +2, 5 darts, 1, "L", "analog, injection", "Popular among the drow on Apostae, this needle gun can deliver deadly poisons. The weapon is so small you gain a +2 bonus to Sleight of Hand checks to hide it on your person."),
	("Radcannon, Electromagnetic", "Heavy 2-H", 4, 2,150, 4, 30, irradiate, 40 charges, 2, "2", "blast, radioactive, unwieldy", "Radcannons are large, dangerous-to-wield weapons typically employed by desperate, reckless, or unliving users. A radcannon’s high-voltage capacitors channel energy through a magnetron and transformer to generate massive blasts of radioactive waves, burning targets and typically exposing the target0and potentially the user0to dangerous levels of radiation. Devourer cultists often employ electromagnetic radcannons, neutron radcannons, and even rapid-decay radcannons, unfazed by the weapons’ danger."),
	("Microfusion Rifle, Medium", "Long Arms 2-H", 12, 40,800, 13, 30, irradiate, 40 charges, 4, "1", "blast, radioactive, unwieldy", "The microfusion rifle is built around a bulbous miniaturized fusion reactor. Plasma is generated and placed under incredible pressure in the reactor before being vented in a sudden blast that sometimes carries dangerous levels of radiation. The sparse shielding on light microfusion rifles often results in the users incurring radiation poisoning, so they tend to be used by undertrained militias that can’t afford (or lack the judgment to use) safer heavy weapons. Medium and heavy microfusion rifles are built with larger reactors, which prove more dangerous to their users and targets alike."),
	("Breaching Gun, Impact", "Long Arms 2-H", 11, 25,300, 16, 30, knockdown, 12 shells, 2, "1", "analog, breach, penetrating", "A breaching gun uses scattergun shells as ammunition against a single target at short range, dealing an impressive amount of damage and even tearing through doors and other objects. These weapons are most commonly seen in the hands of space pirates who need to blast through plastic interior doors, though expert users can use these weapons to break through airlock doors. Breaching guns also saw widespread use on Absalom Station in the aftermath of the Gap, as security forces desperately tried to maintain control over the station’s fractured and panicked population, which often required blasting through barricades and sealed interior airlocks. Utility, snub, impact, vortex, and grapeshot breaching guns are widely available on various worlds."),
	("Breaching Gun, Vortex", "Long Arms 2-H", 15, 119,000, 33, 30, knockdown, 16 shells, 2, "1", "analog, breach, penetrating", "A breaching gun uses scattergun shells as ammunition against a single target at short range, dealing an impressive amount of damage and even tearing through doors and other objects. These weapons are most commonly seen in the hands of space pirates who need to blast through plastic interior doors, though expert users can use these weapons to break through airlock doors. Breaching guns also saw widespread use on Absalom Station in the aftermath of the Gap, as security forces desperately tried to maintain control over the station’s fractured and panicked population, which often required blasting through barricades and sealed interior airlocks. Utility, snub, impact, vortex, and grapeshot breaching guns are widely available on various worlds."),
	("Breaching Gun, Grapeshot", "Long Arms 2-H", 19, 509,000, 55, 30, knockdown, 20 shells, 2, "1", "analog, breach, penetrating", "A breaching gun uses scattergun shells as ammunition against a single target at short range, dealing an impressive amount of damage and even tearing through doors and other objects. These weapons are most commonly seen in the hands of space pirates who need to blast through plastic interior doors, though expert users can use these weapons to break through airlock doors. Breaching guns also saw widespread use on Absalom Station in the aftermath of the Gap, as security forces desperately tried to maintain control over the station’s fractured and panicked population, which often required blasting through barricades and sealed interior airlocks. Utility, snub, impact, vortex, and grapeshot breaching guns are widely available on various worlds."),
	("Freeze Ray, Hiemal", "Long Arms 2-H", 3, 1,420, 2, 30, staggered, 20 charges, 4, "2", "line, unwieldy", "Across the galaxy, practically every sufficiently advanced civilization has created its own variation of the freeze ray. All freeze rays function in a similar way, emitting a long line of supercooled gas, but individual models reflect their species’ design aesthetics. In the Pact Worlds, the most common models reflect the slim profile of Vercite technology or the bony protrusions of Eoxian design. Hiemal, algid, and glacial freeze rays simply produce an extreme reduction in the temperature along the weapon’s line of effect. Isothermal freeze rays cause a persistent temperature drop, dealing further damage, while hypothermic freeze rays causes multiple temperature reductions in rapid succession for further increased destruction."),
	("Coolant Sprayer, Algid", "Heavy 2-H", 7, 7,400, 3, 30, staggered, 40 charges, 4, "3", "blast, entangle (1d4 rounds), unwieldy", "Coolant sprayers were designed following the principles of a flamethrower, but with an eye more toward hindrance than sheer damage. Experts can easily identify a coolant sprayer by the bulky insulation surrounding the sprayer’s coolant reservoir. The weapon expels a cone of activated coolant that stiffens and freezes living tissue. While not harmless, the effect is somewhat less deadly than most energy weapons. Hiemal, algid, glacial, and isothermal coolant sprayers all function in similar ways, though their destructive potential varies from one model to another."),
	("Freeze Ray, Algid", "Long Arms 2-H", 7, 6,300, 5, 30, staggered, 20 charges, 4, "2", "line, unwieldy", "Across the galaxy, practically every sufficiently advanced civilization has created its own variation of the freeze ray. All freeze rays function in a similar way, emitting a long line of supercooled gas, but individual models reflect their species’ design aesthetics. In the Pact Worlds, the most common models reflect the slim profile of Vercite technology or the bony protrusions of Eoxian design. Hiemal, algid, and glacial freeze rays simply produce an extreme reduction in the temperature along the weapon’s line of effect. Isothermal freeze rays cause a persistent temperature drop, dealing further damage, while hypothermic freeze rays causes multiple temperature reductions in rapid succession for further increased destruction."),
	("Frost Projector, Frostbite-Class", "Long Arms 2-H", 6, 5,100, 5, 30, staggered, 40 charges, 2, "1", "integrated (2 slots)", "A frost projector requires two armor upgrade slots to install: one for the short, wide barrel and another for the coolant canister and battery; cables and hoses connect the two components. These weapons are produced in frostbite-class, hailstorm-class, and blizzard-class models."),
	("Frost Projector, Hailstorm-Class", "Long Arms 2-H", 12, 42,000, 11, 30, staggered, 40 charges, 2, "1", "integrated (2 slots)", "A frost projector requires two armor upgrade slots to install: one for the short, wide barrel and another for the coolant canister and battery; cables and hoses connect the two components. These weapons are produced in frostbite-class, hailstorm-class, and blizzard-class models."),
	("Charge Emitter, Jolt", "Long Arms 2-H", 13, 57,000, 16, 30, staggered, 20 charges, 2, "1", "integrated (1 slot), stun", "This series of insulating reinforced-glass rings can be installed into armor upgrade slots and focuses an electrical charge into a targeted bolt. The sheer power necessary to project a bolt of electricity means that even an impulse charge emitter is a substantial weapon, and jolt charge emitters and surge charge emitters are significantly more powerful. Their relatively slim profile makes them popular for a number of users, from androids and others who benefit from a racial armor upgrade slot, to starship-repair crews in hostile space who want to keep their hands free for their work without leaving themselves totally undefended."),
	("Frost Projector, Blizzard-Class", "Long Arms 2-H", 19, 680,000, 27, 30, staggered, 40 charges, 2, "1", "integrated (2 slots)", "A frost projector requires two armor upgrade slots to install: one for the short, wide barrel and another for the coolant canister and battery; cables and hoses connect the two components. These weapons are produced in frostbite-class, hailstorm-class, and blizzard-class models."),
	("Persuader", "Small Arms 1-H", 9, 13,500, 5, 30, wound, 20 charges, 2, "L", "boost 1d4", "This small, brutish sidearm fires a surprisingly large globule of plasma that stretches into a rope as it travels, sometimes inflicting terrible wounds on its target. It is a perennial favorite of officers in the Veskarium; those seeking to surprise and intimidate their foes use the weapon’s reputation to their advantage. Although the first persuaders date back to the Silent War and are considered rare collectibles in the Pact Worlds, dozens of manufacturers make their own modern versions."),
	("Stellar Cannon, Light", "Heavy 2-H", 10, 19,200, 13, 30, wound, 18 shells, 6, "2", "blast", "A stellar cannon is a portable, handheld cannon that fires exploding shells filled with dense flechettes that shred nearby targets. Stellar cannons have a limited range, but they deal traumatic damage to large areas. "
	("Stellar Cannon, Heavy", "Heavy 2-H", 15, 122,800, 26, 30, wound, 32 shells, 8, "2", "blast", "A stellar cannon is a portable, handheld cannon that fires exploding shells filled with dense flechettes that shred nearby targets. Stellar cannons have a limited range, but they deal traumatic damage to large areas. "
	("Foam Grenade, Mk 1", "Grenades 1-H", 3, 410, 0, 31, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (10), extinguish", "A foam grenade explodes on impact to release a burst of fire-suppressant foam akin to that from a fire extinguisher. This foam reduces the damage from the burning condition or from the corrode critical hit effect taken by creatures within the area by the listed amount each round; this ends the burning condition or corrode effect if it reduces the amount of damage to 0. This also ends any active fires within the affected area."),
	("Needler Pistol, Advanced", "Small Arms 1-H", 5, 2,700, 3, 31, Injection DC +2, 8 darts, 1, "L", "analog, injection", "A favorite of assassins and battlefield medics alike, the needler pistol uses magnetic fields or pressurized gas to launch darts that inject a substance into the target. This injection gun can be fitted with cartridges containing medicine or poison."),
	("Foam Grenade, Mk 2", "Grenades 1-H", 9, 3,520, 0, 32, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (20), extinguish", "A foam grenade explodes on impact to release a burst of fire-suppressant foam akin to that from a fire extinguisher. This foam reduces the damage from the burning condition or from the corrode critical hit effect taken by creatures within the area by the listed amount each round; this ends the burning condition or corrode effect if it reduces the amount of damage to 0. This also ends any active fires within the affected area."),
	("Needler Pistol, Elite", "Small Arms 1-H", 10, 17,250, 9, 32, Injection DC +2, 8 darts, 1, "L", "analog, injection", "A favorite of assassins and battlefield medics alike, the needler pistol uses magnetic fields or pressurized gas to launch darts that inject a substance into the target. This injection gun can be fitted with cartridges containing medicine or poison."),
	("Foam Grenade, Mk 3", "Grenades 1-H", 15, 26,100, 0, 33, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (30), extinguish", "A foam grenade explodes on impact to release a burst of fire-suppressant foam akin to that from a fire extinguisher. This foam reduces the damage from the burning condition or from the corrode critical hit effect taken by creatures within the area by the listed amount each round; this ends the burning condition or corrode effect if it reduces the amount of damage to 0. This also ends any active fires within the affected area."),
	("Needler Pistol, Paragon", "Small Arms 1-H", 15, 94,500, 21, 33, Injection DC +2, 8 darts, 1, "L", "analog, injection", "A favorite of assassins and battlefield medics alike, the needler pistol uses magnetic fields or pressurized gas to launch darts that inject a substance into the target. This injection gun can be fitted with cartridges containing medicine or poison."),
	("Web Grenade, Mk 1", "Grenades 1-H", 3, 490, 0, 34, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (10), mire 1d4 rounds", "Developed using samples of haans’ biological webbing, a web grenade explodes to cover the area in sticky strands of hightensile fibers, making the affected area difficult terrain."),
	("Needler Pistol, Supreme", "Small Arms 1-H", 20, 725,000, 36, 34, Injection DC +2, 8 darts, 1, "L", "analog, injection", "A favorite of assassins and battlefield medics alike, the needler pistol uses magnetic fields or pressurized gas to launch darts that inject a substance into the target. This injection gun can be fitted with cartridges containing medicine or poison."),
	("Web Grenade, Mk 2", "Grenades 1-H", 9, 3,950, 0, 35, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (10), mire 2d4 rounds", "Developed using samples of haans’ biological webbing, a web grenade explodes to cover the area in sticky strands of hightensile fibers, making the affected area difficult terrain."),
	("Web Grenade, Mk 3", "Grenades 1-H", 13, 14,700, 0, 36, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (15), mire 1 minute", "Developed using samples of haans’ biological webbing, a web grenade explodes to cover the area in sticky strands of hightensile fibers, making the affected area difficult terrain."),
	("Web Grenade, Mk 4", "Grenades 1-H", 19, 163,000, 0, 37, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (25), mire 1 minute", "Developed using samples of haans’ biological webbing, a web grenade explodes to cover the area in sticky strands of hightensile fibers, making the affected area difficult terrain."),
	("Pulse Grenade, Mk 1", "Grenades 1-H", 5, 950, 0, 38, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (1d10 E; 20), entangle 1 round", "A pulse grenade emits a powerful EMP blast on impact whose damage and effects apply only to constructs with the technological subtype. Constructs reduced to 0 HP by a pulse grenade are not destroyed but simply nonfunctional until restored to 1 or more Hit Points. The EMP wave from a pulse grenade is not intense enough to affect augmentations, weapons, armor, or other technological gear."),
	("Pulse Grenade, Mk 2", "Grenades 1-H", 9, 4,350, 0, 39, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (3d10 E; 20), entangle 1d4 rounds", "A pulse grenade emits a powerful EMP blast on impact whose damage and effects apply only to constructs with the technological subtype. Constructs reduced to 0 HP by a pulse grenade are not destroyed but simply nonfunctional until restored to 1 or more Hit Points. The EMP wave from a pulse grenade is not intense enough to affect augmentations, weapons, armor, or other technological gear."),
	("Pulse Grenade, Mk 3", "Grenades 1-H", 15, 37,500, 0, 40, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (6d10 E; 20), entangle 1d4 rounds", "A pulse grenade emits a powerful EMP blast on impact whose damage and effects apply only to constructs with the technological subtype. Constructs reduced to 0 HP by a pulse grenade are not destroyed but simply nonfunctional until restored to 1 or more Hit Points. The EMP wave from a pulse grenade is not intense enough to affect augmentations, weapons, armor, or other technological gear."),
	("Shield Projector, Defender", "Small Arms 1-H", 9, 13,800, 0, 40, 0, 80 charges, 10, "2", "shield 2d6, unwieldy", "A shield projector is a heavy weapon that encases its target in a short-duration force field, akin to that produced by an armor upgrade. Such force fields are of limited strength, but higherpaizo power shield projectors can create a stronger protective barrier around the target. Shield projectors see the most use among security forces assigned to protect diplomats and high-profile celebrities. Available models0from the least to most powerful0 include sentry, defender, guardian, and warden shield projectors."),
	("Shield Projector, Guardian", "Small Arms 1-H", 14, 75,200, 0, 40, 0, 80 charges, 16, "2", "shield 2d12, unwieldy", "A shield projector is a heavy weapon that encases its target in a short-duration force field, akin to that produced by an armor upgrade. Such force fields are of limited strength, but higherpaizo power shield projectors can create a stronger protective barrier around the target. Shield projectors see the most use among security forces assigned to protect diplomats and high-profile celebrities. Available models0from the least to most powerful0 include sentry, defender, guardian, and warden shield projectors."),
	("Shield Projector, Sentry", "Small Arms 1-H", 4, 2,180, 0, 40, 0, 40 charges, 4, "2", "shield 1d4, unwieldy", "A shield projector is a heavy weapon that encases its target in a short-duration force field, akin to that produced by an armor upgrade. Such force fields are of limited strength, but higherpaizo power shield projectors can create a stronger protective barrier around the target. Shield projectors see the most use among security forces assigned to protect diplomats and high-profile celebrities. Available models0from the least to most powerful0 include sentry, defender, guardian, and warden shield projectors."),
	("Shield Projector, Warden", "Small Arms 1-H", 19, 594,000, 0, 40, 0, 100 charges, 20, "2", "shield 4d12, unwieldy", "A shield projector is a heavy weapon that encases its target in a short-duration force field, akin to that produced by an armor upgrade. Such force fields are of limited strength, but higherpaizo power shield projectors can create a stronger protective barrier around the target. Shield projectors see the most use among security forces assigned to protect diplomats and high-profile celebrities. Available models0from the least to most powerful0 include sentry, defender, guardian, and warden shield projectors."),
	("Bone Pistol, Grave-Class", "Small Arms 1-H", 3, 900, 2, 40, 0, 20 charges, 4, "L", "antibiological", "Usually crafted from bone and gristle, these pistols are prized by the Corpse Fleet and members of the Urgathoan church, but they have also been found in reaches of the galaxy untouched by Eoxian influence. The energy blasts from a bone pistol are a special blend of cold and negative energy that passes harmlessly over the nonliving. Bone pistols are commonly categorized as grave-class, crypt-class, sepulcher-class, and vault-class."),
	("Shoulder Laser, Azimuth", "Small Arms 1-H", 2, 870, 2, 40, 0, 20 charges, 1, "L", "integrated (1 slot)", "This laser weapon has a smooth, curved housing and an eyelike aperture, and it can be installed in an armor upgrade slot, leaving the wielder’s hands free for other tasks. As the name implies, most users mount the eyelike aperture over one shoulder, but it can work just as easily mounted on the torso or a forearm. Many shoulder laser users are androids who integrate them into their bodies as emergency weapons. Azimuth, corona, aphelion, and perihelion shoulder lasers are available in most areas."),
	("Bone Pistol, Crypt-Class", "Small Arms 1-H", 6, 4,350, 3, 40, 0, 20 charges, 4, "L", "antibiological", "Usually crafted from bone and gristle, these pistols are prized by the Corpse Fleet and members of the Urgathoan church, but they have also been found in reaches of the galaxy untouched by Eoxian influence. The energy blasts from a bone pistol are a special blend of cold and negative energy that passes harmlessly over the nonliving. Bone pistols are commonly categorized as grave-class, crypt-class, sepulcher-class, and vault-class."),
	("Infinity Rifle, tactical", "Long Arms 2-H", 3, 1,300, 3, 40, 0, 20 charges, 1, "1", "boost 16", "Infinity rifles take their name from their shape, two conjoined rings similar to an infinity symbol with twin muzzles along the outer edge of one ring. The two rings contain a twisted loop of fiber-optic cabling that channels the laser beam; adding more energy to the loop results in a more powerful blast. These weapons were first introduced to the Pact Worlds by skittermanders (Starfinder Alien Archive 106), though their current nomenclature (tactical, advanced, elite, and paragon) was imposed by other weapons manufacturers."),
	("Storm Coil, Live", "Long Arms 2-H", 3, 1,480, 3, 40, 0, 20 charges, 5, "2", "line, unwieldy", "A storm coil employs an air-core resonant transformer to produce high-voltage electrical output. The resulting bolt of electricity arcs out from the weapon in a line. Though it employs technology similar to the colossus coil, the storm coil was developed independently within the Pact Worlds. Live storm coils and jolt storm coils generate impressive bolts, while the larger impulse and surge storm coils have even farther reach."),
	("Petrol Converter, Light", "Long Arms 2-H", 4, 2,150, 4, 40, 0, 40 petrol, 2, "1", "analog, modal (disintegrator)", "This longarm has an extra cylinder connected to the petrol tank that contains a series of converter filters housing active bacteria. Diverting the petrol flow through this system before firing allows the bacteria to convert the fuel into acid. In addition to the tactical, advanced, elite, and paragon petrol converters, manufacturers have produced a light petrol converter for industrial applications."),
	("Cathode Cannon, Tactical", "Heavy 2-H", 4, 2,040, 5, 40, 0, 40 charges, 4, "2", "unwieldy, wide line", "Cathode cannons were originally designed by members of the Android Abolitionist Front, and many varieties made by different races nonetheless are decorated with circuit designs reminiscent of the weapons’ android inventors. The tactical cathode cannon is a standard-issue weapon for members of the Front, while advanced, elite, paragon, and shockstorm cathode cannons are often used by mercenaries and assault forces with a variety of goals."),
	("Plasma Bolter, Tactical", "Long Arms 2-H", 1, 260, 5, 40, 0, 20 charges, 4, "2", "unwieldy", "One of the most common ranged weapons used by the vesk military during the war between the Pact Worlds and the Veskarium, the plasma bolter is a particularly hefty longarm with a bulky profile that speaks to its vesk origins. Unlike most common ranged plasma weapons, which lay out long lines of plasma or boost their output, plasma bolters focus on delivering a single heavy bolt of plasma. These weapons saw extensive use in fighting back the Swarm, and now many can be easily obtained on the open market as Pact Worlds manufacturers have begun offering their own tactical, advanced, elite, and paragon models of the classic weapon."),
	("Shock Caster, Static", "Heavy 2-H", 6, 4,620, 6, 40, 0, 40 charges, 2, "2", "explode (10), unwieldy", "Shock casters fire a blast of electrical energy that explodes when it impacts, creating an electrical storm that can damage and stun anyone within its radius. "
	("Bone Pistol, Sepulcher-Class", "Small Arms 1-H", 11, 25,500, 9, 40, 0, 20 charges, 4, "L", "antibiological", "Usually crafted from bone and gristle, these pistols are prized by the Corpse Fleet and members of the Urgathoan church, but they have also been found in reaches of the galaxy untouched by Eoxian influence. The energy blasts from a bone pistol are a special blend of cold and negative energy that passes harmlessly over the nonliving. Bone pistols are commonly categorized as grave-class, crypt-class, sepulcher-class, and vault-class."),
	("Stormcaller, Ribbon", "Heavy 2-H", 7, 7,700, 9, 40, 0, 40 charges, 5, "2", "flexible line, living, unwieldy", "Some barathu researchers who intensively study the titanic lightning storms found on their home world become obsessed with the phenomenon. The efforts of such scientists led to the creation of the stormcaller, a living weapon that generates a line of electricity originating not from the wielder but from a single point within the weapon’s relatively short range. Like most barathu creations, stormcallers are living creatures, and their massive shells are large enough to require two hands to wield, aided by the stormcaller wrapping its translucent tentacles around the user’s appendages. Sheet and ribbon stormcallers are powerful weapons in their own right, while rocket and smooth-channel stormcallers can summon electrical currents that live up to the weapons’ namesake."),
	("Shock Caster, Aurora", "Heavy 2-H", 10, 19,100, 13, 40, 0, 40 charges, 4, "2", "explode (15), unwieldy", "Shock casters fire a blast of electrical energy that explodes when it impacts, creating an electrical storm that can damage and stun anyone within its radius. "
	("Lightning Pistol, Smooth-Channel", "Small Arms 1-H", 17, 260,000, 16, 40, 0, 40 charges, 10, "L", "line, stun, unwieldy", "When fired, this weapon erupts with a long, crackling bolt of electricity reminiscent of lightning. Sheet lightning pistols and ribbon lightning pistols are relatively common, but rocket and smooth-channel lightning pistols typically require a special license to carry legally."),
	("Rotating Pistol, Elite", "Small Arms 1-H", 16, 153,000, 20, 40, 0, 9 rounds, 1, "L", "analog, conceal", "A rotating pistol is a modern execution of an ancient design found on Golarion and several other worlds. The multiple barrels on this pistol rotate while firing to dissipate heat, which allows a more powerful shot without melting the weapon. The rotating pistol’s shots deal significant damage to their target, but the weapon requires frequent reloading. Rotating pistols are available in tactical, advanced, and elite models."),
	("Bone Pistol, Vault-Class", "Small Arms 1-H", 18, 591,000, 22, 40, 0, 40 charges, 4, "L", "antibiological", "Usually crafted from bone and gristle, these pistols are prized by the Corpse Fleet and members of the Urgathoan church, but they have also been found in reaches of the galaxy untouched by Eoxian influence. The energy blasts from a bone pistol are a special blend of cold and negative energy that passes harmlessly over the nonliving. Bone pistols are commonly categorized as grave-class, crypt-class, sepulcher-class, and vault-class."),
	("Shock Caster, Storm", "Heavy 2-H", 16, 164,800, 32, 40, 0, 100 charges, 10, "2", "explode (20), unwieldy", "Shock casters fire a blast of electrical energy that explodes when it impacts, creating an electrical storm that can damage and stun anyone within its radius. "
	("Hydra Cannon, Cobra-Series", "Heavy 2-H", 19, 642,000, 35, 40, 0, 20 charges, 2, "2", "blast, shape 4, unwieldy", "Rather than firing a single burst of plasma, a hydra cannon generates countless discrete plasma filaments that spread outward in a pattern reminiscent of crawling serpents. The spread of these filaments can be somewhat controlled, allowing a proficient user to avoid hitting a limited number of creatures within the weapon’s area of effect. Python-series hydra cannons offer the least control, while viper-series, asp-series, and cobraseries hydra cannons offer increasingly fine-tuned control over their target areas."),
	("Shuriken, Dynamo", "Special 1-H", 19, 98,000, 42, 40, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "quick reload, thrown", "Shuriken are bladed thrown weapons most common in the carbonedge form kasathas favor. However, these weapons are versatile and come in various forms for improved cutting power or specialized use. Additionally, the size of shuriken makes them easy to hide and carry. They are ideal for hit-and-run attacks and situations where it might not be prudent to retrieve a thrown weapon. Using the best in miniaturized machine and electronic technology, a dynamo shuriken can use the power it generates when thrown to deliver an electric pulse to a target or to return to its thrower."),
	("Shock Caster, Tempest", "Heavy 2-H", 20, 735,000, 45, 40, 0, 100 charges, 10, "2", "explode (20), unwieldy", "Shock casters fire a blast of electrical energy that explodes when it impacts, creating an electrical storm that can damage and stun anyone within its radius. "
	("Handcoil, Fighter", "Small Arms 1-H", 7, 5,600, 5, 40, arc 1d10, 20 charges, 2, "L", "n/a", "An ultraminiaturized version of the coilguns used on starships, this weapon has a short range but a powerful effect. Some of the first versions were produced by starship manufacturers and were accompanied by a promotional campaign suggesting that a starship’s crew should match the starship itself, complete with flight suits to match a given ship’s paint job. Most manufacturers still use the model classification set forth in those early campaigns: explorer, fighter, pilot, and capital handcoils."),
	("Surgecaster, Standard", "Long Arms 2-H", 5, 3,300, 5, 40, arc 1d10, 20 charges, 2, "1", "boost 1d6, living", "Surgecasters are bioengineered organic weapons; these independent conglomerations of bioelectric cells generate deadly bursts of electricity when fired. They were invented by a flotilla of merged barathus that directed its efforts toward creating such a weapon, and its success has resulted in the continued production of the surgecaster as a viable commercial endeavor. Only two models are currently available on the market: a standard surgecaster and an advanced surgecaster, though the merged barathu entity appears to be continuing its research and development efforts."),
	("Handcoil, Explorer", "Small Arms 1-H", 3, 1,200, 3, 40, arc 1d6, 20 charges, 2, "L", "n/a", "An ultraminiaturized version of the coilguns used on starships, this weapon has a short range but a powerful effect. Some of the first versions were produced by starship manufacturers and were accompanied by a promotional campaign suggesting that a starship’s crew should match the starship itself, complete with flight suits to match a given ship’s paint job. Most manufacturers still use the model classification set forth in those early campaigns: explorer, fighter, pilot, and capital handcoils."),
	("Anchor Pistol, Voltaic", "Small Arms 1-H", 4, 2,100, 3, 40, bind, 40 charges, 2, "L", "nonlethal", "Blasts from this electromagnetic pistol create a magnetic field that hampers a foe’s movement. Barathus working on Liavara developed these weapons, as the magnetic fields ensnare a target without causing it to fall0a useful feature when confronting the operators of illicit harvesting endeavors on a gas giant. Many parts of an anchor pistol are grown from living organisms, resulting in a lightweight pistol that gleams like mother-of-pearl. Voltaic anchor pistols employ typical electromagnetism, while the emergent and inductive anchor pistols use higher symmetries to produce aperiodic force. The flux anchor pistol relies on quantum-phase factors to generate extraordinarily powerful blasts."),
	("Anchor Pistol, Emergent", "Small Arms 1-H", 9, 13,200, 7, 40, bind, 40 charges, 4, "L", "nonlethal", "Blasts from this electromagnetic pistol create a magnetic field that hampers a foe’s movement. Barathus working on Liavara developed these weapons, as the magnetic fields ensnare a target without causing it to fall0a useful feature when confronting the operators of illicit harvesting endeavors on a gas giant. Many parts of an anchor pistol are grown from living organisms, resulting in a lightweight pistol that gleams like mother-of-pearl. Voltaic anchor pistols employ typical electromagnetism, while the emergent and inductive anchor pistols use higher symmetries to produce aperiodic force. The flux anchor pistol relies on quantum-phase factors to generate extraordinarily powerful blasts."),
	("Anchor Pistol, Inductive", "Small Arms 1-H", 15, 108,000, 14, 40, bind, 80 charges, 4, "L", "nonlethal", "Blasts from this electromagnetic pistol create a magnetic field that hampers a foe’s movement. Barathus working on Liavara developed these weapons, as the magnetic fields ensnare a target without causing it to fall0a useful feature when confronting the operators of illicit harvesting endeavors on a gas giant. Many parts of an anchor pistol are grown from living organisms, resulting in a lightweight pistol that gleams like mother-of-pearl. Voltaic anchor pistols employ typical electromagnetism, while the emergent and inductive anchor pistols use higher symmetries to produce aperiodic force. The flux anchor pistol relies on quantum-phase factors to generate extraordinarily powerful blasts."),
	("Perforator Pistol, Phased", "Small Arms 1-H", 20, 732,000, 27, 40, bleed, 40 charges, 8, "L", "penetrating", "Focused sound waves from a perforator pistol punch through objects and bodies. Drow employ perforators because the dark elves enjoy the weapon’s ability to inflict gruesome wounds, which are as effective against morale as against life and limb. Diffraction and refraction perforator pistols align and compound sound waves, while linear and phased perforator pistols are named for the internal matrices that focus wavelengths the pistols emitters generate."),
	("Hail Pistol, Absolute-Zero", "Small Arms 1-H", 17, 218,000, 22, 40, bleed 1d10, 20 charges, 2, "L", "n/a", "A hail pistol includes a chamber behind the barrel that circulates supercooled vapor and causes it to coalesce into razor-edged shards of ice that leave foes with rime-edged bleeding wounds. Subzero, gelid, ultracold, and absolute-zero hail pistols each produce progressively larger and more jagged shards."),
	("Kalo Shredder, Cascade-Class", "Long Arms 2-H", 7, 6,630, 7, 40, bleed 1d6, 16 flechettes, 1, "1", "analog, automatic, underwater", "Favored by the much-romanticized kalo hunters of Kalo-Mahoi, kalo shredders fire razor-sharp flechettes with nearly silent magnetism. The gun’s distinctive organic design is grown from magnetic coral that grants you a +2 bonus to KAC against disarm combat maneuvers."),
	("Hail Pistol, Ultracold", "Small Arms 1-H", 14, 63,200, 13, 40, bleed 1d8, 20 charges, 2, "L", "n/a", "A hail pistol includes a chamber behind the barrel that circulates supercooled vapor and causes it to coalesce into razor-edged shards of ice that leave foes with rime-edged bleeding wounds. Subzero, gelid, ultracold, and absolute-zero hail pistols each produce progressively larger and more jagged shards."),
	("Kalo Shredder, Torrent-Class", "Long Arms 2-H", 11, 26,700, 14, 40, bleed 3d4, 24 flechettes, 1, "1", "analog, automatic, underwater", "Favored by the much-romanticized kalo hunters of Kalo-Mahoi, kalo shredders fire razor-sharp flechettes with nearly silent magnetism. The gun’s distinctive organic design is grown from magnetic coral that grants you a +2 bonus to KAC against disarm combat maneuvers."),
	("Plasma Rifle, Red Star", "Long Arms 2-H", 6, 4,600, 5, 40, burn 1d4, 40 charges, 4, "2", "line, unwieldy", "Plasma rifles fire long lines of ionized plasma that lance through objects and opponents in their path. "
	("Shoulder Laser, Corona", "Small Arms 1-H", 8, 9,700, 4, 40, burn 1d6, 21 charges, 1, "L", "integrated (1 slot)", "This laser weapon has a smooth, curved housing and an eyelike aperture, and it can be installed in an armor upgrade slot, leaving the wielder’s hands free for other tasks. As the name implies, most users mount the eyelike aperture over one shoulder, but it can work just as easily mounted on the torso or a forearm. Many shoulder laser users are androids who integrate them into their bodies as emergency weapons. Azimuth, corona, aphelion, and perihelion shoulder lasers are available in most areas."),
	("Blaze Rifle, Ifrit-Class", "Long Arms 2-H", 4, 1,900, 5, 40, burn 1d6, 40 petrol, 2, "1", "analog, unwieldy", "A blaze rifle is a bulky, ungainly weapon, with a rifle stock and two tanks of petrol mounted atop the barrel. Compared to other petrol weapons, the blaze rifle fires a far narrower stream of petrol, which allows for greater accuracy. Fire-loving mercenaries often choose the blaze rifle to avoid charring their allies. Ifrit-, salamander-, hellhound-, firedrake-, and phoenixclass blaze rifles are common throughout the Pact Worlds."),
	("Plasma Rifle, Yellow Star", "Long Arms 2-H", 10, 16,800, 11, 40, burn 1d8, 40 charges, 4, "2", "line, unwieldy", "Plasma rifles fire long lines of ionized plasma that lance through objects and opponents in their path. "
	("Ember Pistol, Valor-Sequence", "Small Arms 1-H", 11, 23,400, 10, 40, burn 2d4, 12, 1, "L", "n/a", "Lighter and more mobile versions of cinder rifles, these pistols are standard issue to the Dawn Patrol and many Sarenite authorities across the galaxy. The piercing rounds are shot from the bulky pistol at white-hot temperatures and can set their targets on fire. They are still thought of as a humane weapon by some, as the searing bullets often cauterize the wounds that they make."),
	("Shoulder Laser, Aphelion", "Small Arms 1-H", 13, 51,500, 9, 40, burn 2d6, 22 charges, 1, "L", "integrated (1 slot)", "This laser weapon has a smooth, curved housing and an eyelike aperture, and it can be installed in an armor upgrade slot, leaving the wielder’s hands free for other tasks. As the name implies, most users mount the eyelike aperture over one shoulder, but it can work just as easily mounted on the torso or a forearm. Many shoulder laser users are androids who integrate them into their bodies as emergency weapons. Azimuth, corona, aphelion, and perihelion shoulder lasers are available in most areas."),
	("Burner, Salamander-Class", "Heavy 2-H", 7, 6,050, 11, 40, burn 2d6, 40 petrol, 4, "2", "line, unwieldy", "Indistinguishable from a flamethrower to the lay observer, a burner uses petrol as fuel to produce a strong jet of flame. However, the subtly narrower nozzle and recoil-suppressing gyros allow a burner to fire streams of petrol with more control and focus than its traditional cousin. Ifrit-, salamander-, hellhound-, firedrake-, and phoenix-class burners are all widely available."),
	("Ember Pistol, Glory-Sequence", "Small Arms 1-H", 14, 65,800, 14, 40, burn 2d6, 16, 1, "L", "n/a", "Lighter and more mobile versions of cinder rifles, these pistols are standard issue to the Dawn Patrol and many Sarenite authorities across the galaxy. The piercing rounds are shot from the bulky pistol at white-hot temperatures and can set their targets on fire. They are still thought of as a humane weapon by some, as the searing bullets often cauterize the wounds that they make."),
	("Shoulder Laser, Perihelion", "Small Arms 1-H", 18, 383,000, 13, 40, burn 3d6, 23 charges, 1, "L", "integrated (1 slot)", "This laser weapon has a smooth, curved housing and an eyelike aperture, and it can be installed in an armor upgrade slot, leaving the wielder’s hands free for other tasks. As the name implies, most users mount the eyelike aperture over one shoulder, but it can work just as easily mounted on the torso or a forearm. Many shoulder laser users are androids who integrate them into their bodies as emergency weapons. Azimuth, corona, aphelion, and perihelion shoulder lasers are available in most areas."),
	("Plasma Pistol, Blue Star", "Small Arms 1-H", 19, 565,000, 22, 40, burn 3d8, 100 charges, 20, "L", "line, unwieldy", "Plasma pistols fire a line of ionized plasma out to a relatively short range. The plasma can continue to burn after contact. "
	("Dragon Pistol, True", "Small Arms 1-H", 19, 489,000, 22, 40, burn 5d6, 20 petrol, 1, "L", "n/a", "A dragon pistol features a wide muzzle that is often shaped like a dragon’s maw. The weapon discharges discrete orbs of flaming petrol that can cling to targets. A wyrmling dragon pistol casts small petrol globules, while drake and wyvern dragon pistols have increased outputs. The true dragon pistol is as devastating as it is rare."),
	("Acid Cannon, Micrergate", "Small Arms 1-H", 3, 1,500, 2, 40, corrode 1d4, 40 charges, 2, "L", "living, swarm", "Despite its name, derived from Swarm conventions and suggesting a heavier armament, the lightweight acid cannon is a derivation of the Swarm corrovox’s arm-mounted weapon modified to be a stand-alone pistol-sized firearm. The weapon uses small amounts of power to produce caustic fluid. The trigger administers a jolt of electricity to the device, causing a reflexive constriction that forces blobs of this acid out of the weapon’s throatlike barrel."),
	("Disintegrator Cannon, Liquidator", "Heavy 2-H", 6, 4,800, 10, 40, corrode 1d6, 40 charges, 4, "3", "line, unwieldy", "This wide-barreled cannon emits a stream of red-tinged energy that originates from the weapon’s heavy proton tank, affecting all enemies in a line. Like most disintegrator weapons, they are available in liquidator, decimator, executioner, and eradicator models."),
	("Dissolver, Macrergate", "Heavy 2-H", 8, 10,000, 9, 40, corrode 2d4, 40 charges, 4, "L", "blast, living, swarm, unwieldy", "Inspired by the horrific spewing capability of its namesake Swarm component, and much like the acid cannon, the dissolver has two biological glands that use power to produce a couple of highly reactive chemicals. These two chemicals are stable when separate. However, as with the corrovox’s weapon, when an electric jolt causes the dissolver to constrict and release these chemicals, they converge just outside the weapon’s maw, creating an acidic flash fire in a broad arc."),
	("Sting Pistol, Yellow Jacket", "Small Arms 1-H", 10, 18,500, 9, 40, corrode 2d6, 20 charges, 4, "L", "living", "Sting pistols are living weapons based on samples of Swarm technology recovered during the last century. The chitinous weapon converts power to internally generate and shoot acidslicked needles that can cause lasting damage to the target. Ant models are sturdy and commonplace, though yellow jacket and wasp sting pistols are more powerful. Hornet models are the heaviest and most potent of these weapons."),
	("Disintegrator Cannon, Decimator", "Heavy 2-H", 11, 29,500, 16, 40, corrode 2d6, 40 charges, 4, "3", "line, unwieldy", "This wide-barreled cannon emits a stream of red-tinged energy that originates from the weapon’s heavy proton tank, affecting all enemies in a line. Like most disintegrator weapons, they are available in liquidator, decimator, executioner, and eradicator models."),
	("Disintegrator Cannon, Executioner", "Heavy 2-H", 16, 220,000, 27, 40, corrode 3d6, 80 charges, 8, "3", "line, unwieldy", "This wide-barreled cannon emits a stream of red-tinged energy that originates from the weapon’s heavy proton tank, affecting all enemies in a line. Like most disintegrator weapons, they are available in liquidator, decimator, executioner, and eradicator models."),
	("Dissolver, Dinergate", "Heavy 2-H", 8, 50,000, 18, 40, corrode 4d4, 40 charges, 5, "L", "blast, living, swarm, unwieldy", "Inspired by the horrific spewing capability of its namesake Swarm component, and much like the acid cannon, the dissolver has two biological glands that use power to produce a couple of highly reactive chemicals. These two chemicals are stable when separate. However, as with the corrovox’s weapon, when an electric jolt causes the dissolver to constrict and release these chemicals, they converge just outside the weapon’s maw, creating an acidic flash fire in a broad arc."),
	("Disintegrator Cannon, Eradicator", "Heavy 2-H", 20, 765,000, 52, 40, corrode 4d6, 80 charges, 8, "3", "line, unwieldy", "This wide-barreled cannon emits a stream of red-tinged energy that originates from the weapon’s heavy proton tank, affecting all enemies in a line. Like most disintegrator weapons, they are available in liquidator, decimator, executioner, and eradicator models."),
	("Dissolver, Ergatoid", "Heavy 2-H", 8, 380,000, 40, 40, corrode 9d4, 40 charges, 5, "L", "blast, living, swarm, unwieldy", "Inspired by the horrific spewing capability of its namesake Swarm component, and much like the acid cannon, the dissolver has two biological glands that use power to produce a couple of highly reactive chemicals. These two chemicals are stable when separate. However, as with the corrovox’s weapon, when an electric jolt causes the dissolver to constrict and release these chemicals, they converge just outside the weapon’s maw, creating an acidic flash fire in a broad arc."),
	("Resonant Pistol, Lattice", "Small Arms 1-H", 7, 6,100, 3, 40, deafen, 40 charges, 2, "L", "boost 1d6", "The crystalline structure inside a resonant pistol comes from the same synthetic material used in the resonant gauntlet. An electrical current can be directed through a long, conical barrel fitted with layers of the crystal, causing the material to reverberate with a devastating ultrasonic frequency. These weapons are noted for their ease of use, since they create no recoil. The only indication that these weapons have fired is a faint, high-pitched beep. Resonant pistols using a crystal lattice are more common and less expensive than those that contain a crystal matrix."),
	("Boomer Rifle, Tremor", "Long Arms 2-H", 2, 520, 4, 40, deafen, 12 shells, 3, "1", "analog", "The long, rippled barrel of a boomer rifle focuses the sound of several shells ignited simultaneously into a wave of sonic energy. These weapons arose on Akiton as a wayward Veskarian battalion beset a series of scrappy outposts. When lighter rifles failed to pierce the advanced vesk armor, residents used sonic weapons to overwhelm their foes. Tremor and rumbler boomer rifles use low and damaging sonic frequencies. Concussive and shock wave versions also produce a jolt that can knock a target prone."),
	("Sonic Pistol, Thunderstrike", "Small Arms 1-H", 4, 2,300, 4, 40, deafen, 20 charges, 2, "L", "n/a", "Sonic pistols have a stocky barrel capped with a concave resonating chamber that amplifies and directs its sonic blast. They use high-intensity sound to shake molecules apart."),
	("Staccato Rifle, Pulse", "Long Arms 2-H", 4, 2,000, 5, 40, deafen, 40 charges, 1, "2", "automatic", "A baffled tube on the underside of a staccato rifle produces and modulates discrete blasts of sonic frequencies. The rifle’s unique construction enables a fully automatic mode, producing a sound like drumming. The frequencies can leave a target’s auditory senses overwhelmed. Pulse staccato rifles have the shortest sonic projector for reliable repetitive shots with less power usage. Surge, drum, and hammer staccato rifles require more charge for a harder hit."),
	("Boomer Rifle, Rumbler", "Long Arms 2-H", 6, 4,100, 7, 40, deafen, 12 shells, 4, "1", "analog", "The long, rippled barrel of a boomer rifle focuses the sound of several shells ignited simultaneously into a wave of sonic energy. These weapons arose on Akiton as a wayward Veskarian battalion beset a series of scrappy outposts. When lighter rifles failed to pierce the advanced vesk armor, residents used sonic weapons to overwhelm their foes. Tremor and rumbler boomer rifles use low and damaging sonic frequencies. Concussive and shock wave versions also produce a jolt that can knock a target prone."),
	("Sonic Pistol, LFD", "Small Arms 1-H", 11, 26,200, 9, 40, deafen, 40 charges, 4, "L", "boost 1d6", "Sonic pistols have a stocky barrel capped with a concave resonating chamber that amplifies and directs its sonic blast. They use high-intensity sound to shake molecules apart."),
	("Sonic Pistol, HFD", "Small Arms 1-H", 14, 71,300, 13, 40, deafen, 60 charges, 6, "L", "n/a", "Sonic pistols have a stocky barrel capped with a concave resonating chamber that amplifies and directs its sonic blast. They use high-intensity sound to shake molecules apart."),
	("Dirge Cannon, Anharmonic", "Heavy 2-H", 13, 49,900, 17, 40, deafen, 80 charges, 4, "3", "antibiological, blast, unwieldy", "Pirates are the most common users of dirge cannons. The potbellied, shoulder-resting weapons cause a brief but intense sound burst at frequencies and pressure sufficient to rupture living cells while leaving inorganic objects unharmed. The result is a weapon that can eliminate a starship’s crew without causing any damage to the vessel or its cargo. Those who prefer lighter damage favor harmonic and resonant cannons, leaving anharmonic and parametric models for situations that call for carnage."),
	("Resonant Pistol, Matrix", "Small Arms 1-H", 18, 358,000, 17, 40, deafen, 40 charges, 2, "L", "boost 2d6", "The crystalline structure inside a resonant pistol comes from the same synthetic material used in the resonant gauntlet. An electrical current can be directed through a long, conical barrel fitted with layers of the crystal, causing the material to reverberate with a devastating ultrasonic frequency. These weapons are noted for their ease of use, since they create no recoil. The only indication that these weapons have fired is a faint, high-pitched beep. Resonant pistols using a crystal lattice are more common and less expensive than those that contain a crystal matrix."),
	("Sonic Pistol, Banshee", "Small Arms 1-H", 16, 191,000, 18, 40, deafen, 80 charges, 8, "L", "boost 1d10", "Sonic pistols have a stocky barrel capped with a concave resonating chamber that amplifies and directs its sonic blast. They use high-intensity sound to shake molecules apart."),
	("Psychic-Wave Cannon, II", "Heavy 2-H", 5, 3,520, 6, 40, demoralize, 20 charges, 4, "2", "blast, living, mind-affecting, unwieldy", "Unlike weapons that rely on physical projectiles or various energy forms to damage a target, a psychic-wave cannon targets a creature’s mind. The cannon contains an organic neural matrix that converts charges into a mental blast, damaging creatures with overwhelming psychic output. The numeral of a psychicwave cannon’s model indicates the strength of its output, but the weapon can’t harm objects and mindless creatures, as well as those immune to mind-affecting effects."),
	("Shout Projector, Damper", "Heavy 2-H", 6, 4,750, 7, 40, demoralize, 20 charges, 2, "2", "explode (10), integrated (2 slots), nonlethal,unwieldy", "Shout projectors amplify your speech to overwhelming or destructive volume, and then project it in a cone. Words and sheer sonic pressure in this cone can’t be ignored. All shout projectors can be installed as armor upgrades (taking one upgrade slot per hand needed to wield the weapon), allowing the projectors to be used hands-free. That way, a user can carry lethal weaponry, safety gear, or protest signage. Exhorter shout projectors can be useful for crowd control with a lighter touch. Damper and pacifier models are ostensibly for nonlethal but more coercive applications, while the riot and crackdown projectors are for heavy-handed use."),
	("Wraith-Sting Rifle, Yellow Jacket", "Sniper 2-H", 1, 375, 0, 40, Injection DC +2, 1 dart, 1, "1", "injection, sniper (250), subtle, unwieldy", "Wraith-sting rifles fire darts that are loaded with an injectable substance. The low velocity and slim profile of these darts mean the target often remains unaware of the initial attack. Once the effects of the injected substance take hold, however, it is usually easy to identify the delivery method. These insidious weapons are said to be a favorite of reptoid assassins, but as with any information on that race, the veracity of this rumor is suspect. Ironically, this weapon’s models are named after stinging insects: yellow jacket, wasp, and hornet."),
	("Needler Pistol, Tactical", "Small Arms 1-H", 1, 175, 2, 40, Injection DC +2, 8 darts, 1, "1", "analog, injection", "A favorite of assassins and battlefield medics alike, the needler pistol uses magnetic fields or pressurized gas to launch darts that inject a substance into the target. This injection gun can be fitted with cartridges containing medicine or poison."),
	("Injector Pistol, Medic", "Small Arms 1-H", 3, 1,290, 3, 40, Injection DC +2, 10 darts, 1, "L", "injection", "Manufacturers worked to the specifications of xenobiologists to design and produce these firearms, which use magnetic fields to accelerate darts loaded with various substances for injection into the target. They do so far less gently than the smaller needler pistol, however, and they have become a popular tool for poisoners, slavers, and others with less scientific intentions. Medic and zoologist injector pistols are often used by xenobiologists studying unintelligent species; poacher, subjugation, and elite injector pistols are generally regarded as illicit since they more often used to target sentient species, though most markets nevertheless carry the weapons."),
	("Radshot, Electromagnetic", "Small Arms 1-H", 6, 4,010, 5, 40, irradiate, 40 charges, 1, "L", "radioactive", "Banned in most civilized regions of the Pact Worlds, radshots are known for the reckless amount of radiation they generate. Despite the objections of the living, radshots’ signature short barrels and bulky containment sheaths can often be seen in the markets of Eox or at the hip of a Corpse Fleet officer. They are named for the type of radiation waves they emit: electromagnetic, neutron, and rapid-decay."),
	("Radshot, Neutron", "Small Arms 1-H", 14, 69,500, 12, 40, irradiate, 80 charges, 2, "L", "radioactive", "Banned in most civilized regions of the Pact Worlds, radshots are known for the reckless amount of radiation they generate. Despite the objections of the living, radshots’ signature short barrels and bulky containment sheaths can often be seen in the markets of Eox or at the hip of a Corpse Fleet officer. They are named for the type of radiation waves they emit: electromagnetic, neutron, and rapid-decay."),
	("Microfusion Rifle, Heavy", "Long Arms 2-H", 18, 410,000, 22, 40, irradiate, 40 charges, 4, "1", "blast, radioactive, unwieldy", "The microfusion rifle is built around a bulbous miniaturized fusion reactor. Plasma is generated and placed under incredible pressure in the reactor before being vented in a sudden blast that sometimes carries dangerous levels of radiation. The sparse shielding on light microfusion rifles often results in the users incurring radiation poisoning, so they tend to be used by undertrained militias that can’t afford (or lack the judgment to use) safer heavy weapons. Medium and heavy microfusion rifles are built with larger reactors, which prove more dangerous to their users and targets alike."),
	("Radshot, Rapid-Decay", "Small Arms 1-H", 20, 767,000, 27, 40, irradiate, 80 charges, 4, "L", "radioactive", "Banned in most civilized regions of the Pact Worlds, radshots are known for the reckless amount of radiation they generate. Despite the objections of the living, radshots’ signature short barrels and bulky containment sheaths can often be seen in the markets of Eox or at the hip of a Corpse Fleet officer. They are named for the type of radiation waves they emit: electromagnetic, neutron, and rapid-decay."),
	("Handcannon, Swagger", "Small Arms 1-H", 6, 4,350, 6, 40, knockdown, 6 shells, 1, "1", "analog, free hands (1), unwieldy", "Handcannons are popular with those who want to impress or intimidate their foes through the sheer presence of their armament without having to invest in the training required to master longarms or heavy weaponry. Its oversized barrel and muzzle are somewhat precariously balanced on a one-handed grip, though most wielders use both hands to make the weapon more manageable in combat situations. The various model names of this weapon0bravado, swagger, bombast, braggadocio, and gasconade0were originally facetious references to the character of those who tend to favor them, though many users embrace the names unironically."),
	("Handcannon, Bombast", "Small Arms 1-H", 9, 13,200, 11, 40, knockdown, 8 shells, 1, "1", "analog, free hands (1), unwieldy", "Handcannons are popular with those who want to impress or intimidate their foes through the sheer presence of their armament without having to invest in the training required to master longarms or heavy weaponry. Its oversized barrel and muzzle are somewhat precariously balanced on a one-handed grip, though most wielders use both hands to make the weapon more manageable in combat situations. The various model names of this weapon0bravado, swagger, bombast, braggadocio, and gasconade0were originally facetious references to the character of those who tend to favor them, though many users embrace the names unironically."),
	("Handcannon, Braggadocio", "Small Arms 1-H", 12, 35,100, 13, 40, knockdown, 9 shells, 1, "1", "analog, free hands (1), unwieldy", "Handcannons are popular with those who want to impress or intimidate their foes through the sheer presence of their armament without having to invest in the training required to master longarms or heavy weaponry. Its oversized barrel and muzzle are somewhat precariously balanced on a one-handed grip, though most wielders use both hands to make the weapon more manageable in combat situations. The various model names of this weapon0bravado, swagger, bombast, braggadocio, and gasconade0were originally facetious references to the character of those who tend to favor them, though many users embrace the names unironically."),
	("Boomer Rifle, Concussive", "Long Arms 2-H", 11, 24,000, 14, 40, knockdown, 15 shells, 5, "1", "analog", "The long, rippled barrel of a boomer rifle focuses the sound of several shells ignited simultaneously into a wave of sonic energy. These weapons arose on Akiton as a wayward Veskarian battalion beset a series of scrappy outposts. When lighter rifles failed to pierce the advanced vesk armor, residents used sonic weapons to overwhelm their foes. Tremor and rumbler boomer rifles use low and damaging sonic frequencies. Concussive and shock wave versions also produce a jolt that can knock a target prone."),
	("Boomer Rifle, Shockwave", "Long Arms 2-H", 17, 230,000, 28, 40, knockdown, 20 shells, 5, "1", "analog", "The long, rippled barrel of a boomer rifle focuses the sound of several shells ignited simultaneously into a wave of sonic energy. These weapons arose on Akiton as a wayward Veskarian battalion beset a series of scrappy outposts. When lighter rifles failed to pierce the advanced vesk armor, residents used sonic weapons to overwhelm their foes. Tremor and rumbler boomer rifles use low and damaging sonic frequencies. Concussive and shock wave versions also produce a jolt that can knock a target prone."),
	("Handcannon, Gasconade", "Small Arms 1-H", 18, 364,000, 36, 40, knockdown, 12 shells, 1, "1", "analog, free hands (1), unwieldy", "Handcannons are popular with those who want to impress or intimidate their foes through the sheer presence of their armament without having to invest in the training required to master longarms or heavy weaponry. Its oversized barrel and muzzle are somewhat precariously balanced on a one-handed grip, though most wielders use both hands to make the weapon more manageable in combat situations. The various model names of this weapon0bravado, swagger, bombast, braggadocio, and gasconade0were originally facetious references to the character of those who tend to favor them, though many users embrace the names unironically."),
	("Cavitation Pistol, Hydrodynamic", "Small Arms 1-H", 14, 75,200, 13, 40, pulse 2d6, 40 charges, 8, "L", "unwieldy", "A series of prongs takes the place of this pistol’s barrel; firing the weapon causes a small sphere of energy to form at their center and launch forward at speed. If the wielder times the shot perfectly, the plasma sphere pulses just as it hits the target, dealing damage to nearby creatures, but most find the feat difficult to replicate consistently. A vapor cavitation pistol creates a very focused sphere, while the inertial cavitation pistol creates one that implodes on impact. Hydrodynamic and thermodynamic cavitation pistols use more complex reactions that carry significantly more destructive power."),
	("Tetrad Rings, Tactical", "Small Arms 1-H", 7, 6,900, 3, 40, push (5), 20 charges, 2, "L", "force", "Tetrad rings deal lighter damage than weapons of a similar class, but the device launches a bolt of force that bypasses many common defenses. The design of tetrad rings is proprietary witchwyrd technology, which makes them expensive and difficult to find. They are manufactured in only three models: tactical, advanced, and elite. All three are elaborate sets of rings covered in delicate carvings, with a wire mesh to house the battery. Advanced and elite models have finer decorations."),
	("Dirge Pistol, Resonant", "Small Arms 1-H", 6, 4,950, 4, 40, sicken, 20 charges, 1, "L", "antibiological", "The oscillating sonic waves discharged from a dirge pistol work like those fired from a dirge cannon. Raiders and hijackers prize these weapons for their effect against living targets, which can leave many valuables unharmed. Harmonic and resonant dirge pistols generate stable oscillations, while the anharmonic, parametric, and radial dirge pistols have concentric generator cylinders to produce dissonant and more harmful output."),
	("Dirge Pistol, Anharmonic", "Small Arms 1-H", 10, 20,500, 7, 40, sicken, 20 charges, 1, "L", "antibiological", "The oscillating sonic waves discharged from a dirge pistol work like those fired from a dirge cannon. Raiders and hijackers prize these weapons for their effect against living targets, which can leave many valuables unharmed. Harmonic and resonant dirge pistols generate stable oscillations, while the anharmonic, parametric, and radial dirge pistols have concentric generator cylinders to produce dissonant and more harmful output."),
	("Subduer, Frost", "Small Arms 1-H", 2, 790, 2, 40, staggered, 20 charges, 1, "L", "nonlethal", "A subduer resembles a hollow rod with internal coolant reserves, and it relies on the user’s forceful movements to spray the coolant forward. Employed primarily by kasathan security forces to prevent suspects from fleeing, subduers coat their targets in a thin layer of expelled coolants that cause temporary painful freezing of the target’s skin that deals little lasting damage. On a lucky shot, the frozen layer also interferes with the target’s ability to function. Frost and rime subduers are often employed by peacekeeping forces, while sleet and glacier subduers typically see use only by pirates or mercenary groups."),
	("Coolant Sprayer, Glacial", "Heavy 2-H", 12, 41,000, 7, 40, staggered, 40 charges, 4, "3", "blast, entangle (2d4 rounds), unwieldy", "Coolant sprayers were designed following the principles of a flamethrower, but with an eye more toward hindrance than sheer damage. Experts can easily identify a coolant sprayer by the bulky insulation surrounding the sprayer’s coolant reservoir. The weapon expels a cone of activated coolant that stiffens and freezes living tissue. While not harmless, the effect is somewhat less deadly than most energy weapons. Hiemal, algid, glacial, and isothermal coolant sprayers all function in similar ways, though their destructive potential varies from one model to another."),
	("Coolant Sprayer, Isothermal", "Heavy 2-H", 17, 290,000, 10, 40, staggered, 40 charges, 4, "3", "blast, entangle (2d4 rounds), unwieldy", "Coolant sprayers were designed following the principles of a flamethrower, but with an eye more toward hindrance than sheer damage. Experts can easily identify a coolant sprayer by the bulky insulation surrounding the sprayer’s coolant reservoir. The weapon expels a cone of activated coolant that stiffens and freezes living tissue. While not harmless, the effect is somewhat less deadly than most energy weapons. Hiemal, algid, glacial, and isothermal coolant sprayers all function in similar ways, though their destructive potential varies from one model to another."),
	("Freeze Ray, Glacial", "Long Arms 2-H", 11, 24,800, 12, 40, staggered, 20 charges, 4, "2", "line, unwieldy", "Across the galaxy, practically every sufficiently advanced civilization has created its own variation of the freeze ray. All freeze rays function in a similar way, emitting a long line of supercooled gas, but individual models reflect their species’ design aesthetics. In the Pact Worlds, the most common models reflect the slim profile of Vercite technology or the bony protrusions of Eoxian design. Hiemal, algid, and glacial freeze rays simply produce an extreme reduction in the temperature along the weapon’s line of effect. Isothermal freeze rays cause a persistent temperature drop, dealing further damage, while hypothermic freeze rays causes multiple temperature reductions in rapid succession for further increased destruction."),
	("Freeze Ray, Isothermal", "Long Arms 2-H", 16, 165,000, 22, 40, staggered, 20 charges, 4, "2", "line, unwieldy", "Across the galaxy, practically every sufficiently advanced civilization has created its own variation of the freeze ray. All freeze rays function in a similar way, emitting a long line of supercooled gas, but individual models reflect their species’ design aesthetics. In the Pact Worlds, the most common models reflect the slim profile of Vercite technology or the bony protrusions of Eoxian design. Hiemal, algid, and glacial freeze rays simply produce an extreme reduction in the temperature along the weapon’s line of effect. Isothermal freeze rays cause a persistent temperature drop, dealing further damage, while hypothermic freeze rays causes multiple temperature reductions in rapid succession for further increased destruction."),
	("Charge Emitter, Surge", "Long Arms 2-H", 18, 435,000, 27, 40, staggered, 80 charges, 5, "1", "integrated (1 slot), stun", "This series of insulating reinforced-glass rings can be installed into armor upgrade slots and focuses an electrical charge into a targeted bolt. The sheer power necessary to project a bolt of electricity means that even an impulse charge emitter is a substantial weapon, and jolt charge emitters and surge charge emitters are significantly more powerful. Their relatively slim profile makes them popular for a number of users, from androids and others who benefit from a racial armor upgrade slot, to starship-repair crews in hostile space who want to keep their hands free for their work without leaving themselves totally undefended."),
	("Sonic Suppressor, Murmur", "Small Arms 1-H", 3, 1,430, 2, 40, stifle, 20 charges, 2, "L", "n/a", "A sonic suppressor noiselessly creates a static energy field that absorbs and amplifies sound, focusing the captured frequencies back upon the target in a damaging burst. Drow, assassins, and other covert killers favor the weapon because no sound escapes this bubble, resulting in a silent attack and, sometimes, a soundless takedown. The suppressor’s sonic cascade can have an anomalously large initial area, which crashes in from a wider radius, absorbing sound from and damaging those nearby while brutally affecting the intended target. Most manufacturers produce four suppressor models, including the murmur, whisper, hush, and repose."),
	("Sonic Suppressor, Whisper", "Small Arms 1-H", 8, 9,700, 5, 40, stifle, 40 charges, 2, "L", "n/a", "A sonic suppressor noiselessly creates a static energy field that absorbs and amplifies sound, focusing the captured frequencies back upon the target in a damaging burst. Drow, assassins, and other covert killers favor the weapon because no sound escapes this bubble, resulting in a silent attack and, sometimes, a soundless takedown. The suppressor’s sonic cascade can have an anomalously large initial area, which crashes in from a wider radius, absorbing sound from and damaging those nearby while brutally affecting the intended target. Most manufacturers produce four suppressor models, including the murmur, whisper, hush, and repose."),
	("Sonic Suppressor, Hush", "Small Arms 1-H", 12, 36,500, 9, 40, stifle, 40 charges, 2, "L", "n/a", "A sonic suppressor noiselessly creates a static energy field that absorbs and amplifies sound, focusing the captured frequencies back upon the target in a damaging burst. Drow, assassins, and other covert killers favor the weapon because no sound escapes this bubble, resulting in a silent attack and, sometimes, a soundless takedown. The suppressor’s sonic cascade can have an anomalously large initial area, which crashes in from a wider radius, absorbing sound from and damaging those nearby while brutally affecting the intended target. Most manufacturers produce four suppressor models, including the murmur, whisper, hush, and repose."),
	("Sonic Suppressor, Repose", "Small Arms 1-H", 17, 257,000, 18, 40, stifle, 40 charges, 2, "L", "n/a", "A sonic suppressor noiselessly creates a static energy field that absorbs and amplifies sound, focusing the captured frequencies back upon the target in a damaging burst. Drow, assassins, and other covert killers favor the weapon because no sound escapes this bubble, resulting in a silent attack and, sometimes, a soundless takedown. The suppressor’s sonic cascade can have an anomalously large initial area, which crashes in from a wider radius, absorbing sound from and damaging those nearby while brutally affecting the intended target. Most manufacturers produce four suppressor models, including the murmur, whisper, hush, and repose."),
	("Plasma Ring, Single-Valve", "Small Arms 1-H", 4, 2,350, 2, 40, wound, 40 charges, 4, "L", "n/a", "Plasma rings are relatively flat, circular weapons with an easily grippable interior, allowing them to be used in a variety of orientations. Plasma cycles through a channel within the ring at high speeds, and a release valve allows a stream of plasma to escape in a directed jet. Single-valve plasma rings produce a small discharge, while dual-valve plasma rings have a synchronized pair of valves to produce a larger discharge. Multichannel plasma rings build plasma in a series of parallel rings that vent into a single release valve for an extremely powerful blast."),
	("Disruption Pistol, Minor", "Small Arms 1-H", 7, 7,500, 7, 40, staggered, 20 charges, 2, "L", "boost 1d6, relic", ""Dimensional disruption weapons were available in various forms and strengths, but those left within the Gate of Twelve Suns are pistols (small arms), rifles (longarms), and a few grenades. A dimensional disruption weapon creates a streamlike gravitational wave function that disrupts subatomic fields in an effect similar to a sonic attack, but it can stagger a target rather than deafen it, as the wave function momentarily disrupts the fabric of space around the target.
	("Disruption Pistol, Major", "Small Arms 1-H", 12, 40,000, 10, 40, staggered, 40 charges, 4, "L", "boost 2d6, relic", ""Dimensional disruption weapons were available in various forms and strengths, but those left within the Gate of Twelve Suns are pistols (small arms), rifles (longarms), and a few grenades. A dimensional disruption weapon creates a streamlike gravitational wave function that disrupts subatomic fields in an effect similar to a sonic attack, but it can stagger a target rather than deafen it, as the wave function momentarily disrupts the fabric of space around the target.
	("Disruption Rifle, Major", "Long Arms 2-H", 14, 80,000, 27, 40, staggered, 40 charges, 5, "2", "boost 2d8, relic", ""Dimensional disruption weapons were available in various forms and strengths, but those left within the Gate of Twelve Suns are pistols (small arms), rifles (longarms), and a few grenades. A dimensional disruption weapon creates a streamlike gravitational wave function that disrupts subatomic fields in an effect similar to a sonic attack, but it can stagger a target rather than deafen it, as the wave function momentarily disrupts the fabric of space around the target.
	("Pulse Grenade, Mk 4", "Grenades 1-H", 17, 82,500, 0, 41, 0, drawn, 0, "L", "explode (14d6 E; 20), entangle 1d4 rounds", "A pulse grenade emits a powerful EMP blast on impact whose damage and effects apply only to constructs with the technological subtype. Constructs reduced to 0 HP by a pulse grenade are not destroyed but simply nonfunctional until restored to 1 or more Hit Points. The EMP wave from a pulse grenade is not intense enough to affect augmentations, weapons, armor, or other technological gear."),
	("Acid Cannon, Macrergate", "Small Arms 1-H", 7, 7,000, 7, 41, corrode 2d4, 40 charges, 4, "L", "living, swarm", "Despite its name, derived from Swarm conventions and suggesting a heavier armament, the lightweight acid cannon is a derivation of the Swarm corrovox’s arm-mounted weapon modified to be a stand-alone pistol-sized firearm. The weapon uses small amounts of power to produce caustic fluid. The trigger administers a jolt of electricity to the device, causing a reflexive constriction that forces blobs of this acid out of the weapon’s throatlike barrel."),
	("Acid Cannon, Dinergate", "Small Arms 1-H", 12, 36,000, 13, 42, corrode 3d4, 40 charges, 4, "L", "living, swarm", "Despite its name, derived from Swarm conventions and suggesting a heavier armament, the lightweight acid cannon is a derivation of the Swarm corrovox’s arm-mounted weapon modified to be a stand-alone pistol-sized firearm. The weapon uses small amounts of power to produce caustic fluid. The trigger administers a jolt of electricity to the device, causing a reflexive constriction that forces blobs of this acid out of the weapon’s throatlike barrel."),
	("Acid Cannon, Ergatoid", "Small Arms 1-H", 17, 256,000, 22, 43, corrode 4d4, 40 charges, 5, "L", "living, swarm", "Despite its name, derived from Swarm conventions and suggesting a heavier armament, the lightweight acid cannon is a derivation of the Swarm corrovox’s arm-mounted weapon modified to be a stand-alone pistol-sized firearm. The weapon uses small amounts of power to produce caustic fluid. The trigger administers a jolt of electricity to the device, causing a reflexive constriction that forces blobs of this acid out of the weapon’s throatlike barrel."),
	("Anacite Ion Cannon, Aurora", "Heavy 2-H", 8, 10,900, 11, 45, staggered, 40 charges, 4, "2", "line, lockdown, unwieldy", "This heavy weapon was designed by Aballonian law-enforcement agencies for capturing criminal constructs without completely destroying them."),
	("Pulsecaster Rifle", "Long Arms 2-H", 1, 100, 3, 50, 0, 40 charges, 2, "1", "nonlethal", "The pulsecaster rifle sends a low-voltage blast at its target and has a longer range than the handheld pulsecaster. The blast can stun the target and deal nonlethal damage. "
	("Multistage Rifle, Dual", "Sniper 2-H", 4, 2,380, 5, 50, 0, 2 mini-rockets, 2, "2", "indirect, sniper (500), unwieldy", "The multistage rifle requires mini-rocket ammunition, which it detonates in multiple stages. The initial firing of the weapon is a subsonic round that’s boosted by one or more subsequent, stronger discharges some distance from the user. This results in two effects that aid in obfuscating the user’s position: the sound of the weapon firing is displaced, and the later stages can cause subtle changes in direction, creating an impact angle that suggests the mini-rocket had been fired from a different angle. Dual and dual-plus multistage rifles use a two-stage firing process, while triple and triple-plus multistage rifles employ a three-stage process for added range. The quad multistage rifle is the only weapon on the market with an unrivaled four-stage firing process for maximum damage."),
	("Multistage Rifle, Dual-Plus", "Sniper 2-H", 7, 7,500, 9, 50, 0, 2 mini-rockets, 2, "2", "indirect, sniper (500), unwieldy", "The multistage rifle requires mini-rocket ammunition, which it detonates in multiple stages. The initial firing of the weapon is a subsonic round that’s boosted by one or more subsequent, stronger discharges some distance from the user. This results in two effects that aid in obfuscating the user’s position: the sound of the weapon firing is displaced, and the later stages can cause subtle changes in direction, creating an impact angle that suggests the mini-rocket had been fired from a different angle. Dual and dual-plus multistage rifles use a two-stage firing process, while triple and triple-plus multistage rifles employ a three-stage process for added range. The quad multistage rifle is the only weapon on the market with an unrivaled four-stage firing process for maximum damage."),
	("Arc Pistol, Static", "Small Arms 1-H", 2, 750, 3, 50, arc 2, 20 charges, 2, "L", "stun", "Arc pistols fire deadly, stunning blasts of electricity at ranged targets. They have a two-pronged emitter that directs the electrical blast and a bulky chamber that holds the capacitor. "
	("Arc Pistol, Aurora", "Small Arms 1-H", 13, 45,700, 10, 50, arc 2d6, 40 charges, 2, "L", "stun", "Arc pistols fire deadly, stunning blasts of electricity at ranged targets. They have a two-pronged emitter that directs the electrical blast and a bulky chamber that holds the capacitor. "
	("Arc Pistol, Storm", "Small Arms 1-H", 18, 365,500, 19, 50, arc 4d6, 100 charges, 10, "L", "stun", "Arc pistols fire deadly, stunning blasts of electricity at ranged targets. They have a two-pronged emitter that directs the electrical blast and a bulky chamber that holds the capacitor. "
	("Burner, Hellhound-Class", "Heavy 2-H", 11, 23,800, 16, 50, burn 3d6, 40 petrol, 4, "2", "line, unwieldy", "Indistinguishable from a flamethrower to the lay observer, a burner uses petrol as fuel to produce a strong jet of flame. However, the subtly narrower nozzle and recoil-suppressing gyros allow a burner to fire streams of petrol with more control and focus than its traditional cousin. Ifrit-, salamander-, hellhound-, firedrake-, and phoenix-class burners are all widely available."),
	("Acid Lancer, Liquefier-Class", "Heavy 2-H", 14, 75,000, 20, 50, corrode 4d4, 40 caustrol, 8, "2", "analog, boost 1d8, line, unwieldy", "In addition to collecting the valuable composites the creature leaves behind, some entrepreneurs enter surnochs’ territory to hunt and kill them for their acid-producing glands and spines. These components can be made into heavy weapons known as acid lancers, which shoot jets of caustic fluid. A wielder of an acid lancer can squeeze the gland located near the trigger to give her next shot an extra boost of damaging acid. Acid lancers use a special synthetic acid called caustrol for ammunition, which has the same price and comes in the same size containers as petrol."),
	("Acid Lancer, Disintegrator-Class", "Heavy 2-H", 19, 550,000, 36, 50, corrode 6d4, 40 caustrol, 10, "2", "analog, boost 1d10, line, unwieldy", "In addition to collecting the valuable composites the creature leaves behind, some entrepreneurs enter surnochs’ territory to hunt and kill them for their acid-producing glands and spines. These components can be made into heavy weapons known as acid lancers, which shoot jets of caustic fluid. A wielder of an acid lancer can squeeze the gland located near the trigger to give her next shot an extra boost of damaging acid. Acid lancers use a special synthetic acid called caustrol for ammunition, which has the same price and comes in the same size containers as petrol."),
	("Sonic Rifle, Thunderstrike", "Long Arms 2-H", 5, 3,400, 5, 50, deafen, 40 charges, 2, "1", "n/a", "A sonic rifle fires a blast that is loud enough to deafen targets in addition to damaging them. Sonic rifles have snub-nosed barrels and typically incorporate U-shaped prongs to improve beam stability."),
	("Sonic Rifle, LFD", "Long Arms 2-H", 10, 17,000, 11, 50, deafen, 40 charges, 2, "2", "n/a", "A sonic rifle fires a blast that is loud enough to deafen targets in addition to damaging them. Sonic rifles have snub-nosed barrels and typically incorporate U-shaped prongs to improve beam stability."),
	("Sonic Rifle, HFD", "Long Arms 2-H", 14, 80,200, 22, 50, deafen, 80 charges, 4, "2", "n/a", "A sonic rifle fires a blast that is loud enough to deafen targets in addition to damaging them. Sonic rifles have snub-nosed barrels and typically incorporate U-shaped prongs to improve beam stability."),
	("Dirge Cannon, Parametric", "Heavy 2-H", 16, 172,000, 24, 50, deafen, 80 charges, 4, "3", "antibiological, blast, unwieldy", "Pirates are the most common users of dirge cannons. The potbellied, shoulder-resting weapons cause a brief but intense sound burst at frequencies and pressure sufficient to rupture living cells while leaving inorganic objects unharmed. The result is a weapon that can eliminate a starship’s crew without causing any damage to the vessel or its cargo. Those who prefer lighter damage favor harmonic and resonant cannons, leaving anharmonic and parametric models for situations that call for carnage."),
	("Sonic Rifle, Banshee", "Long Arms 2-H", 18, 364,500, 33, 50, deafen, 100 charges, 5, "2", "n/a", "A sonic rifle fires a blast that is loud enough to deafen targets in addition to damaging them. Sonic rifles have snub-nosed barrels and typically incorporate U-shaped prongs to improve beam stability."),
	("Psychic-Wave Cannon, III", "Heavy 2-H", 11, 28,200, 13, 50, demoralize, 20 charges, 4, "2", "blast, living, mind-affecting, unwieldy", "Unlike weapons that rely on physical projectiles or various energy forms to damage a target, a psychic-wave cannon targets a creature’s mind. The cannon contains an organic neural matrix that converts charges into a mental blast, damaging creatures with overwhelming psychic output. The numeral of a psychicwave cannon’s model indicates the strength of its output, but the weapon can’t harm objects and mindless creatures, as well as those immune to mind-affecting effects."),
	("Psychic-Wave Cannon, IV", "Heavy 2-H", 16, 198,000, 26, 50, demoralize, 20 charges, 4, "2", "blast, living, mind-affecting, unwieldy", "Unlike weapons that rely on physical projectiles or various energy forms to damage a target, a psychic-wave cannon targets a creature’s mind. The cannon contains an organic neural matrix that converts charges into a mental blast, damaging creatures with overwhelming psychic output. The numeral of a psychicwave cannon’s model indicates the strength of its output, but the weapon can’t harm objects and mindless creatures, as well as those immune to mind-affecting effects."),
	("Radcannon, Neutron", "Heavy 2-H", 10, 18,700, 10, 50, irradiate, 40 charges, 2, "2", "blast, radioactive, unwieldy", "Radcannons are large, dangerous-to-wield weapons typically employed by desperate, reckless, or unliving users. A radcannon’s high-voltage capacitors channel energy through a magnetron and transformer to generate massive blasts of radioactive waves, burning targets and typically exposing the target0and potentially the user0to dangerous levels of radiation. Devourer cultists often employ electromagnetic radcannons, neutron radcannons, and even rapid-decay radcannons, unfazed by the weapons’ danger."),
	("Streetsweeper, Thunderstrike", "Long Arms 2-H", 7, 7,150, 5, 50, knockdown, 40 charges, 5, "2", "boost 1d6", "Streetsweepers are sonic weapons designed to deliver a low-intensity “punch” of sound. A streetsweeper can be overcharged to deliver a significant sonic blast that can knock down its target."),
	("Streetsweeper, LFD", "Long Arms 2-H", 12, 39,300, 16, 50, knockdown, 40 charges, 5, "2", "boost 1d8", "Streetsweepers are sonic weapons designed to deliver a low-intensity “punch” of sound. A streetsweeper can be overcharged to deliver a significant sonic blast that can knock down its target."),
	("Streetsweeper, HFD", "Long Arms 2-H", 16, 195,000, 27, 50, knockdown, 40 charges, 4, "2", "boost 1d10", "Streetsweepers are sonic weapons designed to deliver a low-intensity “punch” of sound. A streetsweeper can be overcharged to deliver a significant sonic blast that can knock down its target."),
	("Numbing Beam, Tactical", "Long Arms 2-H", 1, 370, 3, 50, staggered, 20 charges, 1, "1", "nonlethal", "Complex algorithms, controls, and safeguards within a numbing beam ensure the weapon never lowers its target’s temperature to lethal levels. Tactical and advanced numbing beams see use in populated areas, while elite and paragon numbing beams are more often employed in military endeavors. Those models intended for use near civilians include prominent external computer interfaces, as though to advertise their safety features, while military models tend toward a sleek, traditional design."),
	("Numbing Beam, Advanced", "Long Arms 2-H", 5, 3,050, 4, 50, staggered, 20 charges, 1, "1", "nonlethal", "Complex algorithms, controls, and safeguards within a numbing beam ensure the weapon never lowers its target’s temperature to lethal levels. Tactical and advanced numbing beams see use in populated areas, while elite and paragon numbing beams are more often employed in military endeavors. Those models intended for use near civilians include prominent external computer interfaces, as though to advertise their safety features, while military models tend toward a sleek, traditional design."),
	("Freeze Ray, Hypothermic", "Long Arms 2-H", 20, 818,000, 32, 50, staggered, 20 charges, 4, "2", "line, unwieldy", "Across the galaxy, practically every sufficiently advanced civilization has created its own variation of the freeze ray. All freeze rays function in a similar way, emitting a long line of supercooled gas, but individual models reflect their species’ design aesthetics. In the Pact Worlds, the most common models reflect the slim profile of Vercite technology or the bony protrusions of Eoxian design. Hiemal, algid, and glacial freeze rays simply produce an extreme reduction in the temperature along the weapon’s line of effect. Isothermal freeze rays cause a persistent temperature drop, dealing further damage, while hypothermic freeze rays causes multiple temperature reductions in rapid succession for further increased destruction."),
	("Plasma Ring, Dual-Valve", "Small Arms 1-H", 11, 27,000, 9, 50, wound, 40 charges, 4, "L", "n/a", "Plasma rings are relatively flat, circular weapons with an easily grippable interior, allowing them to be used in a variety of orientations. Plasma cycles through a channel within the ring at high speeds, and a release valve allows a stream of plasma to escape in a directed jet. Single-valve plasma rings produce a small discharge, while dual-valve plasma rings have a synchronized pair of valves to produce a larger discharge. Multichannel plasma rings build plasma in a series of parallel rings that vent into a single release valve for an extremely powerful blast."),
	("Disruption Rifle, Minor", "Long Arms 2-H", 9, 15,000, 13, 50, staggered, 40 charges, 5, "2", "boost 1d8, relic", ""Dimensional disruption weapons were available in various forms and strengths, but those left within the Gate of Twelve Suns are pistols (small arms), rifles (longarms), and a few grenades. A dimensional disruption weapon creates a streamlike gravitational wave function that disrupts subatomic fields in an effect similar to a sonic attack, but it can stagger a target rather than deafen it, as the wave function momentarily disrupts the fabric of space around the target.
	(The radius of a disruption grenade’s explosion is reduced to 10 feet if it used on any plane other than the Material Plane. If used in the Drift, those caught in the blast radius can roll their saving throws twice and take the better result when attempting to halve the amount of damage taken or negate any secondary effects."),"
	("Compliance Ray, Flare", "Small Arms 1-H", 7, 6,400, 5, 6, blind, 25 charges, 1, "L", "nonlethal", "With a wider beam than typical lasers, the compliance ray is designed for crowd control and other nonmilitary uses. Although these rays are legal for civilians to own, most models are themed to fit in with the local constabulary’s armor; the Stewards’ blue-and-gold models are common throughout the Pact Worlds. Shots from these pistols cause intense discomfort, and a hit to the eyes can cause temporary blindness. Models begin with the flash designation and increase in intensity as follows: flare, strobe, starburst, and sunspot."),
	("Dragon Rifle, Wyrmling", "Long Arms 2-H", 5, 3,020, 4, 6, burn 1d4, 20 petrol, 1, "1", "automatic", "A larger and more powerful version of a dragon pistol, a dragon rifle also commonly bears draconic motifs or iconography in its aesthetic design. The globules of petrol from a dragon rifle are slightly larger than those from a pistol, and the weapon can be set to launch a series of shots in quick succession. Wyrmling, drake, and wyvern dragon rifles are available, along with the powerful and rare true dragon rifle."),
	("Frailty Pistol, Rasp-Class", "Small Arms 1-H", 4, 2,420, 2, 60, 0, 10 charges, 1, "L", "necrotic", "A rib cage of ossified injectors covers the casing of these pistols, corrupting the internal coolant supply with negative energy. These pistols deliver chilling blasts of concentrated entropy at close range."),
	("Autotarget Rifle", "Long Arms 2-H", 2, 755, 3, 60, 0, 10 rounds, 1, "2", "analog, automatic", "An automatic model of the basic rifle, autotarget rifles fire continuously for as long as the trigger is depressed and fresh rounds are available in the magazine. "
	("Bow", "Special 2-H", 1, 255, 3, 60, 0, drawn, 1, "1", "quick reload", "Modern compound bows are made of aluminum alloys, for superior lightness and durability. The string is made of highperformance polyethylene. Bows fire arrows as ammunition, and they can also be used with grenade arrows for more customized damage and effects."),
	("Coil Rifle, Precision", "Sniper 2-H", 1, 390, 3, 60, 0, 4 rounds, 1, "2", "sniper (250.)", "A coil rifle is a long, slender firearm surrounded by a coil that generates carefully aligned magnetic fields that accelerate a single round with impressive power and accuracy. Precision coil rifles are the most affordable of these weapons, while specialist coil rifles have greater range and efficacy. Rangefinder, saboteur, and assassin coil rifles are especially deadly weapons that are appreciated by true connoisseurs, veteran mercenaries, and experienced firearm specialists."),
	("Frailty Rifle, Atrophy-Class", "Long Arms 2-H", 3, 1,650, 3, 60, 0, 20 charges, 2, "1", "necrotic", "Standard issue to many soldiers of the Corpse Fleet, the frailty series of rifles is designed to affect only living enemies. The weapons’ most common application is Corpse Fleet agents firing at enemies engaged by mindless undead, with incidents of friendly fire rewarding allies who are hit with boosts of negative energy."),
	("Scorchgun, Microwave", "Small Arms 1-H", 4, 2,050, 3, 60, 0, 20 charges, 1, "L", "stun", "Common in areas where petrol’s flammability is a liability, such as in the protected jungles of Castrovel, scorchguns employ a microwave emitter to burn targets. The emitter is generally a squat cylinder positioned above the pistol’s trigger, and its adjustable output allows a wielder to deal either lethal or nonlethal damage. The original design, the microwave scorchgun, is the most widely used, and later designs focus on a specific bandwidth, with S-band, C-band, K-band, and X-band scorchguns achieving progressively more power and precision."),
	("Ice Carbine, Subzero", "Long Arms 2-H", 2, 510, 4, 60, 0, 20 charges, 2, "2", "automatic", "Rather than relying on coolant to produce supercooled gas, an ice carbine pumps heat out of large vents integrated in the weapon’s stock and uses the temperature change to produce brittle, razor-sharp shards of ice in the chamber. This design allows it to either fire a short, targeted shot or spray a hailstorm of piercing needles at a group of foes. The heat-exchange technology used in these weapons is common on Verces, where it’s used for many purposes, making it relatively easy to find them in the Pact Worlds, from the subzero models (often built in illicit basement labs) to absolute-zero ice carbines, which are the best in the Pact Worlds. Gelid and ultracold ice carbines improve on the subzero version’s technology and overall power."),
	("Plasma Guide, Series-21", "Sniper 2-H", 2, 1,070, 4, 60, 0, 20 charges, 5, "2", "guided, sniper (250), unwieldy", "A plasma guide maintains a magnetic guidance system around its plasma discharge, which continues guiding the shot after it is fired. This increases accuracy at ranges far beyond those of typical plasma weapons and bypasses the advantage of partial cover as the magnetic guidance directs the plasma toward its target. Vesk snipers are believed to be the earliest users of the plasma guide during the Silent War, but it’s become a standard in many military and mercenary arsenals since then. This weapon has been continually refined since its invention; series-21, series-28, series-37, series-42, series-62, and series-73 plasma guides have proven generally stable and thus remain in production."),
	("Polarity Rifle, Static", "Long Arms 2-H", 4, 2,400, 4, 60, 0, 40 charges, 2, "1", "polarize 1d4", "The polarity rifle was designed by Vercite engineers using the conceptual model that underpins polarity gauntlets. This rifle’s prongs are separately polarized, and it alternates between them as it fires to create a circuit of lightning between the gun and target, causing subsequent attacks to deal additional damage. Static, aurora, storm, and tempest polarity rifles are favored by sharpshooters in many fields, though they are often scorned by kasathas who view them as a vulgarized appropriation of an honorable weapon."),
	("Rail Gun, Tactical", "Long Arms 2-H", 3, 1,150, 4, 60, 0, 12 rounds, 1, "1", "automatic", "Similar in design to the magnetar rifle, a rail gun uses magnetic fields to accelerate its rounds to lethal speeds. While magnetar rifles are more powerful, they’re also larger and heavier, leaving many to favor the smaller and lighter rail gun. The weapons’ affordability makes them a popular choice for members of the Starfinder Society and other exploratory groups. Rail guns come in tactical and advanced models, with the advanced rail gun being slightly larger."),
	("Assassin Rifle, Stalker", "Sniper 2-H", 3, 1,510, 5, 60, 0, 1 round, 1, "1", "breakdown, sniper (250), unwieldy", "When assembled, an assassin rifle looks similar to a typical sniper rifle. Its modular construction, however, allows it to be broken down into small component parts that can be hidden on the user’s person0or even smuggled in a ysoki’s cheek pouches0making the weapon difficult to detect or identify. Assassin rifles are available in stalker, shadow, phantom, spectre, and wraith models."),
	("Blindmark Rifle, Thunderstrike", "Long Arms 2-H", 3, 1,400, 5, 60, 0, 20 charges, 2, "1", "echo, stun", "Blindmark rifles generate sonic frequencies through carefully aligned resonance in multiple magnetic cylinders positioned between the stock and the short muzzle of the weapon. When the rifle’s shot hits a target, that target retains the resonance as a faint or subsonic tone useful for creatures that have blindsense (sound or vibration) or blindsight (sound or vibration). Multiple targets struck by the same blindmark rifle emit identical tones that can be distinguished only by location. Blindmark rifles are manufactured in thunderstrike, LFD (low-frequency device), HFD (high-frequency device), and banshee models."),
	("Excavation Laser, Light", "Long Arms 2-H", 4, 2,050, 5, 60, 0, 40 charges, 2, "2", "penetrating, professional (mining)", "This sturdy, snub-nosed laser rifle resembles a starship’s mining laser in miniature. It fires a powerful beam that loses intensity after a relatively short distance, which makes it not only useful in many mining and quarrying endeavors but also effective in medium-range combat for those trained in its use. Most technologically advanced civilizations develop excavation lasers, and the tools are commonly seen in the hands of workers from the Ulrikka Clanholdings and other miners in the Diaspora. Light, medium, and heavy excavation lasers all see extensive use."),
	("Frailty Pistol, Wail-Class", "Small Arms 1-H", 9, 15,400, 5, 60, 0, 20 charges, 2, "L", "necrotic", "A rib cage of ossified injectors covers the casing of these pistols, corrupting the internal coolant supply with negative energy. These pistols deliver chilling blasts of concentrated entropy at close range."),
	("Infinity Rifle, Advanced", "Long Arms 2-H", 7, 6,100, 5, 60, 0, 20 charges, 1, "1", "boost 2d4", "Infinity rifles take their name from their shape, two conjoined rings similar to an infinity symbol with twin muzzles along the outer edge of one ring. The two rings contain a twisted loop of fiber-optic cabling that channels the laser beam; adding more energy to the loop results in a more powerful blast. These weapons were first introduced to the Pact Worlds by skittermanders (Starfinder Alien Archive 106), though their current nomenclature (tactical, advanced, elite, and paragon) was imposed by other weapons manufacturers."),
	("Machine Gun, Squad", "Heavy 2-H", 4, 2,060, 5, 60, 0, 40 rounds, 2, "2", "analog, automatic", "The most basic and portable machine guns are known as squad guns for their popularity among mercenary groups. Light, medium, and heavy machine guns remain reliable heavy weapons for their automatic fire and damage capability."),
	("Rail Gun, Advanced", "Long Arms 2-H", 6, 3,770, 5, 60, 0, 15 rounds, 1, "1", "automatic", "Similar in design to the magnetar rifle, a rail gun uses magnetic fields to accelerate its rounds to lethal speeds. While magnetar rifles are more powerful, they’re also larger and heavier, leaving many to favor the smaller and lighter rail gun. The weapons’ affordability makes them a popular choice for members of the Starfinder Society and other exploratory groups. Rail guns come in tactical and advanced models, with the advanced rail gun being slightly larger."),
	("Scorchgun, S-Band", "Small Arms 1-H", 8, 9,350, 5, 60, 0, 20 charges, 1, "L", "stun", "Common in areas where petrol’s flammability is a liability, such as in the protected jungles of Castrovel, scorchguns employ a microwave emitter to burn targets. The emitter is generally a squat cylinder positioned above the pistol’s trigger, and its adjustable output allows a wielder to deal either lethal or nonlethal damage. The original design, the microwave scorchgun, is the most widely used, and later designs focus on a specific bandwidth, with S-band, C-band, K-band, and X-band scorchguns achieving progressively more power and precision."),
	("Aeon Guard, Accelerator Rifle", "Long Arms 2-H", 7, 7,500, 7, 60, 0, 16 rounds, 1, "2", "automatic", "The AG series of longarms is manufactured by government-held factories for the sole use of the Aeon Guard. Its ingenious designers are held via lifelong “contracts” as pampered but neurally locked prisoners of the throne. The AG assault rifle is a selective-fire rifle that is standard issue for rank-and-file troops. Other weapons in the series include the AG accelerator rifle, which uses magnetic fields to propel metal projectiles like a magnetar rifle does, and the rocket propelled–projectile rifle (RPPR, or “Ripper,” as it’s known in the ranks of the Aeon Guard), which fires mini-rockets like those used in gyrojet rifles. Pact Worlds intelligence believes that some AG weapons can also be equipped with aeon stones, though what functions they provide and how this hybrid technology actually works is unknown. In the Azlanti Star Empire, civilian possession of any AG-series weapon is a criminal offense punishable by death."),
	("Assassin Rifle, Shadow", "Sniper 2-H", 6, 4,550, 7, 60, 0, 1 round, 1, "1", "breakdown, sniper (500), unwieldy", "When assembled, an assassin rifle looks similar to a typical sniper rifle. Its modular construction, however, allows it to be broken down into small component parts that can be hidden on the user’s person0or even smuggled in a ysoki’s cheek pouches0making the weapon difficult to detect or identify. Assassin rifles are available in stalker, shadow, phantom, spectre, and wraith models."),
	("Frailty Rifle, Rot-Class", "Long Arms 2-H", 7, 7,700, 7, 60, 0, 20 charges, 2, "2", "necrotic", "Standard issue to many soldiers of the Corpse Fleet, the frailty series of rifles is designed to affect only living enemies. The weapons’ most common application is Corpse Fleet agents firing at enemies engaged by mindless undead, with incidents of friendly fire rewarding allies who are hit with boosts of negative energy."),
	("Semi-Auto Pistol, Advanced", "Small Arms 1-H", 7, 5,500, 7, 60, 0, 12 rounds, 1, "L", "analog", "The semiautomatic mechanism of this pistol discharges spent cartridges and reloads fresh ones in the barrel, provided a cartridge remains in the magazine. "
	("Storm Coil, Jolt", "Long Arms 2-H", 7, 6,900, 7, 60, 0, 40 charges, 8, "2", "line, unwieldy", "A storm coil employs an air-core resonant transformer to produce high-voltage electrical output. The resulting bolt of electricity arcs out from the weapon in a line. Though it employs technology similar to the colossus coil, the storm coil was developed independently within the Pact Worlds. Live storm coils and jolt storm coils generate impressive bolts, while the larger impulse and surge storm coils have even farther reach."),
	("Magnetar Rifle, Tactical", "Long Arms 2-H", 9, 11,800, 9, 60, 0, 18 rounds, 1, "2", "analog, automatic", "The magnetar rifle uses magnetic fields to accelerate metallic rounds to high speeds. With few moving parts that can break down, it’s a workhorse automatic rifle popular among planetary explorers. "
	("Assassin Rifle, Phantom", "Sniper 2-H", 9, 14,900, 10, 60, 0, 1 round, 1, "1", "breakdown, sniper (600), unwieldy", "When assembled, an assassin rifle looks similar to a typical sniper rifle. Its modular construction, however, allows it to be broken down into small component parts that can be hidden on the user’s person0or even smuggled in a ysoki’s cheek pouches0making the weapon difficult to detect or identify. Assassin rifles are available in stalker, shadow, phantom, spectre, and wraith models."),
	("Frailty Cannon, Murder-Class", "Heavy 2-H", 10, 20,900, 10, 60, 0, 40 charges, 4, "2", "line, necrotic", "The frailty cannon line produces a jet of necromantically fueled coolant. More easily controlled than their zero cannon counterparts, these weapons are used to bring down enemies as much as they’re used to invigorate nearby undead."),
	("Frailty Pistol, Scream-Class", "Small Arms 1-H", 14, 85,800, 10, 60, 0, 20 charges, 2, "L", "necrotic", "A rib cage of ossified injectors covers the casing of these pistols, corrupting the internal coolant supply with negative energy. These pistols deliver chilling blasts of concentrated entropy at close range."),
	("Semi-Auto Pistol, Elite", "Small Arms 1-H", 10, 18,200, 10, 60, 0, 12 rounds, 1, "L", "analog", "The semiautomatic mechanism of this pistol discharges spent cartridges and reloads fresh ones in the barrel, provided a cartridge remains in the magazine. "
	("Machine Gun, Light", "Heavy 2-H", 8, 8,600, 11, 60, 0, 60 rounds, 2, "2", "analog, automatic", "The most basic and portable machine guns are known as squad guns for their popularity among mercenary groups. Light, medium, and heavy machine guns remain reliable heavy weapons for their automatic fire and damage capability. "
	("Scorchgun, C-Band", "Small Arms 1-H", 13, 49,100, 11, 60, 0, 20 charges, 1, "L", "stun", "Common in areas where petrol’s flammability is a liability, such as in the protected jungles of Castrovel, scorchguns employ a microwave emitter to burn targets. The emitter is generally a squat cylinder positioned above the pistol’s trigger, and its adjustable output allows a wielder to deal either lethal or nonlethal damage. The original design, the microwave scorchgun, is the most widely used, and later designs focus on a specific bandwidth, with S-band, C-band, K-band, and X-band scorchguns achieving progressively more power and precision."),
	("Wave Modulator, V", "Small Arms 1-H", 14, 81,000, 11, 60, 0, 20 charges, 4, "L", "modal (sonic)", "The frequency of a wave modulator’s output can be adjusted to either burn a target or bombard it with damaging sonic bursts. Shirrens favor these boxy pistols because of the thrill of choosing the damage type of every shot fired. Wave modulators come in numbered models."),
	("Cathode Cannon, Advanced", "Heavy 2-H", 8, 9,300, 13, 60, 0, 40 charges, 4, "2", "unwieldy, wide line", "Cathode cannons were originally designed by members of the Android Abolitionist Front, and many varieties made by different races nonetheless are decorated with circuit designs reminiscent of the weapons’ android inventors. The tactical cathode cannon is a standard-issue weapon for members of the Front, while advanced, elite, paragon, and shockstorm cathode cannons are often used by mercenaries and assault forces with a variety of goals."),
	("Ice Carbine, Gelid", "Long Arms 2-H", 9, 12,400, 13, 60, 0, 40 charges, 2, "2", "automatic", "Rather than relying on coolant to produce supercooled gas, an ice carbine pumps heat out of large vents integrated in the weapon’s stock and uses the temperature change to produce brittle, razor-sharp shards of ice in the chamber. This design allows it to either fire a short, targeted shot or spray a hailstorm of piercing needles at a group of foes. The heat-exchange technology used in these weapons is common on Verces, where it’s used for many purposes, making it relatively easy to find them in the Pact Worlds, from the subzero models (often built in illicit basement labs) to absolute-zero ice carbines, which are the best in the Pact Worlds. Gelid and ultracold ice carbines improve on the subzero version’s technology and overall power."),
	("Multistage Rifle, Triple", "Sniper 2-H", 11, 27,900, 13, 60, 0, 3 mini-rockets, 3, "2", "indirect, sniper (750), unwieldy", "The multistage rifle requires mini-rocket ammunition, which it detonates in multiple stages. The initial firing of the weapon is a subsonic round that’s boosted by one or more subsequent, stronger discharges some distance from the user. This results in two effects that aid in obfuscating the user’s position: the sound of the weapon firing is displaced, and the later stages can cause subtle changes in direction, creating an impact angle that suggests the mini-rocket had been fired from a different angle. Dual and dual-plus multistage rifles use a two-stage firing process, while triple and triple-plus multistage rifles employ a three-stage process for added range. The quad multistage rifle is the only weapon on the market with an unrivaled four-stage firing process for maximum damage."),
	("Frailty Rifle, Blight-Class", "Long Arms 2-H", 13, 57,200, 14, 60, 0, 40 charges, 4, "2", "necrotic", "Standard issue to many soldiers of the Corpse Fleet, the frailty series of rifles is designed to affect only living enemies. The weapons’ most common application is Corpse Fleet agents firing at enemies engaged by mindless undead, with incidents of friendly fire rewarding allies who are hit with boosts of negative energy."),
	("Semi-Auto Pistol, Paragon", "Small Arms 1-H", 13, 45,200, 14, 60, 0, 16 rounds, 1, "L", "analog", "The semiautomatic mechanism of this pistol discharges spent cartridges and reloads fresh ones in the barrel, provided a cartridge remains in the magazine. "
	("Frailty Pistol, Deathcry-Class", "Small Arms 1-H", 18, 440,000, 15, 60, 0, 40 charges, 4, "L", "necrotic", "A rib cage of ossified injectors covers the casing of these pistols, corrupting the internal coolant supply with negative energy. These pistols deliver chilling blasts of concentrated entropy at close range."),
	("Excavation Laser, Medium", "Long Arms 2-H", 12, 36,000, 16, 60, 0, 40 charges, 2, "2", "penetrating, professional (mining)", "This sturdy, snub-nosed laser rifle resembles a starship’s mining laser in miniature. It fires a powerful beam that loses intensity after a relatively short distance, which makes it not only useful in many mining and quarrying endeavors but also effective in medium-range combat for those trained in its use. Most technologically advanced civilizations develop excavation lasers, and the tools are commonly seen in the hands of workers from the Ulrikka Clanholdings and other miners in the Diaspora. Light, medium, and heavy excavation lasers all see extensive use."),
	("Machine Gun, Medium", "Heavy 2-H", 11, 23,100, 16, 60, 0, 60 rounds, 2, "2", "analog, automatic", "The most basic and portable machine guns are known as squad guns for their popularity among mercenary groups. Light, medium, and heavy machine guns remain reliable heavy weapons for their automatic fire and damage capability. "
	("Scorchgun, K-Band", "Small Arms 1-H", 16, 165,000, 16, 60, 0, 20 charges, 1, "L", "stun", "Common in areas where petrol’s flammability is a liability, such as in the protected jungles of Castrovel, scorchguns employ a microwave emitter to burn targets. The emitter is generally a squat cylinder positioned above the pistol’s trigger, and its adjustable output allows a wielder to deal either lethal or nonlethal damage. The original design, the microwave scorchgun, is the most widely used, and later designs focus on a specific bandwidth, with S-band, C-band, K-band, and X-band scorchguns achieving progressively more power and precision."),
	("Scorchgun, X-Band", "Small Arms 1-H", 18, 368,000, 16, 60, 0, 20 charges, 1, "L", "stun", "Common in areas where petrol’s flammability is a liability, such as in the protected jungles of Castrovel, scorchguns employ a microwave emitter to burn targets. The emitter is generally a squat cylinder positioned above the pistol’s trigger, and its adjustable output allows a wielder to deal either lethal or nonlethal damage. The original design, the microwave scorchgun, is the most widely used, and later designs focus on a specific bandwidth, with S-band, C-band, K-band, and X-band scorchguns achieving progressively more power and precision."),
	("Wave Modulator, VI", "Small Arms 1-H", 16, 195,000, 16, 60, 0, 40 charges, 4, "L", "modal (sonic)", "The frequency of a wave modulator’s output can be adjusted to either burn a target or bombard it with damaging sonic bursts. Shirrens favor these boxy pistols because of the thrill of choosing the damage type of every shot fired. Wave modulators come in numbered models."),
	("Magnetar Rifle, Advanced", "Long Arms 2-H", 13, 53,700, 18, 60, 0, 24 rounds, 1, "2", "analog, automatic", "The magnetar rifle uses magnetic fields to accelerate metallic rounds to high speeds. With few moving parts that can break down, it’s a workhorse automatic rifle popular among planetary explorers. "
	("Stormcaller, Rocket", "Heavy 2-H", 13, 57,000, 18, 60, 0, 40 charges, 5, "2", "flexible line, living, unwieldy", "Some barathu researchers who intensively study the titanic lightning storms found on their home world become obsessed with the phenomenon. The efforts of such scientists led to the creation of the stormcaller, a living weapon that generates a line of electricity originating not from the wielder but from a single point within the weapon’s relatively short range. Like most barathu creations, stormcallers are living creatures, and their massive shells are large enough to require two hands to wield, aided by the stormcaller wrapping its translucent tentacles around the user’s appendages. Sheet and ribbon stormcallers are powerful weapons in their own right, while rocket and smooth-channel stormcallers can summon electrical currents that live up to the weapons’ namesake."),
	("Cathode Cannon, Elite", "Heavy 2-H", 12, 35,300, 19, 60, 0, 40 charges, 4, "2", "unwieldy, wide line", "Cathode cannons were originally designed by members of the Android Abolitionist Front, and many varieties made by different races nonetheless are decorated with circuit designs reminiscent of the weapons’ android inventors. The tactical cathode cannon is a standard-issue weapon for members of the Front, while advanced, elite, paragon, and shockstorm cathode cannons are often used by mercenaries and assault forces with a variety of goals."),
	("Frailty Cannon, Massacre-Class", "Heavy 2-H", 15, 132,000, 21, 60, 0, 50 charges, 5, "2", "line, necrotic", "The frailty cannon line produces a jet of necromantically fueled coolant. More easily controlled than their zero cannon counterparts, these weapons are used to bring down enemies as much as they’re used to invigorate nearby undead."),
	("Frailty Rifle, Epidemic-Class", "Long Arms 2-H", 17, 297,000, 24, 60, 0, 50 charges, 5, "2", "necrotic", "Standard issue to many soldiers of the Corpse Fleet, the frailty series of rifles is designed to affect only living enemies. The weapons’ most common application is Corpse Fleet agents firing at enemies engaged by mindless undead, with incidents of friendly fire rewarding allies who are hit with boosts of negative energy."),
	("Crossbolter, Elite", "Heavy 2-H", 14, 71,400, 33, 60, 0, 30 arrows, 6, "2", "unwieldy", "This weapon resembles a rifle with a crossbeam near the end of the barrel. A crossbolter uses mechanical power to fire arrows along the barrel. Grenade arrows can also be fired with a crossbolter. "
	("Excavation Laser, Heavy", "Long Arms 2-H", 18, 380,000, 33, 60, 0, 80 charges, 4, "2", "penetrating, professional (mining)", "This sturdy, snub-nosed laser rifle resembles a starship’s mining laser in miniature. It fires a powerful beam that loses intensity after a relatively short distance, which makes it not only useful in many mining and quarrying endeavors but also effective in medium-range combat for those trained in its use. Most technologically advanced civilizations develop excavation lasers, and the tools are commonly seen in the hands of workers from the Ulrikka Clanholdings and other miners in the Diaspora. Light, medium, and heavy excavation lasers all see extensive use."),
	("Stormcaller, Smooth-Channel", "Heavy 2-H", 18, 440,000, 36, 60, 0, 40 charges, 5, "2", "flexible line, living, unwieldy", "Some barathu researchers who intensively study the titanic lightning storms found on their home world become obsessed with the phenomenon. The efforts of such scientists led to the creation of the stormcaller, a living weapon that generates a line of electricity originating not from the wielder but from a single point within the weapon’s relatively short range. Like most barathu creations, stormcallers are living creatures, and their massive shells are large enough to require two hands to wield, aided by the stormcaller wrapping its translucent tentacles around the user’s appendages. Sheet and ribbon stormcallers are powerful weapons in their own right, while rocket and smooth-channel stormcallers can summon electrical currents that live up to the weapons’ namesake."),
	("Crossbolter, Paragon", "Heavy 2-H", 18, 327,200, 55, 60, 0, 40 arrows, 8, "2", "unwieldy", "This weapon resembles a rifle with a crossbeam near the end of the barrel. A crossbolter uses mechanical power to fire arrows along the barrel. Grenade arrows can also be fired with a crossbolter. "
	("NIL Grenade Launcher, Merc", "Heavy 2-H", 1, 280, by grenade, 60, 0, 6 grenades, 1, "2", "analog", "NIL (an acronym for “neutronic individual launcher”) grenade launchers are the most common grenade launcher available on the market. NILs can be fitted with any sort of grenade as ammunition. Grenades are loaded individually, rather than in magazines. You can load different types of grenades into a NIL grenade launcher, and you can select which grenade to fire as part of the action used to make an attack."),
	("Surgecaster, Advanced", "Long Arms 2-H", 14, 83,000, 16, 60, arc 2d10, 40 charges, 2, "1", "boost 1d10, living", "Surgecasters are bioengineered organic weapons; these independent conglomerations of bioelectric cells generate deadly bursts of electricity when fired. They were invented by a flotilla of merged barathus that directed its efforts toward creating such a weapon, and its success has resulted in the continued production of the surgecaster as a viable commercial endeavor. Only two models are currently available on the market: a standard surgecaster and an advanced surgecaster, though the merged barathu entity appears to be continuing its research and development efforts."),
	("Handcoil, Pilot", "Small Arms 1-H", 11, 24,000, 9, 60, arc 2d8, 40 charges, 4, "L", "n/a", "An ultraminiaturized version of the coilguns used on starships, this weapon has a short range but a powerful effect. Some of the first versions were produced by starship manufacturers and were accompanied by a promotional campaign suggesting that a starship’s crew should match the starship itself, complete with flight suits to match a given ship’s paint job. Most manufacturers still use the model classification set forth in those early campaigns: explorer, fighter, pilot, and capital handcoils."),
	("Anchor Pistol, Flux", "Small Arms 1-H", 20, 814,000, 28, 60, bind, 80 charges, 5, "L", "nonlethal", "Blasts from this electromagnetic pistol create a magnetic field that hampers a foe’s movement. Barathus working on Liavara developed these weapons, as the magnetic fields ensnare a target without causing it to fall0a useful feature when confronting the operators of illicit harvesting endeavors on a gas giant. Many parts of an anchor pistol are grown from living organisms, resulting in a lightweight pistol that gleams like mother-of-pearl. Voltaic anchor pistols employ typical electromagnetism, while the emergent and inductive anchor pistols use higher symmetries to produce aperiodic force. The flux anchor pistol relies on quantum-phase factors to generate extraordinarily powerful blasts."),
	("Rail Cannon, Tactical", "Heavy 2-H", 3, 1,410, 5, 60, bleed 1d4, 20 rounds, 5, "2", "line, unwieldy", "Rail cannons are scaled-up versions of rail guns, and like rail guns, they use magnetic fields to rapidly accelerate ammunition. A rail cannon generates such phenomenal force that its rounds can pass entirely through multiple targets, allowing the user to hit multiple targets in a line. Tactical rail cannons are precise and effective, while advanced rail cannons offer more firepower; elite and paragon rail cannons are generally used only by heavyweapons specialists in professional military groups."),
	("Kalo Shredder, Deluge-Class", "Long Arms 2-H", 14, 74,300, 21, 60, bleed 4d4, 36 flechettes, 1, "1", "analog, automatic, underwater", "Favored by the much-romanticized kalo hunters of Kalo-Mahoi, kalo shredders fire razor-sharp flechettes with nearly silent magnetism. The gun’s distinctive organic design is grown from magnetic coral that grants you a +2 bonus to KAC against disarm combat maneuvers."),
	("Kalo Shredder, Monsoon-Class", "Long Arms 2-H", 17, 784,000, 42, 60, bleed 4d6, 48 flechettes, 1, "1", "analog, automatic, underwater", "Favored by the much-romanticized kalo hunters of Kalo-Mahoi, kalo shredders fire razor-sharp flechettes with nearly silent magnetism. The gun’s distinctive organic design is grown from magnetic coral that grants you a +2 bonus to KAC against disarm combat maneuvers."),
	("Shadow Pistol, Caliginous", "Small Arms 1-H", 4, 2,100, 2, 60, blind, 40 charges, 4, "L", "n/a", "Inspired by the Shadow Plane0or, some say, followers of Zon-Kuthon0a shadow pistol replicates the energy of the Plane of Shadow to momentarily separate the target from the thermodynamic energy of the universe, damaging it with the instantaneous change in temperature. With their shadowy appearance, the caliginous and sable models resemble guns cut from polished obsidian, while the more advanced tenebrous and umbral models look more like they were cut from the blackness of space."),
	("Compliance Ray, Flash", "Small Arms 1-H", 3, 1,400, 3, 60, blind, 24 charges, 1, "L", "nonlethal", "With a wider beam than typical lasers, the compliance ray is designed for crowd control and other nonmilitary uses. Although these rays are legal for civilians to own, most models are themed to fit in with the local constabulary’s armor; the Stewards’ blue-and-gold models are common throughout the Pact Worlds. Shots from these pistols cause intense discomfort, and a hit to the eyes can cause temporary blindness. Models begin with the flash designation and increase in intensity as follows: flare, strobe, starburst, and sunspot."),
	("Shadow Pistol, Sable", "Small Arms 1-H", 7, 6,750, 5, 60, blind, 40 charges, 4, "L", "n/a", "Inspired by the Shadow Plane0or, some say, followers of Zon-Kuthon0a shadow pistol replicates the energy of the Plane of Shadow to momentarily separate the target from the thermodynamic energy of the universe, damaging it with the instantaneous change in temperature. With their shadowy appearance, the caliginous and sable models resemble guns cut from polished obsidian, while the more advanced tenebrous and umbral models look more like they were cut from the blackness of space."),
	("Nova Rifle, Yellow Star", "Long Arms 2-H", 7, 6,800, 7, 60, blind, 40 charges, 4, "1", "line, unwieldy", "Much like traditional plasma rifles, nova rifles fire coherent gouts of plasma that can potentially travel some distance and burn multiple targets. However, nova rifles have a slimmer profile overall but a larger aperture, projecting plasma that’s both slightly cooler and more diffuse. The nova rifle’s intense visual display makes it a favorite of icons looking to make a statement or simply add pyrotechnics to their shows. Red star, yellow star, and white star nova rifles are all easily identified by the color of their plasma arcs."),
	("Compliance Ray, Strobe", "Small Arms 1-H", 11, 25,100, 10, 60, blind, 26 charges, 1, "L", "nonlethal", "With a wider beam than typical lasers, the compliance ray is designed for crowd control and other nonmilitary uses. Although these rays are legal for civilians to own, most models are themed to fit in with the local constabulary’s armor; the Stewards’ blue-and-gold models are common throughout the Pact Worlds. Shots from these pistols cause intense discomfort, and a hit to the eyes can cause temporary blindness. Models begin with the flash designation and increase in intensity as follows: flare, strobe, starburst, and sunspot."),
	("Shadow Pistol, Tenebrous", "Small Arms 1-H", 12, 35,400, 11, 60, blind, 40 charges, 4, "L", "n/a", "Inspired by the Shadow Plane0or, some say, followers of Zon-Kuthon0a shadow pistol replicates the energy of the Plane of Shadow to momentarily separate the target from the thermodynamic energy of the universe, damaging it with the instantaneous change in temperature. With their shadowy appearance, the caliginous and sable models resemble guns cut from polished obsidian, while the more advanced tenebrous and umbral models look more like they were cut from the blackness of space."),
	("Compliance Ray, Starburst", "Small Arms 1-H", 15, 171,000, 15, 60, blind, 27 charges, 1, "L", "nonlethal", "With a wider beam than typical lasers, the compliance ray is designed for crowd control and other nonmilitary uses. Although these rays are legal for civilians to own, most models are themed to fit in with the local constabulary’s armor; the Stewards’ blue-and-gold models are common throughout the Pact Worlds. Shots from these pistols cause intense discomfort, and a hit to the eyes can cause temporary blindness. Models begin with the flash designation and increase in intensity as follows: flare, strobe, starburst, and sunspot."),
	("Shadow Pistol, Umbral", "Small Arms 1-H", 20, 855,000, 27, 60, blind, 40 charges, 4, "L", "n/a", "Inspired by the Shadow Plane0or, some say, followers of Zon-Kuthon0a shadow pistol replicates the energy of the Plane of Shadow to momentarily separate the target from the thermodynamic energy of the universe, damaging it with the instantaneous change in temperature. With their shadowy appearance, the caliginous and sable models resemble guns cut from polished obsidian, while the more advanced tenebrous and umbral models look more like they were cut from the blackness of space."),
	("Agitator, Ember", "Heavy 2-H", 1, 330, 4, 60, burn 1d4, 20 charges, 1, "2", "boost 1d4", "An agitator is a portable generator of microwave radiation that rapidly heats up targets to create internal bubbles of steam or makes targets burst into flames. The longer the weapon is focused, the more intense the agitation becomes, making it a favored by the defenders of bunkers, guard posts, and other emplacements. Ember agitators and blaze agitators rely on individual generators, taking the form of a bulky cylinder in the middle of the gun that hums ominously as the weapon fires, but miniaturization technology allows inferno agitators and solar flare agitators to include multiple smaller generators for increased effect."),
	("Cinder Rifle, Truth-Sequence", "Long Arms 2-H", 2, 700, 4, 60, burn 1d6, 10, 1, "2", "n/a", "Designed for the fighting elite of Sarenrae, cinder rifles are similar to most jacketed rifles, but within the framework of the gun, the ammunition becomes superheated. The result is a bullet exiting the gun while white hot, tracing its path through the air with a bright trail."),
	("Divergent Laser, Single-Wave", "Heavy 2-H", 5, 3,430, 4, 60, burn 1d6, 40 charges, 2, "2", "blast, unwieldy", "Originally developed alongside convergent lasers, divergent lasers use multiple laser beams emitting from a blocky casing to produce a cone-shaped output. This weapon’s damage is significantly less than that achieved by the convergent lasers, but the same systems that synchronize wavelengths in a convergent laser allow the divergent laser to focus on multiple targets. The single-color beam of a single-wave divergent laser sets it apart from the shimmering colors of a multiwave divergent laser. A wide-spectrum divergent laser has a nearly white beam and could be mistaken for a spotlight at a glance0though not by a target struck by one!"
	("Flame Launcher, Fireball", "Heavy 2-H", 5, 3,250, 4, 60, burn 1d6, 20 petrol, 2, "2", "explode (10), unwieldy", "Flame launchers sling large globules of aerated petrol with carefully timed ignition. The resulting explosion is usually well contained and can be placed with surprising precision. Although fed by the same sort of petrol tank found in burners and flamethrowers, the weapon is a complicated mess of air tanks, exposed circuitry, and tubing, all required to achieve the perfect mixture for controlled explosions. Fireball flame launchers are the weakest version of this weapon, outpowered by immolation flame launchers and the exceptionally powerful supernova flame launchers."),
	("Flare Rifle, Dazzler", "Long Arms 2-H", 3, 445, 5, 60, burn 1d6, 8 flares, 1, "1", "analog, bright, harrying", "Dazzlers are a form of crowd control used primarily for civil peacekeeping. While the weapons use lasers to damage and sometimes blind targets, the beams are carefully calibrated to avoid inflicting lethal injury. Built on similar principles to the smaller compliance ray, dazzlers also tend to bear the colors of local law-enforcement groups. However, the similarities end there, as the dazzler is a bulky device usually carried with the help of a shoulder strap, with its business end covered by dozens of glassy bulbs surrounded by a conical shield. Downplaying this somewhat disturbing appearance, dazzler manufacturer ATech holds up the weapons as an important tool for safe peacekeeping and spreads the weapons wherever AbadarCorp is found. Dazzlers come in flash, strobe, and sunspot models."),
	("Cinder Rifle, Salvation-Sequence", "Long Arms 2-H", 7, 6,000, 9, 60, burn 1d6, 14, 1, "2", "n/a", "Designed for the fighting elite of Sarenrae, cinder rifles are similar to most jacketed rifles, but within the framework of the gun, the ammunition becomes superheated. The result is a bullet exiting the gun while white hot, tracing its path through the air with a bright trail."),
	("Dragon Rifle, Drake", "Long Arms 2-H", 9, 13,400, 10, 60, burn 2d4, 20 petrol, 1, "1", "automatic", "A larger and more powerful version of a dragon pistol, a dragon rifle also commonly bears draconic motifs or iconography in its aesthetic design. The globules of petrol from a dragon rifle are slightly larger than those from a pistol, and the weapon can be set to launch a series of shots in quick succession. Wyrmling, drake, and wyvern dragon rifles are available, along with the powerful and rare true dragon rifle."),
	("Autobeam Rifle, Tactical", "Long Arms 2-H", 11, 26,900, 12, 60, burn 2d4, 40 charges, 4, "2", "automatic", "Autobeam rifles can fire in automatic mode, spraying a cone of lasers from the barrel. "
	("Blaze Rifle, Salamander-Class", "Long Arms 2-H", 7, 5,800, 9, 60, burn 2d6, 40 petrol, 2, "1", "analog, unwieldy", "A blaze rifle is a bulky, ungainly weapon, with a rifle stock and two tanks of petrol mounted atop the barrel. Compared to other petrol weapons, the blaze rifle fires a far narrower stream of petrol, which allows for greater accuracy. Fire-loving mercenaries often choose the blaze rifle to avoid charring their allies. Ifrit-, salamander-, hellhound-, firedrake-, and phoenixclass blaze rifles are common throughout the Pact Worlds."),
	("Plasma Rifle, White Star", "Long Arms 2-H", 15, 126,600, 22, 60, burn 2d8, 40 charges, 4, "2", "line, unwieldy", "Plasma rifles fire long lines of ionized plasma that lance through objects and opponents in their path. "
	("Autobeam Rifle, Advanced", "Long Arms 2-H", 15, 95,500, 17, 60, burn 3d4, 100 charges, 10, "2", "automatic", "Autobeam rifles can fire in automatic mode, spraying a cone of lasers from the barrel. "
	("Blaze Rifle, Hellhound-Class", "Long Arms 2-H", 11, 23,200, 16, 60, burn 3d6, 40 petrol, 2, "1", "analog, unwieldy", "A blaze rifle is a bulky, ungainly weapon, with a rifle stock and two tanks of petrol mounted atop the barrel. Compared to other petrol weapons, the blaze rifle fires a far narrower stream of petrol, which allows for greater accuracy. Fire-loving mercenaries often choose the blaze rifle to avoid charring their allies. Ifrit-, salamander-, hellhound-, firedrake-, and phoenixclass blaze rifles are common throughout the Pact Worlds."),
	("Blaze Rifle, Firedrake-Class", "Long Arms 2-H", 16, 153,000, 27, 60, burn 4d6, 40 petrol, 2, "1", "analog, unwieldy", "A blaze rifle is a bulky, ungainly weapon, with a rifle stock and two tanks of petrol mounted atop the barrel. Compared to other petrol weapons, the blaze rifle fires a far narrower stream of petrol, which allows for greater accuracy. Fire-loving mercenaries often choose the blaze rifle to avoid charring their allies. Ifrit-, salamander-, hellhound-, firedrake-, and phoenixclass blaze rifles are common throughout the Pact Worlds."),
	("Burner, Firedrake-Class", "Heavy 2-H", 16, 158,000, 33, 60, burn 4d6, 40 petrol, 4, "2", "line, unwieldy", "Indistinguishable from a flamethrower to the lay observer, a burner uses petrol as fuel to produce a strong jet of flame. However, the subtly narrower nozzle and recoil-suppressing gyros allow a burner to fire streams of petrol with more control and focus than its traditional cousin. Ifrit-, salamander-, hellhound-, firedrake-, and phoenix-class burners are all widely available."),
	("Autobeam Rifle, Elite", "Long Arms 2-H", 19, 548,100, 30, 60, burn 5d4, 100 charges, 5, "2", "automatic", "Autobeam rifles can fire in automatic mode, spraying a cone of lasers from the barrel. "
	("Nanite Decoupler, Caustic", "Heavy 2-H", 9, 15,000, 7, 60, corrode 1d6, 10 nanites, 2, "3", "explode (10), unwieldy", "While most disintegrator weapons produce a stream of energy that strikes a single target, a nanite decoupler programs nanites to replicate a disintegrator’s destructive energies over a set area. The integrated generators used to overcharge the nanites for the desired effect make a nanite decoupler a heavy, bulky weapon that requires a skilled user. The caustic nanite decoupler and the vitriolic nanite decoupler are both deadly, destructive weapons."),
	("Sting Pistol, Wasp", "Small Arms 1-H", 15, 113,000, 22, 60, corrode 3d6, 40 charges, 4, "L", "living", "Sting pistols are living weapons based on samples of Swarm technology recovered during the last century. The chitinous weapon converts power to internally generate and shoot acidslicked needles that can cause lasting damage to the target. Ant models are sturdy and commonplace, though yellow jacket and wasp sting pistols are more powerful. Hornet models are the heaviest and most potent of these weapons."),
	("Resonator, Diffraction", "Heavy 2-H", 4, 2,080, 4, 60, deafen, 40 charges, 2, "2", "boost 1d8, penetrating", "A resonator is a boxy device with a terminal along the top and a series of concentric rings of metal and crystal in front to focus the weapon’s harmonics. A shoulder strap helps offset the weapon’s considerable weight, allowing the use of a top handle to direct output while freeing up the other hand to operate the controls. A resonator generates sonic waves at frequencies set to resound within the targeted material, allowing the weapon to deal precise damage regardless of the target’s composition or protection. If the integrated probing function is employed before firing, the resonator’s sonic frequencies can be precisely tuned. Diffraction and refraction resonators align sonic waves in specific patterns, while linear and phased resonators focus the sonic energy through specialized matrices for amplified output."),
	("Screamer, LFD", "Heavy 2-H", 9, 14,000, 11, 60, deafen, 80 charges, 8, "2", "blast, unwieldy", "A screamer is a circular metal device with two handles on the back. The front of a screamer projects a cone of sonic energy that can damage and deafen anyone within the weapon’s area of effect."),
	("Staccato Rifle, Surge", "Long Arms 2-H", 9, 13,000, 11, 60, deafen, 40 charges, 2, "2", "automatic", "A baffled tube on the underside of a staccato rifle produces and modulates discrete blasts of sonic frequencies. The rifle’s unique construction enables a fully automatic mode, producing a sound like drumming. The frequencies can leave a target’s auditory senses overwhelmed. Pulse staccato rifles have the shortest sonic projector for reliable repetitive shots with less power usage. Surge, drum, and hammer staccato rifles require more charge for a harder hit."),
	("Screamer, HFD", "Heavy 2-H", 15, 107,500, 22, 60, deafen, 100 charges, 10, "2", "blast, unwieldy", "A screamer is a circular metal device with two handles on the back. The front of a screamer projects a cone of sonic energy that can damage and deafen anyone within the weapon’s area of effect."),
	("Staccato Rifle, Drum", "Long Arms 2-H", 15, 107,000, 22, 60, deafen, 40 charges, 2, "2", "automatic", "A baffled tube on the underside of a staccato rifle produces and modulates discrete blasts of sonic frequencies. The rifle’s unique construction enables a fully automatic mode, producing a sound like drumming. The frequencies can leave a target’s auditory senses overwhelmed. Pulse staccato rifles have the shortest sonic projector for reliable repetitive shots with less power usage. Surge, drum, and hammer staccato rifles require more charge for a harder hit."),
	("Shout Projector, Pacifier", "Heavy 2-H", 11, 22,800, 13, 60, demoralize, 40 charges, 4, "2", "explode (15), integrated (2 slots), nonlethal,unwieldy", "Shout projectors amplify your speech to overwhelming or destructive volume, and then project it in a cone. Words and sheer sonic pressure in this cone can’t be ignored. All shout projectors can be installed as armor upgrades (taking one upgrade slot per hand needed to wield the weapon), allowing the projectors to be used hands-free. That way, a user can carry lethal weaponry, safety gear, or protest signage. Exhorter shout projectors can be useful for crowd control with a lighter touch. Damper and pacifier models are ostensibly for nonlethal but more coercive applications, while the riot and crackdown projectors are for heavy-handed use."),
	("Shout Projector, Riot", "Heavy 2-H", 17, 304,000, 22, 60, demoralize, 40 charges, 4, "2", "explode (15), integrated (2 slots), nonlethal,unwieldy", "Shout projectors amplify your speech to overwhelming or destructive volume, and then project it in a cone. Words and sheer sonic pressure in this cone can’t be ignored. All shout projectors can be installed as armor upgrades (taking one upgrade slot per hand needed to wield the weapon), allowing the projectors to be used hands-free. That way, a user can carry lethal weaponry, safety gear, or protest signage. Exhorter shout projectors can be useful for crowd control with a lighter touch. Damper and pacifier models are ostensibly for nonlethal but more coercive applications, while the riot and crackdown projectors are for heavy-handed use."),
	("Psychic-Wave Cannon, V", "Heavy 2-H", 20, 990,000, 45, 60, demoralize, 20 charges, 4, "2", "blast, living, mind-affecting, unwieldy", "Unlike weapons that rely on physical projectiles or various energy forms to damage a target, a psychic-wave cannon targets a creature’s mind. The cannon contains an organic neural matrix that converts charges into a mental blast, damaging creatures with overwhelming psychic output. The numeral of a psychicwave cannon’s model indicates the strength of its output, but the weapon can’t harm objects and mindless creatures, as well as those immune to mind-affecting effects."),
	("Caustolance, Liquidator", "Long Arms 2-H", 1, 400, 3, 60, Injection DC +2, 20, 1, "1", "Injection", "Drawing upon the same design and inspirations as the caustoject, this larger weapon is designed to resemble an assault rifle rather than a pistol. As with its smaller cousin, a caustolance uses its battery to generate an acidic field to inject directly into its targets, but it can also handle and discharge other substances that are poured into a special tank that is attached to the weapon’s barrel."),
	("Caustolance, Decimator", "Long Arms 2-H", 6, 4,500, 7, 60, Injection DC +2, 20, 1, "1", "Injection", "Drawing upon the same design and inspirations as the caustoject, this larger weapon is designed to resemble an assault rifle rather than a pistol. As with its smaller cousin, a caustolance uses its battery to generate an acidic field to inject directly into its targets, but it can also handle and discharge other substances that are poured into a special tank that is attached to the weapon’s barrel."),
	("Caustolance, Executioner", "Long Arms 2-H", 12, 38,000, 17, 60, Injection DC +2, 20, 1, "1", "Injection", "Drawing upon the same design and inspirations as the caustoject, this larger weapon is designed to resemble an assault rifle rather than a pistol. As with its smaller cousin, a caustolance uses its battery to generate an acidic field to inject directly into its targets, but it can also handle and discharge other substances that are poured into a special tank that is attached to the weapon’s barrel."),
	("Caustolance, Eradicator", "Long Arms 2-H", 18, 400,000, 42, 60, Injection DC +2, 20, 1, "1", "Injection", "Drawing upon the same design and inspirations as the caustoject, this larger weapon is designed to resemble an assault rifle rather than a pistol. As with its smaller cousin, a caustolance uses its battery to generate an acidic field to inject directly into its targets, but it can also handle and discharge other substances that are poured into a special tank that is attached to the weapon’s barrel."),
	("Wraith-Sting Rifle, Wasp", "Sniper 2-H", 5, 2,980, 0, 60, injection dc +3, 1 dart, 1, "1", "injection, sniper (500), susbtle, unwieldy", "Wraith-sting rifles fire darts that are loaded with an injectable substance. The low velocity and slim profile of these darts mean the target often remains unaware of the initial attack. Once the effects of the injected substance take hold, however, it is usually easy to identify the delivery method. These insidious weapons are said to be a favorite of reptoid assassins, but as with any information on that race, the veracity of this rumor is suspect. Ironically, this weapon’s models are named after stinging insects: yellow jacket, wasp, and hornet."),
	("Injector Pistol, Zoologist", "Small Arms 1-H", 5, 2,890, 4, 60, injection dc +3, 20 darts, 1, "L", "injection", "Manufacturers worked to the specifications of xenobiologists to design and produce these firearms, which use magnetic fields to accelerate darts loaded with various substances for injection into the target. They do so far less gently than the smaller needler pistol, however, and they have become a popular tool for poisoners, slavers, and others with less scientific intentions. Medic and zoologist injector pistols are often used by xenobiologists studying unintelligent species; poacher, subjugation, and elite injector pistols are generally regarded as illicit since they more often used to target sentient species, though most markets nevertheless carry the weapons."),
	("Injector Pistol, Poacher", "Small Arms 1-H", 8, 9,050, 7, 60, injection dc +4, 21 darts, 1, "L", "injection", "Manufacturers worked to the specifications of xenobiologists to design and produce these firearms, which use magnetic fields to accelerate darts loaded with various substances for injection into the target. They do so far less gently than the smaller needler pistol, however, and they have become a popular tool for poisoners, slavers, and others with less scientific intentions. Medic and zoologist injector pistols are often used by xenobiologists studying unintelligent species; poacher, subjugation, and elite injector pistols are generally regarded as illicit since they more often used to target sentient species, though most markets nevertheless carry the weapons."),
	("Radcannon, Rapid-Decay", "Heavy 2-H", 17, 264,000, 31, 60, irradiate, 40 charges, 2, "2", "blast, radioactive, unwieldy", "Radcannons are large, dangerous-to-wield weapons typically employed by desperate, reckless, or unliving users. A radcannon’s high-voltage capacitors channel energy through a magnetron and transformer to generate massive blasts of radioactive waves, burning targets and typically exposing the target0and potentially the user0to dangerous levels of radiation. Devourer cultists often employ electromagnetic radcannons, neutron radcannons, and even rapid-decay radcannons, unfazed by the weapons’ danger."),
	("Graviton Pistol, Chiral", "Small Arms 1-H", 13, 49,500, 0, 60, knockdown, 40 charges, 4, "2", "gravitation (25.)", "Many security forces and peacekeepers employ graviton pistols, since these weapons deal no damage but instead push or pull a target. Long rods running in parallel lines form a barrel-like structure that makes such a pistol easy to identify. The available models of graviton pistols start at linear, with vector, tensor, and chiral models are able to move a target increasing distances."),
	("Graviton Pistol, Tensor", "Small Arms 1-H", 8, 9,800, 0, 60, knockdown, 40 charges, 4, "2", "gravitation (20.)", "Many security forces and peacekeepers employ graviton pistols, since these weapons deal no damage but instead push or pull a target. Long rods running in parallel lines form a barrel-like structure that makes such a pistol easy to identify. The available models of graviton pistols start at linear, with vector, tensor, and chiral models are able to move a target increasing distances."),
	("Graviton Pistol, Vector", "Small Arms 1-H", 5, 3,050, 0, 60, knockdown, 40 charges, 4, "2", "gravitation (15.)", "Many security forces and peacekeepers employ graviton pistols, since these weapons deal no damage but instead push or pull a target. Long rods running in parallel lines form a barrel-like structure that makes such a pistol easy to identify. The available models of graviton pistols start at linear, with vector, tensor, and chiral models are able to move a target increasing distances."),
	("Plasma Fork, 12-Notch", "Long Arms 2-H", 3, 1,290, 4, 60, knockdown, 20 charges, 1, "1", "boost 1d4", "Also known as a plasma rail gun, a plasma fork has two long metal prongs in place of a barrel. The mechanism magnetically accelerates a bolt of plasma between these two prongs, but it can also hold plasma temporarily between the prongs to charge up an even more devastating attack. Each model has a number of notches that infuse the plasma with energy, starting with 12-notch plasma forks and increasing in intensity to 15-notch, 19-notch, and 22-notch plasma forks."),
	("Ice Launcher, Aufeis", "Heavy 2-H", 2, 760, 6, 60, knockdown, 20 charges, 4, "3", "unwieldy", "A decidedly unsubtle weapon, an ice launcher fires a huge block of ice at an opponent. The weapon is heavy and slow to fire, but the weight of the supercooled ice can knock an opponent to the ground and deal extensive cold damage. Aufeis and iceberg launchers produce small enough quantities of ice that it can be stored in the weapon’s square barrel, sometimes making them appear more like bulky appliance than weapons. The more complex floe, glacier, and icecap ice launchers generate a large amount of ice in front of the barrel proper, steadying the mass with clawed protrusions before firing."),
	("Ice Launcher, Iceberg", "Heavy 2-H", 5, 3,100, 9, 60, knockdown, 40 charges, 4, "3", "unwieldy", "A decidedly unsubtle weapon, an ice launcher fires a huge block of ice at an opponent. The weapon is heavy and slow to fire, but the weight of the supercooled ice can knock an opponent to the ground and deal extensive cold damage. Aufeis and iceberg launchers produce small enough quantities of ice that it can be stored in the weapon’s square barrel, sometimes making them appear more like bulky appliance than weapons. The more complex floe, glacier, and icecap ice launchers generate a large amount of ice in front of the barrel proper, steadying the mass with clawed protrusions before firing."),
	("Ice Launcher, Floe", "Heavy 2-H", 8, 9,430, 19, 60, knockdown, 40 charges, 8, "3", "unwieldy", "A decidedly unsubtle weapon, an ice launcher fires a huge block of ice at an opponent. The weapon is heavy and slow to fire, but the weight of the supercooled ice can knock an opponent to the ground and deal extensive cold damage. Aufeis and iceberg launchers produce small enough quantities of ice that it can be stored in the weapon’s square barrel, sometimes making them appear more like bulky appliance than weapons. The more complex floe, glacier, and icecap ice launchers generate a large amount of ice in front of the barrel proper, steadying the mass with clawed protrusions before firing."),
	("Ice Launcher, Glacier", "Heavy 2-H", 15, 108,000, 52, 60, knockdown, 80 charges, 8, "3", "unwieldy", "A decidedly unsubtle weapon, an ice launcher fires a huge block of ice at an opponent. The weapon is heavy and slow to fire, but the weight of the supercooled ice can knock an opponent to the ground and deal extensive cold damage. Aufeis and iceberg launchers produce small enough quantities of ice that it can be stored in the weapon’s square barrel, sometimes making them appear more like bulky appliance than weapons. The more complex floe, glacier, and icecap ice launchers generate a large amount of ice in front of the barrel proper, steadying the mass with clawed protrusions before firing."),
	("Ice Launcher, Icecap", "Heavy 2-H", 20, 892,000, 91, 60, knockdown, 80 charges, 8, "3", "unwieldy", "A decidedly unsubtle weapon, an ice launcher fires a huge block of ice at an opponent. The weapon is heavy and slow to fire, but the weight of the supercooled ice can knock an opponent to the ground and deal extensive cold damage. Aufeis and iceberg launchers produce small enough quantities of ice that it can be stored in the weapon’s square barrel, sometimes making them appear more like bulky appliance than weapons. The more complex floe, glacier, and icecap ice launchers generate a large amount of ice in front of the barrel proper, steadying the mass with clawed protrusions before firing."),
	("Neutriad Pistol", "Small Arms 1-H", 5, 3,200, 3, 60, pulse 1d6, 20 charges, 1, "L", "force", "A neutriad pistol is a 5th level small-arm ranged weapon that deals 1d6 bludgeoning damage and has the pulse (1d6) critical hit effect. It has a range of 60 feet and a capacity of 20 charges (1 usage). It has the force special property and light bulk, and it costs 3,200 credits."),
	("Tetrad Rings, Elite", "Small Arms 1-H", 19, 620,000, 17, 60, push (10), 20 charges, 2, "L", "force", "Tetrad rings deal lighter damage than weapons of a similar class, but the device launches a bolt of force that bypasses many common defenses. The design of tetrad rings is proprietary witchwyrd technology, which makes them expensive and difficult to find. They are manufactured in only three models: tactical, advanced, and elite. All three are elaborate sets of rings covered in delicate carvings, with a wire mesh to house the battery. Advanced and elite models have finer decorations."),
	("Tetrad Rings, Advanced", "Small Arms 1-H", 12, 39,000, 7, 60, push (5), 20 charges, 2, "L", "force", "Tetrad rings deal lighter damage than weapons of a similar class, but the device launches a bolt of force that bypasses many common defenses. The design of tetrad rings is proprietary witchwyrd technology, which makes them expensive and difficult to find. They are manufactured in only three models: tactical, advanced, and elite. All three are elaborate sets of rings covered in delicate carvings, with a wire mesh to house the battery. Advanced and elite models have finer decorations."),
	("Arc Caster, Static", "Heavy 2-H", 1, 375, 4, 60, second arc 1d6, 20 charges, 2, "2", "first arc 1d6, unwieldy", "Flanked by large handles, an arc caster bristles with capacitors and antennae that release more energy than it can realistically control. While many shock weapons have a chance to arc to a second target on a hit, the arc caster is designed to achieve that feat on every shot, and particularly well-aimed strikes can sometimes arc twice. The storm and tempest models feature improvements that build upon the capabilities of static and aurora arc casters. Since there is little way to control which creatures are struck on the subsequent arcs, arc casters are generally used only by solo combatants or those with little regard for their allies’ well-being. More rarely, party members may take particular precautions against electricity damage, such as with a resistant armor spell or an electrostatic field armor upgrade, to protect themselves from an ally wielding an arc caster."),
	("Arc Caster, Aurora", "Heavy 2-H", 5, 3,160, 7, 60, second arc 1d6, 40 charges, 2, "2", "first arc 1d6, unwieldy", "Flanked by large handles, an arc caster bristles with capacitors and antennae that release more energy than it can realistically control. While many shock weapons have a chance to arc to a second target on a hit, the arc caster is designed to achieve that feat on every shot, and particularly well-aimed strikes can sometimes arc twice. The storm and tempest models feature improvements that build upon the capabilities of static and aurora arc casters. Since there is little way to control which creatures are struck on the subsequent arcs, arc casters are generally used only by solo combatants or those with little regard for their allies’ well-being. More rarely, party members may take particular precautions against electricity damage, such as with a resistant armor spell or an electrostatic field armor upgrade, to protect themselves from an ally wielding an arc caster."),
	("Sonic Bolter, Light", "Heavy 2-H", 3, 1,480, 5, 60, sicken, 20 charges, 2, "2", "antibiological, line, unwieldy", "The sound waves a sonic bolter produces tightly focus in a brief but coherent line. This concentrated, low-frequency vibration damages the body and jostles internal organs, causing dizziness, pain, and slight nausea. Members of the Android Abolitionist Front developed the light model upon discovering the effect of a similar beam. Heavy, assault, and devastator bolters can generate sufficient sound pressure to damage artificial and unliving creatures."),
	("Dirge Pistol, Parametric", "Small Arms 1-H", 15, 133,000, 15, 60, sicken, 20 charges, 1, "L", "antibiological", "The oscillating sonic waves discharged from a dirge pistol work like those fired from a dirge cannon. Raiders and hijackers prize these weapons for their effect against living targets, which can leave many valuables unharmed. Harmonic and resonant dirge pistols generate stable oscillations, while the anharmonic, parametric, and radial dirge pistols have concentric generator cylinders to produce dissonant and more harmful output."),
	("Dirge Pistol, Radial", "Small Arms 1-H", 19, 660,000, 25, 60, sicken, 20 charges, 1, "L", "antibiological", "The oscillating sonic waves discharged from a dirge pistol work like those fired from a dirge cannon. Raiders and hijackers prize these weapons for their effect against living targets, which can leave many valuables unharmed. Harmonic and resonant dirge pistols generate stable oscillations, while the anharmonic, parametric, and radial dirge pistols have concentric generator cylinders to produce dissonant and more harmful output."),
	("Zero Pistol, Frostbite-Class", "Small Arms 1-H", 5, 3,060, 3, 60, staggered, 20 charges, 1, "L", "n/a", "Zero pistols have a weighted grip to balance their unusually heavy barrels. A cylindrical canister over the barrel contains and directs the coolants. "
	("Hailcannon, Subzero", "Heavy 2-H", 1, 275, 4, 60, staggered, 20 charges, 2, "2", "automatic", "Hailcannons use a complex integrated coolant system to generate staggering barrages of ice. Unlike with many cryo weapons, the hailcannon’s prolific output and massive barrel allow the weapon to be fired in automatic mode, which can overwhelm targets.  Subzero hailcannons are the standard model, and the increasing damage capacity of gelid, ultracold, absolute-zero, and clathrate hailcannons proves attractive to many who swear by such weapons."),
	("Zero Rifle, Frostbite-Class", "Long Arms 2-H", 4, 2,330, 4, 60, staggered, 40 charges, 2, "1", "n/a", "Zero rifles have long, bulky barrels and tend to be very frontheavy. A heavy tank over the barrel stores the rifle’s coolant supply, contributing most of its bulk. "
	("Subduer, Rime", "Small Arms 1-H", 9, 13,200, 6, 60, staggered, 20 charges, 1, "L", "nonlethal", "A subduer resembles a hollow rod with internal coolant reserves, and it relies on the user’s forceful movements to spray the coolant forward. Employed primarily by kasathan security forces to prevent suspects from fleeing, subduers coat their targets in a thin layer of expelled coolants that cause temporary painful freezing of the target’s skin that deals little lasting damage. On a lucky shot, the frozen layer also interferes with the target’s ability to function. Frost and rime subduers are often employed by peacekeeping forces, while sleet and glacier subduers typically see use only by pirates or mercenary groups."),
	("Zero Pistol, Hailstorm-Class", "Small Arms 1-H", 10, 16,900, 7, 60, staggered, 40 charges, 2, "L", "n/a", "Zero pistols have a weighted grip to balance their unusually heavy barrels. A cylindrical canister over the barrel contains and directs the coolants. "
	("Hailcannon, Gelid", "Heavy 2-H", 6, 4,350, 9, 60, staggered, 40 charges, 4, "2", "automatic", "Hailcannons use a complex integrated coolant system to generate staggering barrages of ice. Unlike with many cryo weapons, the hailcannon’s prolific output and massive barrel allow the weapon to be fired in automatic mode, which can overwhelm targets.  Subzero hailcannons are the standard model, and the increasing damage capacity of gelid, ultracold, absolute-zero, and clathrate hailcannons proves attractive to many who swear by such weapons."),
	("Zero Rifle, Hailstorm-Class", "Long Arms 2-H", 8, 10,100, 9, 60, staggered, 40 charges, 2, "2", "n/a", "Zero rifles have long, bulky barrels and tend to be very frontheavy. A heavy tank over the barrel stores the rifle’s coolant supply, contributing most of its bulk. "
	("Subduer, Sleet", "Small Arms 1-H", 13, 50,500, 10, 60, staggered, 20 charges, 1, "L", "nonlethal", "A subduer resembles a hollow rod with internal coolant reserves, and it relies on the user’s forceful movements to spray the coolant forward. Employed primarily by kasathan security forces to prevent suspects from fleeing, subduers coat their targets in a thin layer of expelled coolants that cause temporary painful freezing of the target’s skin that deals little lasting damage. On a lucky shot, the frozen layer also interferes with the target’s ability to function. Frost and rime subduers are often employed by peacekeeping forces, while sleet and glacier subduers typically see use only by pirates or mercenary groups."),
	("Zero Cannon, Tactical", "Heavy 2-H", 11, 23,000, 13, 60, staggered, 80 charges, 4, "2", "line, unwieldy", "Zero cannons project a freezing line straight out from a generator, affecting any targets within the line. A pair of tanks in the cannon’s heavy stock contain chemical coolants that produce a violent endothermic reaction when mixed in the insulated barrel. "
	("Zero Pistol, Blizzard-Class", "Small Arms 1-H", 15, 94,500, 14, 60, staggered, 40 charges, 2, "L", "n/a", "Zero pistols have a weighted grip to balance their unusually heavy barrels. A cylindrical canister over the barrel contains and directs the coolants. "
	("Subduer, Glacier", "Small Arms 1-H", 16, 169,000, 16, 60, staggered, 20 charges, 1, "L", "nonlethal", "A subduer resembles a hollow rod with internal coolant reserves, and it relies on the user’s forceful movements to spray the coolant forward. Employed primarily by kasathan security forces to prevent suspects from fleeing, subduers coat their targets in a thin layer of expelled coolants that cause temporary painful freezing of the target’s skin that deals little lasting damage. On a lucky shot, the frozen layer also interferes with the target’s ability to function. Frost and rime subduers are often employed by peacekeeping forces, while sleet and glacier subduers typically see use only by pirates or mercenary groups."),
	("Zero Rifle, Blizzard-Class", "Long Arms 2-H", 14, 79,800, 18, 60, staggered, 80 charges, 4, "2", "n/a", "Zero rifles have long, bulky barrels and tend to be very frontheavy. A heavy tank over the barrel stores the rifle’s coolant supply, contributing most of its bulk. "
	("Zero Pistol, Avalanche-Class", "Small Arms 1-H", 19, 492,900, 21, 60, staggered, 80 charges, 4, "L", "n/a", "Zero pistols have a weighted grip to balance their unusually heavy barrels. A cylindrical canister over the barrel contains and directs the coolants. "
	("Zero Cannon, Advanced", "Heavy 2-H", 14, 81,400, 22, 60, staggered, 100 charges, 5, "2", "line, unwieldy", "Zero cannons project a freezing line straight out from a generator, affecting any targets within the line. A pair of tanks in the cannon’s heavy stock contain chemical coolants that produce a violent endothermic reaction when mixed in the insulated barrel. "
	("Zero Rifle, Avalanche-Class", "Long Arms 2-H", 18, 410,200, 31, 60, staggered, 100 charges, 5, "2", "n/a", "Zero rifles have long, bulky barrels and tend to be very frontheavy. A heavy tank over the barrel stores the rifle’s coolant supply, contributing most of its bulk. "
	("Void Rifle, Grave-Class", "Long Arms 2-H", 2, 1,020, 3, 60, suffocate, 20 charges, 1, "1", "antibiological", "A firearm designed with crystals from the Plane of Shadow, a void rifle is unique in that power flowing through those crystals allows the rifle to fire inky bolts of life-sapping cold. The rifle’s frigid energy can harm only the living, so it does nothing to constructs and undead. Regardless, the rifle remains a favorite of followers of Urgathoa. Grave- and crypt-class void rifles are an option for standard issue among rank-and-file marines of the Eoxian navy, while tomb-, ossuary-, and barrow-class void rifles are reserved for elite forces."),
	("Void Rifle, Crypt-Class", "Long Arms 2-H", 6, 4,400, 4, 60, suffocate, 20 charges, 1, "1", "antibiological", "A firearm designed with crystals from the Plane of Shadow, a void rifle is unique in that power flowing through those crystals allows the rifle to fire inky bolts of life-sapping cold. The rifle’s frigid energy can harm only the living, so it does nothing to constructs and undead. Regardless, the rifle remains a favorite of followers of Urgathoa. Grave- and crypt-class void rifles are an option for standard issue among rank-and-file marines of the Eoxian navy, while tomb-, ossuary-, and barrow-class void rifles are reserved for elite forces."),
	("Nanite Thrower, Advanced", "Long Arms 2-H", 12, 35,400, 0, 60, wound, 10 nanites, 1, "1", "deconstruct 3d6", "A nanite thrower has a cylindrical nanite canister above the stock, which serves as ammunition. Instead of firing a single projectile, the nanite thrower hurls a coherent cluster of nanites at the target. These microscopic machines burrow in and damage the target from within. Nanite throwers come in similar models to the nanite rifle0tactical, advanced, and elite. With throwers, however, this line extends to the paragon model."),
	("Nanite Thrower, Tactical", "Long Arms 2-H", 9, 13,300, 0, 60, wound, 10 nanites, 1, "1", "deconstruct 2d6", "A nanite thrower has a cylindrical nanite canister above the stock, which serves as ammunition. Instead of firing a single projectile, the nanite thrower hurls a coherent cluster of nanites at the target. These microscopic machines burrow in and damage the target from within. Nanite throwers come in similar models to the nanite rifle0tactical, advanced, and elite. With throwers, however, this line extends to the paragon model."),
	("Conqueror, Red Star", "Heavy 2-H", 1, 430, 5, 60, wound, 20 charges, 4, "3", "unwieldy", "Conquerors are perhaps the largest and most difficult to handle of the plasma weapon category. A conquerer can deliver a single devastating blast of plasma, but the weapon is rather front-heavy and difficult to maneuver. Some vesk take up the weapon as a sign of their patron deity, Damoritosh, viewing it as the ranged spiritual equivalent of the doshko. In addition to the red star, yellow star, white star, and blue star models, the particularly powerful violet star conqueror has recently made its way onto the market."),
	("Plasma Guide, Series-28", "Sniper 2-H", 6, 4,920, 5, 60, wound, 40 charges, 5, "2", "guided, sniper (250), unwieldy", "A plasma guide maintains a magnetic guidance system around its plasma discharge, which continues guiding the shot after it is fired. This increases accuracy at ranges far beyond those of typical plasma weapons and bypasses the advantage of partial cover as the magnetic guidance directs the plasma toward its target. Vesk snipers are believed to be the earliest users of the plasma guide during the Silent War, but it’s become a standard in many military and mercenary arsenals since then. This weapon has been continually refined since its invention; series-21, series-28, series-37, series-42, series-62, and series-73 plasma guides have proven generally stable and thus remain in production."),
	("Plasma Bolter, Advanced", "Long Arms 2-H", 5, 3,010, 9, 60, wound, 40 charges, 8, "2", "unwieldy", "One of the most common ranged weapons used by the vesk military during the war between the Pact Worlds and the Veskarium, the plasma bolter is a particularly hefty longarm with a bulky profile that speaks to its vesk origins. Unlike most common ranged plasma weapons, which lay out long lines of plasma or boost their output, plasma bolters focus on delivering a single heavy bolt of plasma. These weapons saw extensive use in fighting back the Swarm, and now many can be easily obtained on the open market as Pact Worlds manufacturers have begun offering their own tactical, advanced, elite, and paragon models of the classic weapon."),
	("Nanite Rifle, Tactical", "Sniper 2-H", 10, 20,100, 13, 60, wound, 10 nanites, 10, "1", "sniper (500), unwieldy", "Nanite rifles can fire nanotech-infused darts at targets from extreme ranges. Although the darts deal little damage, the nanites eat into the target immediately and can cause grievous injuries. Nanites from tactical models target the site where they land, while an advanced rifle’s nanites can spread farther within the target. An elite rifle allows its nanites to move even farther from the point struck, dealing more damage."),
	("Plasma Bolter, Elite", "Long Arms 2-H", 9, 14,000, 16, 60, wound, 40 charges, 4, "2", "unwieldy", "One of the most common ranged weapons used by the vesk military during the war between the Pact Worlds and the Veskarium, the plasma bolter is a particularly hefty longarm with a bulky profile that speaks to its vesk origins. Unlike most common ranged plasma weapons, which lay out long lines of plasma or boost their output, plasma bolters focus on delivering a single heavy bolt of plasma. These weapons saw extensive use in fighting back the Swarm, and now many can be easily obtained on the open market as Pact Worlds manufacturers have begun offering their own tactical, advanced, elite, and paragon models of the classic weapon."),
	("Plasma Ring, Multichannel", "Small Arms 1-H", 17, 280,000, 18, 60, wound, 40 charges, 4, "L", "n/a", "Plasma rings are relatively flat, circular weapons with an easily grippable interior, allowing them to be used in a variety of orientations. Plasma cycles through a channel within the ring at high speeds, and a release valve allows a stream of plasma to escape in a directed jet. Single-valve plasma rings produce a small discharge, while dual-valve plasma rings have a synchronized pair of valves to produce a larger discharge. Multichannel plasma rings build plasma in a series of parallel rings that vent into a single release valve for an extremely powerful blast."),
	("Plasma Bolter, Paragon", "Long Arms 2-H", 16, 170,000, 40, 60, wound, 80 charges, 4, "2", "unwieldy", "One of the most common ranged weapons used by the vesk military during the war between the Pact Worlds and the Veskarium, the plasma bolter is a particularly hefty longarm with a bulky profile that speaks to its vesk origins. Unlike most common ranged plasma weapons, which lay out long lines of plasma or boost their output, plasma bolters focus on delivering a single heavy bolt of plasma. These weapons saw extensive use in fighting back the Swarm, and now many can be easily obtained on the open market as Pact Worlds manufacturers have begun offering their own tactical, advanced, elite, and paragon models of the classic weapon."),
	("Diasporan Rifle, Tactical", "Sniper 2-H", 1, 350, 4, 70, 0, 10 charges, 1, "1", "sniper (250), unwieldy", "These sleek firearms were developed by the finest sarcesian engineers for use by elite mercenaries. The most common manufacturer is MuniTech, one of the only corporations fully owned and operated by sarcesians. Diasporan rifles are sniper rifles that belong to the laser category."),
	("Crossbolter, Tactical", "Long Arms 2-H", 2, 475, 5, 70, 0, 1 arrow, 1, "2", "unwieldy", "This weapon resembles a rifle with a crossbeam near the end of the barrel. A crossbolter uses mechanical power to fire arrows along the barrel. Grenade arrows can also be fired with a crossbolter. "
	("Shirren-Eye Rifle, Tactical", "Sniper 2-H", 2, 755, 5, 70, 0, 1 round, 1, "1", "analog, sniper (250), unwieldy", "Shirren-eye rifles are named for their compound sights, which resemble the eyes of the insectile race, but are rarely manufactured by shirren companies. Shirren-eye rifles are extremely accurate and favored by snipers and sharpshooters. "
	("Diasporan Rifle, Advanced", "Sniper 2-H", 5, 3,750, 9, 70, 0, 20 charges, 1, "2", "sniper (500), unwieldy", "These sleek firearms were developed by the finest sarcesian engineers for use by elite mercenaries. The most common manufacturer is MuniTech, one of the only corporations fully owned and operated by sarcesians. Diasporan rifles are sniper rifles that belong to the laser category."),
	("Crossbolter, Dual", "Long Arms 2-H", 8, 8,250, 11, 70, 0, 4 arrows, 2, "2", "unwieldy", "This weapon resembles a rifle with a crossbeam near the end of the barrel. A crossbolter uses mechanical power to fire arrows along the barrel. Grenade arrows can also be fired with a crossbolter. "
	("Shirren-Eye Rifle, Advanced", "Sniper 2-H", 8, 9,350, 11, 70, 0, 4 rounds, 1, "2", "analog, sniper (500), unwieldy", "Shirren-eye rifles are named for their compound sights, which resemble the eyes of the insectile race, but are rarely manufactured by shirren companies. Shirren-eye rifles are extremely accurate and favored by snipers and sharpshooters. "
	("Assassin Rifle, Spectre", "Sniper 2-H", 12, 29,500, 17, 70, 0, 1 round, 1, "1", "breakdown, sniper (750), unwieldy", "When assembled, an assassin rifle looks similar to a typical sniper rifle. Its modular construction, however, allows it to be broken down into small component parts that can be hidden on the user’s person0or even smuggled in a ysoki’s cheek pouches0making the weapon difficult to detect or identify. Assassin rifles are available in stalker, shadow, phantom, spectre, and wraith models."),
	("Crossbolter, Advanced", "Heavy 2-H", 11, 21,900, 22, 70, 0, 12 arrows, 4, "2", "unwieldy", "This weapon resembles a rifle with a crossbeam near the end of the barrel. A crossbolter uses mechanical power to fire arrows along the barrel. Grenade arrows can also be fired with a crossbolter. "
	("Multistage Rifle, Triple-Plus", "Sniper 2-H", 15, 124,000, 31, 70, 0, 3 mini-rockets, 3, "2", "indirect, sniper (750), unwieldy", "The multistage rifle requires mini-rocket ammunition, which it detonates in multiple stages. The initial firing of the weapon is a subsonic round that’s boosted by one or more subsequent, stronger discharges some distance from the user. This results in two effects that aid in obfuscating the user’s position: the sound of the weapon firing is displaced, and the later stages can cause subtle changes in direction, creating an impact angle that suggests the mini-rocket had been fired from a different angle. Dual and dual-plus multistage rifles use a two-stage firing process, while triple and triple-plus multistage rifles employ a three-stage process for added range. The quad multistage rifle is the only weapon on the market with an unrivaled four-stage firing process for maximum damage."),
	("Assassin Rifle, Wraith", "Sniper 2-H", 17, 278,000, 38, 70, 0, 1 round, 1, "1", "breakdown, sniper (1, 000), unwieldy", "When assembled, an assassin rifle looks similar to a typical sniper rifle. Its modular construction, however, allows it to be broken down into small component parts that can be hidden on the user’s person0or even smuggled in a ysoki’s cheek pouches0making the weapon difficult to detect or identify. Assassin rifles are available in stalker, shadow, phantom, spectre, and wraith models."),
	("NIL Grenade Launcher, Squad", "Heavy 2-H", 8, 9,400, by grenade, 70, 0, 12 grenades, 1, "3", "analog", "NIL (an acronym for “neutronic individual launcher”) grenade launchers are the most common grenade launcher available on the market. NILs can be fitted with any sort of grenade as ammunition. Grenades are loaded individually, rather than in magazines. You can load different types of grenades into a NIL grenade launcher, and you can select which grenade to fire as part of the action used to make an attack."),
	("Arc Rifle, Static", "Long Arms 2-H", 6, 4,200, 6, 70, arc 1d6, 40 charges, 1, "2", "stun", "Arc rifles fire deadly electrical blasts and have a longer range than arc pistols. Like arc pistols, arc rifles can stun targets that are not killed outright by the electricity damage. "
	("Arc Rifle, Aurora", "Long Arms 2-H", 11, 24,500, 13, 70, arc 2d6, 40 charges, 1, "2", "stun", "Arc rifles fire deadly electrical blasts and have a longer range than arc pistols. Like arc pistols, arc rifles can stun targets that are not killed outright by the electricity damage. "
	("Coil Rifle, Specialist", "Sniper 2-H", 5, 3,120, 7, 70, bleed 1d6, 6 rounds, 1, "2", "sniper (250.)", "A coil rifle is a long, slender firearm surrounded by a coil that generates carefully aligned magnetic fields that accelerate a single round with impressive power and accuracy. Precision coil rifles are the most affordable of these weapons, while specialist coil rifles have greater range and efficacy. Rangefinder, saboteur, and assassin coil rifles are especially deadly weapons that are appreciated by true connoisseurs, veteran mercenaries, and experienced firearm specialists."),
	("Coil Rifle, Rangefinder", "Sniper 2-H", 10, 18,600, 10, 70, bleed 2d6, 8 rounds, 1, "2", "sniper (500.)", "A coil rifle is a long, slender firearm surrounded by a coil that generates carefully aligned magnetic fields that accelerate a single round with impressive power and accuracy. Precision coil rifles are the most affordable of these weapons, while specialist coil rifles have greater range and efficacy. Rangefinder, saboteur, and assassin coil rifles are especially deadly weapons that are appreciated by true connoisseurs, veteran mercenaries, and experienced firearm specialists."),
	("Needler Rifle, Tactical", "Long Arms 2-H", 1, 200, 3, 70, Injection DC +2, 14 darts, 1, "1", "analog, injection", "Like the needler pistol, this injection gun can be fitted with cartridges containing medicine or poison. The needler rifle fires darts much farther than its smaller counterpart."),
	("Needler Rifle, Tactical", "Long Arms 2-H", 5, 3,000, 4, 70, Injection DC +2, 14 darts, 1, "1", "analog, injection", "Like the needler pistol, this injection gun can be fitted with cartridges containing medicine or poison. The needler rifle fires darts much farther than its smaller counterpart."),
	("Needler Rifle, Tactical", "Long Arms 2-H", 10, 18,000, 14, 70, Injection DC +2, 14 darts, 1, "1", "analog, injection", "Like the needler pistol, this injection gun can be fitted with cartridges containing medicine or poison. The needler rifle fires darts much farther than its smaller counterpart."),
	("Needler Rifle, Tactical", "Long Arms 2-H", 15, 110,000, 28, 70, Injection DC +2, 14 darts, 1, "1", "analog, injection", "Like the needler pistol, this injection gun can be fitted with cartridges containing medicine or poison. The needler rifle fires darts much farther than its smaller counterpart."),
	("Needler Rifle, Tactical", "Long Arms 2-H", 20, 850,000, 56, 70, Injection DC +2, 14 darts, 1, "1", "analog, injection", "Like the needler pistol, this injection gun can be fitted with cartridges containing medicine or poison. The needler rifle fires darts much farther than its smaller counterpart."),
	("Plasma Guide, Series-42", "Sniper 2-H", 11, 28,200, 13, 70, severe wound, 80 charges, 8, "2", "guided, sniper (500), unwieldy", "A plasma guide maintains a magnetic guidance system around its plasma discharge, which continues guiding the shot after it is fired. This increases accuracy at ranges far beyond those of typical plasma weapons and bypasses the advantage of partial cover as the magnetic guidance directs the plasma toward its target. Vesk snipers are believed to be the earliest users of the plasma guide during the Silent War, but it’s become a standard in many military and mercenary arsenals since then. This weapon has been continually refined since its invention; series-21, series-28, series-37, series-42, series-62, and series-73 plasma guides have proven generally stable and thus remain in production."),
	("Plasma Guide, Series-37", "Sniper 2-H", 8, 10,800, 9, 70, wound, 40 charges, 8, "2", "guided, sniper (500), unwieldy", "A plasma guide maintains a magnetic guidance system around its plasma discharge, which continues guiding the shot after it is fired. This increases accuracy at ranges far beyond those of typical plasma weapons and bypasses the advantage of partial cover as the magnetic guidance directs the plasma toward its target. Vesk snipers are believed to be the earliest users of the plasma guide during the Silent War, but it’s become a standard in many military and mercenary arsenals since then. This weapon has been continually refined since its invention; series-21, series-28, series-37, series-42, series-62, and series-73 plasma guides have proven generally stable and thus remain in production."),
	("Burner, Pheonic-Class", "Heavy 2-H", 20, 795,000, 55, 75, burn 5d6, 40 petrol, 4, "2", "line, unwieldy", "Indistinguishable from a flamethrower to the lay observer, a burner uses petrol as fuel to produce a strong jet of flame. However, the subtly narrower nozzle and recoil-suppressing gyros allow a burner to fire streams of petrol with more control and focus than its traditional cousin. Ifrit-, salamander-, hellhound-, firedrake-, and phoenix-class burners are all widely available."),
	("Anacite Ion Cannon, Storm", "Heavy 2-H", 13, 52,900, 22, 75, staggered, 80 charges, 5, "2", "line, lockdown, unwieldy", "This heavy weapon was designed by Aballonian law-enforcement agencies for capturing criminal constructs without completely destroying them."),
	("IMDS Missile Launcher", "Heavy 2-H", 10, 18,200, 0, 80, 0, 1 missile, 1, "2", "n/a", "IMDS (an acronym for “individual missile delivery system”) missile launchers are the most common missile launchers currently on the market. IMDS launchers fire individual missiles as ammunition and use the damage listed for the missiles fired out of them."),
	("Aeon Guard, Assault Rifle", "Long Arms 2-H", 3, 1,400, 4, 80, 0, 12 rounds, 1, "1", "automatic", "The AG series of longarms is manufactured by government-held factories for the sole use of the Aeon Guard. Its ingenious designers are held via lifelong “contracts” as pampered but neurally locked prisoners of the throne. The AG assault rifle is a selective-fire rifle that is standard issue for rank-and-file troops. Other weapons in the series include the AG accelerator rifle, which uses magnetic fields to propel metal projectiles like a magnetar rifle does, and the rocket propelled–projectile rifle (RPPR, or “Ripper,” as it’s known in the ranks of the Aeon Guard), which fires mini-rockets like those used in gyrojet rifles. Pact Worlds intelligence believes that some AG weapons can also be equipped with aeon stones, though what functions they provide and how this hybrid technology actually works is unknown. In the Azlanti Star Empire, civilian possession of any AG-series weapon is a criminal offense punishable by death."),
	("Rocket Rifle", "Long Arms 2-H", 5, 3,010, 6, 80, 0, 5 mini-rockets, 1, "1", "analog, unwieldy", "A rocket rifle is a longarm that uses mini-rockets as ammunition. The weapon and its ammunition are both quite expensive, but they make up for it in firepower. Rocket rifles came into heavy use at the onset of the war with the Swarm, often employed by daring soldiers on high-risk missions into Swarm strongholds."),
	("Infinity Rifle, Elite", "Long Arms 2-H", 10, 17,100, 7, 80, 0, 20 charges, 1, "1", "boost 2d6", "Infinity rifles take their name from their shape, two conjoined rings similar to an infinity symbol with twin muzzles along the outer edge of one ring. The two rings contain a twisted loop of fiber-optic cabling that channels the laser beam; adding more energy to the loop results in a more powerful blast. These weapons were first introduced to the Pact Worlds by skittermanders (Starfinder Alien Archive 106), though their current nomenclature (tactical, advanced, elite, and paragon) was imposed by other weapons manufacturers."),
	("Petrol Converter, Tactical", "Long Arms 2-H", 7, 6,750, 7, 80, 0, 40 petrol, 4, "1", "analog, modal (disintegrator)", "This longarm has an extra cylinder connected to the petrol tank that contains a series of converter filters housing active bacteria. Diverting the petrol flow through this system before firing allows the bacteria to convert the fuel into acid. In addition to the tactical, advanced, elite, and paragon petrol converters, manufacturers have produced a light petrol converter for industrial applications."),
	("Blindmark Rifle, LFD", "Long Arms 2-H", 8, 9,800, 9, 80, 0, 40 charges, 5, "1", "echo, stun", "Blindmark rifles generate sonic frequencies through carefully aligned resonance in multiple magnetic cylinders positioned between the stock and the short muzzle of the weapon. When the rifle’s shot hits a target, that target retains the resonance as a faint or subsonic tone useful for creatures that have blindsense (sound or vibration) or blindsight (sound or vibration). Multiple targets struck by the same blindmark rifle emit identical tones that can be distinguished only by location. Blindmark rifles are manufactured in thunderstrike, LFD (low-frequency device), HFD (high-frequency device), and banshee models."),
	("Polarity Rifle, Aurora", "Long Arms 2-H", 10, 21,000, 9, 80, 0, 40 charges, 2, "1", "polarize 1d10", "The polarity rifle was designed by Vercite engineers using the conceptual model that underpins polarity gauntlets. This rifle’s prongs are separately polarized, and it alternates between them as it fires to create a circuit of lightning between the gun and target, causing subsequent attacks to deal additional damage. Static, aurora, storm, and tempest polarity rifles are favored by sharpshooters in many fields, though they are often scorned by kasathas who view them as a vulgarized appropriation of an honorable weapon."),
	("Petrol Converter, Advanced", "Long Arms 2-H", 10, 18,500, 10, 80, 0, 40 petrol, 1, "1", "analog, modal (disintegrator)", "This longarm has an extra cylinder connected to the petrol tank that contains a series of converter filters housing active bacteria. Diverting the petrol flow through this system before firing allows the bacteria to convert the fuel into acid. In addition to the tactical, advanced, elite, and paragon petrol converters, manufacturers have produced a light petrol converter for industrial applications."),
	("Storm Coil, Impulse", "Long Arms 2-H", 12, 35,200, 14, 80, 0, 80 charges, 10, "2", "line, unwieldy", "A storm coil employs an air-core resonant transformer to produce high-voltage electrical output. The resulting bolt of electricity arcs out from the weapon in a line. Though it employs technology similar to the colossus coil, the storm coil was developed independently within the Pact Worlds. Live storm coils and jolt storm coils generate impressive bolts, while the larger impulse and surge storm coils have even farther reach."),
	("Petrol Converter, Elite", "Long Arms 2-H", 14, 76,500, 17, 80, 0, 40 petrol, 2, "1", "analog, modal (disintegrator)", "This longarm has an extra cylinder connected to the petrol tank that contains a series of converter filters housing active bacteria. Diverting the petrol flow through this system before firing allows the bacteria to convert the fuel into acid. In addition to the tactical, advanced, elite, and paragon petrol converters, manufacturers have produced a light petrol converter for industrial applications."),
	("Diasporan Rifle, Elite", "Sniper 2-H", 10, 17,000, 18, 80, 0, 20 charges, 1, "2", "sniper (750), unwieldy", "These sleek firearms were developed by the finest sarcesian engineers for use by elite mercenaries. The most common manufacturer is MuniTech, one of the only corporations fully owned and operated by sarcesians. Diasporan rifles are sniper rifles that belong to the laser category."),
	("Polarity Rifle, Storm", "Long Arms 2-H", 15, 137,000, 18, 80, 0, 40 charges, 2, "1", "polarize 2d8", "The polarity rifle was designed by Vercite engineers using the conceptual model that underpins polarity gauntlets. This rifle’s prongs are separately polarized, and it alternates between them as it fires to create a circuit of lightning between the gun and target, causing subsequent attacks to deal additional damage. Static, aurora, storm, and tempest polarity rifles are favored by sharpshooters in many fields, though they are often scorned by kasathas who view them as a vulgarized appropriation of an honorable weapon."),
	("Ice Carbine, Ultracold", "Long Arms 2-H", 13, 47,100, 21, 80, 0, 40 charges, 2, "2", "automatic", "Rather than relying on coolant to produce supercooled gas, an ice carbine pumps heat out of large vents integrated in the weapon’s stock and uses the temperature change to produce brittle, razor-sharp shards of ice in the chamber. This design allows it to either fire a short, targeted shot or spray a hailstorm of piercing needles at a group of foes. The heat-exchange technology used in these weapons is common on Verces, where it’s used for many purposes, making it relatively easy to find them in the Pact Worlds, from the subzero models (often built in illicit basement labs) to absolute-zero ice carbines, which are the best in the Pact Worlds. Gelid and ultracold ice carbines improve on the subzero version’s technology and overall power."),
	("Shirren-Eye Rifle, Elite", "Sniper 2-H", 13, 54,000, 22, 80, 0, 6 rounds, 1, "2", "analog, sniper (750), unwieldy", "Shirren-eye rifles are named for their compound sights, which resemble the eyes of the insectile race, but are rarely manufactured by shirren companies. Shirren-eye rifles are extremely accurate and favored by snipers and sharpshooters. "
	("Wave Modulator, VII", "Small Arms 1-H", 20, 919,000, 22, 80, 0, 40 charges, 4, "L", "modal (sonic)", "The frequency of a wave modulator’s output can be adjusted to either burn a target or bombard it with damaging sonic bursts. Shirrens favor these boxy pistols because of the thrill of choosing the damage type of every shot fired. Wave modulators come in numbered models."),
	("Diasporan Rifle, Ultra", "Sniper 2-H", 15, 110,000, 27, 80, 0, 30 charges, 1, "2", "sniper (1, 000), unwieldy", "These sleek firearms were developed by the finest sarcesian engineers for use by elite mercenaries. The most common manufacturer is MuniTech, one of the only corporations fully owned and operated by sarcesians. Diasporan rifles are sniper rifles that belong to the laser category."),
	("Frailty Cannon, Extinction-Class", "Heavy 2-H", 19, 660,000, 31, 80, 0, 50 charges, 5, "2", "line, necrotic", "The frailty cannon line produces a jet of necromantically fueled coolant. More easily controlled than their zero cannon counterparts, these weapons are used to bring down enemies as much as they’re used to invigorate nearby undead."),
	("Petrol Converter, Paragon", "Long Arms 2-H", 18, 385,000, 31, 80, 0, 40 petrol, 2, "1", "analog, modal (disintegrator)", "This longarm has an extra cylinder connected to the petrol tank that contains a series of converter filters housing active bacteria. Diverting the petrol flow through this system before firing allows the bacteria to convert the fuel into acid. In addition to the tactical, advanced, elite, and paragon petrol converters, manufacturers have produced a light petrol converter for industrial applications."),
	("Shirren-Eye Rifle, Paragon", "Sniper 2-H", 16, 147,200, 33, 80, 0, 6 rounds, 1, "1", "analog, sniper (1000), unwieldy", "Shirren-eye rifles are named for their compound sights, which resemble the eyes of the insectile race, but are rarely manufactured by shirren companies. Shirren-eye rifles are extremely accurate and favored by snipers and sharpshooters. "
	("Polarity Rifle, Tempest", "Long Arms 2-H", 20, 1,000,000, 36, 80, 0, 80 charges, 2, "1", "polarize 3d8", "The polarity rifle was designed by Vercite engineers using the conceptual model that underpins polarity gauntlets. This rifle’s prongs are separately polarized, and it alternates between them as it fires to create a circuit of lightning between the gun and target, causing subsequent attacks to deal additional damage. Static, aurora, storm, and tempest polarity rifles are favored by sharpshooters in many fields, though they are often scorned by kasathas who view them as a vulgarized appropriation of an honorable weapon."),
	("Ice Carbine, Absolute-Zero", "Long Arms 2-H", 17, 218,000, 38, 80, 0, 40 charges, 2, "2", "automatic", "Rather than relying on coolant to produce supercooled gas, an ice carbine pumps heat out of large vents integrated in the weapon’s stock and uses the temperature change to produce brittle, razor-sharp shards of ice in the chamber. This design allows it to either fire a short, targeted shot or spray a hailstorm of piercing needles at a group of foes. The heat-exchange technology used in these weapons is common on Verces, where it’s used for many purposes, making it relatively easy to find them in the Pact Worlds, from the subzero models (often built in illicit basement labs) to absolute-zero ice carbines, which are the best in the Pact Worlds. Gelid and ultracold ice carbines improve on the subzero version’s technology and overall power."),
	("Multistage Rifle, Quad", "Sniper 2-H", 18, 627,000, 40, 80, 0, 4 mini-rockets, 4, "2", "indirect, sniper (1, 000), unwieldy", "The multistage rifle requires mini-rocket ammunition, which it detonates in multiple stages. The initial firing of the weapon is a subsonic round that’s boosted by one or more subsequent, stronger discharges some distance from the user. This results in two effects that aid in obfuscating the user’s position: the sound of the weapon firing is displaced, and the later stages can cause subtle changes in direction, creating an impact angle that suggests the mini-rocket had been fired from a different angle. Dual and dual-plus multistage rifles use a two-stage firing process, while triple and triple-plus multistage rifles employ a three-stage process for added range. The quad multistage rifle is the only weapon on the market with an unrivaled four-stage firing process for maximum damage."),
	("Diasporan Rifle, Imperial", "Sniper 2-H", 20, 725,000, 45, 80, 0, 30 charges, 1, "2", "sniper (1, 000), unwieldy", "These sleek firearms were developed by the finest sarcesian engineers for use by elite mercenaries. The most common manufacturer is MuniTech, one of the only corporations fully owned and operated by sarcesians. Diasporan rifles are sniper rifles that belong to the laser category."),
	("Shirren-Eye Rifle, Warpshot", "Sniper 2-H", 20, 740,800, 55, 80, 0, 4 rounds, 1, "1", "analog, sniper (1000), unwieldy", "Shirren-eye rifles are named for their compound sights, which resemble the eyes of the insectile race, but are rarely manufactured by shirren companies. Shirren-eye rifles are extremely accurate and favored by snipers and sharpshooters. "
	("Colossus Coil, Corona", "Heavy 2-H", 3, 1,450, 4, 80, arc 1d6, 20 charges, 4, "3", "boost 1d8", "Where massive creatures roam, those who fight against them for survival develop colossal weapons. Such is the case with the colossus coil, a weapon said to have been developed to hunt colossi on the planet Daimalko. It has since spread to many systems, including the Pact Worlds. This heavy firearm has a barrel sporting a series of toroidal high-voltage generators that collectively produce powerful arcs of electricity, and it can be overcharged to deliver even more destructive blasts. The electric blast sometimes overwhelms its target, branching off to hit another. The corona colossus coil produces a ring of electricity, while a brush colossus coil produces a more diffuse field. A streamer arc colossus coil produces a traditional arc of electricity, while the multistream colossus coil generates multiple such streams for a devastating blast."),
	("Handcoil, Capital", "Small Arms 1-H", 16, 150,000, 13, 80, arc 3d8, 40 charges, 4, "L", "n/a", "An ultraminiaturized version of the coilguns used on starships, this weapon has a short range but a powerful effect. Some of the first versions were produced by starship manufacturers and were accompanied by a promotional campaign suggesting that a starship’s crew should match the starship itself, complete with flight suits to match a given ship’s paint job. Most manufacturers still use the model classification set forth in those early campaigns: explorer, fighter, pilot, and capital handcoils."),
	("Arc Rifle, Storm", "Long Arms 2-H", 16, 190,300, 26, 80, arc 4d6, 80 charges, 2, "2", "stun", "Arc rifles fire deadly electrical blasts and have a longer range than arc pistols. Like arc pistols, arc rifles can stun targets that are not killed outright by the electricity damage. "
	("Arc Rifle, Tempest", "Long Arms 2-H", 19, 622,000, 39, 80, arc 6d6, 100 charges, 2, "2", "stun", "Arc rifles fire deadly electrical blasts and have a longer range than arc pistols. Like arc pistols, arc rifles can stun targets that are not killed outright by the electricity damage. "
	("Rail Cannon, Advanced", "Heavy 2-H", 12, 37,000, 16, 80, bleed 2d4, 40 rounds, 8, "2", "line, unwieldy", "Rail cannons are scaled-up versions of rail guns, and like rail guns, they use magnetic fields to rapidly accelerate ammunition. A rail cannon generates such phenomenal force that its rounds can pass entirely through multiple targets, allowing the user to hit multiple targets in a line. Tactical rail cannons are precise and effective, while advanced rail cannons offer more firepower; elite and paragon rail cannons are generally used only by heavyweapons specialists in professional military groups."),
	("Coil Rifle, Saboteur", "Sniper 2-H", 14, 76,700, 24, 80, bleed 3d6, 12 rounds, 1, "2", "sniper (750.)", "A coil rifle is a long, slender firearm surrounded by a coil that generates carefully aligned magnetic fields that accelerate a single round with impressive power and accuracy. Precision coil rifles are the most affordable of these weapons, while specialist coil rifles have greater range and efficacy. Rangefinder, saboteur, and assassin coil rifles are especially deadly weapons that are appreciated by true connoisseurs, veteran mercenaries, and experienced firearm specialists."),
	("Rail Cannon, Elite", "Heavy 2-H", 16, 176,000, 44, 80, bleed 3d6, 50 rounds, 10, "2", "line, unwieldy", "Rail cannons are scaled-up versions of rail guns, and like rail guns, they use magnetic fields to rapidly accelerate ammunition. A rail cannon generates such phenomenal force that its rounds can pass entirely through multiple targets, allowing the user to hit multiple targets in a line. Tactical rail cannons are precise and effective, while advanced rail cannons offer more firepower; elite and paragon rail cannons are generally used only by heavyweapons specialists in professional military groups."),
	("Nova Rifle, White Star", "Long Arms 2-H", 11, 25,300, 10, 80, blind, 40 charges, 4, "1", "line, unwieldy", "Much like traditional plasma rifles, nova rifles fire coherent gouts of plasma that can potentially travel some distance and burn multiple targets. However, nova rifles have a slimmer profile overall but a larger aperture, projecting plasma that’s both slightly cooler and more diffuse. The nova rifle’s intense visual display makes it a favorite of icons looking to make a statement or simply add pyrotechnics to their shows. Red star, yellow star, and white star nova rifles are all easily identified by the color of their plasma arcs."),
	("Compliance Ray, Sunspot", "Small Arms 1-H", 19, 545,000, 22, 80, blind, 28 charges, 1, "L", "nonlethal", "With a wider beam than typical lasers, the compliance ray is designed for crowd control and other nonmilitary uses. Although these rays are legal for civilians to own, most models are themed to fit in with the local constabulary’s armor; the Stewards’ blue-and-gold models are common throughout the Pact Worlds. Shots from these pistols cause intense discomfort, and a hit to the eyes can cause temporary blindness. Models begin with the flash designation and increase in intensity as follows: flare, strobe, starburst, and sunspot."),
	("Plasma Caster, White Star", "Long Arms 2-H", 13, 49,100, 16, 80, burn 1d10, 100 charges, 5, "2", "boost 1d10", "Plasma casters fling bolts of ionized plasma at a target. They have good range and are easier to use than plasma rifles or pistols, but they strike only a single target. "
	("Laser Pistol, Azimuth", "Small Arms 1-H", 1, 350, 2, 80, burn 1d4, 20 charges, 1, "L", "n/a", "The laser pistol is possibly the most common small arm used by explorers, guards, mercenaries, and traders. Laser pistols are light and reliable, yet they still deal a respectable amount of damage. "
	("Lens Pistol, Cylindrical", "Small Arms 1-H", 4, 1,850, 4, 80, burn 1d4, 29 charges, 2, "L", "unwieldy", "The lenses of this laser pistol reconfigure themselves for optimal focus between every shot, resulting in a more powerfully focused laser at a slower rate of fire. Cylindrical lens pistols and lenticular lens pistols focus their lasers using specially shaped lenses, while electron lens pistols and sunglass lens pistols are made of rarer materials and incorporate fine electronics."),
	("Plasma Array, Red Star", "Heavy 2-H", 3, 1,380, 5, 80, burn 1d4, 20 charges, 1, "2", "automatic", "A retractable coarse mesh of electromagnetically protected wire covers the wide muzzle of a plasma array; this mesh breaks apart plasma into a flurry of discrete charges. Plasma arrays are manufactured in the typical classifications for plasma weapons: red star, yellow star, white star, and blue star."),
	("Membrane Holdout Pistol", "Small Arms 1-H", 3, 1,250, 3, 80, burn 1d6, 20 charges, 1, "L", "n/a", "The original name of these pistols is forgotten, as the membrane ghibranis use them only in the direst circumstances. Under casual inspection, this pistol appears to be a sturdy laser weapon."),
	("Lens Pistol, Lenticular", "Small Arms 1-H", 10, 17,100, 9, 80, burn 1d8, 40 charges, 4, "L", "unwieldy", "The lenses of this laser pistol reconfigure themselves for optimal focus between every shot, resulting in a more powerfully focused laser at a slower rate of fire. Cylindrical lens pistols and lenticular lens pistols focus their lasers using specially shaped lenses, while electron lens pistols and sunglass lens pistols are made of rarer materials and incorporate fine electronics."),
	("Plasma Caster, Blue Star", "Long Arms 2-H", 17, 275,000, 27, 80, burn 2d10, 200 charges, 10, "2", "boost 2d10", "Plasma casters fling bolts of ionized plasma at a target. They have good range and are easier to use than plasma rifles or pistols, but they strike only a single target. "
	("Flare Rifle, Vivifier", "Long Arms 2-H", 6, 3,600, 5, 80, burn 2d4, 8 flares, 1, "1", "analog, bright, harrying", "A flare rifle is similar in appearance to a combat rifle, though it has a slightly wider barrel and magazine. This weapon fires flares, which don’t typically deal tremendous damage but can distract opponents. Dazzler flare rifles fire a single, relatively ordinary flare, while the vivifier flare rifle breaks open the flare and burns it all in moments, causing far greater light and heat. Coruscator, scorcher, and nova models fire more flares at a time to increase their damage output."),
	("Agitator, Blaze", "Heavy 2-H", 6, 4,300, 7, 80, burn 2d4, 40 charges, 1, "2", "boost 1d6", "An agitator is a portable generator of microwave radiation that rapidly heats up targets to create internal bubbles of steam or makes targets burst into flames. The longer the weapon is focused, the more intense the agitation becomes, making it a favored by the defenders of bunkers, guard posts, and other emplacements. Ember agitators and blaze agitators rely on individual generators, taking the form of a bulky cylinder in the middle of the gun that hums ominously as the weapon fires, but miniaturization technology allows inferno agitators and solar flare agitators to include multiple smaller generators for increased effect."),
	("Plasma Array, Yellow Star", "Heavy 2-H", 7, 6,300, 11, 80, burn 2d4, 20 charges, 2, "2", "automatic", "A retractable coarse mesh of electromagnetically protected wire covers the wide muzzle of a plasma array; this mesh breaks apart plasma into a flurry of discrete charges. Plasma arrays are manufactured in the typical classifications for plasma weapons: red star, yellow star, white star, and blue star."),
	("Igniter, Ember", "Long Arms 2-H", 8, 9,900, 0, 80, burn 2d6, 40 charges, 4, "1", "ignite 2d6", "An igniter has a deep-red crystal rod in place of a typical longarm barrel. This crystal focuses infrared light on a distant foe, causing the target to burst into flames. Assassins and drow in particular often favor the weapon due to its absence of any visible discharge. Ember, blaze, inferno, and solar flare igniters are common in many places."),
	("Flame Launcher, Immolation", "Heavy 2-H", 9, 14,200, 9, 80, burn 2d6, 40 petrol, 4, "2", "explode (10), unwieldy", "Flame launchers sling large globules of aerated petrol with carefully timed ignition. The resulting explosion is usually well contained and can be placed with surprising precision. Although fed by the same sort of petrol tank found in burners and flamethrowers, the weapon is a complicated mess of air tanks, exposed circuitry, and tubing, all required to achieve the perfect mixture for controlled explosions. Fireball flame launchers are the weakest version of this weapon, outpowered by immolation flame launchers and the exceptionally powerful supernova flame launchers."),
	("Flare Rifle, Coruscator", "Long Arms 2-H", 10, 15,700, 12, 80, burn 2d6, 12 flares, 2, "1", "analog, bright, harrying", "A flare rifle is similar in appearance to a combat rifle, though it has a slightly wider barrel and magazine. This weapon fires flares, which don’t typically deal tremendous damage but can distract opponents. Dazzler flare rifles fire a single, relatively ordinary flare, while the vivifier flare rifle breaks open the flare and burns it all in moments, causing far greater light and heat. Coruscator, scorcher, and nova models fire more flares at a time to increase their damage output."),
	("Cinder Rifle, Valor-Sequence", "Long Arms 2-H", 11, 23,700, 13, 80, burn 2d6, 20, 1, "2", "n/a", "Designed for the fighting elite of Sarenrae, cinder rifles are similar to most jacketed rifles, but within the framework of the gun, the ammunition becomes superheated. The result is a bullet exiting the gun while white hot, tracing its path through the air with a bright trail."),
	("Divergent Laser, Multiwave", "Heavy 2-H", 12, 41,200, 18, 80, burn 2d6, 40 charges, 2, "2", "blast, unwieldy", "Originally developed alongside convergent lasers, divergent lasers use multiple laser beams emitting from a blocky casing to produce a cone-shaped output. This weapon’s damage is significantly less than that achieved by the convergent lasers, but the same systems that synchronize wavelengths in a convergent laser allow the divergent laser to focus on multiple targets. The single-color beam of a single-wave divergent laser sets it apart from the shimmering colors of a multiwave divergent laser. A wide-spectrum divergent laser has a nearly white beam and could be mistaken for a spotlight at a glance0though not by a target struck by one!"
	("Cinder Rifle, Glory-Sequence", "Long Arms 2-H", 15, 102,200, 27, 80, burn 2d6, 24, 1, "2", "n/a", "Designed for the fighting elite of Sarenrae, cinder rifles are similar to most jacketed rifles, but within the framework of the gun, the ammunition becomes superheated. The result is a bullet exiting the gun while white hot, tracing its path through the air with a bright trail."),
	("Agitator, Inferno", "Heavy 2-H", 13, 50,800, 21, 80, burn 3d4, 40 charges, 2, "2", "boost 2d6", "An agitator is a portable generator of microwave radiation that rapidly heats up targets to create internal bubbles of steam or makes targets burst into flames. The longer the weapon is focused, the more intense the agitation becomes, making it a favored by the defenders of bunkers, guard posts, and other emplacements. Ember agitators and blaze agitators rely on individual generators, taking the form of a bulky cylinder in the middle of the gun that hums ominously as the weapon fires, but miniaturization technology allows inferno agitators and solar flare agitators to include multiple smaller generators for increased effect."),
	("Dragon Rifle, Wyvern", "Long Arms 2-H", 14, 72,200, 21, 80, burn 3d5, 20 petrol, 1, "1", "automatic", "A larger and more powerful version of a dragon pistol, a dragon rifle also commonly bears draconic motifs or iconography in its aesthetic design. The globules of petrol from a dragon rifle are slightly larger than those from a pistol, and the weapon can be set to launch a series of shots in quick succession. Wyrmling, drake, and wyvern dragon rifles are available, along with the powerful and rare true dragon rifle."),
	("Igniter, Blaze", "Long Arms 2-H", 12, 34,200, 0, 80, burn 3d6, 40 charges, 4, "1", "ignite 3d6", "An igniter has a deep-red crystal rod in place of a typical longarm barrel. This crystal focuses infrared light on a distant foe, causing the target to burst into flames. Assassins and drow in particular often favor the weapon due to its absence of any visible discharge. Ember, blaze, inferno, and solar flare igniters are common in many places."),
	("Flare Rifle, Scorcher", "Long Arms 2-H", 13, 43,800, 17, 80, burn 3d6, 12 flares, 3, "1", "analog, bright, harrying", "A flare rifle is similar in appearance to a combat rifle, though it has a slightly wider barrel and magazine. This weapon fires flares, which don’t typically deal tremendous damage but can distract opponents. Dazzler flare rifles fire a single, relatively ordinary flare, while the vivifier flare rifle breaks open the flare and burns it all in moments, causing far greater light and heat. Coruscator, scorcher, and nova models fire more flares at a time to increase their damage output."),
	("Igniter, Inferno", "Long Arms 2-H", 15, 108,000, 0, 80, burn 4d6, 40 charges, 4, "1", "ignite 4d6", "An igniter has a deep-red crystal rod in place of a typical longarm barrel. This crystal focuses infrared light on a distant foe, causing the target to burst into flames. Assassins and drow in particular often favor the weapon due to its absence of any visible discharge. Ember, blaze, inferno, and solar flare igniters are common in many places."),
	("Igniter, Solar Flare", "Long Arms 2-H", 18, 360,000, 0, 80, burn 5d6, 40 charges, 4, "1", "ignite 5d6", "An igniter has a deep-red crystal rod in place of a typical longarm barrel. This crystal focuses infrared light on a distant foe, causing the target to burst into flames. Assassins and drow in particular often favor the weapon due to its absence of any visible discharge. Ember, blaze, inferno, and solar flare igniters are common in many places."),
	("Blaze Rifle, Pheonix-Class", "Long Arms 2-H", 20, 765,000, 49, 80, burn 5d6, 40 petrol, 2, "1", "analog, unwieldy", "A blaze rifle is a bulky, ungainly weapon, with a rifle stock and two tanks of petrol mounted atop the barrel. Compared to other petrol weapons, the blaze rifle fires a far narrower stream of petrol, which allows for greater accuracy. Fire-loving mercenaries often choose the blaze rifle to avoid charring their allies. Ifrit-, salamander-, hellhound-, firedrake-, and phoenixclass blaze rifles are common throughout the Pact Worlds."),
	("Acid Dart Rifle, Tactical", "Long Arms 2-H", 2, 485, 4, 80, corrode 1d4, 10 darts, 1, "1", "analog", "An acid dart rifle has a nonreactive polymer reservoir that can be filled with whatever acid the wielder desires. The automatic loading process fills the rifle darts with acid as they are moved into the chamber. Dual acid dart rifles fire two darts simultaneously, while complex acid dart rifles hold concentrated doses of acid."),
	("Nanite Decoupler, Vitriolic", "Heavy 2-H", 19, 650,000, 21, 80, corrode 3d6, 10 nanites, 5, "3", "explode (20), unwieldy", "While most disintegrator weapons produce a stream of energy that strikes a single target, a nanite decoupler programs nanites to replicate a disintegrator’s destructive energies over a set area. The integrated generators used to overcharge the nanites for the desired effect make a nanite decoupler a heavy, bulky weapon that requires a skilled user. The caustic nanite decoupler and the vitriolic nanite decoupler are both deadly, destructive weapons."),
	("Sting Pistol, Hornet", "Small Arms 1-H", 18, 381,000, 27, 80, corrode 4d6, 40 charges, 2, "L", "living", "Sting pistols are living weapons based on samples of Swarm technology recovered during the last century. The chitinous weapon converts power to internally generate and shoot acidslicked needles that can cause lasting damage to the target. Ant models are sturdy and commonplace, though yellow jacket and wasp sting pistols are more powerful. Hornet models are the heaviest and most potent of these weapons."),
	("Resonator, Refraction", "Heavy 2-H", 10, 18,300, 9, 80, deafen, 40 charges, 2, "2", "boost 2d8, penetrating", "A resonator is a boxy device with a terminal along the top and a series of concentric rings of metal and crystal in front to focus the weapon’s harmonics. A shoulder strap helps offset the weapon’s considerable weight, allowing the use of a top handle to direct output while freeing up the other hand to operate the controls. A resonator generates sonic waves at frequencies set to resound within the targeted material, allowing the weapon to deal precise damage regardless of the target’s composition or protection. If the integrated probing function is employed before firing, the resonator’s sonic frequencies can be precisely tuned. Diffraction and refraction resonators align sonic waves in specific patterns, while linear and phased resonators focus the sonic energy through specialized matrices for amplified output."),
	("Staccato Rifle, Hammer", "Long Arms 2-H", 20, 810,000, 44, 80, deafen, 80 charges, 4, "2", "automatic", "A baffled tube on the underside of a staccato rifle produces and modulates discrete blasts of sonic frequencies. The rifle’s unique construction enables a fully automatic mode, producing a sound like drumming. The frequencies can leave a target’s auditory senses overwhelmed. Pulse staccato rifles have the shortest sonic projector for reliable repetitive shots with less power usage. Surge, drum, and hammer staccato rifles require more charge for a harder hit."),
	("Shout Projector, Crackdown", "Heavy 2-H", 20, 918,000, 40, 80, demoralize, 80 charges, 8, "2", "explode (20), integrated (2 slots), nonlethal,unwieldy", "Shout projectors amplify your speech to overwhelming or destructive volume, and then project it in a cone. Words and sheer sonic pressure in this cone can’t be ignored. All shout projectors can be installed as armor upgrades (taking one upgrade slot per hand needed to wield the weapon), allowing the projectors to be used hands-free. That way, a user can carry lethal weaponry, safety gear, or protest signage. Exhorter shout projectors can be useful for crowd control with a lighter touch. Damper and pacifier models are ostensibly for nonlethal but more coercive applications, while the riot and crackdown projectors are for heavy-handed use."),
	("Wraith-Sting Rifle, Hornet", "Sniper 2-H", 14, 71,200, 0, 80, injection dc +4, 1 dart, 1, "1", "injection, sniper (750), susbtle, unwieldy", "Wraith-sting rifles fire darts that are loaded with an injectable substance. The low velocity and slim profile of these darts mean the target often remains unaware of the initial attack. Once the effects of the injected substance take hold, however, it is usually easy to identify the delivery method. These insidious weapons are said to be a favorite of reptoid assassins, but as with any information on that race, the veracity of this rumor is suspect. Ironically, this weapon’s models are named after stinging insects: yellow jacket, wasp, and hornet."),
	("Injector Pistol, Subjugation", "Small Arms 1-H", 14, 68,500, 17, 80, injection dc +5, 22 darts, 1, "L", "injection", "Manufacturers worked to the specifications of xenobiologists to design and produce these firearms, which use magnetic fields to accelerate darts loaded with various substances for injection into the target. They do so far less gently than the smaller needler pistol, however, and they have become a popular tool for poisoners, slavers, and others with less scientific intentions. Medic and zoologist injector pistols are often used by xenobiologists studying unintelligent species; poacher, subjugation, and elite injector pistols are generally regarded as illicit since they more often used to target sentient species, though most markets nevertheless carry the weapons."),
	("Injector Pistol, Elite", "Small Arms 1-H", 19, 532,000, 31, 80, injection dc +6, 23 darts, 1, "L", "injection", "Manufacturers worked to the specifications of xenobiologists to design and produce these firearms, which use magnetic fields to accelerate darts loaded with various substances for injection into the target. They do so far less gently than the smaller needler pistol, however, and they have become a popular tool for poisoners, slavers, and others with less scientific intentions. Medic and zoologist injector pistols are often used by xenobiologists studying unintelligent species; poacher, subjugation, and elite injector pistols are generally regarded as illicit since they more often used to target sentient species, though most markets nevertheless carry the weapons."),
	("Gamma Rifle, Terrestrial", "Sniper 2-H", 4, 2,120, 5, 80, irradiate, 40 charges, 4, "1", "radioactive, sniper (500), unwieldy", "Gamma rifles direct concentrated bursts of gamma radiation that are strong enough to overcome normal environmental protections, burning targets from a distance, though users of such weapons risk exposure to that very radiation. Many find that the destructive effects of the ray are sufficient to outweigh the risk, and targets can even be subject to radiation sickness when struck in a vital organ. Terrestrial gamma rifles and ionizing gamma rifles feed energy through a mass of radioactive material in the muzzle to produce their deadly effects. Fusion and synchrotron gamma rifles instead produce radiation in a torus near the rifle’s stock, making them far more powerful, though still dangerous to the user."),
	("Gamma Rifle, Ionizing", "Sniper 2-H", 9, 13,600, 11, 80, irradiate, 40 charges, 5, "1", "radioactive, sniper (500), unwieldy", "Gamma rifles direct concentrated bursts of gamma radiation that are strong enough to overcome normal environmental protections, burning targets from a distance, though users of such weapons risk exposure to that very radiation. Many find that the destructive effects of the ray are sufficient to outweigh the risk, and targets can even be subject to radiation sickness when struck in a vital organ. Terrestrial gamma rifles and ionizing gamma rifles feed energy through a mass of radioactive material in the muzzle to produce their deadly effects. Fusion and synchrotron gamma rifles instead produce radiation in a torus near the rifle’s stock, making them far more powerful, though still dangerous to the user."),
	("Plasma Fork, 15-Notch", "Long Arms 2-H", 8, 8,850, 5, 80, knockdown, 20 charges, 1, "1", "boost 1d10", "Also known as a plasma rail gun, a plasma fork has two long metal prongs in place of a barrel. The mechanism magnetically accelerates a bolt of plasma between these two prongs, but it can also hold plasma temporarily between the prongs to charge up an even more devastating attack. Each model has a number of notches that infuse the plasma with energy, starting with 12-notch plasma forks and increasing in intensity to 15-notch, 19-notch, and 22-notch plasma forks."),
	("Plasma Fork, 19-Notch", "Long Arms 2-H", 14, 64,800, 16, 80, knockdown, 40 charges, 2, "1", "boost 2d10", "Also known as a plasma rail gun, a plasma fork has two long metal prongs in place of a barrel. The mechanism magnetically accelerates a bolt of plasma between these two prongs, but it can also hold plasma temporarily between the prongs to charge up an even more devastating attack. Each model has a number of notches that infuse the plasma with energy, starting with 12-notch plasma forks and increasing in intensity to 15-notch, 19-notch, and 22-notch plasma forks."),
	("Gyrojet Pistol, Tactical", "Small Arms 1-H", 15, 91,500, 19, 80, knockdown, 8 mini-rockets, 1, "L", "analog", "Gyrojet pistols fire mini-rockets that can hit with a force great enough to knock down targets. Gyrojet pistols are slightly larger than semiautomatic pistols, and they have a reinforced barrel. "
	("Gyrojet Pistol, Advanced", "Small Arms 1-H", 17, 212,700, 26, 80, knockdown, 8 mini-rockets, 1, "L", "analog", "Gyrojet pistols fire mini-rockets that can hit with a force great enough to knock down targets. Gyrojet pistols are slightly larger than semiautomatic pistols, and they have a reinforced barrel. "
	("Gyrojet Pistol, Elite", "Small Arms 1-H", 20, 715,800, 32, 80, knockdown, 8 mini-rockets, 1, "L", "analog", "Gyrojet pistols fire mini-rockets that can hit with a force great enough to knock down targets. Gyrojet pistols are slightly larger than semiautomatic pistols, and they have a reinforced barrel. "
	("Arc Caster, Storm", "Heavy 2-H", 11, 25,600, 17, 80, second arc 2d6, 40 charges, 4, "2", "first arc 2d6, unwieldy", "Flanked by large handles, an arc caster bristles with capacitors and antennae that release more energy than it can realistically control. While many shock weapons have a chance to arc to a second target on a hit, the arc caster is designed to achieve that feat on every shot, and particularly well-aimed strikes can sometimes arc twice. The storm and tempest models feature improvements that build upon the capabilities of static and aurora arc casters. Since there is little way to control which creatures are struck on the subsequent arcs, arc casters are generally used only by solo combatants or those with little regard for their allies’ well-being. More rarely, party members may take particular precautions against electricity damage, such as with a resistant armor spell or an electrostatic field armor upgrade, to protect themselves from an ally wielding an arc caster."),
	("Arc Caster, Tempest", "Heavy 2-H", 17, 262,000, 35, 80, second arc 4d6, 40 charges, 5, "2", "first arc 4d6, unwieldy", "Flanked by large handles, an arc caster bristles with capacitors and antennae that release more energy than it can realistically control. While many shock weapons have a chance to arc to a second target on a hit, the arc caster is designed to achieve that feat on every shot, and particularly well-aimed strikes can sometimes arc twice. The storm and tempest models feature improvements that build upon the capabilities of static and aurora arc casters. Since there is little way to control which creatures are struck on the subsequent arcs, arc casters are generally used only by solo combatants or those with little regard for their allies’ well-being. More rarely, party members may take particular precautions against electricity damage, such as with a resistant armor spell or an electrostatic field armor upgrade, to protect themselves from an ally wielding an arc caster."),
	("Nanite Thrower, Elite", "Long Arms 2-H", 15, 110,000, 0, 80, severe wound, 10 nanites, 2, "1", "deconstruct 4d6", "A nanite thrower has a cylindrical nanite canister above the stock, which serves as ammunition. Instead of firing a single projectile, the nanite thrower hurls a coherent cluster of nanites at the target. These microscopic machines burrow in and damage the target from within. Nanite throwers come in similar models to the nanite rifle0tactical, advanced, and elite. With throwers, however, this line extends to the paragon model."),
	("Nanite Thrower, Paragon", "Long Arms 2-H", 20, 830,000, 0, 80, severe wound, 10 nanites, 2, "1", "deconstruct 5d6", "A nanite thrower has a cylindrical nanite canister above the stock, which serves as ammunition. Instead of firing a single projectile, the nanite thrower hurls a coherent cluster of nanites at the target. These microscopic machines burrow in and damage the target from within. Nanite throwers come in similar models to the nanite rifle0tactical, advanced, and elite. With throwers, however, this line extends to the paragon model."),
	("Nanite Rifle, Advanced", "Sniper 2-H", 15, 131,000, 19, 80, severe wound, 10 nanites, 5, "1", "sniper (750), unwieldy", "Nanite rifles can fire nanotech-infused darts at targets from extreme ranges. Although the darts deal little damage, the nanites eat into the target immediately and can cause grievous injuries. Nanites from tactical models target the site where they land, while an advanced rifle’s nanites can spread farther within the target. An elite rifle allows its nanites to move even farther from the point struck, dealing more damage."),
	("Plasma Guide, Series-62", "Sniper 2-H", 16, 193,000, 22, 80, severe wound, 80 charges, 10, "2", "guided, sniper (750), unwieldy", "A plasma guide maintains a magnetic guidance system around its plasma discharge, which continues guiding the shot after it is fired. This increases accuracy at ranges far beyond those of typical plasma weapons and bypasses the advantage of partial cover as the magnetic guidance directs the plasma toward its target. Vesk snipers are believed to be the earliest users of the plasma guide during the Silent War, but it’s become a standard in many military and mercenary arsenals since then. This weapon has been continually refined since its invention; series-21, series-28, series-37, series-42, series-62, and series-73 plasma guides have proven generally stable and thus remain in production."),
	("Plasma Guide, Series-73", "Sniper 2-H", 20, 980,000, 40, 80, severe wound, 100 charges, 10, "2", "guided, sniper (1, 000), unwieldy", "A plasma guide maintains a magnetic guidance system around its plasma discharge, which continues guiding the shot after it is fired. This increases accuracy at ranges far beyond those of typical plasma weapons and bypasses the advantage of partial cover as the magnetic guidance directs the plasma toward its target. Vesk snipers are believed to be the earliest users of the plasma guide during the Silent War, but it’s become a standard in many military and mercenary arsenals since then. This weapon has been continually refined since its invention; series-21, series-28, series-37, series-42, series-62, and series-73 plasma guides have proven generally stable and thus remain in production."),
	("Sonic Bolter, Heavy", "Heavy 2-H", 8, 10,100, 11, 80, sicken, 20 charges, 2, "2", "antibiological, line, unwieldy", "The sound waves a sonic bolter produces tightly focus in a brief but coherent line. This concentrated, low-frequency vibration damages the body and jostles internal organs, causing dizziness, pain, and slight nausea. Members of the Android Abolitionist Front developed the light model upon discovering the effect of a similar beam. Heavy, assault, and devastator bolters can generate sufficient sound pressure to damage artificial and unliving creatures."),
	("Sonic Bolter, Assault", "Heavy 2-H", 12, 38,000, 19, 80, sicken, 20 charges, 2, "2", "antibiological, line, unwieldy", "The sound waves a sonic bolter produces tightly focus in a brief but coherent line. This concentrated, low-frequency vibration damages the body and jostles internal organs, causing dizziness, pain, and slight nausea. Members of the Android Abolitionist Front developed the light model upon discovering the effect of a similar beam. Heavy, assault, and devastator bolters can generate sufficient sound pressure to damage artificial and unliving creatures."),
	("Numbing Beam, Elite", "Long Arms 2-H", 10, 18,000, 10, 80, staggered, 20 charges, 1, "1", "nonlethal", "Complex algorithms, controls, and safeguards within a numbing beam ensure the weapon never lowers its target’s temperature to lethal levels. Tactical and advanced numbing beams see use in populated areas, while elite and paragon numbing beams are more often employed in military endeavors. Those models intended for use near civilians include prominent external computer interfaces, as though to advertise their safety features, while military models tend toward a sleek, traditional design."),
	("Hailcannon, Ultracold", "Heavy 2-H", 9, 14,300, 18, 80, staggered, 40 charges, 4, "2", "automatic", "Hailcannons use a complex integrated coolant system to generate staggering barrages of ice. Unlike with many cryo weapons, the hailcannon’s prolific output and massive barrel allow the weapon to be fired in automatic mode, which can overwhelm targets.  Subzero hailcannons are the standard model, and the increasing damage capacity of gelid, ultracold, absolute-zero, and clathrate hailcannons proves attractive to many who swear by such weapons."),
	("Numbing Beam, Paragon", "Long Arms 2-H", 15, 112,000, 21, 80, staggered, 20 charges, 1, "1", "nonlethal", "Complex algorithms, controls, and safeguards within a numbing beam ensure the weapon never lowers its target’s temperature to lethal levels. Tactical and advanced numbing beams see use in populated areas, while elite and paragon numbing beams are more often employed in military endeavors. Those models intended for use near civilians include prominent external computer interfaces, as though to advertise their safety features, while military models tend toward a sleek, traditional design."),
	("Hailcannon, Absolute-Zero", "Heavy 2-H", 13, 50,800, 27, 80, staggered, 80 charges, 5, "2", "automatic", "Hailcannons use a complex integrated coolant system to generate staggering barrages of ice. Unlike with many cryo weapons, the hailcannon’s prolific output and massive barrel allow the weapon to be fired in automatic mode, which can overwhelm targets.  Subzero hailcannons are the standard model, and the increasing damage capacity of gelid, ultracold, absolute-zero, and clathrate hailcannons proves attractive to many who swear by such weapons."),
	("Zero Cannon, Elite", "Heavy 2-H", 18, 412,800, 36, 80, staggered, 100 charges, 5, "2", "line, unwieldy", "Zero cannons project a freezing line straight out from a generator, affecting any targets within the line. A pair of tanks in the cannon’s heavy stock contain chemical coolants that produce a violent endothermic reaction when mixed in the insulated barrel. "
	("Void Rifle, Tomb-Class", "Long Arms 2-H", 11, 26,300, 11, 80, suffocate, 40 charges, 2, "1", "antibiological", "A firearm designed with crystals from the Plane of Shadow, a void rifle is unique in that power flowing through those crystals allows the rifle to fire inky bolts of life-sapping cold. The rifle’s frigid energy can harm only the living, so it does nothing to constructs and undead. Regardless, the rifle remains a favorite of followers of Urgathoa. Grave- and crypt-class void rifles are an option for standard issue among rank-and-file marines of the Eoxian navy, while tomb-, ossuary-, and barrow-class void rifles are reserved for elite forces."),
	("Huchket Rifle", "Long Arms 2-H", 3, 1,400, 5, 80, wound, 6 rounds, 1, "1", "analog", "The huchket is a generational weapon of the husk ghibranis. It includes some technological elements from the ghibrani’s past, but is otherwise appears like an archaic projectile longarm."),
	("Conqueror, Yellow Star", "Heavy 2-H", 4, 2,400, 6, 80, wound, 40 charges, 4, "3", "unwieldy", "Conquerors are perhaps the largest and most difficult to handle of the plasma weapon category. A conquerer can deliver a single devastating blast of plasma, but the weapon is rather front-heavy and difficult to maneuver. Some vesk take up the weapon as a sign of their patron deity, Damoritosh, viewing it as the ranged spiritual equivalent of the doshko. In addition to the red star, yellow star, white star, and blue star models, the particularly powerful violet star conqueror has recently made its way onto the market."),
	("Conqueror, White Star", "Heavy 2-H", 9, 15,200, 19, 80, wound, 40 charges, 4, "3", "unwieldy", "Conquerors are perhaps the largest and most difficult to handle of the plasma weapon category. A conquerer can deliver a single devastating blast of plasma, but the weapon is rather front-heavy and difficult to maneuver. Some vesk take up the weapon as a sign of their patron deity, Damoritosh, viewing it as the ranged spiritual equivalent of the doshko. In addition to the red star, yellow star, white star, and blue star models, the particularly powerful violet star conqueror has recently made its way onto the market."),
	("Plasma Flare, Luminous", "Heavy 2-H", 5, 2,950, 7, 80, 0, 20 charges, 1, "2", "bright, unwieldy", "Azlanti arms scientists developed the plasma flare as a assault weapon and a tactical aid. The weapon hurls bright balls of plasma at foes, scorching them and illuminating the area for better target designation in situations of diminished light. The Aeon Guard also finds the radiance to be an effective intimidation tactic, especially against civilizations that have yet to develop advanced technology."),
	("Trilaser, Tactical", "Small Arms 1-H", 5, 3,200, 3, 80, burn 1d4, 20 charges, 1, "L", "aeon", "Members of the Aeon Guard who function in support roles or who are assigned to missions where subtlety is key favor the unique design of the trilaser. The weapon is more effective than but just as light as typical laser small arms, and even more so with a slotted aeon stone. A trilaser is also a prestige item, since carrying one openly is a privilege Aeon Guards can enjoy even in civilian garb."),
	("Hunting Rifle", "Long Arms 2-H", 1, 240, 4, 90, 0, 6 rounds, 1, "1", "analog", "This basic rifle is used mainly for personal defense and hunting. More advanced rifles have military uses. "
	("Reaction Cannon, Light", "Heavy 2-H", 1, 250, 5, 90, 0, 6 rounds, 1, "3", "penetrating", "An ancient yet still popular vesk weapon, the reaction cannon uses advanced materials and technology to redirect the recoil of a projectile back into the projectile itself, making it an extremely damaging heavy weapon. "
	("Reaction Cannon, Tactical", "Heavy 2-H", 7, 6,100, 11, 90, 0, 6 rounds, 1, "3", "penetrating", "An ancient yet still popular vesk weapon, the reaction cannon uses advanced materials and technology to redirect the recoil of a projectile back into the projectile itself, making it an extremely damaging heavy weapon. "
	("Combat Rifle", "Long Arms 2-H", 10, 16,500, 13, 90, 0, 12 rounds, 1, "1", "analog", "This utilitarian rifle is favored by mercenaries who aren’t looking for flashy weapons."),
	("Coil Rifle, Assassin", "Sniper 2-H", 19, 590,000, 42, 90, bleed 4d6, 16 rounds, 1, "2", "sniper (750.)", "A coil rifle is a long, slender firearm surrounded by a coil that generates carefully aligned magnetic fields that accelerate a single round with impressive power and accuracy. Precision coil rifles are the most affordable of these weapons, while specialist coil rifles have greater range and efficacy. Rangefinder, saboteur, and assassin coil rifles are especially deadly weapons that are appreciated by true connoisseurs, veteran mercenaries, and experienced firearm specialists."),
	("Laser Pistol, Corona", "Small Arms 1-H", 6, 4,270, 5, 90, burn 1d4, 20 charges, 1, "L", "n/a", "The laser pistol is possibly the most common small arm used by explorers, guards, mercenaries, and traders. Laser pistols are light and reliable, yet they still deal a respectable amount of damage. "
	("Laser Pistol, Aphelion", "Small Arms 1-H", 9, 14,820, 7, 90, burn 1d4, 40 charges, 2, "L", "boost 1d4", "The laser pistol is possibly the most common small arm used by explorers, guards, mercenaries, and traders. Laser pistols are light and reliable, yet they still deal a respectable amount of damage. "
	("Laser Pistol, Perihelion", "Small Arms 1-H", 12, 40,200, 10, 90, burn 2d4, 40 charges, 2, "L", "n/a", "The laser pistol is possibly the most common small arm used by explorers, guards, mercenaries, and traders. Laser pistols are light and reliable, yet they still deal a respectable amount of damage. "
	("Laser Pistol, Parallax", "Small Arms 1-H", 14, 82,000, 12, 90, burn 3d4, 80 charges, 4, "L", "boost 2d4", "The laser pistol is possibly the most common small arm used by explorers, guards, mercenaries, and traders. Laser pistols are light and reliable, yet they still deal a respectable amount of damage. "
	("Divergent Laser, Wide-Spectrum", "Heavy 2-H", 18, 414,000, 31, 90, burn 3d6, 40 charges, 2, "2", "blast, unwieldy", "Originally developed alongside convergent lasers, divergent lasers use multiple laser beams emitting from a blocky casing to produce a cone-shaped output. This weapon’s damage is significantly less than that achieved by the convergent lasers, but the same systems that synchronize wavelengths in a convergent laser allow the divergent laser to focus on multiple targets. The single-color beam of a single-wave divergent laser sets it apart from the shimmering colors of a multiwave divergent laser. A wide-spectrum divergent laser has a nearly white beam and could be mistaken for a spotlight at a glance0though not by a target struck by one!"
	("Acid Dart Rifle, Dual", "Long Arms 2-H", 7, 6,900, 9, 90, corrode 2d4, 24 darts, 2, "1", "analog", "An acid dart rifle has a nonreactive polymer reservoir that can be filled with whatever acid the wielder desires. The automatic loading process fills the rifle darts with acid as they are moved into the chamber. Dual acid dart rifles fire two darts simultaneously, while complex acid dart rifles hold concentrated doses of acid."),
	("Acid Dart Rifle, Complex", "Long Arms 2-H", 12, 39,200, 18, 90, corrode 4d4, 48 darts, 4, "2", "analog", "An acid dart rifle has a nonreactive polymer reservoir that can be filled with whatever acid the wielder desires. The automatic loading process fills the rifle darts with acid as they are moved into the chamber. Dual acid dart rifles fire two darts simultaneously, while complex acid dart rifles hold concentrated doses of acid."),
	("Sonic Bolter, Devastator", "Heavy 2-H", 18, 398,000, 19, 90, sicken, 20 charges, 2, "2", "antibiological, line, unwieldy", "The sound waves a sonic bolter produces tightly focus in a brief but coherent line. This concentrated, low-frequency vibration damages the body and jostles internal organs, causing dizziness, pain, and slight nausea. Members of the Android Abolitionist Front developed the light model upon discovering the effect of a similar beam. Heavy, assault, and devastator bolters can generate sufficient sound pressure to damage artificial and unliving creatures."),
	("Energy Converter, Tactical", "Heavy 2-H", 4, 2,400, 3, 90, staggered, 20 charges, 1, "3", "explode (10), unwieldy", "Boxy devices covered with various gauges and protruding antennae, energy converters resemble dangerously experimental pieces of hardware. These devices invert matter-antimatter annihilation; instead of generating massive amounts of heat from a tiny speck of matter, an energy converter generates a tiny speck of matter by drawing an incredible amount of heat energy from a nearby area. Tactical, advanced, and elite energy converters each create relatively larger flecks of matter, drawing their energy from a larger area in order to do so."),
	("Energy Converter, Advanced", "Heavy 2-H", 10, 20,900, 9, 90, staggered, 20 charges, 1, "3", "explode (15), unwieldy", "Boxy devices covered with various gauges and protruding antennae, energy converters resemble dangerously experimental pieces of hardware. These devices invert matter-antimatter annihilation; instead of generating massive amounts of heat from a tiny speck of matter, an energy converter generates a tiny speck of matter by drawing an incredible amount of heat energy from a nearby area. Tactical, advanced, and elite energy converters each create relatively larger flecks of matter, drawing their energy from a larger area in order to do so."),
	("Trilaser, Advanced", "Small Arms 1-H", 10, 17,600, 7, 90, burn 2d4, 40 charges, 2, "L", "aeon", "Members of the Aeon Guard who function in support roles or who are assigned to missions where subtlety is key favor the unique design of the trilaser. The weapon is more effective than but just as light as typical laser small arms, and even more so with a slotted aeon stone. A trilaser is also a prestige item, since carrying one openly is a privilege Aeon Guards can enjoy even in civilian garb."),
	("Trilaser, Elite", "Small Arms 1-H", 15, 105,600, 14, 90, burn 3d4, 40 charges, 2, "L", "aeon", "Members of the Aeon Guard who function in support roles or who are assigned to missions where subtlety is key favor the unique design of the trilaser. The weapon is more effective than but just as light as typical laser small arms, and even more so with a slotted aeon stone. A trilaser is also a prestige item, since carrying one openly is a privilege Aeon Guards can enjoy even in civilian garb."),
	("Cestus Pistol, Tactical", "Small Arms 1-H", 1, 250, 2, 5, Bleed 1d4, 1, 1, "0", "Conceal, Punch gun", "This weapon consists of a black leather glove that is mounted with a small, single-round firearm. Unlike most firearms, the weapon is designed to fire when pressure is placed upon its barrel rather than using a hand-based triggering mechanism. As a result, wielders must press a cestus pistol up against whatever they intend to shoot in order to discharge the weapon’s round, giving the weapon limited range."),
	("Cestus Pistol, Advanced", "Small Arms 1-H", 6, 4,170, 6, 6, Bleed 1d4, 1, 1, "0", "Conceal, Punch gun", "This weapon consists of a black leather glove that is mounted with a small, single-round firearm. Unlike most firearms, the weapon is designed to fire when pressure is placed upon its barrel rather than using a hand-based triggering mechanism. As a result, wielders must press a cestus pistol up against whatever they intend to shoot in order to discharge the weapon’s round, giving the weapon limited range."),
	("Cestus Pistol, Elite", "Small Arms 1-H", 11, 24,400, 19, 7, Bleed 1d4, 1, 1, "0", "Conceal, Punch gun", "This weapon consists of a black leather glove that is mounted with a small, single-round firearm. Unlike most firearms, the weapon is designed to fire when pressure is placed upon its barrel rather than using a hand-based triggering mechanism. As a result, wielders must press a cestus pistol up against whatever they intend to shoot in order to discharge the weapon’s round, giving the weapon limited range."),
	("Cestus Pistol, Paragon", "Small Arms 1-H", 16, 162,000, 39, 8, Bleed 1d4, 1, 1, "0", "Conceal, Punch gun", "This weapon consists of a black leather glove that is mounted with a small, single-round firearm. Unlike most firearms, the weapon is designed to fire when pressure is placed upon its barrel rather than using a hand-based triggering mechanism. As a result, wielders must press a cestus pistol up against whatever they intend to shoot in order to discharge the weapon’s round, giving the weapon limited range."),
	("Glove Needler, Tactical", "Small Arms 1-H", 2, 560, 2, 9, Injection DC +2, 1, 1, "0", "Conceal, Injection, Punch gun", "Featuring a hand-mounted firing device that injects its target with acidic compounds, this weapon resembles a cross between a caustoject and cestus pistol. By default, the weapon uses a miniature battery to create caustic fields to inject into foes, but it can launch syringes of other substances when properly loaded with them."),
	("Glove Needler, Advanced", "Small Arms 1-H", 7, 5,800, 6, 10, Injection DC +2, 1, 1, "0", "Conceal, Injection, Punch gun", "Featuring a hand-mounted firing device that injects its target with acidic compounds, this weapon resembles a cross between a caustoject and cestus pistol. By default, the weapon uses a miniature battery to create caustic fields to inject into foes, but it can launch syringes of other substances when properly loaded with them."),
	("Glove Needler, Elite", "Small Arms 1-H", 14, 69,300, 19, 11, Injection DC +2, 1, 1, "0", "Conceal, Injection, Punch gun", "Featuring a hand-mounted firing device that injects its target with acidic compounds, this weapon resembles a cross between a caustoject and cestus pistol. By default, the weapon uses a miniature battery to create caustic fields to inject into foes, but it can launch syringes of other substances when properly loaded with them."),
	("Glove Needler, Paragon", "Small Arms 1-H", 20, 765,000, 39, 12, Injection DC +2, 1, 1, "0", "Conceal, Injection, Punch gun", "Featuring a hand-mounted firing device that injects its target with acidic compounds, this weapon resembles a cross between a caustoject and cestus pistol. By default, the weapon uses a miniature battery to create caustic fields to inject into foes, but it can launch syringes of other substances when properly loaded with them."),
	("Cluster Launcher, Advanced", "Heavy 2-H", 12, 35,800, 0, 60, 0, 10 grenades, 1, "3", "cluster (10.)", "The cluster launcher fires multiple grenades as a single shot, granting those grenades increased range and a larger blast radius. Each of the models0tactical, advanced, elite, and paragon0features an increase in range, capacity, and overall explosive power."),
	("Cluster Launcher, Elite", "Heavy 2-H", 15, 105,000, 0, 70, 0, 12 grenades, 1, "3", "cluster (10.)", "The cluster launcher fires multiple grenades as a single shot, granting those grenades increased range and a larger blast radius. Each of the models0tactical, advanced, elite, and paragon0features an increase in range, capacity, and overall explosive power."),
	("Cluster Launcher, Paragon", "Heavy 2-H", 18, 360,000, 0, 80, 0, 16 grenades, 1, "3", "cluster (15.)", "The cluster launcher fires multiple grenades as a single shot, granting those grenades increased range and a larger blast radius. Each of the models0tactical, advanced, elite, and paragon0features an increase in range, capacity, and overall explosive power."),
	("Cluster Launcher, Tactical", "Heavy 2-H", 6, 4,150, 0, 100, 0, 8 grenades, 1, "2", "cluster (5.)", "The cluster launcher fires multiple grenades as a single shot, granting those grenades increased range and a larger blast radius. Each of the models0tactical, advanced, elite, and paragon0features an increase in range, capacity, and overall explosive power."),
	("Minelayer, Command", "Heavy 2-H", 17, 243,000, 0, 40, 0, 20 grenades, 1, "2", "mine", "A specialized form of grenade launcher, a minelayer surrounds its ordnance with a cushioning magnetic field. Grenades must be loaded into a minelayer individually, and a user can decide which grenade to fire with each shot. A merc minelayer holds up to 8 grenades at once, a squad model holds 12, a platoon version can carry up to 16, and the command minelayer can hold an impressive 20 grenades."),
	("Minelayer, Merc", "Heavy 2-H", 3, 1,470, 0, 50, 0, 8 grenades, 1, "2", "mine", "A specialized form of grenade launcher, a minelayer surrounds its ordnance with a cushioning magnetic field. Grenades must be loaded into a minelayer individually, and a user can decide which grenade to fire with each shot. A merc minelayer holds up to 8 grenades at once, a squad model holds 12, a platoon version can carry up to 16, and the command minelayer can hold an impressive 20 grenades."),
	("Minelayer, Platoon", "Heavy 2-H", 13, 51,400, 0, 60, 0, 16 grenades, 1, "2", "mine", "A specialized form of grenade launcher, a minelayer surrounds its ordnance with a cushioning magnetic field. Grenades must be loaded into a minelayer individually, and a user can decide which grenade to fire with each shot. A merc minelayer holds up to 8 grenades at once, a squad model holds 12, a platoon version can carry up to 16, and the command minelayer can hold an impressive 20 grenades."),
	("Minelayer, Squad", "Heavy 2-H", 7, 6,930, 0, 80, 0, 12 grenades, 1, "2", "mine", "A specialized form of grenade launcher, a minelayer surrounds its ordnance with a cushioning magnetic field. Grenades must be loaded into a minelayer individually, and a user can decide which grenade to fire with each shot. A merc minelayer holds up to 8 grenades at once, a squad model holds 12, a platoon version can carry up to 16, and the command minelayer can hold an impressive 20 grenades.");
INSERT INTO Armor (name, itemlevel, type, price, EACbonus, KACbonus, maxdexbonus, armorcheckpenalty, speedadjustment, bulk, special) VALUES
	("Stationwear, Flight Suit", 1, "Light", 95, 0, 1, 6, 0, 0, "L", Many types of reinforced clothing afford protection without sacrificing comfort or fashion. The prevalence of this kind of light armor on Absalom Station has led to the colloquial term “stationwear.” Stationwear ranges in style from casual wear to business suits and more formal garb. The usual environmental protections of armor are concealed in the design of these outfits. The grades of armor0business, casual, elite, and flight suit0refer to the quality of the garments, not the style."),
	("Ceremonial Plate, Troop", 1, "Heavy", 110, 1, 3, 2, -3, -10, "3", While this heavy armor of sculpted metal plates offers good protection to the wearer, its main purpose is to intimidate enemies. Often used for honor guards, military exercises, or parades, ceremonial plate is usually brightly colored or made of shining metal, with elaborate helmets."),
	("Shobhad Harness, Recruit", 1, "Light", 150, 0, 2, 4, -1, 0, "1", "While a few shobhads still wear armor crafted from leather reinforced with metal plates, the shobhad-neh typically incorporate more advanced materials such as ballistic mesh and ceramic plates into the traditional designs of their ancestors. Despite having a high bulk for light armor, war harnesses are well padded and ventilated for comfort, as shobhads rarely remove their armor. Though some shobhad disdain the life support systems built into advanced armor, most recognize their value. The protective headgear, leggings, and sleeves used for such conditions stow discretely out of sight when not needed.
(The shobhad war harness comes in recruit, veteran, warleader, and chieftain varieties. The grades vary by quality of manufacture rather than appearance."	"
	("Reinforced EVA Suit, I", 1, "Heavy", 200, 1, 4, 1, -3, -5, "2", Although designed for extravehicular activity in hazardous conditions, reinforced EVA suits function as durable, if clunky, heavy armor. This full-body suit has a rigid shell covering the back and chest, with heavy gloves, padded boots, and rugged fabric rounding out the ensemble. A wide helmet design provides good visibility and includes a retractable glare shield. The suit’s excellent air recycling makes for a more comfortable environment than many more battle-worthy designs."),
	("Second Skin", 1, "Light", 250, 1, 2, 5, 0, 0, "L", This flexible body stocking fits tightly against its wearer and can be worn under ordinary clothes. If a second skin matches the wearer’s skin tone, this type of light armor can be difficult to detect. A second skin can also accept upgrades, making it popular for celebrities, diplomats, and other individuals who want protection without appearing to wear armor."),
	("Golemforged Plating, I", 1, "Heavy", 250, 2, 5, 0, -3, -10, "3", An economical choice for many mercenaries, golemforged plating is one of the universe’s most popular heavy armors. Golemforged plating consists of a close-fitting polycarbonate suit fitted with ports and sockets to fit most armor customization options. Suits of golemforged plating include flexible boots and gloves as well as a standard helmet with a clear visor."),
	("Estex Suit, I", 1, "Light", 410, 0, 1, 5, -1, 0, "1", Estex is a thick, durable fabric most often used to make flight suits and environmental suits. Estex suits cover the wearer from the neck down and can be modified with armor upgrades as needed. Higher-quality estex suits grant a better level of protection and allow for more upgrades, though they are often bulkier than comparable suits of light armor."),
	("Lashunta Ringwear, I", 1, "Heavy", 415, 2, 4, 2, -2, -5, "2", These beautiful suits of heavy armor feature engraved metal bands that fit above and below the body’s major joints. Metal guards, woven chain sheets, and force fields stretch between the bands to form a complete set of protective gear. Tinted crystals are often added during the forging process to the ore used for ringwear to create glimmering suits of different hues."),
	("Kasatha Microcord, I", 2, "Light", 460, 1, 3, 3, -1, 0, "1", These suits of ribbed protective fabric are slightly less advanced than comparable light armor but still provide good-quality protection at an affordable price. Kasatha-made microcord suits are typically one-piece outfits of dark colors, sometimes with glowing trim, but other manufacturers produce such suits in a variety of colors and styles."),
	("Hidden Soldier Armor", 2, "Heavy", 465, 3, 5, 2, -2, -5, "2", Made by the kasatha, these suits of heavy armor are so named for their slitted helmets, which reveal only the eyes. A rebreather lets the wearer keep their faces completely covered. A ceramic breastplate, shoulder guards, bracers, and greaves protect the wearer while facilitating the graceful kasathan close-combat style."),
	("Formian Plate, Worker", 2, "Heavy", 480, 3, 6, 1, -3, -5, "3", The exoskeletons of deceased formians can be crafted into armor that retains some of these creatures’ defenses."),
	("Preserver's Mantle, I", 2, "Light", 520, 1, 2, 6, 0, 0, "L", The Xenowardens bioengineered the preserver’s mantle as a form of living armor. Rather than donning the mantle, a creature steps onto it and allows the armor to wrap itself around and over the creature’s body. Insulating moss acts as padding, while vines and wood match the strength of the advanced composites of other light armors. When the armor’s environmental protections are activated, the external surface of the plants interlace into an  airtight barrier, while the moss regulates the temperature and converts exhaled gases back into breathable air. Like other armors, the mantle must be adjusted to fit a new wearer (though this requires a Life Science check, rather than an Engineering check."),
	("Zeizerer Diffractor, I", 2, "Light", 650, 2, 2, 4, 0, 0, "L", Crafted by the talented smiths of the drow of Apostae, this armor is designed to be light and supple. Its refractive planes are all at the molecular level, resulting in armor that appears to almost absorb light. House Zeizerer is the main distributor of this armor to the rest of the Pact Worlds, but other drow houses have been known to manufacture their own versions."),
	("Freebooter Armor, I", 2, "Light", 750, 2, 3, 4, 0, 0, "L", Popularized by the Free Captains of the Diaspora, freebooter armor features an armored jacket or breastplate, heavy boots and gloves, numerous straps and hidden weapons, and a helmet. Novice explorers and mercenaries beginning their career sometimes choose freebooter armor for the air of rakish experience this light armor lends its wearer."),
	("Iridishell, Basic", 2, "Heavy", 755, 3, 6, 2, -2, -5, "2", These gleaming metal plates lock together to form a suit of heavy armor reminiscent of an insect’s shell. Although the iridishell was initially designed for shirrens, its beauty combined and functionality makes it a popular choice for many. More expensive suits of iridishell not only offer more protection but feature elaborate designs with gold or silver trim and embedded jewels."),
	("Kyokor Plating, I", 2, "Heavy", 800, 2, 4, 3, -1, -5, "1", "Scavengers on Daimalko dare to brave the wastes of their world to gather the enamel-like hulls that kyokors occasionally shed from their crowns. These toothy moltings are enormous, and once they’re retrieved, they require a great deal of effort to grind into plates that can be used to craft armor. Despite this and the dangers of gathering the requisite moltings, suits of kyokor plating are in demand throughout the universe, making collection of the raw materials and subsequent forging into lucrative careers.
	("Mining Jack, I", 2, "Heavy", 825, 4, 6, 1, -3, -10, "3", Asteroid miners wear mining jacks for both life support and protection against the hazards of vacuum mining. As they are designed for use in low and zero gravity, the jacks are quite bulky, with alloys chosen for strength and durability rather than weight. Because miners often spend the entire day in a vacuum, mining jacks have storage compartments  accessible within the armor. The breastplate of a mining jack can expand outward without being removed, allowing the wearer a modest amount of space to pull her arms inside and enjoy a beverage or meal. Each suit includes a pair of miniature airlocks that allow safe transfer of small objects from outside to inside the suit as a full action. A pair of mining jacks can even link locks to trade gear without exposing the item or either wearer to vacuum. The first mining jacks were dwarven designs, but their ingenious design and utility have made them popular throughout the Diaspora."),
	("Vesk Brigandine, I", 2, "Light", 950, 2, 2, 5, 0, 0, "L", The core of vesk brigandine is a lightweight breastplate made of interlocking polymer hexagons. It flexes almost as well as fabric under normal use, but it becomes rigid as steel in response to impact. Its slim profile lets it be worn either over or under clothing. More advanced brigandine designs incorporate inertial dampeners to enhance protection. Vesk who prize mobility over maximum protection favor this style of light armor, and its use has spread throughout the Pact Worlds to the degree that any similar design is often referred to as vesk brigandine."),
	("Hellknight Plate, Armiger", 2, "Heavy", 980, 4, 5, 2, -2, -10, "3", The stern and unrelenting Hellknights are known as much for their distinctive plate armor as for their fearsome adherence to rigid order. This variant of ceremonial plate is predominantly black with protruding spikes, and each Hellknight order has its own distinct design."),
	("Thinplate", 2, "Heavy", 1,000, 4, 6, 2, -3, -10, "3", Devised by androids, thinplate is a dense polyethylene layer that looks lightweight while providing significant protection. This type of heavy armor is thin enough to be worn under loose outfits, but the rigid polyethylene restricts movement and slows the wearer. Thinplate can be molded into a variety of styles, though a simple breastplate plus limb guards is the most common form."),
	("Hardened Resin", 3, "Light", 1,200, 2, 3, 5, -1, 0, "1", Many insectile haans of Bretheda shun all but the simplest tools, but some skilled armorsmiths among them incorporate pieces of their own molted exoskeletons into simple protective shells. While the armor usually built to fit Large creatures, suits designed for smaller wearers can sometimes be found."),
	("Skitterhide, I", 3, "Light", 1,200, 2, 3, 5, 0, 0, "L", This armor is made from the harvested hides of the remains of destroyed undead, making it resemble a macabre skinsuit. Ossified studs and embellishments reinforce the alchemically treated skin, which is otherwise designed to support Corpse Fleet agents favoring speed and stealth."),
	("Carbon Skin, Graphite", 3, "Light", 1,220, 3, 4, 4, -1, 0, "1", Though these suits of light armor appear to be made of stiff fabric, they are actually woven from carbon fibers. Higher-quality carbon skins are reinforced with carbon allotypes, such as white carbon or diamond, and the heightened sheen of the fabric hints at their expensive construction."),
	("Defiance Series, Squad", 3, "Heavy", 1,220, 5, 8, 1, -4, -10, "3", The defiance series of heavy armor is the workhorse of squad armor. A formed hard shell overlays a suit of para-aramids, creating a bulky and solid protective outfit. Defiance series helmets have wide, tinted visors to allow peripheral vision."),
	("Stationwear, Casual", 3, "Light", 1,300, 1, 2, 6, 0, 0, "L", Many types of reinforced clothing afford protection without sacrificing comfort or fashion. The prevalence of this kind of light armor on Absalom Station has led to the colloquial term “stationwear.” Stationwear ranges in style from casual wear to business suits and more formal garb. The usual environmental protections of armor are concealed in the design of these outfits. The grades of armor0business, casual, elite, and flight suit0refer to the quality of the garments, not the style."),
	("Reinforced EVA Suit, II", 3, "Heavy", 1,300, 4, 8, 1, -3, -5, "3", Although designed for extravehicular activity in hazardous conditions, reinforced EVA suits function as durable, if clunky, heavy armor. This full-body suit has a rigid shell covering the back and chest, with heavy gloves, padded boots, and rugged fabric rounding out the ensemble. A wide helmet design provides good visibility and includes a retractable glare shield. The suit’s excellent air recycling makes for a more comfortable environment than many more battle-worthy designs."),
	("Clearweave, I", 3, "Light", 1,350, 3, 3, 5, 0, 0, "L", "The formfitting fabric of clearweave light armor is completely transparent to better display the fashion choices beneath it. Discrete force field generators along each side resemble intricate tattoos as much as they resemble circuitry. Clearweave darkens automatically when exposed to harmful solar radiation or laser fire. 
	("Regimental Dress, I", 3, "Light", 1,450, 2, 3, 5, 0, 0, "L", Regimental dress is the light armor counterpart to ceremonial plate. Often stylized to the extreme, regimental dress comes in as many variations as there are military forces, militias, and private security details. Regimental dress uses advanced fibers and strategically placed ceramic plates to avoid ruining the design lines of the uniforms. A force field projector concealed in the collar activates as needed to provide life support and protection for the head. Integrated holographic imaging projects rank insignia, medals, and ribbons, and supports gesture-activated informational displays for each honor."),
	("Golemforged Plating, II", 3, "Heavy", 1,610, 5, 7, 2, -2, -10, "3", An economical choice for many mercenaries, golemforged plating is one of the universe’s most popular heavy armors. Golemforged plating consists of a close-fitting polycarbonate suit fitted with ports and sockets to fit most armor customization options. Suits of golemforged plating include flexible boots and gloves as well as a standard helmet with a clear visor."),
	("Aeon Guard, Battle Dress (Trooper)", 3, "Heavy", 1,650, 5, 7, 2, -3, -10, "3", "Standard issue for soldiers of the Azlanti Star Empire’s elite military, Aeon Guard battle dress is a suit of heavy armor consisting of close-fitting ceramic and polycarbonate plates overlaid with an energy-reflective molecular coating. SpecOps armor, designed for use by Aeon Guard specialists, is of the same design but in a lighter, more agile package. In addition to slots for traditional armor upgrades, each suit of Aeon Guard battle dress also includes additional aeon upgrade slots that can be used to house only aeon stones. Placing an aeon stone in an aeon upgrade slot allows you to benefit from the aeon stone’s abilities as if it was orbiting your head. In the Azlanti Star Empire, civilian possession of a suit of Aeon Guard battle dress is a criminal offense punishable by death.
	("Formian Plate, Warrior", 4, "Heavy", 1,830, 5, 8, 1, -3, -5, "3", The exoskeletons of deceased formians can be crafted into armor that retains some of these creatures’ defenses."),
	("Shobhad Harness, Veteran", 4, "Light", 1,850, 3, 5, 5, -1, 0, "1", "While a few shobhads still wear armor crafted from leather reinforced with metal plates, the shobhad-neh typically incorporate more advanced materials such as ballistic mesh and ceramic plates into the traditional designs of their ancestors. Despite having a high bulk for light armor, war harnesses are well padded and ventilated for comfort, as shobhads rarely remove their armor. Though some shobhad disdain the life support systems built into advanced armor, most recognize their value. The protective headgear, leggings, and sleeves used for such conditions stow discretely out of sight when not needed.
	("Lashunta Tempweave, Basic", 4, "Light", 1,950, 4, 4, 5, 0, 0, "L", Lashuntas developed tempweave light armor by threading temperature-regulating wires through reinforced clothing. The result is a protective, flexible outfit that maintains a comfortable temperature for the wearer. Most tempweave outfits feature a fitted tunic over breeches, making them a popular choice for explorers venturing to hot or humid environments."),
	("Kalo Encounter Suit, I", 4, "Heavy", 1,980, 7, 8, 2, -3, -10, "3", When they first ventured beyond the frigid seas of Kalo-Mahoi, the kalo brought the waters of their moon with them in specially engineered suits. The kalo encounter suit represents the latest evolution of that design0a portable ocean that keeps the kalo at the near freezing temperatures they prefer. The suit’s air supply doubles as ballast to keep the wearer neutrally buoyant in water despite the armor’s weight, and the idiomatic design accommodates and protects the kalo’s swimming membranes. While the armor can be adapted to circulate water instead of air, kalos prefer their comfort of their own technology. Similarly, the filters and seals of kalo encounter suits can be adapted to the needs of air breathers, although such suits tend to accumulate excess moisture and develop mold or mildew."),
	("Grave Mantle, Enlisted", 4, "Light", 2,100, 4, 5, 4, 0, 0, "L", "The utilitarian grave mantle is common both on Eox and among the Eoxian expatriates of the Corpse Fleet. The base model worn by rankand- file troops consists of a tabard of ballistic fabric worn over plastic mesh, with additional layers of fabric reinforcing the joints. More expensive models enhance the mesh with nanowire and place ceramic plates beneath the tabard. Despite Eoxian armies having no need for air, grave mantles retain life support systems as a defense against corrosive atmospheres and related hazards.
	("Acrochor Hide, Basic", 4, "Light", 2,100, 5, 5, 5, 0, 0, "L", Crafted from the hides of acrochors0serpentine predators that crush their prey (see page 55)0these suits of light armor offer both protection and flexibility. Acrochor hide has the archaic armor special property."),
	("Dendron Armor, Ash", 4, "Heavy", 2,100, 5, 8, 3, -2, -5, "2", "A living defense designed by the Xenowardens, dendron armor melds bioengineered wood with advanced microbespun polymers. A mossy layer beneath this outer shell provides cushioning and life support. Xenowardens stylize this heavy armor to resemble the sentient trees found on Castrovel and other verdant worlds. The organic design of dendron armor makes adding upgrades a challenge, but it offers a good balance between mobility and protection.
	("Defrex Hide, Basic", 4, "Light", 2,250, 5, 5, 4, 0, 0, "L", Made from the hide of a ferocious mammal native to Vesk-2, this light armor is popular among vesk but less often worn by other races. Tanned stretches of the creature’s thick hide are stitched together with metal wires, and the suits are reinforced with metal studs or scales."),
	("Ceremonial Plate, Officer", 4, "Heavy", 2,275, 6, 8, 2, -2, -5, "2", While this heavy armor of sculpted metal plates offers good protection to the wearer, its main purpose is to intimidate enemies. Often used for honor guards, military exercises, or parades, ceremonial plate is usually brightly colored or made of shining metal, with elaborate helmets."),
	("Formian Hide, Basic", 4, "Heavy", 2,400, 7, 8, 2, -3, -5, "2", The vicious wars between lashuntas and formians drove many technomagical advances, including this armor made to emulate the chitinous skins of formians. The armor includes a helmet that boosts the wearer’s natural telepathy; if you have the limited telepathy racial trait, you add 10 feet to the range of that ability. This increase doesn’t stack with other effects that extend the range of your telepathy, such as a psychic booster."),
	("Stationwear, Business", 5, "Light", 2,600, 2, 3, 6, 0, 0, "L", Many types of reinforced clothing afford protection without sacrificing comfort or fashion. The prevalence of this kind of light armor on Absalom Station has led to the colloquial term “stationwear.” Stationwear ranges in style from casual wear to business suits and more formal garb. The usual environmental protections of armor are concealed in the design of these outfits. The grades of armor0business, casual, elite, and flight suit0refer to the quality of the garments, not the style."),
	("Vesk Brigandine, II", 5, "Light", 2,650, 5, 5, 5, 0, 0, "L", The core of vesk brigandine is a lightweight breastplate made of interlocking polymer hexagons. It flexes almost as well as fabric under normal use, but it becomes rigid as steel in response to impact. Its slim profile lets it be worn either over or under clothing. More advanced brigandine designs incorporate inertial dampeners to enhance protection. Vesk who prize mobility over maximum protection favor this style of light armor, and its use has spread throughout the Pact Worlds to the degree that any similar design is often referred to as vesk brigandine."),
	("Estex Suit, II", 5, "Light", 2,700, 4, 5, 5, -1, 0, "1", Estex is a thick, durable fabric most often used to make flight suits and environmental suits. Estex suits cover the wearer from the neck down and can be modified with armor upgrades as needed. Higher-quality estex suits grant a better level of protection and allow for more upgrades, though they are often bulkier than comparable suits of light armor."),
	("Mining Jack, II", 5, "Heavy", 2,750, 8, 11, 1, -3, -10, "3", Asteroid miners wear mining jacks for both life support and protection against the hazards of vacuum mining. As they are designed for use in low and zero gravity, the jacks are quite bulky, with alloys chosen for strength and durability rather than weight. Because miners often spend the entire day in a vacuum, mining jacks have storage compartments  accessible within the armor. The breastplate of a mining jack can expand outward without being removed, allowing the wearer a modest amount of space to pull her arms inside and enjoy a beverage or meal. Each suit includes a pair of miniature airlocks that allow safe transfer of small objects from outside to inside the suit as a full action. A pair of mining jacks can even link locks to trade gear without exposing the item or either wearer to vacuum. The first mining jacks were dwarven designs, but their ingenious design and utility have made them popular throughout the Diaspora."),
	("Lashunta Ringwear, II", 5, "Heavy", 2,970, 8, 10, 2, -2, -5, "2", These beautiful suits of heavy armor feature engraved metal bands that fit above and below the body’s major joints. Metal guards, woven chain sheets, and force fields stretch between the bands to form a complete set of protective gear. Tinted crystals are often added during the forging process to the ore used for ringwear to create glimmering suits of different hues."),
	("D-Suit, I", 5, "Light", 2,980, 5, 6, 5, 0, 0, "L", Disembarkment suits, or d-suits, are designed for spacefarers who expect to leave their ship and visit a planet’s surface. Most d-suits are jumpsuits or flight suits worn under reinforced breeches, heavy boots, and a thick jacket. A helmet or rebreather and a utility belt with an attached holster complete the outfit."),
	("Hardplate, Basic", 5, "Heavy", 3,000, 10, 11, 3, -2, -5, "2", Kishalee building materials are some of the sturdiest and long-lasting substances ever made, and kish have taken debris from collapsed structures0and have sometimes even intentionally demolished buildings0to make these suits of heavy armor. Hardplate has the archaic armor special property."),
	("Enforcer Armor, I", 5, "Heavy", 3,100, 9, 10, 2, -4, -10, "3", "The faceless, slate-gray design of enforcer armor blends intimidation and anonymity. This heavy armor’s design echoes the aegis series’ personal tank approach, albeit with markedly inferior protection. Enforcer armor often towers a full foot over the wearer’s natural height, with most of the wearer’s head safely sheltered behind the breastplate and sensory input handled through projected video and audio feeds. Criminal organizations use enforcer armor to keep their hired muscle impersonal and enigmatic.
	("Fossilwrap, I", 5, "Heavy", 3,100, 9, 9, 2, -2, -5, "2", Meant for first-wave boarding actions, fossilwrap armor is a cage of alchemically treated bones and steel. This armor is meant to shrug off most incoming blows while giving the wearer some amount of mobility in the thick of combat."),
	("Hellknight Plate, Lictor", 5, "Heavy", 3,300, 9, 10, 2, -2, -10, "3", The stern and unrelenting Hellknights are known as much for their distinctive plate armor as for their fearsome adherence to rigid order. This variant of ceremonial plate is predominantly black with protruding spikes, and each Hellknight order has its own distinct design."),
	("Kasatha Microcord, II", 6, "Light", 3,670, 6, 8, 4, -1, 0, "L", These suits of ribbed protective fabric are slightly less advanced than comparable light armor but still provide good-quality protection at an affordable price. Kasatha-made microcord suits are typically one-piece outfits of dark colors, sometimes with glowing trim, but other manufacturers produce such suits in a variety of colors and styles."),
	("Vesk Overplate, I", 6, "Heavy", 3,910, 9, 11, 3, -2, -5, "2", These utilitarian suits of heavy armor reflect the brute strength of their inventors. Overplate makes no concession to comfort. Instead, each polycarbonate suit is solid, dense, and often unadorned, though the high-quality craftsmanship of each suit is apparent. Overplate has a reputation for withstanding any sort of trauma, thanks to its coating of thermoplastic resin."),
	("Reinforced EVA Suit, III", 6, "Heavy", 4,060, 8, 12, 2, -3, -5, "3", Although designed for extravehicular activity in hazardous conditions, reinforced EVA suits function as durable, if clunky, heavy armor. This full-body suit has a rigid shell covering the back and chest, with heavy gloves, padded boots, and rugged fabric rounding out the ensemble. A wide helmet design provides good visibility and includes a retractable glare shield. The suit’s excellent air recycling makes for a more comfortable environment than many more battle-worthy designs."),
	("Stationwear, Elite", 6, "Light", 4,100, 4, 5, 7, 0, 0, "L", Many types of reinforced clothing afford protection without sacrificing comfort or fashion. The prevalence of this kind of light armor on Absalom Station has led to the colloquial term “stationwear.” Stationwear ranges in style from casual wear to business suits and more formal garb. The usual environmental protections of armor are concealed in the design of these outfits. The grades of armor0business, casual, elite, and flight suit0refer to the quality of the garments, not the style."),
	("Ysoki Refractor Suit", 6, "Light", 4,120, 7, 7, 5, 0, 0, "L", The innovative ysoki created this reinforced jumpsuit layered with energy-reflective foil. This light armor is undeniably noticeable, but it also protects against energy attacks with the same efficacy as it does kinetic attacks. Ysoki refractor suits are popular among all races now and can be tinted in different metallic shades."),
	("Zeizerer Diffractor, II", 6, "Light", 4,150, 6, 6, 6, 0, 0, "L", Crafted by the talented smiths of the drow of Apostae, this armor is designed to be light and supple. Its refractive planes are all at the molecular level, resulting in armor that appears to almost absorb light. House Zeizerer is the main distributor of this armor to the rest of the Pact Worlds, but other drow houses have been known to manufacture their own versions."),
	("Polyplate, Basic", 6, "Light", 4,200, 5, 7, 4, 0, 0, "L", Polyplate is flexible armor composed of interlocking scales that protects its wearer against trauma, absorbing blows and distributing the force across a wide area to lessen its impact. By default, the armor protects against bludgeoning damage, providing DR against that damage equal to half the armor’s item level. As a move action, a creature wearing polyplate can swipe a limb across the armor, changing its DR to protect against piercing or slashing damage, or back to bludgeoning. Polyplate is also highly adaptable, easily incorporating armor upgrades."),
	("Lashunta Mind Mail, I", 6, "Light", 4,250, 6, 6, 6, 0, 0, "L", Each link in a suit of mind mail is a nanotechnological marvel: a psychically active circuit reactive to the thoughts of its wearer. When donned, mind mail floats just above the skin and alternates between rigidity and supple motion in response to its wearer’s thoughts and movement, with hundreds of tiny force fields filling the gaps between links as needed.  The mail covers the entire body except for the face. The coif retracts into the collar at a mental command, and the mesh gloves likewise unlink and recede into the sleeves when a delicate touch is required. Mind mail offers a comfortable alternative to climate control in tropical environs such as Castrovel, as the armor does not make direct contact with the body  and the open mesh provides ample airflow. The wearers of mind mail often personalize their armor with intricate designs woven with varicolored metals into the pattern of the mail. These designs can be altered with an Engineering check at the same DC as a check for adjusting armor (Core Rulebook 196)."),
	("Inheritor's Grace, I", 6, "Heavy", 4,450, 9, 10, 3, -2, -5, "2", "When first commissioned by the Church of Iomedae, this heavy armor was dubbed Armor of the Inheritor Ascendant. This cumbersome mouthful was soon supplanted by the tongue-and-cheek nickname “Inheritor’s grace,” as “by her grace, we are protected.” Now only the dourest of Iomedae’s church refer to her armor by its proper title. Each suit of Inheritor’s grace armor constructed by the church receives blessings as part of its construction, though otherwise identical knock-offs and officially licensed suits also exist. The armor is extremely common among worshipers of Iomedae and Knights of Golarion, but it is also worn by those with no connection to her faith.
	("Freebooter Armor, II", 6, "Light", 4,720, 6, 8, 5, 0, 0, "L", Popularized by the Free Captains of the Diaspora, freebooter armor features an armored jacket or breastplate, heavy boots and gloves, numerous straps and hidden weapons, and a helmet. Novice explorers and mercenaries beginning their career sometimes choose freebooter armor for the air of rakish experience this light armor lends its wearer."),
	("Kyokor Plating, II", 6, "Heavy", 4,820, 8, 10, 4, -1, -5, "1", "Scavengers on Daimalko dare to brave the wastes of their world to gather the enamel-like hulls that kyokors occasionally shed from their crowns. These toothy moltings are enormous, and once they’re retrieved, they require a great deal of effort to grind into plates that can be used to craft armor. Despite this and the dangers of gathering the requisite moltings, suits of kyokor plating are in demand throughout the universe, making collection of the raw materials and subsequent forging into lucrative careers.
	("Dust Manta Hide, Basic", 6, "Light", 5,150, 5, 7, 5, 0, 0, "L", In Fullbright, some brave0or perhaps foolish0game hunters in the Outlaw Kingdoms pursue dust mantas for their desertadapted hides, despite the inherent danger in doing so. Those fortunate enough to survive their hunts craft suits of light armor from the hides, using  anocarbon filaments to stitch the armor together. The basic dust manta hide grants resistance to fire 5, and the advanced dust manta hide, fashioned from a dust manta monarch, grants resistance to fire 10. Both models also grant a +4 circumstance bonus to Stealth checks to hide in a desert environment."),
	("Estex Suit, III", 7, "Light", 5,500, 7, 8, 5, -1, 0, "1", Estex is a thick, durable fabric most often used to make flight suits and environmental suits. Estex suits cover the wearer from the neck down and can be modified with armor upgrades as needed. Higher-quality estex suits grant a better level of protection and allow for more upgrades, though they are often bulkier than comparable suits of light armor."),
	("Golemforged Plating, III", 7, "Heavy", 5,500, 10, 12, 3, -2, -5, "2", An economical choice for many mercenaries, golemforged plating is one of the universe’s most popular heavy armors. Golemforged plating consists of a close-fitting polycarbonate suit fitted with ports and sockets to fit most armor customization options. Suits of golemforged plating include flexible boots and gloves as well as a standard helmet with a clear visor."),
	("Formian Hide, Advanced", 7, "Heavy", 6,100, 10, 12, 3, -3, -5, "2", The vicious wars between lashuntas and formians drove many technomagical advances, including this armor made to emulate the chitinous skins of formians. The armor includes a helmet that boosts the wearer’s natural telepathy; if you have the limited telepathy racial trait, you add 10 feet to the range of that ability. This increase doesn’t stack with other effects that extend the range of your telepathy, such as a psychic booster."),
	("Defiance Series, Elite", 7, "Heavy", 6,300, 10, 13, 2, -4, -10, "3", The defiance series of heavy armor is the workhorse of squad armor. A formed hard shell overlays a suit of para-aramids, creating a bulky and solid protective outfit. Defiance series helmets have wide, tinted visors to allow peripheral vision."),
	("Preserver's Mantle, II", 7, "Light", 6,400, 6, 9, 6, 0, 0, "L", The Xenowardens bioengineered the preserver’s mantle as a form of living armor. Rather than donning the mantle, a creature steps onto it and allows the armor to wrap itself around and over the creature’s body. Insulating moss acts as padding, while vines and wood match the strength of the advanced composites of other light armors. When the armor’s environmental protections are activated, the external surface of the plants interlace into an  airtight barrier, while the moss regulates the temperature and converts exhaled gases back into breathable air. Like other armors, the mantle must be adjusted to fit a new wearer (though this requires a Life Science check, rather than an Engineering check."),
	("Dendron Armor, Yew", 7, "Heavy", 6,600, 10, 13, 3, -2, -5, "2", "A living defense designed by the Xenowardens, dendron armor melds bioengineered wood with advanced microbespun polymers. A mossy layer beneath this outer shell provides cushioning and life support. Xenowardens stylize this heavy armor to resemble the sentient trees found on Castrovel and other verdant worlds. The organic design of dendron armor makes adding upgrades a challenge, but it offers a good balance between mobility and protection.
	("D-Suit, II", 7, "Light", 6,900, 8, 9, 5, 0, 0, "L", Disembarkment suits, or d-suits, are designed for spacefarers who expect to leave their ship and visit a planet’s surface. Most d-suits are jumpsuits or flight suits worn under reinforced breeches, heavy boots, and a thick jacket. A helmet or rebreather and a utility belt with an attached holster complete the outfit."),
	("AbadarCorp Travel Suit, Silver", 7, "Light", 7,250, 6, 7, 7, 0, 0, "L", AbadarCorp executives popularized these light armor business suits for boardrooms and diplomatic meetings. Contingent force fields and concealed rebreathers protect the wearer in hostile environmental conditions. Higher grades of travel suits offer more protection0along with a designer label."),
	("Ceremonial Plate, Commander", 7, "Heavy", 7,350, 10, 12, 2, -3, -10, "3", While this heavy armor of sculpted metal plates offers good protection to the wearer, its main purpose is to intimidate enemies. Often used for honor guards, military exercises, or parades, ceremonial plate is usually brightly colored or made of shining metal, with elaborate helmets."),
	("Aeon Guard, SpecOps Armor", 7, "Light", 7,500, 7, 8, 5, -1, 0, "1", """Standard issue for soldiers of the Azlanti Star Empire’s elite military, Aeon Guard battle dress is a suit of heavy armor consisting of close-fitting ceramic and polycarbonate plates overlaid with an energy-reflective molecular coating. SpecOps armor, designed for use by Aeon Guard specialists, is of the same design but in a lighter, more agile package. In addition to slots for traditional armor upgrades, each suit of Aeon Guard battle dress also includes additional aeon upgrade slots that can be used to house only aeon stones. Placing an aeon stone in an aeon upgrade slot allows you to benefit from the aeon stone’s abilities as if it was orbiting your head. In the Azlanti Star Empire, civilian possession of a suit of Aeon Guard battle dress is a criminal offense punishable by death.
	("Azlanti Royal Battle Regalia", 7, "Light", 8,000, 7, 8, 5, 0, 0, "1", "Zolan’s minions took Parept Ameondria’s armor from the Royal Venture and turned it over to him when they left Nakondis. Extremely rare, suits of Azlanti royal battle regalia are reserved for the upper echelons of Azlanti nobility and are usually marked with insignia of the wearer’s lineage. When caught, any non-Azlanti audacious enough to don one of these ceremonial suits is tortured for years before being put to death.
	("Acrochor Hide, Advanced", 8, "Light", 8,250, 10, 10, 6, 0, 0, "L", Crafted from the hides of acrochors0serpentine predators that crush their prey (see page 55)0these suits of light armor offer both protection and flexibility. Acrochor hide has the archaic armor special property."),
	("Lashunta Ringwear, III", 8, "Heavy", 8,420, 12, 14, 3, -2, -5, "2", These beautiful suits of heavy armor feature engraved metal bands that fit above and below the body’s major joints. Metal guards, woven chain sheets, and force fields stretch between the bands to form a complete set of protective gear. Tinted crystals are often added during the forging process to the ore used for ringwear to create glimmering suits of different hues."),
	("Lashunta Tempweave, Advanced", 8, "Light", 8,500, 9, 10, 6, 0, 0, "L", Lashuntas developed tempweave light armor by threading temperature-regulating wires through reinforced clothing. The result is a protective, flexible outfit that maintains a comfortable temperature for the wearer. Most tempweave outfits feature a fitted tunic over breeches, making them a popular choice for explorers venturing to hot or humid environments."),
	("Shobhad Harness, Warleader", 8, "Light", 8,600, 9, 11, 5, -1, 0, "1", "While a few shobhads still wear armor crafted from leather reinforced with metal plates, the shobhad-neh typically incorporate more advanced materials such as ballistic mesh and ceramic plates into the traditional designs of their ancestors. Despite having a high bulk for light armor, war harnesses are well padded and ventilated for comfort, as shobhads rarely remove their armor. Though some shobhad disdain the life support systems built into advanced armor, most recognize their value. The protective headgear, leggings, and sleeves used for such conditions stow discretely out of sight when not needed.
	("Vesk Brigandine, III", 8, "Light", 8,800, 10, 10, 5, 0, 0, "L", The core of vesk brigandine is a lightweight breastplate made of interlocking polymer hexagons. It flexes almost as well as fabric under normal use, but it becomes rigid as steel in response to impact. Its slim profile lets it be worn either over or under clothing. More advanced brigandine designs incorporate inertial dampeners to enhance protection. Vesk who prize mobility over maximum protection favor this style of light armor, and its use has spread throughout the Pact Worlds to the degree that any similar design is often referred to as vesk brigandine."),
	("Kasatha Microcord, III", 8, "Light", 9,000, 9, 11, 5, -1, 0, "1", These suits of ribbed protective fabric are slightly less advanced than comparable light armor but still provide good-quality protection at an affordable price. Kasatha-made microcord suits are typically one-piece outfits of dark colors, sometimes with glowing trim, but other manufacturers produce such suits in a variety of colors and styles."),
	("Night Plate, I", 8, "Heavy", 9,400, 11, 13, 4, -2, -5, "2", Based on designs reverse-engineered from ancient troves and alloys rediscovered through painstaking research, night plate is the heavy armor of choice for the drow of Apostae. It blends archaic armor sensibilities with cutting-edge technology, resulting in an appearance that resembles a metallic construct as much as armor. Night plate’s design incorporates flaring cauldrons and razor-sharp leg spurs, though these impressive adornments have little function beyond intimidation. Highergrade models incorporate even more of these embellishments, cunningly designed to avoid interference with the armor’s primary functions."),
	("Vesk Overplate, II", 8, "Heavy", 10,250, 13, 15, 2, -3, -10, "3", These utilitarian suits of heavy armor reflect the brute strength of their inventors. Overplate makes no concession to comfort. Instead, each polycarbonate suit is solid, dense, and often unadorned, though the high-quality craftsmanship of each suit is apparent. Overplate has a reputation for withstanding any sort of trauma, thanks to its coating of thermoplastic resin."),
	("Hardplate, Advanced", 9, "Heavy", 12,000, 15, 16, 3, -2, -5, "2", Kishalee building materials are some of the sturdiest and long-lasting substances ever made, and kish have taken debris from collapsed structures0and have sometimes even intentionally demolished buildings0to make these suits of heavy armor. Hardplate has the archaic armor special property."),
	("AbadarCorp Travel Suit, Gold", 9, "Light", 12,100, 9, 10, 8, 0, 0, "L", AbadarCorp executives popularized these light armor business suits for boardrooms and diplomatic meetings. Contingent force fields and concealed rebreathers protect the wearer in hostile environmental conditions. Higher grades of travel suits offer more protection0along with a designer label."),
	("Skitterhide, II", 9, "Light", 12,500, 10, 11, 7, 0, 0, "L", This armor is made from the harvested hides of the remains of destroyed undead, making it resemble a macabre skinsuit. Ossified studs and embellishments reinforce the alchemically treated skin, which is otherwise designed to support Corpse Fleet agents favoring speed and stealth."),
	("Zeizerer Diffractor, III", 9, "Light", 12,500, 11, 11, 7, 0, 0, "L", Crafted by the talented smiths of the drow of Apostae, this armor is designed to be light and supple. Its refractive planes are all at the molecular level, resulting in armor that appears to almost absorb light. House Zeizerer is the main distributor of this armor to the rest of the Pact Worlds, but other drow houses have been known to manufacture their own versions."),
	("Kalo Encounter Suit, II", 9, "Heavy", 12,900, 15, 16, 2, -3, -10, "3", When they first ventured beyond the frigid seas of Kalo-Mahoi, the kalo brought the waters of their moon with them in specially engineered suits. The kalo encounter suit represents the latest evolution of that design0a portable ocean that keeps the kalo at the near freezing temperatures they prefer. The suit’s air supply doubles as ballast to keep the wearer neutrally buoyant in water despite the armor’s weight, and the idiomatic design accommodates and protects the kalo’s swimming membranes. While the armor can be adapted to circulate water instead of air, kalos prefer their comfort of their own technology. Similarly, the filters and seals of kalo encounter suits can be adapted to the needs of air breathers, although such suits tend to accumulate excess moisture and develop mold or mildew."),
	("Iridishell, Advanced", 9, "Heavy", 13,100, 13, 15, 3, 0, 0, "2", These gleaming metal plates lock together to form a suit of heavy armor reminiscent of an insect’s shell. Although the iridishell was initially designed for shirrens, its beauty combined and functionality makes it a popular choice for many. More expensive suits of iridishell not only offer more protection but feature elaborate designs with gold or silver trim and embedded jewels."),
	("Clearweave, II", 9, "Light", 13,150, 12, 12, 5, 0, 0, "L", "The formfitting fabric of clearweave light armor is completely transparent to better display the fashion choices beneath it. Discrete force field generators along each side resemble intricate tattoos as much as they resemble circuitry. Clearweave darkens automatically when exposed to harmful solar radiation or laser fire. 
	("D-Suit, III", 9, "Light", 13,300, 11, 12, 6, 0, 0, "L", Disembarkment suits, or d-suits, are designed for spacefarers who expect to leave their ship and visit a planet’s surface. Most d-suits are jumpsuits or flight suits worn under reinforced breeches, heavy boots, and a thick jacket. A helmet or rebreather and a utility belt with an attached holster complete the outfit."),
	("Shiftskin, I", 9, "Light", 13,850, 10, 11, 7, -1, 0, "1", "Developed by the reptoids for their agents, shiftskin comes in a variety of designs styled to resemble normal clothing, uniforms, and even other light armors. Each suit of shiftskin is designed to accommodate both its owner’s natural form and one other specific assumed form of another race, shifting and reshaping as needed when the reptoid changes shape. Thus a suit of shiftskin can be adjusted to accommodate two different forms (Core Rulebook 196), rather than fitting only one form at a time.
	("Skyfire Armor, Pinion", 9, "Heavy", 14,200, 14, 16, 3, -2, -5, "2", These suits of interlocking metal and ceramic plates are usually highly decorated. Gold trim, exaggerated shoulder guards, and stylized Skyfire logos on the breastplates are common. These iconic outfits are worn by the storied members of the Skyfire Legion, though other groups and individuals have copied the Legion’s distinctively decorated heavy armor. Skyfire armor ordinarily comes with force fields that encase the wearer’s head when needed."),
	("Hellknight Plate, Maralictor", 9, "Heavy", 14,500, 16, 17, 2, -2, -10, "3", The stern and unrelenting Hellknights are known as much for their distinctive plate armor as for their fearsome adherence to rigid order. This variant of ceremonial plate is predominantly black with protruding spikes, and each Hellknight order has its own distinct design."),
	("Formian Hide, Superior", 10, "Heavy", 16,500, 15, 17, 3, -4, -5, "2", The vicious wars between lashuntas and formians drove many technomagical advances, including this armor made to emulate the chitinous skins of formians. The armor includes a helmet that boosts the wearer’s natural telepathy; if you have the limited telepathy racial trait, you add 10 feet to the range of that ability. This increase doesn’t stack with other effects that extend the range of your telepathy, such as a psychic booster."),
	("Freebooter Armor, III", 10, "Light", 16,900, 12, 13, 6, 0, 0, "L", Popularized by the Free Captains of the Diaspora, freebooter armor features an armored jacket or breastplate, heavy boots and gloves, numerous straps and hidden weapons, and a helmet. Novice explorers and mercenaries beginning their career sometimes choose freebooter armor for the air of rakish experience this light armor lends its wearer."),
	("Defiance Series, Specialist", 10, "Heavy", 16,950, 15, 18, 2, -4, -10, "3", The defiance series of heavy armor is the workhorse of squad armor. A formed hard shell overlays a suit of para-aramids, creating a bulky and solid protective outfit. Defiance series helmets have wide, tinted visors to allow peripheral vision."),
	("Kyokor Plating, III", 10, "Heavy", 17,100, 13, 16, 4, -2, -5, "1", "Scavengers on Daimalko dare to brave the wastes of their world to gather the enamel-like hulls that kyokors occasionally shed from their crowns. These toothy moltings are enormous, and once they’re retrieved, they require a great deal of effort to grind into plates that can be used to craft armor. Despite this and the dangers of gathering the requisite moltings, suits of kyokor plating are in demand throughout the universe, making collection of the raw materials and subsequent forging into lucrative careers.
	("Mining Jack, III", 10, "Heavy", 17,150, 15, 19, 1, -3, -10, "3", Asteroid miners wear mining jacks for both life support and protection against the hazards of vacuum mining. As they are designed for use in low and zero gravity, the jacks are quite bulky, with alloys chosen for strength and durability rather than weight. Because miners often spend the entire day in a vacuum, mining jacks have storage compartments  accessible within the armor. The breastplate of a mining jack can expand outward without being removed, allowing the wearer a modest amount of space to pull her arms inside and enjoy a beverage or meal. Each suit includes a pair of miniature airlocks that allow safe transfer of small objects from outside to inside the suit as a full action. A pair of mining jacks can even link locks to trade gear without exposing the item or either wearer to vacuum. The first mining jacks were dwarven designs, but their ingenious design and utility have made them popular throughout the Diaspora."),
	("Polyplate, Advanced", 10, "Light", 17,400, 11, 13, 5, 0, 0, "L", Polyplate is flexible armor composed of interlocking scales that protects its wearer against trauma, absorbing blows and distributing the force across a wide area to lessen its impact. By default, the armor protects against bludgeoning damage, providing DR against that damage equal to half the armor’s item level. As a move action, a creature wearing polyplate can swipe a limb across the armor, changing its DR to protect against piercing or slashing damage, or back to bludgeoning. Polyplate is also highly adaptable, easily incorporating armor upgrades."),
	("Grave Mantle, Specialist", 10, "Light", 17,950, 13, 15, 4, 0, 0, "L", "The utilitarian grave mantle is common both on Eox and among the Eoxian expatriates of the Corpse Fleet. The base model worn by rankand- file troops consists of a tabard of ballistic fabric worn over plastic mesh, with additional layers of fabric reinforcing the joints. More expensive models enhance the mesh with nanowire and place ceramic plates beneath the tabard. Despite Eoxian armies having no need for air, grave mantles retain life support systems as a defense against corrosive atmospheres and related hazards.
	("Dendron Armor, Oak", 10, "Heavy", 18,450, 14, 17, 3, -2, -5, "2", "A living defense designed by the Xenowardens, dendron armor melds bioengineered wood with advanced microbespun polymers. A mossy layer beneath this outer shell provides cushioning and life support. Xenowardens stylize this heavy armor to resemble the sentient trees found on Castrovel and other verdant worlds. The organic design of dendron armor makes adding upgrades a challenge, but it offers a good balance between mobility and protection.
	("Regimental Dress, II", 10, "Light", 18,600, 13, 13, 5, 0, 0, "L", Regimental dress is the light armor counterpart to ceremonial plate. Often stylized to the extreme, regimental dress comes in as many variations as there are military forces, militias, and private security details. Regimental dress uses advanced fibers and strategically placed ceramic plates to avoid ruining the design lines of the uniforms. A force field projector concealed in the collar activates as needed to provide life support and protection for the head. Integrated holographic imaging projects rank insignia, medals, and ribbons, and supports gesture-activated informational displays for each honor."),
	("Aeon Guard, Battle Dress (Command)", 10, "Heavy", 18,750, 15, 17, 3, -3, -10, "3", "Standard issue for soldiers of the Azlanti Star Empire’s elite military, Aeon Guard battle dress is a suit of heavy armor consisting of close-fitting ceramic and polycarbonate plates overlaid with an energy-reflective molecular coating. SpecOps armor, designed for use by Aeon Guard specialists, is of the same design but in a lighter, more agile package. In addition to slots for traditional armor upgrades, each suit of Aeon Guard battle dress also includes additional aeon upgrade slots that can be used to house only aeon stones. Placing an aeon stone in an aeon upgrade slot allows you to benefit from the aeon stone’s abilities as if it was orbiting your head. In the Azlanti Star Empire, civilian possession of a suit of Aeon Guard battle dress is a criminal offense punishable by death.
	("Carbon Skin, White Carbon", 10, "Light", 19,650, 12, 14, 5, -1, 0, "1", Though these suits of light armor appear to be made of stiff fabric, they are actually woven from carbon fibers. Higher-quality carbon skins are reinforced with carbon allotypes, such as white carbon or diamond, and the heightened sheen of the fabric hints at their expensive construction."),
	("Void Hide I", 10, "Light", 20,000, 13, 15, 4, -1, 0, "1", Made from void troll skin, void hide armor quivers of its own volition, as if the manufacturing process could not subdue the troll’s life force. You can trigger void hide to react to an attack as though you had the reflecting armor spell cast on you. Once you have used a specific suit of void hide in this way, you can use a different suit only after 24 hours have passed. A magic resistor upgrade installed in void hide takes up one upgrade slot fewer than normal (minimum 0), as does a spell reflector upgrade."),
	("Vesk Overplate, III", 11, "Heavy", 23,400, 16, 18, 3, -2, -5, "2", These utilitarian suits of heavy armor reflect the brute strength of their inventors. Overplate makes no concession to comfort. Instead, each polycarbonate suit is solid, dense, and often unadorned, though the high-quality craftsmanship of each suit is apparent. Overplate has a reputation for withstanding any sort of trauma, thanks to its coating of thermoplastic resin."),
	("Vesk Brigandine, IV", 11, "Light", 23,500, 14, 14, 5, 0, 0, "L", The core of vesk brigandine is a lightweight breastplate made of interlocking polymer hexagons. It flexes almost as well as fabric under normal use, but it becomes rigid as steel in response to impact. Its slim profile lets it be worn either over or under clothing. More advanced brigandine designs incorporate inertial dampeners to enhance protection. Vesk who prize mobility over maximum protection favor this style of light armor, and its use has spread throughout the Pact Worlds to the degree that any similar design is often referred to as vesk brigandine."),
	("Enforcer Armor, II", 11, "Heavy", 23,725, 17, 19, 2, -4, -10, "3", "The faceless, slate-gray design of enforcer armor blends intimidation and anonymity. This heavy armor’s design echoes the aegis series’ personal tank approach, albeit with markedly inferior protection. Enforcer armor often towers a full foot over the wearer’s natural height, with most of the wearer’s head safely sheltered behind the breastplate and sensory input handled through projected video and audio feeds. Criminal organizations use enforcer armor to keep their hired muscle impersonal and enigmatic.
	("Kasatha Microcord, IV", 11, "Light", 23,800, 13, 15, 5, -1, 0, "1", These suits of ribbed protective fabric are slightly less advanced than comparable light armor but still provide good-quality protection at an affordable price. Kasatha-made microcord suits are typically one-piece outfits of dark colors, sometimes with glowing trim, but other manufacturers produce such suits in a variety of colors and styles."),
	("Lashunta Mind Mail, II", 11, "Light", 24,500, 13, 14, 6, 0, 0, "L", Each link in a suit of mind mail is a nanotechnological marvel: a psychically active circuit reactive to the thoughts of its wearer. When donned, mind mail floats just above the skin and alternates between rigidity and supple motion in response to its wearer’s thoughts and movement, with hundreds of tiny force fields filling the gaps between links as needed.  The mail covers the entire body except for the face. The coif retracts into the collar at a mental command, and the mesh gloves likewise unlink and recede into the sleeves when a delicate touch is required. Mind mail offers a comfortable alternative to climate control in tropical environs such as Castrovel, as the armor does not make direct contact with the body  and the open mesh provides ample airflow. The wearers of mind mail often personalize their armor with intricate designs woven with varicolored metals into the pattern of the mail. These designs can be altered with an Engineering check at the same DC as a check for adjusting armor (Core Rulebook 196)."),
	("Golemforged Plating, IV", 11, "Heavy", 24,800, 15, 17, 3, -3, -10, "3", An economical choice for many mercenaries, golemforged plating is one of the universe’s most popular heavy armors. Golemforged plating consists of a close-fitting polycarbonate suit fitted with ports and sockets to fit most armor customization options. Suits of golemforged plating include flexible boots and gloves as well as a standard helmet with a clear visor."),
	("Lashunta Ringwear, IV", 11, "Heavy", 27,100, 16, 18, 4, -3, -5, "2", These beautiful suits of heavy armor feature engraved metal bands that fit above and below the body’s major joints. Metal guards, woven chain sheets, and force fields stretch between the bands to form a complete set of protective gear. Tinted crystals are often added during the forging process to the ore used for ringwear to create glimmering suits of different hues."),
	("Acrochor Hide, Elite", 12, "Light", 28,000, 15, 15, 7, 0, 0, "L", Crafted from the hides of acrochors0serpentine predators that crush their prey (see page 55)0these suits of light armor offer both protection and flexibility. Acrochor hide has the archaic armor special property."),
	("Hardlight Series, Squad", 12, "Light", 30,750, 15, 15, 6, 0, 0, "L", The last word in light infantry armor, hardlight series armor features an inflexible, lightweight breastplate, limb guards, and a helmet over a smooth and formfitting jumpsuit. Manufacturers often make custom armor for military organizations, but off-therack armor of differing qualities is also available to mercenaries and explorers."),
	("Defrex Hide, Advanced", 12, "Light", 33,000, 14, 16, 5, 0, 0, "L", Made from the hide of a ferocious mammal native to Vesk-2, this light armor is popular among vesk but less often worn by other races. Tanned stretches of the creature’s thick hide are stitched together with metal wires, and the suits are reinforced with metal studs or scales."),
	("AbadarCorp Travel Suit, Platinum", 12, "Light", 34,600, 12, 13, 8, 0, 0, "L", AbadarCorp executives popularized these light armor business suits for boardrooms and diplomatic meetings. Contingent force fields and concealed rebreathers protect the wearer in hostile environmental conditions. Higher grades of travel suits offer more protection0along with a designer label."),
	("Preserver's Mantle, III", 12, "Light", 35,400, 12, 15, 7, 0, 0, "L", The Xenowardens bioengineered the preserver’s mantle as a form of living armor. Rather than donning the mantle, a creature steps onto it and allows the armor to wrap itself around and over the creature’s body. Insulating moss acts as padding, while vines and wood match the strength of the advanced composites of other light armors. When the armor’s environmental protections are activated, the external surface of the plants interlace into an  airtight barrier, while the moss regulates the temperature and converts exhaled gases back into breathable air. Like other armors, the mantle must be adjusted to fit a new wearer (though this requires a Life Science check, rather than an Engineering check."),
	("Night Plate, II", 12, "Heavy", 37,500, 15, 17, 5, -2, -5, "2", Based on designs reverse-engineered from ancient troves and alloys rediscovered through painstaking research, night plate is the heavy armor of choice for the drow of Apostae. It blends archaic armor sensibilities with cutting-edge technology, resulting in an appearance that resembles a metallic construct as much as armor. Night plate’s design incorporates flaring cauldrons and razor-sharp leg spurs, though these impressive adornments have little function beyond intimidation. Highergrade models incorporate even more of these embellishments, cunningly designed to avoid interference with the armor’s primary functions."),
	("Light Experimental Neural Interface Exosuit", 12, "Light", 38,000, 14, 14, 8, 0, 0, "L", The Light Experimental Neural Interface Exosuit is a 12thlevel suit of light armor that provides a +14 armor bonus to both EAC and KAC. It has a maximum Dexterity bonus of +8 and no armor check penalty. Three of its four upgrade slots contain a targeting computer with an artificial personality, a forcepack, and a mk 2 thermal capacitor. This hybrid armor molds perfectly to your shape, regardless of body type and size, and the armor’s artificial personality monitors your vital signs and informs you when you are diseased, poisoned, or exposed to radiation. However, when you wear this armor, you become addicted to pain, and if you go more than 4 hours without taking damage, you gain the fatigued and sickened conditions until the next time you take damage. You also gain a +1 morale bonus to attack rolls for 1 round after you score a critical hit on a significant foe. Without any of its upgrades, the Light Experimental Neural Interface Exosuit costs 38,000 credits (though it isn’t yet available for purchase by the general public) and has light bulk. Though it is a hybrid suit of armor, it doesn’t count as a worn item."),
	("Vesk Monolith, I", 12, "Heavy", 39,650, 16, 18, 4, -2, -5, "2", The ultimate battle gear, pioneered by the vesk, these suits of heavy armor have a dappled polycarbonate shell that resembles stone in texture. A monolith suit looks like a massive articulated golem formed of stone plates. Despite its size, monolith armor moves easily thanks to its power-assisted joints. Sigils and personal emblems can be “chiseled” on the breastplate or shoulder guards of a monolith suit to signal the wearer’s allegiance."),
	("Formian Plate, Taskmaster", 12, "Heavy", 42,000, 16, 19, 3, -4, -10, "3", The exoskeletons of deceased formians can be crafted into armor that retains some of these creatures’ defenses. Taskmaster and myrmarch formian plate grant resistance to sonic 5."),
	("Iridishell, Superior", 12, "Heavy", 42,250, 17, 18, 4, 0, 0, "2", These gleaming metal plates lock together to form a suit of heavy armor reminiscent of an insect’s shell. Although the iridishell was initially designed for shirrens, its beauty combined and functionality makes it a popular choice for many. More expensive suits of iridishell not only offer more protection but feature elaborate designs with gold or silver trim and embedded jewels."),
	("Dust Manta Hide, Advanced", 12, "Light", 43,250, 15, 16, 6, 0, 0, "L", In Fullbright, some brave0or perhaps foolish0game hunters in the Outlaw Kingdoms pursue dust mantas for their desertadapted hides, despite the inherent danger in doing so. Those fortunate enough to survive their hunts craft suits of light armor from the hides, using  anocarbon filaments to stitch the armor together. The basic dust manta hide grants resistance to fire 5, and the advanced dust manta hide, fashioned from a dust manta monarch, grants resistance to fire 10. Both models also grant a +4 circumstance bonus to Stealth checks to hide in a desert environment."),
	("Aegis Series, Squad", 12, "Heavy", 45,200, 17, 19, 3, -5, -10, "3", Aegis suits of heavy armor cover wearers entirely, leading to the suits’ nickname of “personal tanks.” Helmet visors are narrow or nonexistent, instead projecting video and audio feeds to the wearer. Power-assisted limbs allow the wearer to move intuitively with the suit on."),
	("D-Suit, IV", 13, "Light", 45,800, 16, 17, 6, 0, 0, "L", Disembarkment suits, or d-suits, are designed for spacefarers who expect to leave their ship and visit a planet’s surface. Most d-suits are jumpsuits or flight suits worn under reinforced breeches, heavy boots, and a thick jacket. A helmet or rebreather and a utility belt with an attached holster complete the outfit."),
	("Shobhad Harness, Chieftain", 13, "Light", 46,900, 15, 17, 5, -1, 0, "1", "While a few shobhads still wear armor crafted from leather reinforced with metal plates, the shobhad-neh typically incorporate more advanced materials such as ballistic mesh and ceramic plates into the traditional designs of their ancestors. Despite having a high bulk for light armor, war harnesses are well padded and ventilated for comfort, as shobhads rarely remove their armor. Though some shobhad disdain the life support systems built into advanced armor, most recognize their value. The protective headgear, leggings, and sleeves used for such conditions stow discretely out of sight when not needed.
	("Hardplate, Elite", 13, "Heavy", 48,000, 19, 20, 4, -3, -5, "2", Kishalee building materials are some of the sturdiest and long-lasting substances ever made, and kish have taken debris from collapsed structures0and have sometimes even intentionally demolished buildings0to make these suits of heavy armor. Hardplate has the archaic armor special property."),
	("Zeizerer Diffractor, IV", 13, "Light", 48,500, 15, 15, 8, 0, 0, "L", Crafted by the talented smiths of the drow of Apostae, this armor is designed to be light and supple. Its refractive planes are all at the molecular level, resulting in armor that appears to almost absorb light. House Zeizerer is the main distributor of this armor to the rest of the Pact Worlds, but other drow houses have been known to manufacture their own versions."),
	("Kalo Encounter Suit, III", 13, "Heavy", 48,500, 20, 21, 3, -3, -10, "3", When they first ventured beyond the frigid seas of Kalo-Mahoi, the kalo brought the waters of their moon with them in specially engineered suits. The kalo encounter suit represents the latest evolution of that design0a portable ocean that keeps the kalo at the near freezing temperatures they prefer. The suit’s air supply doubles as ballast to keep the wearer neutrally buoyant in water despite the armor’s weight, and the idiomatic design accommodates and protects the kalo’s swimming membranes. While the armor can be adapted to circulate water instead of air, kalos prefer their comfort of their own technology. Similarly, the filters and seals of kalo encounter suits can be adapted to the needs of air breathers, although such suits tend to accumulate excess moisture and develop mold or mildew."),
	("Estex Suit, IV", 13, "Light", 49,250, 15, 16, 6, -1, 0, "1", Estex is a thick, durable fabric most often used to make flight suits and environmental suits. Estex suits cover the wearer from the neck down and can be modified with armor upgrades as needed. Higher-quality estex suits grant a better level of protection and allow for more upgrades, though they are often bulkier than comparable suits of light armor."),
	("Skyfire Armor, Exident", 13, "Heavy", 53,600, 18, 20, 4, -2, -5, "2", These suits of interlocking metal and ceramic plates are usually highly decorated. Gold trim, exaggerated shoulder guards, and stylized Skyfire logos on the breastplates are common. These iconic outfits are worn by the storied members of the Skyfire Legion, though other groups and individuals have copied the Legion’s distinctively decorated heavy armor. Skyfire armor ordinarily comes with force fields that encase the wearer’s head when needed."),
	("Fossilwrap, II", 13, "Heavy", 55,000, 19, 19, 4, -2, -5, "2", Meant for first-wave boarding actions, fossilwrap armor is a cage of alchemically treated bones and steel. This armor is meant to shrug off most incoming blows while giving the wearer some amount of mobility in the thick of combat."),
	("Freebooter Armor, IV", 14, "Light", 60,600, 17, 18, 6, 0, 0, "L", Popularized by the Free Captains of the Diaspora, freebooter armor features an armored jacket or breastplate, heavy boots and gloves, numerous straps and hidden weapons, and a helmet. Novice explorers and mercenaries beginning their career sometimes choose freebooter armor for the air of rakish experience this light armor lends its wearer."),
	("Golemforged Plating, V", 14, "Heavy", 63,750, 18, 20, 4, -3, -10, "3", An economical choice for many mercenaries, golemforged plating is one of the universe’s most popular heavy armors. Golemforged plating consists of a close-fitting polycarbonate suit fitted with ports and sockets to fit most armor customization options. Suits of golemforged plating include flexible boots and gloves as well as a standard helmet with a clear visor."),
	("Polyplate, Elite", 14, "Light", 65,000, 15, 17, 6, 0, 0, "L", Polyplate is flexible armor composed of interlocking scales that protects its wearer against trauma, absorbing blows and distributing the force across a wide area to lessen its impact. By default, the armor protects against bludgeoning damage, providing DR against that damage equal to half the armor’s item level. As a move action, a creature wearing polyplate can swipe a limb across the armor, changing its DR to protect against piercing or slashing damage, or back to bludgeoning. Polyplate is also highly adaptable, easily incorporating armor upgrades."),
	("Inheritor's Grace, II", 14, "Heavy", 67,400, 20, 21, 3, -2, -5, "2", "When first commissioned by the Church of Iomedae, this heavy armor was dubbed Armor of the Inheritor Ascendant. This cumbersome mouthful was soon supplanted by the tongue-and-cheek nickname “Inheritor’s grace,” as “by her grace, we are protected.” Now only the dourest of Iomedae’s church refer to her armor by its proper title. Each suit of Inheritor’s grace armor constructed by the church receives blessings as part of its construction, though otherwise identical knock-offs and officially licensed suits also exist. The armor is extremely common among worshipers of Iomedae and Knights of Golarion, but it is also worn by those with no connection to her faith.
	("Echelon Fashion, Ready to Wear", 14, "Light", 71,300, 15, 16, 8, 0, 0, "L", Modeled after the universe’s most cutting-edge fashions, this lightly armored clothing is available in daring modern designs, using force fields and the highest-tech fibers to create any sort of outfit imaginable. Bespoke echelon fashions are often tailormade for the orderer and meant to look unique."),
	("Vesk Overplate, IV", 14, "Heavy", 71,850, 19, 21, 4, -2, -5, "2", These utilitarian suits of heavy armor reflect the brute strength of their inventors. Overplate makes no concession to comfort. Instead, each polycarbonate suit is solid, dense, and often unadorned, though the high-quality craftsmanship of each suit is apparent. Overplate has a reputation for withstanding any sort of trauma, thanks to its coating of thermoplastic resin."),
	("Kyokor Plating, IV", 14, "Heavy", 76,000, 17, 19, 5, -2, -5, "1", "Scavengers on Daimalko dare to brave the wastes of their world to gather the enamel-like hulls that kyokors occasionally shed from their crowns. These toothy moltings are enormous, and once they’re retrieved, they require a great deal of effort to grind into plates that can be used to craft armor. Despite this and the dangers of gathering the requisite moltings, suits of kyokor plating are in demand throughout the universe, making collection of the raw materials and subsequent forging into lucrative careers.
	("Shiftskin, II", 14, "Light", 76,830, 16, 17, 7, -1, 0, "1", "Developed by the reptoids for their agents, shiftskin comes in a variety of designs styled to resemble normal clothing, uniforms, and even other light armors. Each suit of shiftskin is designed to accommodate both its owner’s natural form and one other specific assumed form of another race, shifting and reshaping as needed when the reptoid changes shape. Thus a suit of shiftskin can be adjusted to accommodate two different forms (Core Rulebook 196), rather than fitting only one form at a time.
	("Hellknight Plate, Paralictor", 14, "Heavy", 80,000, 21, 22, 3, -2, -10, "3", The stern and unrelenting Hellknights are known as much for their distinctive plate armor as for their fearsome adherence to rigid order. This variant of ceremonial plate is predominantly black with protruding spikes, and each Hellknight order has its own distinct design."),
	("Void Hide II", 14, "Light", 90,000, 16, 18, 5, -1, 0, "1", Made from void troll skin, void hide armor quivers of its own volition, as if the manufacturing process could not subdue the troll’s life force. You can trigger void hide to react to an attack as though you had the reflecting armor spell cast on you. Once you have used a specific suit of void hide in this way, you can use a different suit only after 24 hours have passed. A magic resistor upgrade installed in void hide takes up one upgrade slot fewer than normal (minimum 0), as does a spell reflector upgrade."),
	("Lashunta Ringwear, V", 15, "Heavy", 94,200, 20, 22, 4, -2, -5, "2", These beautiful suits of heavy armor feature engraved metal bands that fit above and below the body’s major joints. Metal guards, woven chain sheets, and force fields stretch between the bands to form a complete set of protective gear. Tinted crystals are often added during the forging process to the ore used for ringwear to create glimmering suits of different hues."),
	("Swarmsuit", 15, "Light", 95,200, 18, 19, 6, 0, 0, "L", Inspired by Swarm technology and designed specifically for shirrens, a swarmsuit is a collection of ablative plates backed with reinforced padding and linked with mesh straps. The light armor’s unique arrangement makes it perfect for creatures with unusual physiologies. The wearer arranges the straps in a comfortable formation and slides the ablative plates to cover vulnerable areas."),
	("Vesk Brigandine, V", 15, "Light", 99,900, 19, 20, 5, 0, 0, "L", The core of vesk brigandine is a lightweight breastplate made of interlocking polymer hexagons. It flexes almost as well as fabric under normal use, but it becomes rigid as steel in response to impact. Its slim profile lets it be worn either over or under clothing. More advanced brigandine designs incorporate inertial dampeners to enhance protection. Vesk who prize mobility over maximum protection favor this style of light armor, and its use has spread throughout the Pact Worlds to the degree that any similar design is often referred to as vesk brigandine."),
	("Enforcer Armor, III", 15, "Heavy", 101,150, 21, 23, 3, -3, -10, "3", "The faceless, slate-gray design of enforcer armor blends intimidation and anonymity. This heavy armor’s design echoes the aegis series’ personal tank approach, albeit with markedly inferior protection. Enforcer armor often towers a full foot over the wearer’s natural height, with most of the wearer’s head safely sheltered behind the breastplate and sensory input handled through projected video and audio feeds. Criminal organizations use enforcer armor to keep their hired muscle impersonal and enigmatic.
	("Enginerunner", 15, "Heavy", 120,900, 21, 22, 4, 0, 0, "2", The ysoki popularized this seemingly lightweight but incredibly durable heavy armor. Small squares of dense metal lie between two layers of reinforced fiber weave, giving the appearance of a padded flight suit but offering considerably more protection."),
	("Hardlight Series, Elite", 15, "Light", 123,500, 18, 18, 7, 0, 0, "L", The last word in light infantry armor, hardlight series armor features an inflexible, lightweight breastplate, limb guards, and a helmet over a smooth and formfitting jumpsuit. Manufacturers often make custom armor for military organizations, but off-therack armor of differing qualities is also available to mercenaries and explorers."),
	("Carbon Skin, Diamond", 15, "Light", 126,400, 17, 19, 7, -1, 0, "1", Though these suits of light armor appear to be made of stiff fabric, they are actually woven from carbon fibers. Higher-quality carbon skins are reinforced with carbon allotypes, such as white carbon or diamond, and the heightened sheen of the fabric hints at their expensive construction."),
	("Skitterhide, III", 16, "Light", 144,000, 19, 19, 8, 0, 0, "L", This armor is made from the harvested hides of the remains of destroyed undead, making it resemble a macabre skinsuit. Ossified studs and embellishments reinforce the alchemically treated skin, which is otherwise designed to support Corpse Fleet agents favoring speed and stealth."),
	("Steelbones", 16, "Heavy", 145,500, 21, 23, 4, -3, -5, "2", A framework of metal ribs covers this suit of heavy armor. Force fields bridge the gaps between the metal ribs, which give the armor the macabre look of a metal skeleton. Officers of the Corpse Fleet favor this armor for its unsettling appearance, but steelbones can be worn by anyone who values an intimidating style."),
	("Shotalashu Armor", 16, "Light", 149,500, 19, 20, 7, 0, 0, "L", The lashunta shotalashu cavalry wear this protective gear while riding their bonded saurian mounts. Layers of thin, ablative plates make for light armor that moves with the rider while providing maximum protection. Military merchants have taken to creating knock-off shotalashu armor in more modern styles, as some of the traditional nature themes are no longer fashionable."),
	("Vesk Monolith, II", 16, "Heavy", 163,400, 22, 24, 4, -3, -5, "2", The ultimate battle gear, pioneered by the vesk, these suits of heavy armor have a dappled polycarbonate shell that resembles stone in texture. A monolith suit looks like a massive articulated golem formed of stone plates. Despite its size, monolith armor moves easily thanks to its power-assisted joints. Sigils and personal emblems can be “chiseled” on the breastplate or shoulder guards of a monolith suit to signal the wearer’s allegiance."),
	("Lashunta Mind Mail, III", 16, "Light", 166,500, 20, 20, 7, 0, 0, "L", Each link in a suit of mind mail is a nanotechnological marvel: a psychically active circuit reactive to the thoughts of its wearer. When donned, mind mail floats just above the skin and alternates between rigidity and supple motion in response to its wearer’s thoughts and movement, with hundreds of tiny force fields filling the gaps between links as needed.  The mail covers the entire body except for the face. The coif retracts into the collar at a mental command, and the mesh gloves likewise unlink and recede into the sleeves when a delicate touch is required. Mind mail offers a comfortable alternative to climate control in tropical environs such as Castrovel, as the armor does not make direct contact with the body  and the open mesh provides ample airflow. The wearers of mind mail often personalize their armor with intricate designs woven with varicolored metals into the pattern of the mail. These designs can be altered with an Engineering check at the same DC as a check for adjusting armor (Core Rulebook 196)."),
	("Night Plate, III", 16, "Heavy", 177,300, 21, 24, 5, -1, -5, "2", Based on designs reverse-engineered from ancient troves and alloys rediscovered through painstaking research, night plate is the heavy armor of choice for the drow of Apostae. It blends archaic armor sensibilities with cutting-edge technology, resulting in an appearance that resembles a metallic construct as much as armor. Night plate’s design incorporates flaring cauldrons and razor-sharp leg spurs, though these impressive adornments have little function beyond intimidation. Highergrade models incorporate even more of these embellishments, cunningly designed to avoid interference with the armor’s primary functions."),
	("Aegis Series, Elite", 17, "Heavy", 209,000, 23, 27, 3, -5, -10, "3", Aegis suits of heavy armor cover wearers entirely, leading to the suits’ nickname of “personal tanks.” Helmet visors are narrow or nonexistent, instead projecting video and audio feeds to the wearer. Power-assisted limbs allow the wearer to move intuitively with the suit on."),
	("D-Suit, V", 17, "Light", 244,300, 20, 21, 7, 0, 0, "L", Disembarkment suits, or d-suits, are designed for spacefarers who expect to leave their ship and visit a planet’s surface. Most d-suits are jumpsuits or flight suits worn under reinforced breeches, heavy boots, and a thick jacket. A helmet or rebreather and a utility belt with an attached holster complete the outfit."),
	("Grave Mantle, Officer", 17, "Light", 256,500, 20, 22, 5, 0, 0, "L", "The utilitarian grave mantle is common both on Eox and among the Eoxian expatriates of the Corpse Fleet. The base model worn by rankand- file troops consists of a tabard of ballistic fabric worn over plastic mesh, with additional layers of fabric reinforcing the joints. More expensive models enhance the mesh with nanowire and place ceramic plates beneath the tabard. Despite Eoxian armies having no need for air, grave mantles retain life support systems as a defense against corrosive atmospheres and related hazards."),
	("Dendron Armor, Sequoia", 17, "Heavy", 256,500, 23, 25, 4, -2, -5, "2", "A living defense designed by the Xenowardens, dendron armor melds bioengineered wood with advanced microbespun polymers. A mossy layer beneath this outer shell provides cushioning and life support. Xenowardens stylize this heavy armor to resemble the sentient trees found on Castrovel and other verdant worlds. The organic design of dendron armor makes adding upgrades a challenge, but it offers a good balance between mobility and protection."),
	("Echelon Fashion, Bespoke", 17, "Light", 285,000, 18, 19, 8, 0, 0, "L", Modeled after the universe’s most cutting-edge fashions, this lightly armored clothing is available in daring modern designs, using force fields and the highest-tech fibers to create any sort of outfit imaginable. Bespoke echelon fashions are often tailormade for the orderer and meant to look unique."),
	("Zeizerer Diffractor, V", 18, "Light", 340,000, 20, 20, 9, 0, 0, "L", Crafted by the talented smiths of the drow of Apostae, this armor is designed to be light and supple. Its refractive planes are all at the molecular level, resulting in armor that appears to almost absorb light. House Zeizerer is the main distributor of this armor to the rest of the Pact Worlds, but other drow houses have been known to manufacture their own versions."),
	("Polyplate, Paragon", 18, "Light", 345,000, 19, 21, 7, 0, 0, "L", Polyplate is flexible armor composed of interlocking scales that protects its wearer against trauma, absorbing blows and distributing the force across a wide area to lessen its impact. By default, the armor protects against bludgeoning damage, providing DR against that damage equal to half the armor’s item level. As a move action, a creature wearing polyplate can swipe a limb across the armor, changing its DR to protect against piercing or slashing damage, or back to bludgeoning. Polyplate is also highly adaptable, easily incorporating armor upgrades."),
	("Kalo Encounter Suit, IV", 18, "Heavy", 360,000, 25, 26, 4, -3, -10, "3", When they first ventured beyond the frigid seas of Kalo-Mahoi, the kalo brought the waters of their moon with them in specially engineered suits. The kalo encounter suit represents the latest evolution of that design0a portable ocean that keeps the kalo at the near freezing temperatures they prefer. The suit’s air supply doubles as ballast to keep the wearer neutrally buoyant in water despite the armor’s weight, and the idiomatic design accommodates and protects the kalo’s swimming membranes. While the armor can be adapted to circulate water instead of air, kalos prefer their comfort of their own technology. Similarly, the filters and seals of kalo encounter suits can be adapted to the needs of air breathers, although such suits tend to accumulate excess moisture and develop mold or mildew."),
	("Vitrum Plate", 18, "Heavy", 365,650, 23, 24, 5, 0, 0, "1", Made of transparent polyethylene, vitrum plate resembles a suit of carved crystal. Though the material is hard as metal, it shimmers and refracts light like glass. The difficulty of compressing polyethylene to preserve its lightness while affording such protection makes this type of heavy armor expensive."),
	("Freebooter Armor, V", 18, "Light", 367,650, 20, 21, 8, 0, 0, "L", Popularized by the Free Captains of the Diaspora, freebooter armor features an armored jacket or breastplate, heavy boots and gloves, numerous straps and hidden weapons, and a helmet. Novice explorers and mercenaries beginning their career sometimes choose freebooter armor for the air of rakish experience this light armor lends its wearer."),
	("Kyokor Plating, V", 18, "Heavy", 371,000, 23, 24, 5, -2, -5, "1", "Scavengers on Daimalko dare to brave the wastes of their world to gather the enamel-like hulls that kyokors occasionally shed from their crowns. These toothy moltings are enormous, and once they’re retrieved, they require a great deal of effort to grind into plates that can be used to craft armor. Despite this and the dangers of gathering the requisite moltings, suits of kyokor plating are in demand throughout the universe, making collection of the raw materials and subsequent forging into lucrative careers."),
	("Void Hide III", 18, "Light", 382,500, 20, 22, 6, -1, 0, "1", Made from void troll skin, void hide armor quivers of its own volition, as if the manufacturing process could not subdue the troll’s life force. You can trigger void hide to react to an attack as though you had the reflecting armor spell cast on you. Once you have used a specific suit of void hide in this way, you can use a different suit only after 24 hours have passed. A magic resistor upgrade installed in void hide takes up one upgrade slot fewer than normal (minimum 0), as does a spell reflector upgrade."),
	("Regimental Dress, III", 18, "Light", 387,000, 22, 22, 6, 0, 0, "L", Regimental dress is the light armor counterpart to ceremonial plate. Often stylized to the extreme, regimental dress comes in as many variations as there are military forces, militias, and private security details. Regimental dress uses advanced fibers and strategically placed ceramic plates to avoid ruining the design lines of the uniforms. A force field projector concealed in the collar activates as needed to provide life support and protection for the head. Integrated holographic imaging projects rank insignia, medals, and ribbons, and supports gesture-activated informational displays for each honor."),
	("Vesk Overplate, V", 18, "Heavy", 415,800, 24, 26, 4, -3, -5, "2", These utilitarian suits of heavy armor reflect the brute strength of their inventors. Overplate makes no concession to comfort. Instead, each polycarbonate suit is solid, dense, and often unadorned, though the high-quality craftsmanship of each suit is apparent. Overplate has a reputation for withstanding any sort of trauma, thanks to its coating of thermoplastic resin."),
	("D-Suit, VI", 19, "Light", 552,000, 21, 22, 8, 0, 0, "L", Disembarkment suits, or d-suits, are designed for spacefarers who expect to leave their ship and visit a planet’s surface. Most d-suits are jumpsuits or flight suits worn under reinforced breeches, heavy boots, and a thick jacket. A helmet or rebreather and a utility belt with an attached holster complete the outfit."),
	("Lashunta Mind Mail, IV", 19, "Light", 556,000, 22, 22, 7, 0, 0, "L", Each link in a suit of mind mail is a nanotechnological marvel: a psychically active circuit reactive to the thoughts of its wearer. When donned, mind mail floats just above the skin and alternates between rigidity and supple motion in response to its wearer’s thoughts and movement, with hundreds of tiny force fields filling the gaps between links as needed.  The mail covers the entire body except for the face. The coif retracts into the collar at a mental command, and the mesh gloves likewise unlink and recede into the sleeves when a delicate touch is required. Mind mail offers a comfortable alternative to climate control in tropical environs such as Castrovel, as the armor does not make direct contact with the body  and the open mesh provides ample airflow. The wearers of mind mail often personalize their armor with intricate designs woven with varicolored metals into the pattern of the mail. These designs can be altered with an Engineering check at the same DC as a check for adjusting armor (Core Rulebook 196)."),
	("Formian Plate, Myrmarch", 19, "Heavy", 557,000, 24, 27, 3, -4, -10, "3", The exoskeletons of deceased formians can be crafted into armor that retains some of these creatures’ defenses. Taskmaster and myrmarch formian plate grant resistance to sonic 5."),
	("Inheritor's Grace, III", 19, "Heavy", 591,000, 25, 27, 4, -2, -5, "2", "When first commissioned by the Church of Iomedae, this heavy armor was dubbed Armor of the Inheritor Ascendant. This cumbersome mouthful was soon supplanted by the tongue-and-cheek nickname “Inheritor’s grace,” as “by her grace, we are protected.” Now only the dourest of Iomedae’s church refer to her armor by its proper title. Each suit of Inheritor’s grace armor constructed by the church receives blessings as part of its construction, though otherwise identical knock-offs and officially licensed suits also exist. The armor is extremely common among worshipers of Iomedae and Knights of Golarion, but it is also worn by those with no connection to her faith."),
	("Voidshield Armor", 19, "Heavy", 610,250, 25, 26, 5, -3, -5, "2", Constructed from interlocking carbon nanotubes, voidshield armor is a matte black and remarkably thin. Android armorsmiths were the first to develop this heavy armor, and most suits bear a mechanical, robotic design. Voidshield armor sets are suitable for many upgrades and are popular among experienced explorers."),
	("Fossilwrap, III", 19, "Heavy", 645,000, 25, 25, 6, -2, -5, "2", Meant for first-wave boarding actions, fossilwrap armor is a cage of alchemically treated bones and steel. This armor is meant to shrug off most incoming blows while giving the wearer some amount of mobility in the thick of combat."),
	("Carbon Skin, Nanotube", 20, "Light", 825,000, 21, 23, 8, -1, 0, "1", Though these suits of light armor appear to be made of stiff fabric, they are actually woven from carbon fibers. Higher-quality carbon skins are reinforced with carbon allotypes, such as white carbon or diamond, and the heightened sheen of the fabric hints at their expensive construction."),
	("Vesk Monolith, III", 20, "Heavy", 827,250, 26, 27, 5, -2, -5, "2", The ultimate battle gear, pioneered by the vesk, these suits of heavy armor have a dappled polycarbonate shell that resembles stone in texture. A monolith suit looks like a massive articulated golem formed of stone plates. Despite its size, monolith armor moves easily thanks to its power-assisted joints. Sigils and personal emblems can be “chiseled” on the breastplate or shoulder guards of a monolith suit to signal the wearer’s allegiance."),
	("Shiftskin, III", 20, "Light", 886,500, 22, 24, 7, -1, 0, "1", "Developed by the reptoids for their agents, shiftskin comes in a variety of designs styled to resemble normal clothing, uniforms, and even other light armors. Each suit of shiftskin is designed to accommodate both its owner’s natural form and one other specific assumed form of another race, shifting and reshaping as needed when the reptoid changes shape. Thus a suit of shiftskin can be adjusted to accommodate two different forms (Core Rulebook 196), rather than fitting only one form at a time."),
	("Night Plate, IV", 20, "Heavy", 886,500, 25, 26, 6, 0, 0, "2", Based on designs reverse-engineered from ancient troves and alloys rediscovered through painstaking research, night plate is the heavy armor of choice for the drow of Apostae. It blends archaic armor sensibilities with cutting-edge technology, resulting in an appearance that resembles a metallic construct as much as armor. Night plate’s design incorporates flaring cauldrons and razor-sharp leg spurs, though these impressive adornments have little function beyond intimidation. Highergrade models incorporate even more of these embellishments, cunningly designed to avoid interference with the armor’s primary functions."),
	("Hardlight Series, Specialist", 20, "Light", 928,000, 22, 22, 8, 0, 0, "L", The last word in light infantry armor, hardlight series armor features an inflexible, lightweight breastplate, limb guards, and a helmet over a smooth and formfitting jumpsuit. Manufacturers often make custom armor for military organizations, but off-therack armor of differing qualities is also available to mercenaries and explorers."),
	("Aegis Series, Specialist", 20, "Heavy", 932,000, 25, 28, 4, -4, -10, "3", Aegis suits of heavy armor cover wearers entirely, leading to the suits’ nickname of “personal tanks.” Helmet visors are narrow or nonexistent, instead projecting video and audio feeds to the wearer. Power-assisted limbs allow the wearer to move intuitively with the suit on.");
